4473
4474#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
4475 mtu = SCTP_GATHER_MTU_FROM_ROUTE(net->ro._s_addr, &net->ro._l_addr.sa, ro->ro_nh);
4476#else
4477 mtu = SCTP_GATHER_MTU_FROM_ROUTE(net->ro._s_addr, &net->ro._l_addr.sa, ro->ro_rt);
4478#endif
4479 if (mtu > 0) {
4480 if (net->port) {
4481 mtu -= sizeof(struct udphdr);
4482 }
4483 if (mtu < net->mtu) {
4484 if ((stcb != NULL) && (stcb->asoc.smallest_mtu > mtu)) {
4485 sctp_mtu_size_reset(inp, &stcb->asoc, mtu);
4486 }
4487 net->mtu = mtu;
4488 }
4489 }
4490#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
4491 } else if (ro->ro_nh == NULL) {
4492#else
4493 } else if (ro->ro_rt == NULL) {
4494#endif
4495 /* route was freed */
4496 if (net->ro._s_addr &&
4497 net->src_addr_selected) {
4498 sctp_free_ifa(net->ro._s_addr);
4499 net->ro._s_addr = NULL;
4500 }
4501 net->src_addr_selected = 0;
4502 }
4503 }
4504 return (ret);
4505 }
4506#endif
4507#ifdef INET6
4508 case AF_INET6:
4509 {
4510 uint32_t flowlabel, flowinfo;
4511 struct ip6_hdr *ip6h;
4512 struct route_in6 ip6route;
4513#if !defined(__Userspace__)
4514 struct ifnet *ifp;
4515#endif
4516 struct sockaddr_in6 *sin6, tmp, *lsa6, lsa6_tmp;
4517 int prev_scope = 0;
4518#ifdef SCTP_EMBEDDED_V6_SCOPE
4519 struct sockaddr_in6 lsa6_storage;
4520 int error;
4521#endif
4522 u_short prev_port = 0;
4523 int len;
4524
4525 if (net) {
4526 flowlabel = net->flowlabel;
4527 } else if (stcb) {
4528 flowlabel = stcb->asoc.default_flowlabel;
4529 } else {
4530 flowlabel = inp->sctp_ep.default_flowlabel;
4531 }
4532 if (flowlabel == 0) {
4533 /*
4534 * This means especially, that it is not set at the
4535 * SCTP layer. So use the value from the IP layer.
4536 */
4537#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__) && (!defined(APPLE_LEOPARD) && !defined(APPLE_SNOWLEOPARD) && !defined(APPLE_LION) && !defined(APPLE_MOUNTAINLION))
4538 flowlabel = ntohl(inp->ip_inp.inp.inp_flow);
4539#else
4540 flowlabel = ntohl(((struct inpcb *)inp)->inp_flow);
4541#endif
4542 }
4543 flowlabel &= 0x000fffff;
4544 len = SCTP_MIN_OVERHEAD;
4545 if (port) {
4546 len += sizeof(struct udphdr);
4547 }
4548 newm = sctp_get_mbuf_for_msg(len, 1, M_NOWAIT, 1, MT_DATA);
4549 if (newm == NULL) {
4550 sctp_m_freem(m);
4551 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, stcb, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, ENOMEM);
4552 return (ENOMEM);
4553 }
4554 SCTP_ALIGN_TO_END(newm, len);
4555 SCTP_BUF_LEN(newm) = len;
4556 SCTP_BUF_NEXT(newm) = m;
4557 m = newm;
4558#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
4559 if (net != NULL) {
4560 m->m_pkthdr.flowid = net->flowid;
4561 M_HASHTYPE_SET(m, net->flowtype);
4562 } else {
4563 m->m_pkthdr.flowid = mflowid;
4564 M_HASHTYPE_SET(m, mflowtype);
4565 }
4566#endif
4567 packet_length = sctp_calculate_len(m);
4568
4569 ip6h = mtod(m, struct ip6_hdr *);
4570 /* protect *sin6 from overwrite */
4571 sin6 = (struct sockaddr_in6 *)to;
4572 tmp = *sin6;
4573 sin6 = &tmp;
4574
4575#ifdef SCTP_EMBEDDED_V6_SCOPE
4576 /* KAME hack: embed scopeid */
4577#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
4578#if defined(APPLE_LEOPARD) || defined(APPLE_SNOWLEOPARD)
4579 if (in6_embedscope(&sin6->sin6_addr, sin6, NULL, NULL) != 0)
4580#else
4581 if (in6_embedscope(&sin6->sin6_addr, sin6, NULL, NULL, NULL) != 0)
4582#endif
4583#elif defined(SCTP_KAME)
4584 if (sa6_embedscope(sin6, MODULE_GLOBAL(ip6_use_defzone)) != 0)
4585#else
4586 if (in6_embedscope(&sin6->sin6_addr, sin6) != 0)
4587#endif
4588 {
4589 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET_PKT(m, inp, stcb, net, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, EINVAL);
4590 sctp_m_freem(m);
4591 return (EINVAL);
4592 }
4593#endif /* SCTP_EMBEDDED_V6_SCOPE */
4594 if (net == NULL) {
4595 memset(&ip6route, 0, sizeof(ip6route));
4596 ro = (sctp_route_t *)&ip6route;
4597#ifdef HAVE_SIN6_LEN
4598 memcpy(&ro->ro_dst, sin6, sin6->sin6_len);
4599#else
4600 memcpy(&ro->ro_dst, sin6, sizeof(struct sockaddr_in6));
4601#endif
4602 } else {
4603 ro = (sctp_route_t *)&net->ro;
4604 }
4605 /*
4606 * We assume here that inp_flow is in host byte order within
4607 * the TCB!
4608 */
4609 if (tos_value == 0) {
4610 /*
4611 * This means especially, that it is not set at the
4612 * SCTP layer. So use the value from the IP layer.
4613 */
4614#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__) && (!defined(APPLE_LEOPARD) && !defined(APPLE_SNOWLEOPARD) && !defined(APPLE_LION) && !defined(APPLE_MOUNTAINLION))
4615 tos_value = (ntohl(inp->ip_inp.inp.inp_flow) >> 20) & 0xff;
4616#else
4617 tos_value = (ntohl(((struct inpcb *)inp)->inp_flow) >> 20) & 0xff;
4618#endif
4619 }
4620 tos_value &= 0xfc;
4621 if (ecn_ok) {
4622 tos_value |= sctp_get_ect(stcb);
4623 }
4624 flowinfo = 0x06;
4625 flowinfo <<= 8;
4626 flowinfo |= tos_value;
4627 flowinfo <<= 20;
4628 flowinfo |= flowlabel;
4629 ip6h->ip6_flow = htonl(flowinfo);
4630 if (port) {
4631 ip6h->ip6_nxt = IPPROTO_UDP;
4632 } else {
4633 ip6h->ip6_nxt = IPPROTO_SCTP;
4634 }
4635 ip6h->ip6_plen = htons((uint16_t)(packet_length - sizeof(struct ip6_hdr)));
4636 ip6h->ip6_dst = sin6->sin6_addr;
4637
4638 /*
4639 * Add SRC address selection here: we can only reuse to a
4640 * limited degree the kame src-addr-sel, since we can try
4641 * their selection but it may not be bound.
4642 */
4643 memset(&lsa6_tmp, 0, sizeof(lsa6_tmp));
4644 lsa6_tmp.sin6_family = AF_INET6;
4645#ifdef HAVE_SIN6_LEN
4646 lsa6_tmp.sin6_len = sizeof(lsa6_tmp);
4647#endif
4648 lsa6 = &lsa6_tmp;
4649 if (net && out_of_asoc_ok == 0) {
4650 if (net->ro._s_addr && (net->ro._s_addr->localifa_flags & (SCTP_BEING_DELETED|SCTP_ADDR_IFA_UNUSEABLE))) {
4651 sctp_free_ifa(net->ro._s_addr);
4652 net->ro._s_addr = NULL;
4653 net->src_addr_selected = 0;
4654#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
4655 RO_NHFREE(ro);
4656#else
4657 if (ro->ro_rt) {
4658 RTFREE(ro->ro_rt);
4659 ro->ro_rt = NULL;
4660 }
4661#endif
4662 }
4663 if (net->src_addr_selected == 0) {
4664#ifdef SCTP_EMBEDDED_V6_SCOPE
4665 sin6 = (struct sockaddr_in6 *)&net->ro._l_addr;
4666 /* KAME hack: embed scopeid */
4667#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
4668#if defined(APPLE_LEOPARD) || defined(APPLE_SNOWLEOPARD)
4669 if (in6_embedscope(&sin6->sin6_addr, sin6, NULL, NULL) != 0)
4670#else
4671 if (in6_embedscope(&sin6->sin6_addr, sin6, NULL, NULL, NULL) != 0)
4672#endif
4673#elif defined(SCTP_KAME)
4674 if (sa6_embedscope(sin6, MODULE_GLOBAL(ip6_use_defzone)) != 0)
4675#else
4676 if (in6_embedscope(&sin6->sin6_addr, sin6) != 0)
4677#endif
4678 {
4679 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET_PKT(m, inp, stcb, net, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, EINVAL);
4680 sctp_m_freem(m);
4681 return (EINVAL);
4682 }
4683#endif /* SCTP_EMBEDDED_V6_SCOPE */
4684 /* Cache the source address */
4685 net->ro._s_addr = sctp_source_address_selection(inp,
4686 stcb,
4687 ro,
4688 net,
4689 0,
4690 vrf_id);
4691#ifdef SCTP_EMBEDDED_V6_SCOPE
4692#ifdef SCTP_KAME
4693 (void)sa6_recoverscope(sin6);
4694#else
4695 (void)in6_recoverscope(sin6, &sin6->sin6_addr, NULL);
4696#endif /* SCTP_KAME */
4697#endif /* SCTP_EMBEDDED_V6_SCOPE */
4698 net->src_addr_selected = 1;
4699 }
4700 if (net->ro._s_addr == NULL) {
4701 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT3, "V6:No route to host\n");
4702 net->src_addr_selected = 0;
4703 sctp_handle_no_route(stcb, net, so_locked);
4704 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET_PKT(m, inp, stcb, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, EHOSTUNREACH);
4705 sctp_m_freem(m);
4706 return (EHOSTUNREACH);
4707 }
4708 lsa6->sin6_addr = net->ro._s_addr->address.sin6.sin6_addr;
4709 } else {
4710#ifdef SCTP_EMBEDDED_V6_SCOPE
4711 sin6 = (struct sockaddr_in6 *)&ro->ro_dst;
4712 /* KAME hack: embed scopeid */
4713#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
4714#if defined(APPLE_LEOPARD) || defined(APPLE_SNOWLEOPARD)
4715 if (in6_embedscope(&sin6->sin6_addr, sin6, NULL, NULL) != 0)
4716#else
4717 if (in6_embedscope(&sin6->sin6_addr, sin6, NULL, NULL, NULL) != 0)
4718#endif
4719#elif defined(SCTP_KAME)
4720 if (sa6_embedscope(sin6, MODULE_GLOBAL(ip6_use_defzone)) != 0)
4721#else
4722 if (in6_embedscope(&sin6->sin6_addr, sin6) != 0)
4723#endif
4724 {
4725 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET_PKT(m, inp, stcb, net, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, EINVAL);
4726 sctp_m_freem(m);
4727 return (EINVAL);
4728 }
4729#endif /* SCTP_EMBEDDED_V6_SCOPE */
4730 if (over_addr == NULL) {
4731 struct sctp_ifa *_lsrc;
4732
4733 _lsrc = sctp_source_address_selection(inp, stcb, ro,
4734 net,
4735 out_of_asoc_ok,
4736 vrf_id);
4737 if (_lsrc == NULL) {
4738 sctp_handle_no_route(stcb, net, so_locked);
4739 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET_PKT(m, inp, stcb, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, EHOSTUNREACH);
4740 sctp_m_freem(m);
4741 return (EHOSTUNREACH);
4742 }
4743 lsa6->sin6_addr = _lsrc->address.sin6.sin6_addr;
4744 sctp_free_ifa(_lsrc);
4745 } else {
4746 lsa6->sin6_addr = over_addr->sin6.sin6_addr;
4747 SCTP_RTALLOC(ro, vrf_id, inp->fibnum);
4748 }
4749#ifdef SCTP_EMBEDDED_V6_SCOPE
4750#ifdef SCTP_KAME
4751 (void)sa6_recoverscope(sin6);
4752#else
4753 (void)in6_recoverscope(sin6, &sin6->sin6_addr, NULL);
4754#endif /* SCTP_KAME */
4755#endif /* SCTP_EMBEDDED_V6_SCOPE */
4756 }
4757 lsa6->sin6_port = inp->sctp_lport;
4758
4759#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
4760 if (ro->ro_nh == NULL) {
4761#else
4762 if (ro->ro_rt == NULL) {
4763#endif
4764 /*
4765 * src addr selection failed to find a route (or
4766 * valid source addr), so we can't get there from
4767 * here!
4768 */
4769 sctp_handle_no_route(stcb, net, so_locked);
4770 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET_PKT(m, inp, stcb, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, EHOSTUNREACH);
4771 sctp_m_freem(m);
4772 return (EHOSTUNREACH);
4773 }
4774#ifndef SCOPEDROUTING
4775#ifdef SCTP_EMBEDDED_V6_SCOPE
4776 /*
4777 * XXX: sa6 may not have a valid sin6_scope_id in the
4778 * non-SCOPEDROUTING case.
4779 */
4780 memset(&lsa6_storage, 0, sizeof(lsa6_storage));
4781 lsa6_storage.sin6_family = AF_INET6;
4782#ifdef HAVE_SIN6_LEN
4783 lsa6_storage.sin6_len = sizeof(lsa6_storage);
4784#endif
4785#ifdef SCTP_KAME
4786 lsa6_storage.sin6_addr = lsa6->sin6_addr;
4787 if ((error = sa6_recoverscope(&lsa6_storage)) != 0) {
4788#else
4789 if ((error = in6_recoverscope(&lsa6_storage, &lsa6->sin6_addr,
4790 NULL)) != 0) {
4791#endif /* SCTP_KAME */
4792 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT3, "recover scope fails error %d\n", error);
4793 sctp_m_freem(m);
4794 return (error);
4795 }
4796 /* XXX */
4797 lsa6_storage.sin6_addr = lsa6->sin6_addr;
4798 lsa6_storage.sin6_port = inp->sctp_lport;
4799 lsa6 = &lsa6_storage;
4800#endif /* SCTP_EMBEDDED_V6_SCOPE */
4801#endif /* SCOPEDROUTING */
4802 ip6h->ip6_src = lsa6->sin6_addr;
4803
4804 if (port) {
4805 if (htons(SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_udp_tunneling_port)) == 0) {
4806 sctp_handle_no_route(stcb, net, so_locked);
4807 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET_PKT(m, inp, stcb, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, EHOSTUNREACH);
4808 sctp_m_freem(m);
4809 return (EHOSTUNREACH);
4810 }
4811 udp = (struct udphdr *)((caddr_t)ip6h + sizeof(struct ip6_hdr));
4812 udp->uh_sport = htons(SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_udp_tunneling_port));
4813 udp->uh_dport = port;
4814 udp->uh_ulen = htons((uint16_t)(packet_length - sizeof(struct ip6_hdr)));
4815 udp->uh_sum = 0;
4816 sctphdr = (struct sctphdr *)((caddr_t)udp + sizeof(struct udphdr));
4817 } else {
4818 sctphdr = (struct sctphdr *)((caddr_t)ip6h + sizeof(struct ip6_hdr));
4819 }
4820
4821 sctphdr->src_port = src_port;
4822 sctphdr->dest_port = dest_port;
4823 sctphdr->v_tag = v_tag;
4824 sctphdr->checksum = 0;
4825
4826 /*
4827 * We set the hop limit now since there is a good chance
4828 * that our ro pointer is now filled
4829 */
4830 ip6h->ip6_hlim = SCTP_GET_HLIM(inp, ro);
4831#if !defined(__Userspace__)
4832 ifp = SCTP_GET_IFN_VOID_FROM_ROUTE(ro);
4833#endif
4834
4835#ifdef SCTP_DEBUG
4836 /* Copy to be sure something bad is not happening */
4837 sin6->sin6_addr = ip6h->ip6_dst;
4838 lsa6->sin6_addr = ip6h->ip6_src;
4839#endif
4840
4841 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT3, "Calling ipv6 output routine from low level\n");
4842 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT3, "src: ");
4843 SCTPDBG_ADDR(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT3, (struct sockaddr *)lsa6);
4844 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT3, "dst: ");
4845 SCTPDBG_ADDR(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT3, (struct sockaddr *)sin6);
4846 if (net) {
4847 sin6 = (struct sockaddr_in6 *)&net->ro._l_addr;
4848 /* preserve the port and scope for link local send */
4849 prev_scope = sin6->sin6_scope_id;
4850 prev_port = sin6->sin6_port;
4851 }
4852
4853 if (SCTP_GET_HEADER_FOR_OUTPUT(o_pak)) {
4854 /* failed to prepend data, give up */
4855 sctp_m_freem(m);
4856 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, stcb, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, ENOMEM);
4857 return (ENOMEM);
4858 }
4859 SCTP_ATTACH_CHAIN(o_pak, m, packet_length);
4860 if (port) {
4861 sctphdr->checksum = sctp_calculate_cksum(m, sizeof(struct ip6_hdr) + sizeof(struct udphdr));
4862 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_sendswcrc);
4863#if !defined(__Userspace__)
4864#if defined(_WIN32)
4865 udp->uh_sum = 0;
4866#else
4867 if ((udp->uh_sum = in6_cksum(o_pak, IPPROTO_UDP, sizeof(struct ip6_hdr), packet_length - sizeof(struct ip6_hdr))) == 0) {
4868 udp->uh_sum = 0xffff;
4869 }
4870#endif
4871#endif
4872 } else {
4873#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
4874 m->m_pkthdr.csum_flags = CSUM_SCTP_IPV6;
4875 m->m_pkthdr.csum_data = offsetof(struct sctphdr, checksum);
4876 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_sendhwcrc);
4877#else
4878 if (!(SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_no_csum_on_loopback) &&
4879 (stcb) && (stcb->asoc.scope.loopback_scope))) {
4880 sctphdr->checksum = sctp_calculate_cksum(m, sizeof(struct ip6_hdr));
4881 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_sendswcrc);
4882 } else {
4883 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_sendhwcrc);
4884 }
4885#endif
4886 }
4887 /* send it out. table id is taken from stcb */
4888#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
4889 if ((SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_output_unlocked)) && (so_locked)) {
4890 so = SCTP_INP_SO(inp);
4891 SCTP_SOCKET_UNLOCK(so, 0);
4892 }
4893#endif
4894#ifdef SCTP_PACKET_LOGGING
4895 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_LAST_PACKET_TRACING)
4896 sctp_packet_log(o_pak);
4897#endif
4898#if !defined(__Userspace__)
4899#if defined(__FreeBSD__)
4900 SCTP_PROBE5(send, NULL, stcb, ip6h, stcb, sctphdr);
4901#endif
4902 SCTP_IP6_OUTPUT(ret, o_pak, (struct route_in6 *)ro, &ifp, stcb, vrf_id);
4903#else
4904 SCTP_IP6_OUTPUT(ret, o_pak, (struct route_in6 *)ro, NULL, stcb, vrf_id);
4905#endif
4906#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
4907 if ((SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_output_unlocked)) && (so_locked)) {
4908 atomic_add_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
4909 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
4910 SCTP_SOCKET_LOCK(so, 0);
4911 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
4912 atomic_subtract_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
4913 }
4914#endif
4915 if (net) {
4916 /* for link local this must be done */
4917 sin6->sin6_scope_id = prev_scope;
4918 sin6->sin6_port = prev_port;
4919 }
4920 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT3, "return from send is %d\n", ret);
4921#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
4922 if (port) {
4923 UDPSTAT_INC(udps_opackets);
4924 }
4925#endif
4926 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_sendpackets);
4927 SCTP_STAT_INCR_COUNTER64(sctps_outpackets);
4928 if (ret) {
4929 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_senderrors);
4930 }
4931 if (net == NULL) {
4932 /* Now if we had a temp route free it */
4933#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
4934 RO_NHFREE(ro);
4935#else
4936 if (ro->ro_rt) {
4937 RTFREE(ro->ro_rt);
4938 ro->ro_rt = NULL;
4939 }
4940#endif
4941 } else {
4942 /* PMTU check versus smallest asoc MTU goes here */
4943#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
4944 if (ro->ro_nh == NULL) {
4945#else
4946 if (ro->ro_rt == NULL) {
4947#endif
4948 /* Route was freed */
4949 if (net->ro._s_addr &&
4950 net->src_addr_selected) {
4951 sctp_free_ifa(net->ro._s_addr);
4952 net->ro._s_addr = NULL;
4953 }
4954 net->src_addr_selected = 0;
4955 }
4956#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
4957 if ((ro->ro_nh != NULL) && (net->ro._s_addr) &&
4958#else
4959 if ((ro->ro_rt != NULL) && (net->ro._s_addr) &&
4960#endif
4961 ((net->dest_state & SCTP_ADDR_NO_PMTUD) == 0)) {
4962 uint32_t mtu;
4963
4964#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
4965 mtu = SCTP_GATHER_MTU_FROM_ROUTE(net->ro._s_addr, &net->ro._l_addr.sa, ro->ro_nh);
4966#else
4967 mtu = SCTP_GATHER_MTU_FROM_ROUTE(net->ro._s_addr, &net->ro._l_addr.sa, ro->ro_rt);
4968#endif
4969 if (mtu > 0) {
4970 if (net->port) {
4971 mtu -= sizeof(struct udphdr);
4972 }
4973 if (mtu < net->mtu) {
4974 if ((stcb != NULL) && (stcb->asoc.smallest_mtu > mtu)) {
4975 sctp_mtu_size_reset(inp, &stcb->asoc, mtu);
4976 }
4977 net->mtu = mtu;
4978 }
4979 }
4980 }
4981#if !defined(__Userspace__)
4982 else if (ifp) {
4983#if defined(_WIN32)
4984#define ND_IFINFO(ifp) (ifp)
4985#define linkmtu if_mtu
4986#endif
4987 if (ND_IFINFO(ifp)->linkmtu &&
4988 (stcb->asoc.smallest_mtu > ND_IFINFO(ifp)->linkmtu)) {
4989 sctp_mtu_size_reset(inp,
4990 &stcb->asoc,
4991 ND_IFINFO(ifp)->linkmtu);
4992 }
4993 }
4994#endif
4995 }
4996 return (ret);
4997 }
4998#endif
4999#if defined(__Userspace__)
5000 case AF_CONN:
5001 {
5002 char *buffer;
5003 struct sockaddr_conn *sconn;
5004 int len;
5005
5006 sconn = (struct sockaddr_conn *)to;
5007 len = sizeof(struct sctphdr);
5008 newm = sctp_get_mbuf_for_msg(len, 1, M_NOWAIT, 1, MT_DATA);
5009 if (newm == NULL) {
5010 sctp_m_freem(m);
5011 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, stcb, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, ENOMEM);
5012 return (ENOMEM);
5013 }
5014 SCTP_ALIGN_TO_END(newm, len);
5015 SCTP_BUF_LEN(newm) = len;
5016 SCTP_BUF_NEXT(newm) = m;
5017 m = newm;
5018 packet_length = sctp_calculate_len(m);
5019 sctphdr = mtod(m, struct sctphdr *);
5020 sctphdr->src_port = src_port;
5021 sctphdr->dest_port = dest_port;
5022 sctphdr->v_tag = v_tag;
5023 sctphdr->checksum = 0;
5024 if (SCTP_BASE_VAR(crc32c_offloaded) == 0) {
5025 sctphdr->checksum = sctp_calculate_cksum(m, 0);
5026 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_sendswcrc);
5027 } else {
5028 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_sendhwcrc);
5029 }
5030 if (tos_value == 0) {
5031 tos_value = inp->ip_inp.inp.inp_ip_tos;
5032 }
5033 tos_value &= 0xfc;
5034 if (ecn_ok) {
5035 tos_value |= sctp_get_ect(stcb);
5036 }
5037 /* Don't alloc/free for each packet */
5038 if ((buffer = malloc(packet_length)) != NULL) {
5039 m_copydata(m, 0, packet_length, buffer);
5040 ret = SCTP_BASE_VAR(conn_output)(sconn->sconn_addr, buffer, packet_length, tos_value, nofragment_flag);
5041 free(buffer);
5042 } else {
5043 ret = ENOMEM;
5044 }
5045 sctp_m_freem(m);
5046 return (ret);
5047 }
5048#endif
5049 default:
5050 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT1, "Unknown protocol (TSNH) type %d\n",
5051 ((struct sockaddr *)to)->sa_family);
5052 sctp_m_freem(m);
5053 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET_PKT(m, inp, stcb, net, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, EFAULT);
5054 return (EFAULT);
5055 }
5056}
5057
5058void
5059sctp_send_initiate(struct sctp_inpcb *inp, struct sctp_tcb *stcb, int so_locked)
5060{
5061 struct mbuf *m, *m_last;
5062 struct sctp_nets *net;
5063 struct sctp_init_chunk *init;
5064 struct sctp_supported_addr_param *sup_addr;
5065 struct sctp_adaptation_layer_indication *ali;
5066 struct sctp_supported_chunk_types_param *pr_supported;
5067 struct sctp_paramhdr *ph;
5068 int cnt_inits_to = 0;
5069 int error;
5070 uint16_t num_ext, chunk_len, padding_len, parameter_len;
5071
5072#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
5073 if (so_locked) {
5074 sctp_lock_assert(SCTP_INP_SO(inp));
5075 } else {
5076 sctp_unlock_assert(SCTP_INP_SO(inp));
5077 }
5078#endif
5079 /* INIT's always go to the primary (and usually ONLY address) */
5080 net = stcb->asoc.primary_destination;
5081 if (net == NULL) {
5082 net = TAILQ_FIRST(&stcb->asoc.nets);
5083 if (net == NULL) {
5084 /* TSNH */
5085 return;
5086 }
5087 /* we confirm any address we send an INIT to */
5088 net->dest_state &= ~SCTP_ADDR_UNCONFIRMED;
5089 (void)sctp_set_primary_addr(stcb, NULL, net);
5090 } else {
5091 /* we confirm any address we send an INIT to */
5092 net->dest_state &= ~SCTP_ADDR_UNCONFIRMED;
5093 }
5094 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT4, "Sending INIT\n");
5095#ifdef INET6
5096 if (net->ro._l_addr.sa.sa_family == AF_INET6) {
5097 /*
5098 * special hook, if we are sending to link local it will not
5099 * show up in our private address count.
5100 */
5101 if (IN6_IS_ADDR_LINKLOCAL(&net->ro._l_addr.sin6.sin6_addr))
5102 cnt_inits_to = 1;
5103 }
5104#endif
5105 if (SCTP_OS_TIMER_PENDING(&net->rxt_timer.timer)) {
5106 /* This case should not happen */
5107 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT4, "Sending INIT - failed timer?\n");
5108 return;
5109 }
5110 /* start the INIT timer */
5111 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_INIT, inp, stcb, net);
5112
5113 m = sctp_get_mbuf_for_msg(MCLBYTES, 1, M_NOWAIT, 1, MT_DATA);
5114 if (m == NULL) {
5115 /* No memory, INIT timer will re-attempt. */
5116 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT4, "Sending INIT - mbuf?\n");
5117 return;
5118 }
5119 chunk_len = (uint16_t)sizeof(struct sctp_init_chunk);
5120 padding_len = 0;
5121 /* Now lets put the chunk header in place */
5122 init = mtod(m, struct sctp_init_chunk *);
5123 /* now the chunk header */
5124 init->ch.chunk_type = SCTP_INITIATION;
5125 init->ch.chunk_flags = 0;
5126 /* fill in later from mbuf we build */
5127 init->ch.chunk_length = 0;
5128 /* place in my tag */
5129 init->init.initiate_tag = htonl(stcb->asoc.my_vtag);
5130 /* set up some of the credits. */
5131 init->init.a_rwnd = htonl(max(inp->sctp_socket?SCTP_SB_LIMIT_RCV(inp->sctp_socket):0,
5132 SCTP_MINIMAL_RWND));
5133 init->init.num_outbound_streams = htons(stcb->asoc.pre_open_streams);
5134 init->init.num_inbound_streams = htons(stcb->asoc.max_inbound_streams);
5135 init->init.initial_tsn = htonl(stcb->asoc.init_seq_number);
5136
5137 /* Adaptation layer indication parameter */
5138 if (inp->sctp_ep.adaptation_layer_indicator_provided) {
5139 parameter_len = (uint16_t)sizeof(struct sctp_adaptation_layer_indication);
5140 ali = (struct sctp_adaptation_layer_indication *)(mtod(m, caddr_t) + chunk_len);
5141 ali->ph.param_type = htons(SCTP_ULP_ADAPTATION);
5142 ali->ph.param_length = htons(parameter_len);
5143 ali->indication = htonl(inp->sctp_ep.adaptation_layer_indicator);
5144 chunk_len += parameter_len;
5145 }
5146
5147 /* ECN parameter */
5148 if (stcb->asoc.ecn_supported == 1) {
5149 parameter_len = (uint16_t)sizeof(struct sctp_paramhdr);
5150 ph = (struct sctp_paramhdr *)(mtod(m, caddr_t) + chunk_len);
5151 ph->param_type = htons(SCTP_ECN_CAPABLE);
5152 ph->param_length = htons(parameter_len);
5153 chunk_len += parameter_len;
5154 }
5155
5156 /* PR-SCTP supported parameter */
5157 if (stcb->asoc.prsctp_supported == 1) {
5158 parameter_len = (uint16_t)sizeof(struct sctp_paramhdr);
5159 ph = (struct sctp_paramhdr *)(mtod(m, caddr_t) + chunk_len);
5160 ph->param_type = htons(SCTP_PRSCTP_SUPPORTED);
5161 ph->param_length = htons(parameter_len);
5162 chunk_len += parameter_len;
5163 }
5164
5165 /* Add NAT friendly parameter. */
5166 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_inits_include_nat_friendly)) {
5167 parameter_len = (uint16_t)sizeof(struct sctp_paramhdr);
5168 ph = (struct sctp_paramhdr *)(mtod(m, caddr_t) + chunk_len);
5169 ph->param_type = htons(SCTP_HAS_NAT_SUPPORT);
5170 ph->param_length = htons(parameter_len);
5171 chunk_len += parameter_len;
5172 }
5173
5174 /* And now tell the peer which extensions we support */
5175 num_ext = 0;
5176 pr_supported = (struct sctp_supported_chunk_types_param *)(mtod(m, caddr_t) + chunk_len);
5177 if (stcb->asoc.prsctp_supported == 1) {
5178 pr_supported->chunk_types[num_ext++] = SCTP_FORWARD_CUM_TSN;
5179 if (stcb->asoc.idata_supported) {
5180 pr_supported->chunk_types[num_ext++] = SCTP_IFORWARD_CUM_TSN;
5181 }
5182 }
5183 if (stcb->asoc.auth_supported == 1) {
5184 pr_supported->chunk_types[num_ext++] = SCTP_AUTHENTICATION;
5185 }
5186 if (stcb->asoc.asconf_supported == 1) {
5187 pr_supported->chunk_types[num_ext++] = SCTP_ASCONF;
5188 pr_supported->chunk_types[num_ext++] = SCTP_ASCONF_ACK;
5189 }
5190 if (stcb->asoc.reconfig_supported == 1) {
5191 pr_supported->chunk_types[num_ext++] = SCTP_STREAM_RESET;
5192 }
5193 if (stcb->asoc.idata_supported) {
5194 pr_supported->chunk_types[num_ext++] = SCTP_IDATA;
5195 }
5196 if (stcb->asoc.nrsack_supported == 1) {
5197 pr_supported->chunk_types[num_ext++] = SCTP_NR_SELECTIVE_ACK;
5198 }
5199 if (stcb->asoc.pktdrop_supported == 1) {
5200 pr_supported->chunk_types[num_ext++] = SCTP_PACKET_DROPPED;
5201 }
5202 if (num_ext > 0) {
5203 parameter_len = (uint16_t)sizeof(struct sctp_supported_chunk_types_param) + num_ext;
5204 pr_supported->ph.param_type = htons(SCTP_SUPPORTED_CHUNK_EXT);
5205 pr_supported->ph.param_length = htons(parameter_len);
5206 padding_len = SCTP_SIZE32(parameter_len) - parameter_len;
5207 chunk_len += parameter_len;
5208 }
5209 /* add authentication parameters */
5210 if (stcb->asoc.auth_supported) {
5211 /* attach RANDOM parameter, if available */
5212 if (stcb->asoc.authinfo.random != NULL) {
5213 struct sctp_auth_random *randp;
5214
5215 if (padding_len > 0) {
5216 memset(mtod(m, caddr_t) + chunk_len, 0, padding_len);
5217 chunk_len += padding_len;
5218 padding_len = 0;
5219 }
5220 randp = (struct sctp_auth_random *)(mtod(m, caddr_t) + chunk_len);
5221 parameter_len = (uint16_t)sizeof(struct sctp_auth_random) + stcb->asoc.authinfo.random_len;
5222 /* random key already contains the header */
5223 memcpy(randp, stcb->asoc.authinfo.random->key, parameter_len);
5224 padding_len = SCTP_SIZE32(parameter_len) - parameter_len;
5225 chunk_len += parameter_len;
5226 }
5227 /* add HMAC_ALGO parameter */
5228 if (stcb->asoc.local_hmacs != NULL) {
5229 struct sctp_auth_hmac_algo *hmacs;
5230
5231 if (padding_len > 0) {
5232 memset(mtod(m, caddr_t) + chunk_len, 0, padding_len);
5233 chunk_len += padding_len;
5234 padding_len = 0;
5235 }
5236 hmacs = (struct sctp_auth_hmac_algo *)(mtod(m, caddr_t) + chunk_len);
5237 parameter_len = (uint16_t)(sizeof(struct sctp_auth_hmac_algo) +
5238 stcb->asoc.local_hmacs->num_algo * sizeof(uint16_t));
5239 hmacs->ph.param_type = htons(SCTP_HMAC_LIST);
5240 hmacs->ph.param_length = htons(parameter_len);
5241 sctp_serialize_hmaclist(stcb->asoc.local_hmacs, (uint8_t *)hmacs->hmac_ids);
5242 padding_len = SCTP_SIZE32(parameter_len) - parameter_len;
5243 chunk_len += parameter_len;
5244 }
5245 /* add CHUNKS parameter */
5246 if (stcb->asoc.local_auth_chunks != NULL) {
5247 struct sctp_auth_chunk_list *chunks;
5248
5249 if (padding_len > 0) {
5250 memset(mtod(m, caddr_t) + chunk_len, 0, padding_len);
5251 chunk_len += padding_len;
5252 padding_len = 0;
5253 }
5254 chunks = (struct sctp_auth_chunk_list *)(mtod(m, caddr_t) + chunk_len);
5255 parameter_len = (uint16_t)(sizeof(struct sctp_auth_chunk_list) +
5256 sctp_auth_get_chklist_size(stcb->asoc.local_auth_chunks));
5257 chunks->ph.param_type = htons(SCTP_CHUNK_LIST);
5258 chunks->ph.param_length = htons(parameter_len);
5259 sctp_serialize_auth_chunks(stcb->asoc.local_auth_chunks, chunks->chunk_types);
5260 padding_len = SCTP_SIZE32(parameter_len) - parameter_len;
5261 chunk_len += parameter_len;
5262 }
5263 }
5264
5265 /* now any cookie time extensions */
5266 if (stcb->asoc.cookie_preserve_req > 0) {
5267 struct sctp_cookie_perserve_param *cookie_preserve;
5268
5269 if (padding_len > 0) {
5270 memset(mtod(m, caddr_t) + chunk_len, 0, padding_len);
5271 chunk_len += padding_len;
5272 padding_len = 0;
5273 }
5274 parameter_len = (uint16_t)sizeof(struct sctp_cookie_perserve_param);
5275 cookie_preserve = (struct sctp_cookie_perserve_param *)(mtod(m, caddr_t) + chunk_len);
5276 cookie_preserve->ph.param_type = htons(SCTP_COOKIE_PRESERVE);
5277 cookie_preserve->ph.param_length = htons(parameter_len);
5278 cookie_preserve->time = htonl(stcb->asoc.cookie_preserve_req);
5279 stcb->asoc.cookie_preserve_req = 0;
5280 chunk_len += parameter_len;
5281 }
5282
5283 if (stcb->asoc.scope.ipv4_addr_legal || stcb->asoc.scope.ipv6_addr_legal) {
5284 uint8_t i;
5285
5286 if (padding_len > 0) {
5287 memset(mtod(m, caddr_t) + chunk_len, 0, padding_len);
5288 chunk_len += padding_len;
5289 padding_len = 0;
5290 }
5291 parameter_len = (uint16_t)sizeof(struct sctp_paramhdr);
5292 if (stcb->asoc.scope.ipv4_addr_legal) {
5293 parameter_len += (uint16_t)sizeof(uint16_t);
5294 }
5295 if (stcb->asoc.scope.ipv6_addr_legal) {
5296 parameter_len += (uint16_t)sizeof(uint16_t);
5297 }
5298 sup_addr = (struct sctp_supported_addr_param *)(mtod(m, caddr_t) + chunk_len);
5299 sup_addr->ph.param_type = htons(SCTP_SUPPORTED_ADDRTYPE);
5300 sup_addr->ph.param_length = htons(parameter_len);
5301 i = 0;
5302 if (stcb->asoc.scope.ipv4_addr_legal) {
5303 sup_addr->addr_type[i++] = htons(SCTP_IPV4_ADDRESS);
5304 }
5305 if (stcb->asoc.scope.ipv6_addr_legal) {
5306 sup_addr->addr_type[i++] = htons(SCTP_IPV6_ADDRESS);
5307 }
5308 padding_len = 4 - 2 * i;
5309 chunk_len += parameter_len;
5310 }
5311
5312 SCTP_BUF_LEN(m) = chunk_len;
5313 /* now the addresses */
5314 /* To optimize this we could put the scoping stuff
5315 * into a structure and remove the individual uint8's from
5316 * the assoc structure. Then we could just sifa in the
5317 * address within the stcb. But for now this is a quick
5318 * hack to get the address stuff teased apart.
5319 */
5320 m_last = sctp_add_addresses_to_i_ia(inp, stcb, &stcb->asoc.scope,
5321 m, cnt_inits_to,
5322 &padding_len, &chunk_len);
5323
5324 init->ch.chunk_length = htons(chunk_len);
5325 if (padding_len > 0) {
5326 if (sctp_add_pad_tombuf(m_last, padding_len) == NULL) {
5327 sctp_m_freem(m);
5328 return;
5329 }
5330 }
5331 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT4, "Sending INIT - calls lowlevel_output\n");
5332 if ((error = sctp_lowlevel_chunk_output(inp, stcb, net,
5333 (struct sockaddr *)&net->ro._l_addr,
5334 m, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0,
5335 inp->sctp_lport, stcb->rport, htonl(0),
5336 net->port, NULL,
5337#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
5338 0, 0,
5339#endif
5340 so_locked))) {
5341 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT4, "Gak send error %d\n", error);
5342 if (error == ENOBUFS) {
5343 stcb->asoc.ifp_had_enobuf = 1;
5344 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_lowlevelerr);
5345 }
5346 } else {
5347 stcb->asoc.ifp_had_enobuf = 0;
5348 }
5349 SCTP_STAT_INCR_COUNTER64(sctps_outcontrolchunks);
5350 (void)SCTP_GETTIME_TIMEVAL(&net->last_sent_time);
5351}
5352
5353struct mbuf *
5354sctp_arethere_unrecognized_parameters(struct mbuf *in_initpkt,
5355 int param_offset, int *abort_processing,
5356 struct sctp_chunkhdr *cp,
5357 int *nat_friendly,
5358 int *cookie_found)
5359{
5360 /*
5361 * Given a mbuf containing an INIT or INIT-ACK with the param_offset
5362 * being equal to the beginning of the params i.e. (iphlen +
5363 * sizeof(struct sctp_init_msg) parse through the parameters to the
5364 * end of the mbuf verifying that all parameters are known.
5365 *
5366 * For unknown parameters build and return a mbuf with
5367 * UNRECOGNIZED_PARAMETER errors. If the flags indicate to stop
5368 * processing this chunk stop, and set *abort_processing to 1.
5369 *
5370 * By having param_offset be pre-set to where parameters begin it is
5371 * hoped that this routine may be reused in the future by new
5372 * features.
5373 */
5374 struct sctp_paramhdr *phdr, params;
5375
5376 struct mbuf *mat, *m_tmp, *op_err, *op_err_last;
5377 int at, limit, pad_needed;
5378 uint16_t ptype, plen, padded_size;
5379
5380 *abort_processing = 0;
5381 if (cookie_found != NULL) {
5382 *cookie_found = 0;
5383 }
5384 mat = in_initpkt;
5385 limit = ntohs(cp->chunk_length) - sizeof(struct sctp_init_chunk);
5386 at = param_offset;
5387 op_err = NULL;
5388 op_err_last = NULL;
5389 pad_needed = 0;
5390 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT1, "Check for unrecognized param's\n");
5391 phdr = sctp_get_next_param(mat, at, &params, sizeof(params));
5392 while ((phdr != NULL) && ((size_t)limit >= sizeof(struct sctp_paramhdr))) {
5393 ptype = ntohs(phdr->param_type);
5394 plen = ntohs(phdr->param_length);
5395 if ((plen > limit) || (plen < sizeof(struct sctp_paramhdr))) {
5396 /* wacked parameter */
5397 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT1, "Invalid size - error %d\n", plen);
5398 goto invalid_size;
5399 }
5400 limit -= SCTP_SIZE32(plen);
5401 /*-
5402 * All parameters for all chunks that we know/understand are
5403 * listed here. We process them other places and make
5404 * appropriate stop actions per the upper bits. However this
5405 * is the generic routine processor's can call to get back
5406 * an operr.. to either incorporate (init-ack) or send.
5407 */
5408 padded_size = SCTP_SIZE32(plen);
5409 switch (ptype) {
5410 /* Param's with variable size */
5411 case SCTP_HEARTBEAT_INFO:
5412 case SCTP_UNRECOG_PARAM:
5413 case SCTP_ERROR_CAUSE_IND:
5414 /* ok skip fwd */
5415 at += padded_size;
5416 break;
5417 case SCTP_STATE_COOKIE:
5418 if (cookie_found != NULL) {
5419 *cookie_found = 1;
5420 }
5421 at += padded_size;
5422 break;
5423 /* Param's with variable size within a range */
5424 case SCTP_CHUNK_LIST:
5425 case SCTP_SUPPORTED_CHUNK_EXT:
5426 if (padded_size > (sizeof(struct sctp_supported_chunk_types_param) + (sizeof(uint8_t) * SCTP_MAX_SUPPORTED_EXT))) {
5427 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT1, "Invalid size - error chklist %d\n", plen);
5428 goto invalid_size;
5429 }
5430 at += padded_size;
5431 break;
5432 case SCTP_SUPPORTED_ADDRTYPE:
5433 if (padded_size > SCTP_MAX_ADDR_PARAMS_SIZE) {
5434 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT1, "Invalid size - error supaddrtype %d\n", plen);
5435 goto invalid_size;
5436 }
5437 at += padded_size;
5438 break;
5439 case SCTP_RANDOM:
5440 if (padded_size > (sizeof(struct sctp_auth_random) + SCTP_RANDOM_MAX_SIZE)) {
5441 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT1, "Invalid size - error random %d\n", plen);
5442 goto invalid_size;
5443 }
5444 at += padded_size;
5445 break;
5446 case SCTP_SET_PRIM_ADDR:
5447 case SCTP_DEL_IP_ADDRESS:
5448 case SCTP_ADD_IP_ADDRESS:
5449 if ((padded_size != sizeof(struct sctp_asconf_addrv4_param)) &&
5450 (padded_size != sizeof(struct sctp_asconf_addr_param))) {
5451 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT1, "Invalid size - error setprim %d\n", plen);
5452 goto invalid_size;
5453 }
5454 at += padded_size;
5455 break;
5456 /* Param's with a fixed size */
5457 case SCTP_IPV4_ADDRESS:
5458 if (padded_size != sizeof(struct sctp_ipv4addr_param)) {
5459 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT1, "Invalid size - error ipv4 addr %d\n", plen);
5460 goto invalid_size;
5461 }
5462 at += padded_size;
5463 break;
5464 case SCTP_IPV6_ADDRESS:
5465 if (padded_size != sizeof(struct sctp_ipv6addr_param)) {
5466 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT1, "Invalid size - error ipv6 addr %d\n", plen);
5467 goto invalid_size;
5468 }
5469 at += padded_size;
5470 break;
5471 case SCTP_COOKIE_PRESERVE:
5472 if (padded_size != sizeof(struct sctp_cookie_perserve_param)) {
5473 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT1, "Invalid size - error cookie-preserve %d\n", plen);
5474 goto invalid_size;
5475 }
5476 at += padded_size;
5477 break;
5478 case SCTP_HAS_NAT_SUPPORT:
5479 *nat_friendly = 1;
5480 /* fall through */
5481 case SCTP_PRSCTP_SUPPORTED:
5482 if (padded_size != sizeof(struct sctp_paramhdr)) {
5483 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT1, "Invalid size - error prsctp/nat support %d\n", plen);
5484 goto invalid_size;
5485 }
5486 at += padded_size;
5487 break;
5488 case SCTP_ECN_CAPABLE:
5489 if (padded_size != sizeof(struct sctp_paramhdr)) {
5490 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT1, "Invalid size - error ecn %d\n", plen);
5491 goto invalid_size;
5492 }
5493 at += padded_size;
5494 break;
5495 case SCTP_ULP_ADAPTATION:
5496 if (padded_size != sizeof(struct sctp_adaptation_layer_indication)) {
5497 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT1, "Invalid size - error adapatation %d\n", plen);
5498 goto invalid_size;
5499 }
5500 at += padded_size;
5501 break;
5502 case SCTP_SUCCESS_REPORT:
5503 if (padded_size != sizeof(struct sctp_asconf_paramhdr)) {
5504 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT1, "Invalid size - error success %d\n", plen);
5505 goto invalid_size;
5506 }
5507 at += padded_size;
5508 break;
5509 case SCTP_HOSTNAME_ADDRESS:
5510 {
5511 /* Hostname parameters are deprecated. */
5512 struct sctp_gen_error_cause *cause;
5513 int l_len;
5514
5515 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT1, "Can't handle hostname addresses.. abort processing\n");
5516 *abort_processing = 1;
5517 sctp_m_freem(op_err);
5518 op_err = NULL;
5519 op_err_last = NULL;
5520#ifdef INET6
5521 l_len = SCTP_MIN_OVERHEAD;
5522#else
5523 l_len = SCTP_MIN_V4_OVERHEAD;
5524#endif
5525 l_len += sizeof(struct sctp_chunkhdr);
5526 l_len += sizeof(struct sctp_gen_error_cause);
5527 op_err = sctp_get_mbuf_for_msg(l_len, 0, M_NOWAIT, 1, MT_DATA);
5528 if (op_err != NULL) {
5529 /*
5530 * Pre-reserve space for IP, SCTP, and
5531 * chunk header.
5532 */
5533#ifdef INET6
5534 SCTP_BUF_RESV_UF(op_err, sizeof(struct ip6_hdr));
5535#else
5536 SCTP_BUF_RESV_UF(op_err, sizeof(struct ip));
5537#endif
5538 SCTP_BUF_RESV_UF(op_err, sizeof(struct sctphdr));
5539 SCTP_BUF_RESV_UF(op_err, sizeof(struct sctp_chunkhdr));
5540 SCTP_BUF_LEN(op_err) = sizeof(struct sctp_gen_error_cause);
5541 cause = mtod(op_err, struct sctp_gen_error_cause *);
5542 cause->code = htons(SCTP_CAUSE_UNRESOLVABLE_ADDR);
5543 cause->length = htons((uint16_t)(sizeof(struct sctp_gen_error_cause) + plen));
5544 SCTP_BUF_NEXT(op_err) = SCTP_M_COPYM(mat, at, plen, M_NOWAIT);
5545 if (SCTP_BUF_NEXT(op_err) == NULL) {
5546 sctp_m_freem(op_err);
5547 op_err = NULL;
5548 op_err_last = NULL;
5549 }
5550 }
5551 return (op_err);
5552 }
5553 default:
5554 /*
5555 * we do not recognize the parameter figure out what
5556 * we do.
5557 */
5558 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT1, "Hit default param %x\n", ptype);
5559 if ((ptype & 0x4000) == 0x4000) {
5560 /* Report bit is set?? */
5561 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT1, "report op err\n");
5562 if (op_err == NULL) {
5563 int l_len;
5564 /* Ok need to try to get an mbuf */
5565#ifdef INET6
5566 l_len = SCTP_MIN_OVERHEAD;
5567#else
5568 l_len = SCTP_MIN_V4_OVERHEAD;
5569#endif
5570 l_len += sizeof(struct sctp_chunkhdr);
5571 l_len += sizeof(struct sctp_paramhdr);
5572 op_err = sctp_get_mbuf_for_msg(l_len, 0, M_NOWAIT, 1, MT_DATA);
5573 if (op_err) {
5574 SCTP_BUF_LEN(op_err) = 0;
5575#ifdef INET6
5576 SCTP_BUF_RESV_UF(op_err, sizeof(struct ip6_hdr));
5577#else
5578 SCTP_BUF_RESV_UF(op_err, sizeof(struct ip));
5579#endif
5580 SCTP_BUF_RESV_UF(op_err, sizeof(struct sctphdr));
5581 SCTP_BUF_RESV_UF(op_err, sizeof(struct sctp_chunkhdr));
5582 op_err_last = op_err;
5583 }
5584 }
5585 if (op_err != NULL) {
5586 /* If we have space */
5587 struct sctp_paramhdr *param;
5588
5589 if (pad_needed > 0) {
5590 op_err_last = sctp_add_pad_tombuf(op_err_last, pad_needed);
5591 }
5592 if (op_err_last == NULL) {
5593 sctp_m_freem(op_err);
5594 op_err = NULL;
5595 op_err_last = NULL;
5596 goto more_processing;
5597 }
5598 if (M_TRAILINGSPACE(op_err_last) < (int)sizeof(struct sctp_paramhdr)) {
5599 m_tmp = sctp_get_mbuf_for_msg(sizeof(struct sctp_paramhdr), 0, M_NOWAIT, 1, MT_DATA);
5600 if (m_tmp == NULL) {
5601 sctp_m_freem(op_err);
5602 op_err = NULL;
5603 op_err_last = NULL;
5604 goto more_processing;
5605 }
5606 SCTP_BUF_LEN(m_tmp) = 0;
5607 SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m_tmp) = NULL;
5608 SCTP_BUF_NEXT(op_err_last) = m_tmp;
5609 op_err_last = m_tmp;
5610 }
5611 param = (struct sctp_paramhdr *)(mtod(op_err_last, caddr_t) + SCTP_BUF_LEN(op_err_last));
5612 param->param_type = htons(SCTP_UNRECOG_PARAM);
5613 param->param_length = htons((uint16_t)sizeof(struct sctp_paramhdr) + plen);
5614 SCTP_BUF_LEN(op_err_last) += sizeof(struct sctp_paramhdr);
5615 SCTP_BUF_NEXT(op_err_last) = SCTP_M_COPYM(mat, at, plen, M_NOWAIT);
5616 if (SCTP_BUF_NEXT(op_err_last) == NULL) {
5617 sctp_m_freem(op_err);
5618 op_err = NULL;
5619 op_err_last = NULL;
5620 goto more_processing;
5621 } else {
5622 while (SCTP_BUF_NEXT(op_err_last) != NULL) {
5623 op_err_last = SCTP_BUF_NEXT(op_err_last);
5624 }
5625 }
5626 if (plen % 4 != 0) {
5627 pad_needed = 4 - (plen % 4);
5628 } else {
5629 pad_needed = 0;
5630 }
5631 }
5632 }
5633 more_processing:
5634 if ((ptype & 0x8000) == 0x0000) {
5635 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT1, "stop proc\n");
5636 return (op_err);
5637 } else {
5638 /* skip this chunk and continue processing */
5639 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT1, "move on\n");
5640 at += SCTP_SIZE32(plen);
5641 }
5642 break;
5643 }
5644 phdr = sctp_get_next_param(mat, at, &params, sizeof(params));
5645 }
5646 return (op_err);
5647 invalid_size:
5648 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT1, "abort flag set\n");
5649 *abort_processing = 1;
5650 sctp_m_freem(op_err);
5651 op_err = NULL;
5652 op_err_last = NULL;
5653 if (phdr != NULL) {
5654 struct sctp_paramhdr *param;
5655 int l_len;
5656#ifdef INET6
5657 l_len = SCTP_MIN_OVERHEAD;
5658#else
5659 l_len = SCTP_MIN_V4_OVERHEAD;
5660#endif
5661 l_len += sizeof(struct sctp_chunkhdr);
5662 l_len += (2 * sizeof(struct sctp_paramhdr));
5663 op_err = sctp_get_mbuf_for_msg(l_len, 0, M_NOWAIT, 1, MT_DATA);
5664 if (op_err) {
5665 SCTP_BUF_LEN(op_err) = 0;
5666#ifdef INET6
5667 SCTP_BUF_RESV_UF(op_err, sizeof(struct ip6_hdr));
5668#else
5669 SCTP_BUF_RESV_UF(op_err, sizeof(struct ip));
5670#endif
5671 SCTP_BUF_RESV_UF(op_err, sizeof(struct sctphdr));
5672 SCTP_BUF_RESV_UF(op_err, sizeof(struct sctp_chunkhdr));
5673 SCTP_BUF_LEN(op_err) = 2 * sizeof(struct sctp_paramhdr);
5674 param = mtod(op_err, struct sctp_paramhdr *);
5675 param->param_type = htons(SCTP_CAUSE_PROTOCOL_VIOLATION);
5676 param->param_length = htons(2 * sizeof(struct sctp_paramhdr));
5677 param++;
5678 param->param_type = htons(ptype);
5679 param->param_length = htons(plen);
5680 }
5681 }
5682 return (op_err);
5683}
5684
5685/*
5686 * Given a INIT chunk, look through the parameters to verify that there
5687 * are no new addresses.
5688 * Return true, if there is a new address or there is a problem parsing
5689 the parameters. Provide an optional error cause used when sending an ABORT.
5690 * Return false, if there are no new addresses and there is no problem in
5691 parameter processing.
5692 */
5693static bool
5694sctp_are_there_new_addresses(struct sctp_association *asoc,
5695 struct mbuf *in_initpkt, int offset, int limit, struct sockaddr *src,
5696 struct mbuf **op_err)
5697{
5698 struct sockaddr *sa_touse;
5699 struct sockaddr *sa;
5700 struct sctp_paramhdr *phdr, params;
5701 struct sctp_nets *net;
5702#ifdef INET
5703 struct sockaddr_in sin4, *sa4;
5704#endif
5705#ifdef INET6
5706 struct sockaddr_in6 sin6, *sa6;
5707#endif
5708#if defined(__Userspace__)
5709 struct sockaddr_conn *sac;
5710#endif
5711 uint16_t ptype, plen;
5712 bool fnd, check_src;
5713
5714 *op_err = NULL;
5715#ifdef INET
5716 memset(&sin4, 0, sizeof(sin4));
5717 sin4.sin_family = AF_INET;
5718#ifdef HAVE_SIN_LEN
5719 sin4.sin_len = sizeof(sin4);
5720#endif
5721#endif
5722#ifdef INET6
5723 memset(&sin6, 0, sizeof(sin6));
5724 sin6.sin6_family = AF_INET6;
5725#ifdef HAVE_SIN6_LEN
5726 sin6.sin6_len = sizeof(sin6);
5727#endif
5728#endif
5729 /* First what about the src address of the pkt ? */
5730 check_src = false;
5731 switch (src->sa_family) {
5732#ifdef INET
5733 case AF_INET:
5734 if (asoc->scope.ipv4_addr_legal) {
5735 check_src = true;
5736 }
5737 break;
5738#endif
5739#ifdef INET6
5740 case AF_INET6:
5741 if (asoc->scope.ipv6_addr_legal) {
5742 check_src = true;
5743 }
5744 break;
5745#endif
5746#if defined(__Userspace__)
5747 case AF_CONN:
5748 if (asoc->scope.conn_addr_legal) {
5749 check_src = true;
5750 }
5751 break;
5752#endif
5753 default:
5754 /* TSNH */
5755 break;
5756 }
5757 if (check_src) {
5758 fnd = false;
5759 TAILQ_FOREACH(net, &asoc->nets, sctp_next) {
5760 sa = (struct sockaddr *)&net->ro._l_addr;
5761 if (sa->sa_family == src->sa_family) {
5762#ifdef INET
5763 if (sa->sa_family == AF_INET) {
5764 struct sockaddr_in *src4;
5765
5766 sa4 = (struct sockaddr_in *)sa;
5767 src4 = (struct sockaddr_in *)src;
5768 if (sa4->sin_addr.s_addr == src4->sin_addr.s_addr) {
5769 fnd = true;
5770 break;
5771 }
5772 }
5773#endif
5774#ifdef INET6
5775 if (sa->sa_family == AF_INET6) {
5776 struct sockaddr_in6 *src6;
5777
5778 sa6 = (struct sockaddr_in6 *)sa;
5779 src6 = (struct sockaddr_in6 *)src;
5780 if (SCTP6_ARE_ADDR_EQUAL(sa6, src6)) {
5781 fnd = true;
5782 break;
5783 }
5784 }
5785#endif
5786#if defined(__Userspace__)
5787 if (sa->sa_family == AF_CONN) {
5788 struct sockaddr_conn *srcc;
5789
5790 sac = (struct sockaddr_conn *)sa;
5791 srcc = (struct sockaddr_conn *)src;
5792 if (sac->sconn_addr == srcc->sconn_addr) {
5793 fnd = true;
5794 break;
5795 }
5796 }
5797#endif
5798 }
5799 }
5800 if (!fnd) {
5801 /*
5802 * If sending an ABORT in case of an additional address,
5803 * don't use the new address error cause.
5804 * This looks no different than if no listener was
5805 * present.
5806 */
5807 *op_err = sctp_generate_cause(SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_diag_info_code), "Address added");
5808 return (true);
5809 }
5810 }
5811 /* Ok so far lets munge through the rest of the packet */
5812 offset += sizeof(struct sctp_init_chunk);
5813 phdr = sctp_get_next_param(in_initpkt, offset, &params, sizeof(params));
5814 while (phdr) {
5815 sa_touse = NULL;
5816 ptype = ntohs(phdr->param_type);
5817 plen = ntohs(phdr->param_length);
5818 if (offset + plen > limit) {
5819 *op_err = sctp_generate_cause(SCTP_CAUSE_PROTOCOL_VIOLATION, "Partial parameter");
5820 return (true);
5821 }
5822 if (plen < sizeof(struct sctp_paramhdr)) {
5823 *op_err = sctp_generate_cause(SCTP_CAUSE_PROTOCOL_VIOLATION, "Parameter length too small");
5824 return (true);
5825 }
5826 switch (ptype) {
5827#ifdef INET
5828 case SCTP_IPV4_ADDRESS:
5829 {
5830 struct sctp_ipv4addr_param *p4, p4_buf;
5831
5832 if (plen != sizeof(struct sctp_ipv4addr_param)) {
5833 *op_err = sctp_generate_cause(SCTP_CAUSE_PROTOCOL_VIOLATION, "Parameter length illegal");
5834 return (true);
5835 }
5836 phdr = sctp_get_next_param(in_initpkt, offset,
5837 (struct sctp_paramhdr *)&p4_buf, sizeof(p4_buf));
5838 if (phdr == NULL) {
5839 *op_err = sctp_generate_cause(SCTP_CAUSE_PROTOCOL_VIOLATION, "");
5840 return (true);
5841 }
5842 if (asoc->scope.ipv4_addr_legal) {
5843 p4 = (struct sctp_ipv4addr_param *)phdr;
5844 sin4.sin_addr.s_addr = p4->addr;
5845 sa_touse = (struct sockaddr *)&sin4;
5846 }
5847 break;
5848 }
5849#endif
5850#ifdef INET6
5851 case SCTP_IPV6_ADDRESS:
5852 {
5853 struct sctp_ipv6addr_param *p6, p6_buf;
5854
5855 if (plen != sizeof(struct sctp_ipv6addr_param)) {
5856 *op_err = sctp_generate_cause(SCTP_CAUSE_PROTOCOL_VIOLATION, "Parameter length illegal");
5857 return (true);
5858 }
5859 phdr = sctp_get_next_param(in_initpkt, offset,
5860 (struct sctp_paramhdr *)&p6_buf, sizeof(p6_buf));
5861 if (phdr == NULL) {
5862 *op_err = sctp_generate_cause(SCTP_CAUSE_PROTOCOL_VIOLATION, "");
5863 return (true);
5864 }
5865 if (asoc->scope.ipv6_addr_legal) {
5866 p6 = (struct sctp_ipv6addr_param *)phdr;
5867 memcpy((caddr_t)&sin6.sin6_addr, p6->addr,
5868 sizeof(p6->addr));
5869 sa_touse = (struct sockaddr *)&sin6;
5870 }
5871 break;
5872 }
5873#endif
5874 default:
5875 sa_touse = NULL;
5876 break;
5877 }
5878 if (sa_touse) {
5879 /* ok, sa_touse points to one to check */
5880 fnd = false;
5881 TAILQ_FOREACH(net, &asoc->nets, sctp_next) {
5882 sa = (struct sockaddr *)&net->ro._l_addr;
5883 if (sa->sa_family != sa_touse->sa_family) {
5884 continue;
5885 }
5886#ifdef INET
5887 if (sa->sa_family == AF_INET) {
5888 sa4 = (struct sockaddr_in *)sa;
5889 if (sa4->sin_addr.s_addr ==
5890 sin4.sin_addr.s_addr) {
5891 fnd = true;
5892 break;
5893 }
5894 }
5895#endif
5896#ifdef INET6
5897 if (sa->sa_family == AF_INET6) {
5898 sa6 = (struct sockaddr_in6 *)sa;
5899 if (SCTP6_ARE_ADDR_EQUAL(
5900 sa6, &sin6)) {
5901 fnd = true;
5902 break;
5903 }
5904 }
5905#endif
5906 }
5907 if (!fnd) {
5908 /*
5909 * If sending an ABORT in case of an additional
5910 * address, don't use the new address error
5911 * cause.
5912 * This looks no different than if no listener
5913 * was present.
5914 */
5915 *op_err = sctp_generate_cause(SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_diag_info_code), "Address added");
5916 return (true);
5917 }
5918 }
5919 offset += SCTP_SIZE32(plen);
5920 if (offset >= limit) {
5921 break;
5922 }
5923 phdr = sctp_get_next_param(in_initpkt, offset, &params, sizeof(params));
5924 }
5925 return (false);
5926}
5927
5928/*
5929 * Given a MBUF chain that was sent into us containing an INIT. Build a
5930 * INIT-ACK with COOKIE and send back. We assume that the in_initpkt has done
5931 * a pullup to include IPv6/4header, SCTP header and initial part of INIT
5932 * message (i.e. the struct sctp_init_msg).
5933 */
5934void
5935sctp_send_initiate_ack(struct sctp_inpcb *inp, struct sctp_tcb *stcb,
5936 struct sctp_nets *src_net, struct mbuf *init_pkt,
5937 int iphlen, int offset,
5938 struct sockaddr *src, struct sockaddr *dst,
5939 struct sctphdr *sh, struct sctp_init_chunk *init_chk,
5940#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
5941 uint8_t mflowtype, uint32_t mflowid,
5942#endif
5943 uint32_t vrf_id, uint16_t port)
5944{
5945 struct sctp_association *asoc;
5946 struct mbuf *m, *m_tmp, *m_last, *m_cookie, *op_err;
5947 struct sctp_init_ack_chunk *initack;
5948 struct sctp_adaptation_layer_indication *ali;
5949 struct sctp_supported_chunk_types_param *pr_supported;
5950 struct sctp_paramhdr *ph;
5951 union sctp_sockstore *over_addr;
5952 struct sctp_scoping scp;
5953 struct timeval now;
5954#ifdef INET
5955 struct sockaddr_in *dst4 = (struct sockaddr_in *)dst;
5956 struct sockaddr_in *src4 = (struct sockaddr_in *)src;
5957 struct sockaddr_in *sin;
5958#endif
5959#ifdef INET6
5960 struct sockaddr_in6 *dst6 = (struct sockaddr_in6 *)dst;
5961 struct sockaddr_in6 *src6 = (struct sockaddr_in6 *)src;
5962 struct sockaddr_in6 *sin6;
5963#endif
5964#if defined(__Userspace__)
5965 struct sockaddr_conn *dstconn = (struct sockaddr_conn *)dst;
5966 struct sockaddr_conn *srcconn = (struct sockaddr_conn *)src;
5967 struct sockaddr_conn *sconn;
5968#endif
5969 struct sockaddr *to;
5970 struct sctp_state_cookie stc;
5971 struct sctp_nets *net = NULL;
5972 uint8_t *signature = NULL;
5973 int cnt_inits_to = 0;
5974 uint16_t his_limit, i_want;
5975 int abort_flag;
5976 int nat_friendly = 0;
5977 int error;
5978 struct socket *so;
5979 uint16_t num_ext, chunk_len, padding_len, parameter_len;
5980
5981 if (stcb) {
5982 asoc = &stcb->asoc;
5983 } else {
5984 asoc = NULL;
5985 }
5986 if ((asoc != NULL) &&
5987 (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) != SCTP_STATE_COOKIE_WAIT)) {
5988 if (sctp_are_there_new_addresses(asoc, init_pkt, offset, offset + ntohs(init_chk->ch.chunk_length), src, &op_err)) {
5989 /*
5990 * new addresses, out of here in non-cookie-wait states
5991 */
5992 sctp_send_abort(init_pkt, iphlen, src, dst, sh, 0, op_err,
5993#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
5994 mflowtype, mflowid, inp->fibnum,
5995#endif
5996 vrf_id, port);
5997 return;
5998 }
5999 if (src_net != NULL && (src_net->port != port)) {
6000 /*
6001 * change of remote encapsulation port, out of here in
6002 * non-cookie-wait states
6003 *
6004 * Send an ABORT, without an specific error cause.
6005 * This looks no different than if no listener
6006 * was present.
6007 */
6008 op_err = sctp_generate_cause(SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_diag_info_code),
6009 "Remote encapsulation port changed");
6010 sctp_send_abort(init_pkt, iphlen, src, dst, sh, 0, op_err,
6011#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6012 mflowtype, mflowid, inp->fibnum,
6013#endif
6014 vrf_id, port);
6015 return;
6016 }
6017 }
6018 abort_flag = 0;
6019 op_err = sctp_arethere_unrecognized_parameters(init_pkt,
6020 (offset + sizeof(struct sctp_init_chunk)),
6021 &abort_flag,
6022 (struct sctp_chunkhdr *)init_chk,
6023 &nat_friendly, NULL);
6024 if (abort_flag) {
6025 do_a_abort:
6026 if (op_err == NULL) {
6027 char msg[SCTP_DIAG_INFO_LEN];
6028
6029 SCTP_SNPRINTF(msg, sizeof(msg), "%s:%d at %s", __FILE__, __LINE__, __func__);
6030 op_err = sctp_generate_cause(SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_diag_info_code),
6031 msg);
6032 }
6033 sctp_send_abort(init_pkt, iphlen, src, dst, sh,
6034 init_chk->init.initiate_tag, op_err,
6035#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6036 mflowtype, mflowid, inp->fibnum,
6037#endif
6038 vrf_id, port);
6039 return;
6040 }
6041 m = sctp_get_mbuf_for_msg(MCLBYTES, 0, M_NOWAIT, 1, MT_DATA);
6042 if (m == NULL) {
6043 /* No memory, INIT timer will re-attempt. */
6044 sctp_m_freem(op_err);
6045 return;
6046 }
6047 chunk_len = (uint16_t)sizeof(struct sctp_init_ack_chunk);
6048 padding_len = 0;
6049
6050 /*
6051 * We might not overwrite the identification[] completely and on
6052 * some platforms time_entered will contain some padding.
6053 * Therefore zero out the cookie to avoid putting
6054 * uninitialized memory on the wire.
6055 */
6056 memset(&stc, 0, sizeof(struct sctp_state_cookie));
6057
6058 /* the time I built cookie */
6059 (void)SCTP_GETTIME_TIMEVAL(&now);
6060 stc.time_entered.tv_sec = now.tv_sec;
6061 stc.time_entered.tv_usec = now.tv_usec;
6062
6063 /* populate any tie tags */
6064 if (asoc != NULL) {
6065 /* unlock before tag selections */
6066 stc.tie_tag_my_vtag = asoc->my_vtag_nonce;
6067 stc.tie_tag_peer_vtag = asoc->peer_vtag_nonce;
6068 stc.cookie_life = asoc->cookie_life;
6069 net = asoc->primary_destination;
6070 } else {
6071 stc.tie_tag_my_vtag = 0;
6072 stc.tie_tag_peer_vtag = 0;
6073 /* life I will award this cookie */
6074 stc.cookie_life = inp->sctp_ep.def_cookie_life;
6075 }
6076
6077 /* copy in the ports for later check */
6078 stc.myport = sh->dest_port;
6079 stc.peerport = sh->src_port;
6080
6081 /*
6082 * If we wanted to honor cookie life extensions, we would add to
6083 * stc.cookie_life. For now we should NOT honor any extension
6084 */
6085 stc.site_scope = stc.local_scope = stc.loopback_scope = 0;
6086 if (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_BOUND_V6) {
6087 stc.ipv6_addr_legal = 1;
6088 if (SCTP_IPV6_V6ONLY(inp)) {
6089 stc.ipv4_addr_legal = 0;
6090 } else {
6091 stc.ipv4_addr_legal = 1;
6092 }
6093#if defined(__Userspace__)
6094 stc.conn_addr_legal = 0;
6095#endif
6096 } else {
6097 stc.ipv6_addr_legal = 0;
6098#if defined(__Userspace__)
6099 if (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_BOUND_CONN) {
6100 stc.conn_addr_legal = 1;
6101 stc.ipv4_addr_legal = 0;
6102 } else {
6103 stc.conn_addr_legal = 0;
6104 stc.ipv4_addr_legal = 1;
6105 }
6106#else
6107 stc.ipv4_addr_legal = 1;
6108#endif
6109 }
6110 stc.ipv4_scope = 0;
6111 if (net == NULL) {
6112 to = src;
6113 switch (dst->sa_family) {
6114#ifdef INET
6115 case AF_INET:
6116 {
6117 /* lookup address */
6118 stc.address[0] = src4->sin_addr.s_addr;
6119 stc.address[1] = 0;
6120 stc.address[2] = 0;
6121 stc.address[3] = 0;
6122 stc.addr_type = SCTP_IPV4_ADDRESS;
6123 /* local from address */
6124 stc.laddress[0] = dst4->sin_addr.s_addr;
6125 stc.laddress[1] = 0;
6126 stc.laddress[2] = 0;
6127 stc.laddress[3] = 0;
6128 stc.laddr_type = SCTP_IPV4_ADDRESS;
6129 /* scope_id is only for v6 */
6130 stc.scope_id = 0;
6131 if ((IN4_ISPRIVATE_ADDRESS(&src4->sin_addr)) ||
6132 (IN4_ISPRIVATE_ADDRESS(&dst4->sin_addr))){
6133 stc.ipv4_scope = 1;
6134 }
6135 /* Must use the address in this case */
6136 if (sctp_is_address_on_local_host(src, vrf_id)) {
6137 stc.loopback_scope = 1;
6138 stc.ipv4_scope = 1;
6139 stc.site_scope = 1;
6140 stc.local_scope = 0;
6141 }
6142 break;
6143 }
6144#endif
6145#ifdef INET6
6146 case AF_INET6:
6147 {
6148 stc.addr_type = SCTP_IPV6_ADDRESS;
6149 memcpy(&stc.address, &src6->sin6_addr, sizeof(struct in6_addr));
6150#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6151 stc.scope_id = ntohs(in6_getscope(&src6->sin6_addr));
6152#else
6153 stc.scope_id = 0;
6154#endif
6155 if (sctp_is_address_on_local_host(src, vrf_id)) {
6156 stc.loopback_scope = 1;
6157 stc.local_scope = 0;
6158 stc.site_scope = 1;
6159 stc.ipv4_scope = 1;
6160 } else if (IN6_IS_ADDR_LINKLOCAL(&src6->sin6_addr) ||
6161 IN6_IS_ADDR_LINKLOCAL(&dst6->sin6_addr)) {
6162 /*
6163 * If the new destination or source is a
6164 * LINK_LOCAL we must have common both site and
6165 * local scope. Don't set local scope though
6166 * since we must depend on the source to be
6167 * added implicitly. We cannot assure just
6168 * because we share one link that all links are
6169 * common.
6170 */
6171#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6172 /* Mac OS X currently doesn't have in6_getscope() */
6173 stc.scope_id = src6->sin6_addr.s6_addr16[1];
6174#endif
6175 stc.local_scope = 0;
6176 stc.site_scope = 1;
6177 stc.ipv4_scope = 1;
6178 /*
6179 * we start counting for the private address
6180 * stuff at 1. since the link local we
6181 * source from won't show up in our scoped
6182 * count.
6183 */
6184 cnt_inits_to = 1;
6185 /* pull out the scope_id from incoming pkt */
6186 } else if (IN6_IS_ADDR_SITELOCAL(&src6->sin6_addr) ||
6187 IN6_IS_ADDR_SITELOCAL(&dst6->sin6_addr)) {
6188 /*
6189 * If the new destination or source is
6190 * SITE_LOCAL then we must have site scope in
6191 * common.
6192 */
6193 stc.site_scope = 1;
6194 }
6195 memcpy(&stc.laddress, &dst6->sin6_addr, sizeof(struct in6_addr));
6196 stc.laddr_type = SCTP_IPV6_ADDRESS;
6197 break;
6198 }
6199#endif
6200#if defined(__Userspace__)
6201 case AF_CONN:
6202 {
6203 /* lookup address */
6204 stc.address[0] = 0;
6205 stc.address[1] = 0;
6206 stc.address[2] = 0;
6207 stc.address[3] = 0;
6208 memcpy(&stc.address, &srcconn->sconn_addr, sizeof(void *));
6209 stc.addr_type = SCTP_CONN_ADDRESS;
6210 /* local from address */
6211 stc.laddress[0] = 0;
6212 stc.laddress[1] = 0;
6213 stc.laddress[2] = 0;
6214 stc.laddress[3] = 0;
6215 memcpy(&stc.laddress, &dstconn->sconn_addr, sizeof(void *));
6216 stc.laddr_type = SCTP_CONN_ADDRESS;
6217 /* scope_id is only for v6 */
6218 stc.scope_id = 0;
6219 break;
6220 }
6221#endif
6222 default:
6223 /* TSNH */
6224 goto do_a_abort;
6225 break;
6226 }
6227 } else {
6228 /* set the scope per the existing tcb */
6229
6230#ifdef INET6
6231 struct sctp_nets *lnet;
6232#endif
6233
6234 stc.loopback_scope = asoc->scope.loopback_scope;
6235 stc.ipv4_scope = asoc->scope.ipv4_local_scope;
6236 stc.site_scope = asoc->scope.site_scope;
6237 stc.local_scope = asoc->scope.local_scope;
6238#ifdef INET6
6239 /* Why do we not consider IPv4 LL addresses? */
6240 TAILQ_FOREACH(lnet, &asoc->nets, sctp_next) {
6241 if (lnet->ro._l_addr.sin6.sin6_family == AF_INET6) {
6242 if (IN6_IS_ADDR_LINKLOCAL(&lnet->ro._l_addr.sin6.sin6_addr)) {
6243 /*
6244 * if we have a LL address, start
6245 * counting at 1.
6246 */
6247 cnt_inits_to = 1;
6248 }
6249 }
6250 }
6251#endif
6252 /* use the net pointer */
6253 to = (struct sockaddr *)&net->ro._l_addr;
6254 switch (to->sa_family) {
6255#ifdef INET
6256 case AF_INET:
6257 sin = (struct sockaddr_in *)to;
6258 stc.address[0] = sin->sin_addr.s_addr;
6259 stc.address[1] = 0;
6260 stc.address[2] = 0;
6261 stc.address[3] = 0;
6262 stc.addr_type = SCTP_IPV4_ADDRESS;
6263 if (net->src_addr_selected == 0) {
6264 /*
6265 * strange case here, the INIT should have
6266 * did the selection.
6267 */
6268 net->ro._s_addr = sctp_source_address_selection(inp,
6269 stcb, (sctp_route_t *)&net->ro,
6270 net, 0, vrf_id);
6271 if (net->ro._s_addr == NULL) {
6272 sctp_m_freem(op_err);
6273 sctp_m_freem(m);
6274 return;
6275 }
6276
6277 net->src_addr_selected = 1;
6278 }
6279 stc.laddress[0] = net->ro._s_addr->address.sin.sin_addr.s_addr;
6280 stc.laddress[1] = 0;
6281 stc.laddress[2] = 0;
6282 stc.laddress[3] = 0;
6283 stc.laddr_type = SCTP_IPV4_ADDRESS;
6284 /* scope_id is only for v6 */
6285 stc.scope_id = 0;
6286 break;
6287#endif
6288#ifdef INET6
6289 case AF_INET6:
6290 sin6 = (struct sockaddr_in6 *)to;
6291 memcpy(&stc.address, &sin6->sin6_addr,
6292 sizeof(struct in6_addr));
6293 stc.addr_type = SCTP_IPV6_ADDRESS;
6294 stc.scope_id = sin6->sin6_scope_id;
6295 if (net->src_addr_selected == 0) {
6296 /*
6297 * strange case here, the INIT should have
6298 * done the selection.
6299 */
6300 net->ro._s_addr = sctp_source_address_selection(inp,
6301 stcb, (sctp_route_t *)&net->ro,
6302 net, 0, vrf_id);
6303 if (net->ro._s_addr == NULL) {
6304 sctp_m_freem(op_err);
6305 sctp_m_freem(m);
6306 return;
6307 }
6308
6309 net->src_addr_selected = 1;
6310 }
6311 memcpy(&stc.laddress, &net->ro._s_addr->address.sin6.sin6_addr,
6312 sizeof(struct in6_addr));
6313 stc.laddr_type = SCTP_IPV6_ADDRESS;
6314 break;
6315#endif
6316#if defined(__Userspace__)
6317 case AF_CONN:
6318 sconn = (struct sockaddr_conn *)to;
6319 stc.address[0] = 0;
6320 stc.address[1] = 0;
6321 stc.address[2] = 0;
6322 stc.address[3] = 0;
6323 memcpy(&stc.address, &sconn->sconn_addr, sizeof(void *));
6324 stc.addr_type = SCTP_CONN_ADDRESS;
6325 stc.laddress[0] = 0;
6326 stc.laddress[1] = 0;
6327 stc.laddress[2] = 0;
6328 stc.laddress[3] = 0;
6329 memcpy(&stc.laddress, &sconn->sconn_addr, sizeof(void *));
6330 stc.laddr_type = SCTP_CONN_ADDRESS;
6331 stc.scope_id = 0;
6332 break;
6333#endif
6334 }
6335 }
6336 /* Now lets put the SCTP header in place */
6337 initack = mtod(m, struct sctp_init_ack_chunk *);
6338 /* Save it off for quick ref */
6339 stc.peers_vtag = ntohl(init_chk->init.initiate_tag);
6340 /* who are we */
6341 memcpy(stc.identification, SCTP_VERSION_STRING,
6342 min(strlen(SCTP_VERSION_STRING), sizeof(stc.identification)));
6343 memset(stc.reserved, 0, SCTP_RESERVE_SPACE);
6344 /* now the chunk header */
6345 initack->ch.chunk_type = SCTP_INITIATION_ACK;
6346 initack->ch.chunk_flags = 0;
6347 /* fill in later from mbuf we build */
6348 initack->ch.chunk_length = 0;
6349 /* place in my tag */
6350 if ((asoc != NULL) &&
6351 ((SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_COOKIE_WAIT) ||
6352 (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_INUSE) ||
6353 (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_COOKIE_ECHOED))) {
6354 /* re-use the v-tags and init-seq here */
6355 initack->init.initiate_tag = htonl(asoc->my_vtag);
6356 initack->init.initial_tsn = htonl(asoc->init_seq_number);
6357 } else {
6358 uint32_t vtag, itsn;
6359
6360 if (asoc) {
6361 atomic_add_int(&asoc->refcnt, 1);
6362 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
6363 new_tag:
6364 vtag = sctp_select_a_tag(inp, inp->sctp_lport, sh->src_port, 1);
6365 if ((asoc->peer_supports_nat) && (vtag == asoc->my_vtag)) {
6366 /* Got a duplicate vtag on some guy behind a nat
6367 * make sure we don't use it.
6368 */
6369 goto new_tag;
6370 }
6371 initack->init.initiate_tag = htonl(vtag);
6372 /* get a TSN to use too */
6373 itsn = sctp_select_initial_TSN(&inp->sctp_ep);
6374 initack->init.initial_tsn = htonl(itsn);
6375 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
6376 atomic_add_int(&asoc->refcnt, -1);
6377 } else {
6378 SCTP_INP_INCR_REF(inp);
6379 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
6380 vtag = sctp_select_a_tag(inp, inp->sctp_lport, sh->src_port, 1);
6381 initack->init.initiate_tag = htonl(vtag);
6382 /* get a TSN to use too */
6383 initack->init.initial_tsn = htonl(sctp_select_initial_TSN(&inp->sctp_ep));
6384 SCTP_INP_RLOCK(inp);
6385 SCTP_INP_DECR_REF(inp);
6386 }
6387 }
6388 /* save away my tag to */
6389 stc.my_vtag = initack->init.initiate_tag;
6390
6391 /* set up some of the credits. */
6392 so = inp->sctp_socket;
6393 if (so == NULL) {
6394 /* memory problem */
6395 sctp_m_freem(op_err);
6396 sctp_m_freem(m);
6397 return;
6398 } else {
6399 initack->init.a_rwnd = htonl(max(SCTP_SB_LIMIT_RCV(so), SCTP_MINIMAL_RWND));
6400 }
6401 /* set what I want */
6402 his_limit = ntohs(init_chk->init.num_inbound_streams);
6403 /* choose what I want */
6404 if (asoc != NULL) {
6405 if (asoc->streamoutcnt > asoc->pre_open_streams) {
6406 i_want = asoc->streamoutcnt;
6407 } else {
6408 i_want = asoc->pre_open_streams;
6409 }
6410 } else {
6411 i_want = inp->sctp_ep.pre_open_stream_count;
6412 }
6413 if (his_limit < i_want) {
6414 /* I Want more :< */
6415 initack->init.num_outbound_streams = init_chk->init.num_inbound_streams;
6416 } else {
6417 /* I can have what I want :> */
6418 initack->init.num_outbound_streams = htons(i_want);
6419 }
6420 /* tell him his limit. */
6421 initack->init.num_inbound_streams =
6422 htons(inp->sctp_ep.max_open_streams_intome);
6423
6424 /* adaptation layer indication parameter */
6425 if (inp->sctp_ep.adaptation_layer_indicator_provided) {
6426 parameter_len = (uint16_t)sizeof(struct sctp_adaptation_layer_indication);
6427 ali = (struct sctp_adaptation_layer_indication *)(mtod(m, caddr_t) + chunk_len);
6428 ali->ph.param_type = htons(SCTP_ULP_ADAPTATION);
6429 ali->ph.param_length = htons(parameter_len);
6430 ali->indication = htonl(inp->sctp_ep.adaptation_layer_indicator);
6431 chunk_len += parameter_len;
6432 }
6433
6434 /* ECN parameter */
6435 if (((asoc != NULL) && (asoc->ecn_supported == 1)) ||
6436 ((asoc == NULL) && (inp->ecn_supported == 1))) {
6437 parameter_len = (uint16_t)sizeof(struct sctp_paramhdr);
6438 ph = (struct sctp_paramhdr *)(mtod(m, caddr_t) + chunk_len);
6439 ph->param_type = htons(SCTP_ECN_CAPABLE);
6440 ph->param_length = htons(parameter_len);
6441 chunk_len += parameter_len;
6442 }
6443
6444 /* PR-SCTP supported parameter */
6445 if (((asoc != NULL) && (asoc->prsctp_supported == 1)) ||
6446 ((asoc == NULL) && (inp->prsctp_supported == 1))) {
6447 parameter_len = (uint16_t)sizeof(struct sctp_paramhdr);
6448 ph = (struct sctp_paramhdr *)(mtod(m, caddr_t) + chunk_len);
6449 ph->param_type = htons(SCTP_PRSCTP_SUPPORTED);
6450 ph->param_length = htons(parameter_len);
6451 chunk_len += parameter_len;
6452 }
6453
6454 /* Add NAT friendly parameter */
6455 if (nat_friendly) {
6456 parameter_len = (uint16_t)sizeof(struct sctp_paramhdr);
6457 ph = (struct sctp_paramhdr *)(mtod(m, caddr_t) + chunk_len);
6458 ph->param_type = htons(SCTP_HAS_NAT_SUPPORT);
6459 ph->param_length = htons(parameter_len);
6460 chunk_len += parameter_len;
6461 }
6462
6463 /* And now tell the peer which extensions we support */
6464 num_ext = 0;
6465 pr_supported = (struct sctp_supported_chunk_types_param *)(mtod(m, caddr_t) + chunk_len);
6466 if (((asoc != NULL) && (asoc->prsctp_supported == 1)) ||
6467 ((asoc == NULL) && (inp->prsctp_supported == 1))) {
6468 pr_supported->chunk_types[num_ext++] = SCTP_FORWARD_CUM_TSN;
6469 if (((asoc != NULL) && (asoc->idata_supported == 1)) ||
6470 ((asoc == NULL) && (inp->idata_supported == 1))) {
6471 pr_supported->chunk_types[num_ext++] = SCTP_IFORWARD_CUM_TSN;
6472 }
6473 }
6474 if (((asoc != NULL) && (asoc->auth_supported == 1)) ||
6475 ((asoc == NULL) && (inp->auth_supported == 1))) {
6476 pr_supported->chunk_types[num_ext++] = SCTP_AUTHENTICATION;
6477 }
6478 if (((asoc != NULL) && (asoc->asconf_supported == 1)) ||
6479 ((asoc == NULL) && (inp->asconf_supported == 1))) {
6480 pr_supported->chunk_types[num_ext++] = SCTP_ASCONF;
6481 pr_supported->chunk_types[num_ext++] = SCTP_ASCONF_ACK;
6482 }
6483 if (((asoc != NULL) && (asoc->reconfig_supported == 1)) ||
6484 ((asoc == NULL) && (inp->reconfig_supported == 1))) {
6485 pr_supported->chunk_types[num_ext++] = SCTP_STREAM_RESET;
6486 }
6487 if (((asoc != NULL) && (asoc->idata_supported == 1)) ||
6488 ((asoc == NULL) && (inp->idata_supported == 1))) {
6489 pr_supported->chunk_types[num_ext++] = SCTP_IDATA;
6490 }
6491 if (((asoc != NULL) && (asoc->nrsack_supported == 1)) ||
6492 ((asoc == NULL) && (inp->nrsack_supported == 1))) {
6493 pr_supported->chunk_types[num_ext++] = SCTP_NR_SELECTIVE_ACK;
6494 }
6495 if (((asoc != NULL) && (asoc->pktdrop_supported == 1)) ||
6496 ((asoc == NULL) && (inp->pktdrop_supported == 1))) {
6497 pr_supported->chunk_types[num_ext++] = SCTP_PACKET_DROPPED;
6498 }
6499 if (num_ext > 0) {
6500 parameter_len = (uint16_t)sizeof(struct sctp_supported_chunk_types_param) + num_ext;
6501 pr_supported->ph.param_type = htons(SCTP_SUPPORTED_CHUNK_EXT);
6502 pr_supported->ph.param_length = htons(parameter_len);
6503 padding_len = SCTP_SIZE32(parameter_len) - parameter_len;
6504 chunk_len += parameter_len;
6505 }
6506
6507 /* add authentication parameters */
6508 if (((asoc != NULL) && (asoc->auth_supported == 1)) ||
6509 ((asoc == NULL) && (inp->auth_supported == 1))) {
6510 struct sctp_auth_random *randp;
6511 struct sctp_auth_hmac_algo *hmacs;
6512 struct sctp_auth_chunk_list *chunks;
6513
6514 if (padding_len > 0) {
6515 memset(mtod(m, caddr_t) + chunk_len, 0, padding_len);
6516 chunk_len += padding_len;
6517 padding_len = 0;
6518 }
6519 /* generate and add RANDOM parameter */
6520 randp = (struct sctp_auth_random *)(mtod(m, caddr_t) + chunk_len);
6521 parameter_len = (uint16_t)sizeof(struct sctp_auth_random) +
6522 SCTP_AUTH_RANDOM_SIZE_DEFAULT;
6523 randp->ph.param_type = htons(SCTP_RANDOM);
6524 randp->ph.param_length = htons(parameter_len);
6525 SCTP_READ_RANDOM(randp->random_data, SCTP_AUTH_RANDOM_SIZE_DEFAULT);
6526 padding_len = SCTP_SIZE32(parameter_len) - parameter_len;
6527 chunk_len += parameter_len;
6528
6529 if (padding_len > 0) {
6530 memset(mtod(m, caddr_t) + chunk_len, 0, padding_len);
6531 chunk_len += padding_len;
6532 padding_len = 0;
6533 }
6534 /* add HMAC_ALGO parameter */
6535 hmacs = (struct sctp_auth_hmac_algo *)(mtod(m, caddr_t) + chunk_len);
6536 parameter_len = (uint16_t)sizeof(struct sctp_auth_hmac_algo) +
6537 sctp_serialize_hmaclist(inp->sctp_ep.local_hmacs,
6538 (uint8_t *)hmacs->hmac_ids);
6539 hmacs->ph.param_type = htons(SCTP_HMAC_LIST);
6540 hmacs->ph.param_length = htons(parameter_len);
6541 padding_len = SCTP_SIZE32(parameter_len) - parameter_len;
6542 chunk_len += parameter_len;
6543
6544 if (padding_len > 0) {
6545 memset(mtod(m, caddr_t) + chunk_len, 0, padding_len);
6546 chunk_len += padding_len;
6547 padding_len = 0;
6548 }
6549 /* add CHUNKS parameter */
6550 chunks = (struct sctp_auth_chunk_list *)(mtod(m, caddr_t) + chunk_len);
6551 parameter_len = (uint16_t)sizeof(struct sctp_auth_chunk_list) +
6552 sctp_serialize_auth_chunks(inp->sctp_ep.local_auth_chunks,
6553 chunks->chunk_types);
6554 chunks->ph.param_type = htons(SCTP_CHUNK_LIST);
6555 chunks->ph.param_length = htons(parameter_len);
6556 padding_len = SCTP_SIZE32(parameter_len) - parameter_len;
6557 chunk_len += parameter_len;
6558 }
6559 SCTP_BUF_LEN(m) = chunk_len;
6560 m_last = m;
6561 /* now the addresses */
6562 /* To optimize this we could put the scoping stuff
6563 * into a structure and remove the individual uint8's from
6564 * the stc structure. Then we could just sifa in the
6565 * address within the stc.. but for now this is a quick
6566 * hack to get the address stuff teased apart.
6567 */
6568 scp.ipv4_addr_legal = stc.ipv4_addr_legal;
6569 scp.ipv6_addr_legal = stc.ipv6_addr_legal;
6570#if defined(__Userspace__)
6571 scp.conn_addr_legal = stc.conn_addr_legal;
6572#endif
6573 scp.loopback_scope = stc.loopback_scope;
6574 scp.ipv4_local_scope = stc.ipv4_scope;
6575 scp.local_scope = stc.local_scope;
6576 scp.site_scope = stc.site_scope;
6577 m_last = sctp_add_addresses_to_i_ia(inp, stcb, &scp, m_last,
6578 cnt_inits_to,
6579 &padding_len, &chunk_len);
6580 /* padding_len can only be positive, if no addresses have been added */
6581 if (padding_len > 0) {
6582 memset(mtod(m, caddr_t) + chunk_len, 0, padding_len);
6583 chunk_len += padding_len;
6584 SCTP_BUF_LEN(m) += padding_len;
6585 padding_len = 0;
6586 }
6587
6588 /* tack on the operational error if present */
6589 if (op_err) {
6590 parameter_len = 0;
6591 for (m_tmp = op_err; m_tmp != NULL; m_tmp = SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m_tmp)) {
6592 parameter_len += SCTP_BUF_LEN(m_tmp);
6593 }
6594 padding_len = SCTP_SIZE32(parameter_len) - parameter_len;
6595 SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m_last) = op_err;
6596 while (SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m_last) != NULL) {
6597 m_last = SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m_last);
6598 }
6599 chunk_len += parameter_len;
6600 }
6601 if (padding_len > 0) {
6602 m_last = sctp_add_pad_tombuf(m_last, padding_len);
6603 if (m_last == NULL) {
6604 /* Houston we have a problem, no space */
6605 sctp_m_freem(m);
6606 return;
6607 }
6608 chunk_len += padding_len;
6609 padding_len = 0;
6610 }
6611 /* Now we must build a cookie */
6612 m_cookie = sctp_add_cookie(init_pkt, offset, m, 0, &stc, &signature);
6613 if (m_cookie == NULL) {
6614 /* memory problem */
6615 sctp_m_freem(m);
6616 return;
6617 }
6618 /* Now append the cookie to the end and update the space/size */
6619 SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m_last) = m_cookie;
6620 parameter_len = 0;
6621 for (m_tmp = m_cookie; m_tmp != NULL; m_tmp = SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m_tmp)) {
6622 parameter_len += SCTP_BUF_LEN(m_tmp);
6623 if (SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m_tmp) == NULL) {
6624 m_last = m_tmp;
6625 }
6626 }
6627 padding_len = SCTP_SIZE32(parameter_len) - parameter_len;
6628 chunk_len += parameter_len;
6629
6630 /* Place in the size, but we don't include
6631 * the last pad (if any) in the INIT-ACK.
6632 */
6633 initack->ch.chunk_length = htons(chunk_len);
6634
6635 /* Time to sign the cookie, we don't sign over the cookie
6636 * signature though thus we set trailer.
6637 */
6638 (void)sctp_hmac_m(SCTP_HMAC,
6639 (uint8_t *)inp->sctp_ep.secret_key[(int)(inp->sctp_ep.current_secret_number)],
6640 SCTP_SECRET_SIZE, m_cookie, sizeof(struct sctp_paramhdr),
6641 (uint8_t *)signature, SCTP_SIGNATURE_SIZE);
6642#if defined(__Userspace__)
6643 /*
6644 * Don't put AF_CONN addresses on the wire, in case this is critical
6645 * for the application. However, they are protected by the HMAC and
6646 * need to be reconstructed before checking the HMAC.
6647 * Clearing is only done in the mbuf chain, since the local stc is
6648 * not used anymore.
6649 */
6650 if (stc.addr_type == SCTP_CONN_ADDRESS) {
6651 const void *p = NULL;
6652
6653 m_copyback(m_cookie, sizeof(struct sctp_paramhdr) + offsetof(struct sctp_state_cookie, address),
6654 (int)sizeof(void *), (caddr_t)&p);
6655 }
6656 if (stc.laddr_type == SCTP_CONN_ADDRESS) {
6657 const void *p = NULL;
6658
6659 m_copyback(m_cookie, sizeof(struct sctp_paramhdr) + offsetof(struct sctp_state_cookie, laddress),
6660 (int)sizeof(void *), (caddr_t)&p);
6661 }
6662#endif
6663 /*
6664 * We sifa 0 here to NOT set IP_DF if its IPv4, we ignore the return
6665 * here since the timer will drive a retranmission.
6666 */
6667 if (padding_len > 0) {
6668 if (sctp_add_pad_tombuf(m_last, padding_len) == NULL) {
6669 sctp_m_freem(m);
6670 return;
6671 }
6672 }
6673 if (stc.loopback_scope) {
6674 over_addr = (union sctp_sockstore *)dst;
6675 } else {
6676 over_addr = NULL;
6677 }
6678
6679 if ((error = sctp_lowlevel_chunk_output(inp, NULL, NULL, to, m, 0, NULL, 0, 0,
6680 0, 0,
6681 inp->sctp_lport, sh->src_port, init_chk->init.initiate_tag,
6682 port, over_addr,
6683#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6684 mflowtype, mflowid,
6685#endif
6686 SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED))) {
6687 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT4, "Gak send error %d\n", error);
6688 if (error == ENOBUFS) {
6689 if (asoc != NULL) {
6690 asoc->ifp_had_enobuf = 1;
6691 }
6692 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_lowlevelerr);
6693 }
6694 } else {
6695 if (asoc != NULL) {
6696 asoc->ifp_had_enobuf = 0;
6697 }
6698 }
6699 SCTP_STAT_INCR_COUNTER64(sctps_outcontrolchunks);
6700}
6701
6702static void
6703sctp_prune_prsctp(struct sctp_tcb *stcb,
6704 struct sctp_association *asoc,
6705 struct sctp_sndrcvinfo *srcv,
6706 int dataout)
6707{
6708 int freed_spc = 0;
6709 struct sctp_tmit_chunk *chk, *nchk;
6710
6711 SCTP_TCB_LOCK_ASSERT(stcb);
6712 if ((asoc->prsctp_supported) &&
6713 (asoc->sent_queue_cnt_removeable > 0)) {
6714 TAILQ_FOREACH(chk, &asoc->sent_queue, sctp_next) {
6715 /*
6716 * Look for chunks marked with the PR_SCTP flag AND
6717 * the buffer space flag. If the one being sent is
6718 * equal or greater priority then purge the old one
6719 * and free some space.
6720 */
6721 if (PR_SCTP_BUF_ENABLED(chk->flags)) {
6722 /*
6723 * This one is PR-SCTP AND buffer space
6724 * limited type
6725 */
6726 if (chk->rec.data.timetodrop.tv_sec > (long)srcv->sinfo_timetolive) {
6727 /*
6728 * Lower numbers equates to higher
6729 * priority. So if the one we are
6730 * looking at has a larger priority,
6731 * we want to drop the data and NOT
6732 * retransmit it.
6733 */
6734 if (chk->data) {
6735 /*
6736 * We release the book_size
6737 * if the mbuf is here
6738 */
6739 int ret_spc;
6740 uint8_t sent;
6741
6742 if (chk->sent > SCTP_DATAGRAM_UNSENT)
6743 sent = 1;
6744 else
6745 sent = 0;
6746 ret_spc = sctp_release_pr_sctp_chunk(stcb, chk,
6747 sent,
6748 SCTP_SO_LOCKED);
6749 freed_spc += ret_spc;
6750 if (freed_spc >= dataout) {
6751 return;
6752 }
6753 } /* if chunk was present */
6754 } /* if of sufficient priority */
6755 } /* if chunk has enabled */
6756 } /* tailqforeach */
6757
6758 TAILQ_FOREACH_SAFE(chk, &asoc->send_queue, sctp_next, nchk) {
6759 /* Here we must move to the sent queue and mark */
6760 if (PR_SCTP_BUF_ENABLED(chk->flags)) {
6761 if (chk->rec.data.timetodrop.tv_sec > (long)srcv->sinfo_timetolive) {
6762 if (chk->data) {
6763 /*
6764 * We release the book_size
6765 * if the mbuf is here
6766 */
6767 int ret_spc;
6768
6769 ret_spc = sctp_release_pr_sctp_chunk(stcb, chk,
6770 0, SCTP_SO_LOCKED);
6771
6772 freed_spc += ret_spc;
6773 if (freed_spc >= dataout) {
6774 return;
6775 }
6776 } /* end if chk->data */
6777 } /* end if right class */
6778 } /* end if chk pr-sctp */
6779 } /* tailqforeachsafe (chk) */
6780 } /* if enabled in asoc */
6781}
6782
6783int
6784sctp_get_frag_point(struct sctp_tcb *stcb,
6785 struct sctp_association *asoc)
6786{
6787 int siz, ovh;
6788
6789 /*
6790 * For endpoints that have both v6 and v4 addresses we must reserve
6791 * room for the ipv6 header, for those that are only dealing with V4
6792 * we use a larger frag point.
6793 */
6794 if (stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_BOUND_V6) {
6795 ovh = SCTP_MIN_OVERHEAD;
6796 } else {
6797#if defined(__Userspace__)
6798 if (stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_BOUND_CONN) {
6799 ovh = sizeof(struct sctphdr);
6800 } else {
6801 ovh = SCTP_MIN_V4_OVERHEAD;
6802 }
6803#else
6804 ovh = SCTP_MIN_V4_OVERHEAD;
6805#endif
6806 }
6807 ovh += SCTP_DATA_CHUNK_OVERHEAD(stcb);
6808 if (stcb->asoc.sctp_frag_point > asoc->smallest_mtu)
6809 siz = asoc->smallest_mtu - ovh;
6810 else
6811 siz = (stcb->asoc.sctp_frag_point - ovh);
6812 /*
6813 * if (siz > (MCLBYTES-sizeof(struct sctp_data_chunk))) {
6814 */
6815 /* A data chunk MUST fit in a cluster */
6816 /* siz = (MCLBYTES - sizeof(struct sctp_data_chunk)); */
6817 /* } */
6818
6819 /* adjust for an AUTH chunk if DATA requires auth */
6820 if (sctp_auth_is_required_chunk(SCTP_DATA, stcb->asoc.peer_auth_chunks))
6821 siz -= sctp_get_auth_chunk_len(stcb->asoc.peer_hmac_id);
6822
6823 if (siz % 4) {
6824 /* make it an even word boundary please */
6825 siz -= (siz % 4);
6826 }
6827 return (siz);
6828}
6829
6830static void
6831sctp_set_prsctp_policy(struct sctp_stream_queue_pending *sp)
6832{
6833 /*
6834 * We assume that the user wants PR_SCTP_TTL if the user
6835 * provides a positive lifetime but does not specify any
6836 * PR_SCTP policy.
6837 */
6838 if (PR_SCTP_ENABLED(sp->sinfo_flags)) {
6839 sp->act_flags |= PR_SCTP_POLICY(sp->sinfo_flags);
6840 } else if (sp->timetolive > 0) {
6841 sp->sinfo_flags |= SCTP_PR_SCTP_TTL;
6842 sp->act_flags |= PR_SCTP_POLICY(sp->sinfo_flags);
6843 } else {
6844 return;
6845 }
6846 switch (PR_SCTP_POLICY(sp->sinfo_flags)) {
6847 case CHUNK_FLAGS_PR_SCTP_BUF:
6848 /*
6849 * Time to live is a priority stored in tv_sec when
6850 * doing the buffer drop thing.
6851 */
6852 sp->ts.tv_sec = sp->timetolive;
6853 sp->ts.tv_usec = 0;
6854 break;
6855 case CHUNK_FLAGS_PR_SCTP_TTL:
6856 {
6857 struct timeval tv;
6858 (void)SCTP_GETTIME_TIMEVAL(&sp->ts);
6859 tv.tv_sec = sp->timetolive / 1000;
6860 tv.tv_usec = (sp->timetolive * 1000) % 1000000;
6861 /* TODO sctp_constants.h needs alternative time macros when
6862 * _KERNEL is undefined.
6863 */
6864#if !(defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__))
6865 timeradd(&sp->ts, &tv, &sp->ts);
6866#else
6867 timevaladd(&sp->ts, &tv);
6868#endif
6869 }
6870 break;
6871 case CHUNK_FLAGS_PR_SCTP_RTX:
6872 /*
6873 * Time to live is a the number or retransmissions
6874 * stored in tv_sec.
6875 */
6876 sp->ts.tv_sec = sp->timetolive;
6877 sp->ts.tv_usec = 0;
6878 break;
6879 default:
6880 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_USRREQ1,
6881 "Unknown PR_SCTP policy %u.\n",
6882 PR_SCTP_POLICY(sp->sinfo_flags));
6883 break;
6884 }
6885}
6886
6887static int
6888sctp_msg_append(struct sctp_tcb *stcb,
6889 struct sctp_nets *net,
6890 struct mbuf *m,
6891 struct sctp_sndrcvinfo *srcv, int hold_stcb_lock)
6892{
6893 int error = 0;
6894 struct mbuf *at;
6895 struct sctp_stream_queue_pending *sp = NULL;
6896 struct sctp_stream_out *strm;
6897
6898 /* Given an mbuf chain, put it
6899 * into the association send queue and
6900 * place it on the wheel
6901 */
6902 if (srcv->sinfo_stream >= stcb->asoc.streamoutcnt) {
6903 /* Invalid stream number */
6904 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET_PKT(m, NULL, stcb, net, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, EINVAL);
6905 error = EINVAL;
6906 goto out_now;
6907 }
