6908 if ((stcb->asoc.stream_locked) &&
6909 (stcb->asoc.stream_locked_on != srcv->sinfo_stream)) {
6910 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET_PKT(m, NULL, stcb, net, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, EINVAL);
6911 error = EINVAL;
6912 goto out_now;
6913 }
6914 strm = &stcb->asoc.strmout[srcv->sinfo_stream];
6915 /* Now can we send this? */
6916 if ((SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_SENT) ||
6917 (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_ACK_SENT) ||
6918 (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_RECEIVED) ||
6919 (stcb->asoc.state & SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_PENDING)) {
6920 /* got data while shutting down */
6921 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(NULL, stcb, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, ECONNRESET);
6922 error = ECONNRESET;
6923 goto out_now;
6924 }
6925 sctp_alloc_a_strmoq(stcb, sp);
6926 if (sp == NULL) {
6927 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(NULL, stcb, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, ENOMEM);
6928 error = ENOMEM;
6929 goto out_now;
6930 }
6931 sp->sinfo_flags = srcv->sinfo_flags;
6932 sp->timetolive = srcv->sinfo_timetolive;
6933 sp->ppid = srcv->sinfo_ppid;
6934 sp->context = srcv->sinfo_context;
6935 sp->fsn = 0;
6936 if (sp->sinfo_flags & SCTP_ADDR_OVER) {
6937 sp->net = net;
6938 atomic_add_int(&sp->net->ref_count, 1);
6939 } else {
6940 sp->net = NULL;
6941 }
6942 (void)SCTP_GETTIME_TIMEVAL(&sp->ts);
6943 sp->sid = srcv->sinfo_stream;
6944 sp->msg_is_complete = 1;
6945 sp->sender_all_done = 1;
6946 sp->some_taken = 0;
6947 sp->data = m;
6948 sp->tail_mbuf = NULL;
6949 sctp_set_prsctp_policy(sp);
6950 /* We could in theory (for sendall) sifa the length
6951 * in, but we would still have to hunt through the
6952 * chain since we need to setup the tail_mbuf
6953 */
6954 sp->length = 0;
6955 for (at = m; at; at = SCTP_BUF_NEXT(at)) {
6956 if (SCTP_BUF_NEXT(at) == NULL)
6957 sp->tail_mbuf = at;
6958 sp->length += SCTP_BUF_LEN(at);
6959 }
6960 if (srcv->sinfo_keynumber_valid) {
6961 sp->auth_keyid = srcv->sinfo_keynumber;
6962 } else {
6963 sp->auth_keyid = stcb->asoc.authinfo.active_keyid;
6964 }
6965 if (sctp_auth_is_required_chunk(SCTP_DATA, stcb->asoc.peer_auth_chunks)) {
6966 sctp_auth_key_acquire(stcb, sp->auth_keyid);
6967 sp->holds_key_ref = 1;
6968 }
6969 if (hold_stcb_lock == 0) {
6970 SCTP_TCB_SEND_LOCK(stcb);
6971 }
6972 sctp_snd_sb_alloc(stcb, sp->length);
6973 atomic_add_int(&stcb->asoc.stream_queue_cnt, 1);
6974 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&strm->outqueue, sp, next);
6975 stcb->asoc.ss_functions.sctp_ss_add_to_stream(stcb, &stcb->asoc, strm, sp, 1);
6976 m = NULL;
6977 if (hold_stcb_lock == 0) {
6978 SCTP_TCB_SEND_UNLOCK(stcb);
6979 }
6980out_now:
6981 if (m) {
6982 sctp_m_freem(m);
6983 }
6984 return (error);
6985}
6986
6987static struct mbuf *
6988sctp_copy_mbufchain(struct mbuf *clonechain,
6989 struct mbuf *outchain,
6990 struct mbuf **endofchain,
6991 int can_take_mbuf,
6992 int sizeofcpy,
6993 uint8_t copy_by_ref)
6994{
6995 struct mbuf *m;
6996 struct mbuf *appendchain;
6997 caddr_t cp;
6998 int len;
6999
7000 if (endofchain == NULL) {
7001 /* error */
7002 error_out:
7003 if (outchain)
7004 sctp_m_freem(outchain);
7005 return (NULL);
7006 }
7007 if (can_take_mbuf) {
7008 appendchain = clonechain;
7009 } else {
7010 if (!copy_by_ref &&
7011 (sizeofcpy <= (int)((((SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_mbuf_threshold_count) - 1) * MLEN) + MHLEN)))) {
7012 /* Its not in a cluster */
7013 if (*endofchain == NULL) {
7014 /* lets get a mbuf cluster */
7015 if (outchain == NULL) {
7016 /* This is the general case */
7017 new_mbuf:
7018 outchain = sctp_get_mbuf_for_msg(MCLBYTES, 0, M_NOWAIT, 1, MT_HEADER);
7019 if (outchain == NULL) {
7020 goto error_out;
7021 }
7022 SCTP_BUF_LEN(outchain) = 0;
7023 *endofchain = outchain;
7024 /* get the prepend space */
7025 SCTP_BUF_RESV_UF(outchain, (SCTP_FIRST_MBUF_RESV+4));
7026 } else {
7027 /* We really should not get a NULL in endofchain */
7028 /* find end */
7029 m = outchain;
7030 while (m) {
7031 if (SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m) == NULL) {
7032 *endofchain = m;
7033 break;
7034 }
7035 m = SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m);
7036 }
7037 /* sanity */
7038 if (*endofchain == NULL) {
7039 /* huh, TSNH XXX maybe we should panic */
7040 sctp_m_freem(outchain);
7041 goto new_mbuf;
7042 }
7043 }
7044 /* get the new end of length */
7045 len = (int)M_TRAILINGSPACE(*endofchain);
7046 } else {
7047 /* how much is left at the end? */
7048 len = (int)M_TRAILINGSPACE(*endofchain);
7049 }
7050 /* Find the end of the data, for appending */
7051 cp = (mtod((*endofchain), caddr_t) + SCTP_BUF_LEN((*endofchain)));
7052
7053 /* Now lets copy it out */
7054 if (len >= sizeofcpy) {
7055 /* It all fits, copy it in */
7056 m_copydata(clonechain, 0, sizeofcpy, cp);
7057 SCTP_BUF_LEN((*endofchain)) += sizeofcpy;
7058 } else {
7059 /* fill up the end of the chain */
7060 if (len > 0) {
7061 m_copydata(clonechain, 0, len, cp);
7062 SCTP_BUF_LEN((*endofchain)) += len;
7063 /* now we need another one */
7064 sizeofcpy -= len;
7065 }
7066 m = sctp_get_mbuf_for_msg(MCLBYTES, 0, M_NOWAIT, 1, MT_HEADER);
7067 if (m == NULL) {
7068 /* We failed */
7069 goto error_out;
7070 }
7071 SCTP_BUF_NEXT((*endofchain)) = m;
7072 *endofchain = m;
7073 cp = mtod((*endofchain), caddr_t);
7074 m_copydata(clonechain, len, sizeofcpy, cp);
7075 SCTP_BUF_LEN((*endofchain)) += sizeofcpy;
7076 }
7077 return (outchain);
7078 } else {
7079 /* copy the old fashion way */
7080 appendchain = SCTP_M_COPYM(clonechain, 0, M_COPYALL, M_NOWAIT);
7081#ifdef SCTP_MBUF_LOGGING
7082 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_MBUF_LOGGING_ENABLE) {
7083 sctp_log_mbc(appendchain, SCTP_MBUF_ICOPY);
7084 }
7085#endif
7086 }
7087 }
7088 if (appendchain == NULL) {
7089 /* error */
7090 if (outchain)
7091 sctp_m_freem(outchain);
7092 return (NULL);
7093 }
7094 if (outchain) {
7095 /* tack on to the end */
7096 if (*endofchain != NULL) {
7097 SCTP_BUF_NEXT(((*endofchain))) = appendchain;
7098 } else {
7099 m = outchain;
7100 while (m) {
7101 if (SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m) == NULL) {
7102 SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m) = appendchain;
7103 break;
7104 }
7105 m = SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m);
7106 }
7107 }
7108 /*
7109 * save off the end and update the end-chain
7110 * position
7111 */
7112 m = appendchain;
7113 while (m) {
7114 if (SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m) == NULL) {
7115 *endofchain = m;
7116 break;
7117 }
7118 m = SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m);
7119 }
7120 return (outchain);
7121 } else {
7122 /* save off the end and update the end-chain position */
7123 m = appendchain;
7124 while (m) {
7125 if (SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m) == NULL) {
7126 *endofchain = m;
7127 break;
7128 }
7129 m = SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m);
7130 }
7131 return (appendchain);
7132 }
7133}
7134
7135static int
7136sctp_med_chunk_output(struct sctp_inpcb *inp,
7137 struct sctp_tcb *stcb,
7138 struct sctp_association *asoc,
7139 int *num_out,
7140 int *reason_code,
7141 int control_only, int from_where,
7142 struct timeval *now, int *now_filled, int frag_point, int so_locked);
7143
7144static void
7145sctp_sendall_iterator(struct sctp_inpcb *inp, struct sctp_tcb *stcb, void *ptr,
7146 uint32_t val SCTP_UNUSED)
7147{
7148 struct sctp_copy_all *ca;
7149 struct mbuf *m;
7150 int ret = 0;
7151 int added_control = 0;
7152 int un_sent, do_chunk_output = 1;
7153 struct sctp_association *asoc;
7154 struct sctp_nets *net;
7155
7156 ca = (struct sctp_copy_all *)ptr;
7157 if (ca->m == NULL) {
7158 return;
7159 }
7160 if (ca->inp != inp) {
7161 /* TSNH */
7162 return;
7163 }
7164 if (ca->sndlen > 0) {
7165 m = SCTP_M_COPYM(ca->m, 0, M_COPYALL, M_NOWAIT);
7166 if (m == NULL) {
7167 /* can't copy so we are done */
7168 ca->cnt_failed++;
7169 return;
7170 }
7171#ifdef SCTP_MBUF_LOGGING
7172 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_MBUF_LOGGING_ENABLE) {
7173 sctp_log_mbc(m, SCTP_MBUF_ICOPY);
7174 }
7175#endif
7176 } else {
7177 m = NULL;
7178 }
7179 SCTP_TCB_LOCK_ASSERT(stcb);
7180 if (stcb->asoc.alternate) {
7181 net = stcb->asoc.alternate;
7182 } else {
7183 net = stcb->asoc.primary_destination;
7184 }
7185 if (ca->sndrcv.sinfo_flags & SCTP_ABORT) {
7186 /* Abort this assoc with m as the user defined reason */
7187 if (m != NULL) {
7188 SCTP_BUF_PREPEND(m, sizeof(struct sctp_paramhdr), M_NOWAIT);
7189 } else {
7190 m = sctp_get_mbuf_for_msg(sizeof(struct sctp_paramhdr),
7191 0, M_NOWAIT, 1, MT_DATA);
7192 SCTP_BUF_LEN(m) = sizeof(struct sctp_paramhdr);
7193 }
7194 if (m != NULL) {
7195 struct sctp_paramhdr *ph;
7196
7197 ph = mtod(m, struct sctp_paramhdr *);
7198 ph->param_type = htons(SCTP_CAUSE_USER_INITIATED_ABT);
7199 ph->param_length = htons((uint16_t)(sizeof(struct sctp_paramhdr) + ca->sndlen));
7200 }
7201 /* We add one here to keep the assoc from
7202 * dis-appearing on us.
7203 */
7204 atomic_add_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
7205 sctp_abort_an_association(inp, stcb, m, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
7206 /* sctp_abort_an_association calls sctp_free_asoc()
7207 * free association will NOT free it since we
7208 * incremented the refcnt .. we do this to prevent
7209 * it being freed and things getting tricky since
7210 * we could end up (from free_asoc) calling inpcb_free
7211 * which would get a recursive lock call to the
7212 * iterator lock.. But as a consequence of that the
7213 * stcb will return to us un-locked.. since free_asoc
7214 * returns with either no TCB or the TCB unlocked, we
7215 * must relock.. to unlock in the iterator timer :-0
7216 */
7217 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
7218 atomic_add_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, -1);
7219 goto no_chunk_output;
7220 } else {
7221 if (m) {
7222 ret = sctp_msg_append(stcb, net, m,
7223 &ca->sndrcv, 1);
7224 }
7225 asoc = &stcb->asoc;
7226 if (ca->sndrcv.sinfo_flags & SCTP_EOF) {
7227 /* shutdown this assoc */
7228 if (TAILQ_EMPTY(&asoc->send_queue) &&
7229 TAILQ_EMPTY(&asoc->sent_queue) &&
7230 sctp_is_there_unsent_data(stcb, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED) == 0) {
7231 if ((*asoc->ss_functions.sctp_ss_is_user_msgs_incomplete)(stcb, asoc)) {
7232 goto abort_anyway;
7233 }
7234 /* there is nothing queued to send, so I'm done... */
7235 if ((SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) != SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_SENT) &&
7236 (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) != SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_RECEIVED) &&
7237 (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) != SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_ACK_SENT)) {
7238 /* only send SHUTDOWN the first time through */
7239 if (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_OPEN) {
7240 SCTP_STAT_DECR_GAUGE32(sctps_currestab);
7241 }
7242 SCTP_SET_STATE(stcb, SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_SENT);
7243 sctp_stop_timers_for_shutdown(stcb);
7244 sctp_send_shutdown(stcb, net);
7245 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_SHUTDOWN, stcb->sctp_ep, stcb,
7246 net);
7247 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_SHUTDOWNGUARD, stcb->sctp_ep, stcb,
7248 NULL);
7249 added_control = 1;
7250 do_chunk_output = 0;
7251 }
7252 } else {
7253 /*
7254 * we still got (or just got) data to send, so set
7255 * SHUTDOWN_PENDING
7256 */
7257 /*
7258 * XXX sockets draft says that SCTP_EOF should be
7259 * sent with no data. currently, we will allow user
7260 * data to be sent first and move to
7261 * SHUTDOWN-PENDING
7262 */
7263 if ((SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) != SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_SENT) &&
7264 (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) != SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_RECEIVED) &&
7265 (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) != SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_ACK_SENT)) {
7266 if ((*asoc->ss_functions.sctp_ss_is_user_msgs_incomplete)(stcb, asoc)) {
7267 SCTP_ADD_SUBSTATE(stcb, SCTP_STATE_PARTIAL_MSG_LEFT);
7268 }
7269 SCTP_ADD_SUBSTATE(stcb, SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_PENDING);
7270 if (TAILQ_EMPTY(&asoc->send_queue) &&
7271 TAILQ_EMPTY(&asoc->sent_queue) &&
7272 (asoc->state & SCTP_STATE_PARTIAL_MSG_LEFT)) {
7273 struct mbuf *op_err;
7274 char msg[SCTP_DIAG_INFO_LEN];
7275
7276 abort_anyway:
7277 SCTP_SNPRINTF(msg, sizeof(msg),
7278 "%s:%d at %s", __FILE__, __LINE__, __func__);
7279 op_err = sctp_generate_cause(SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_diag_info_code),
7280 msg);
7281 atomic_add_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
7282 sctp_abort_an_association(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb,
7283 op_err, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
7284 atomic_add_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, -1);
7285 goto no_chunk_output;
7286 }
7287 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_SHUTDOWNGUARD, stcb->sctp_ep, stcb,
7288 NULL);
7289 }
7290 }
7291 }
7292 }
7293 un_sent = ((stcb->asoc.total_output_queue_size - stcb->asoc.total_flight) +
7294 (stcb->asoc.stream_queue_cnt * SCTP_DATA_CHUNK_OVERHEAD(stcb)));
7295
7296 if ((sctp_is_feature_off(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_NODELAY)) &&
7297 (stcb->asoc.total_flight > 0) &&
7298 (un_sent < (int)(stcb->asoc.smallest_mtu - SCTP_MIN_OVERHEAD))) {
7299 do_chunk_output = 0;
7300 }
7301 if (do_chunk_output)
7302 sctp_chunk_output(inp, stcb, SCTP_OUTPUT_FROM_USR_SEND, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
7303 else if (added_control) {
7304 int num_out, reason, now_filled = 0;
7305 struct timeval now;
7306 int frag_point;
7307
7308 frag_point = sctp_get_frag_point(stcb, &stcb->asoc);
7309 (void)sctp_med_chunk_output(inp, stcb, &stcb->asoc, &num_out,
7310 &reason, 1, 1, &now, &now_filled, frag_point, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
7311 }
7312 no_chunk_output:
7313 if (ret) {
7314 ca->cnt_failed++;
7315 } else {
7316 ca->cnt_sent++;
7317 }
7318}
7319
7320static void
7321sctp_sendall_completes(void *ptr, uint32_t val SCTP_UNUSED)
7322{
7323 struct sctp_copy_all *ca;
7324
7325 ca = (struct sctp_copy_all *)ptr;
7326 /*
7327 * Do a notify here? Kacheong suggests that the notify be done at
7328 * the send time.. so you would push up a notification if any send
7329 * failed. Don't know if this is feasible since the only failures we
7330 * have is "memory" related and if you cannot get an mbuf to send
7331 * the data you surely can't get an mbuf to send up to notify the
7332 * user you can't send the data :->
7333 */
7334
7335 /* now free everything */
7336 if (ca->inp) {
7337 /* Lets clear the flag to allow others to run. */
7338 ca->inp->sctp_flags &= ~SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SND_ITERATOR_UP;
7339 }
7340 sctp_m_freem(ca->m);
7341 SCTP_FREE(ca, SCTP_M_COPYAL);
7342}
7343
7344static struct mbuf *
7345sctp_copy_out_all(struct uio *uio, ssize_t len)
7346{
7347 struct mbuf *ret, *at;
7348 ssize_t left, willcpy, cancpy, error;
7349
7350 ret = sctp_get_mbuf_for_msg(MCLBYTES, 0, M_WAITOK, 1, MT_DATA);
7351 if (ret == NULL) {
7352 /* TSNH */
7353 return (NULL);
7354 }
7355 left = len;
7356 SCTP_BUF_LEN(ret) = 0;
7357 /* save space for the data chunk header */
7358 cancpy = (int)M_TRAILINGSPACE(ret);
7359 willcpy = min(cancpy, left);
7360 at = ret;
7361 while (left > 0) {
7362 /* Align data to the end */
7363 error = uiomove(mtod(at, caddr_t), (int)willcpy, uio);
7364 if (error) {
7365 err_out_now:
7366 sctp_m_freem(at);
7367 return (NULL);
7368 }
7369 SCTP_BUF_LEN(at) = (int)willcpy;
7370 SCTP_BUF_NEXT_PKT(at) = SCTP_BUF_NEXT(at) = 0;
7371 left -= willcpy;
7372 if (left > 0) {
7373 SCTP_BUF_NEXT(at) = sctp_get_mbuf_for_msg((unsigned int)left, 0, M_WAITOK, 1, MT_DATA);
7374 if (SCTP_BUF_NEXT(at) == NULL) {
7375 goto err_out_now;
7376 }
7377 at = SCTP_BUF_NEXT(at);
7378 SCTP_BUF_LEN(at) = 0;
7379 cancpy = (int)M_TRAILINGSPACE(at);
7380 willcpy = min(cancpy, left);
7381 }
7382 }
7383 return (ret);
7384}
7385
7386static int
7387sctp_sendall(struct sctp_inpcb *inp, struct uio *uio, struct mbuf *m,
7388 struct sctp_sndrcvinfo *srcv)
7389{
7390 int ret;
7391 struct sctp_copy_all *ca;
7392
7393 if (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SND_ITERATOR_UP) {
7394 /* There is another. */
7395 return (EBUSY);
7396 }
7397#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
7398#if defined(APPLE_LEOPARD)
7399 if (uio->uio_resid > SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_sendall_limit)) {
7400#else
7401 if (uio_resid(uio) > SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_sendall_limit)) {
7402#endif
7403#else
7404 if (uio->uio_resid > (ssize_t)SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_sendall_limit)) {
7405#endif
7406 /* You must not be larger than the limit! */
7407 return (EMSGSIZE);
7408 }
7409 SCTP_MALLOC(ca, struct sctp_copy_all *, sizeof(struct sctp_copy_all),
7410 SCTP_M_COPYAL);
7411 if (ca == NULL) {
7412 sctp_m_freem(m);
7413 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, ENOMEM);
7414 return (ENOMEM);
7415 }
7416 memset(ca, 0, sizeof(struct sctp_copy_all));
7417
7418 ca->inp = inp;
7419 if (srcv) {
7420 memcpy(&ca->sndrcv, srcv, sizeof(struct sctp_nonpad_sndrcvinfo));
7421 }
7422 /*
7423 * take off the sendall flag, it would be bad if we failed to do
7424 * this :-0
7425 */
7426 ca->sndrcv.sinfo_flags &= ~SCTP_SENDALL;
7427 /* get length and mbuf chain */
7428 if (uio) {
7429#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
7430#if defined(APPLE_LEOPARD)
7431 ca->sndlen = uio->uio_resid;
7432#else
7433 ca->sndlen = uio_resid(uio);
7434#endif
7435#else
7436 ca->sndlen = uio->uio_resid;
7437#endif
7438#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
7439 SCTP_SOCKET_UNLOCK(SCTP_INP_SO(inp), 0);
7440#endif
7441 ca->m = sctp_copy_out_all(uio, ca->sndlen);
7442#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
7443 SCTP_SOCKET_LOCK(SCTP_INP_SO(inp), 0);
7444#endif
7445 if (ca->m == NULL) {
7446 SCTP_FREE(ca, SCTP_M_COPYAL);
7447 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, ENOMEM);
7448 return (ENOMEM);
7449 }
7450 } else {
7451 /* Gather the length of the send */
7452 struct mbuf *mat;
7453
7454 ca->sndlen = 0;
7455 for (mat = m; mat; mat = SCTP_BUF_NEXT(mat)) {
7456 ca->sndlen += SCTP_BUF_LEN(mat);
7457 }
7458 }
7459 inp->sctp_flags |= SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SND_ITERATOR_UP;
7460 ret = sctp_initiate_iterator(NULL, sctp_sendall_iterator, NULL,
7461 SCTP_PCB_ANY_FLAGS, SCTP_PCB_ANY_FEATURES,
7462 SCTP_ASOC_ANY_STATE,
7463 (void *)ca, 0,
7464 sctp_sendall_completes, inp, 1);
7465 if (ret) {
7466 inp->sctp_flags &= ~SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SND_ITERATOR_UP;
7467 SCTP_FREE(ca, SCTP_M_COPYAL);
7468 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET_PKT(m, inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, EFAULT);
7469 return (EFAULT);
7470 }
7471 return (0);
7472}
7473
7474void
7475sctp_toss_old_cookies(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sctp_association *asoc)
7476{
7477 struct sctp_tmit_chunk *chk, *nchk;
7478
7479 TAILQ_FOREACH_SAFE(chk, &asoc->control_send_queue, sctp_next, nchk) {
7480 if (chk->rec.chunk_id.id == SCTP_COOKIE_ECHO) {
7481 TAILQ_REMOVE(&asoc->control_send_queue, chk, sctp_next);
7482 asoc->ctrl_queue_cnt--;
7483 if (chk->data) {
7484 sctp_m_freem(chk->data);
7485 chk->data = NULL;
7486 }
7487 sctp_free_a_chunk(stcb, chk, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
7488 }
7489 }
7490}
7491
7492void
7493sctp_toss_old_asconf(struct sctp_tcb *stcb)
7494{
7495 struct sctp_association *asoc;
7496 struct sctp_tmit_chunk *chk, *nchk;
7497 struct sctp_asconf_chunk *acp;
7498
7499 asoc = &stcb->asoc;
7500 TAILQ_FOREACH_SAFE(chk, &asoc->asconf_send_queue, sctp_next, nchk) {
7501 /* find SCTP_ASCONF chunk in queue */
7502 if (chk->rec.chunk_id.id == SCTP_ASCONF) {
7503 if (chk->data) {
7504 acp = mtod(chk->data, struct sctp_asconf_chunk *);
7505 if (SCTP_TSN_GT(ntohl(acp->serial_number), asoc->asconf_seq_out_acked)) {
7506 /* Not Acked yet */
7507 break;
7508 }
7509 }
7510 TAILQ_REMOVE(&asoc->asconf_send_queue, chk, sctp_next);
7511 asoc->ctrl_queue_cnt--;
7512 if (chk->data) {
7513 sctp_m_freem(chk->data);
7514 chk->data = NULL;
7515 }
7516 sctp_free_a_chunk(stcb, chk, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
7517 }
7518 }
7519}
7520
7521static void
7522sctp_clean_up_datalist(struct sctp_tcb *stcb,
7523 struct sctp_association *asoc,
7524 struct sctp_tmit_chunk **data_list,
7525 int bundle_at,
7526 struct sctp_nets *net)
7527{
7528 int i;
7529 struct sctp_tmit_chunk *tp1;
7530
7531 for (i = 0; i < bundle_at; i++) {
7532 /* off of the send queue */
7533 TAILQ_REMOVE(&asoc->send_queue, data_list[i], sctp_next);
7534 asoc->send_queue_cnt--;
7535 if (i > 0) {
7536 /*
7537 * Any chunk NOT 0 you zap the time chunk 0 gets
7538 * zapped or set based on if a RTO measurment is
7539 * needed.
7540 */
7541 data_list[i]->do_rtt = 0;
7542 }
7543 /* record time */
7544 data_list[i]->sent_rcv_time = net->last_sent_time;
7545 data_list[i]->rec.data.cwnd_at_send = net->cwnd;
7546 data_list[i]->rec.data.fast_retran_tsn = data_list[i]->rec.data.tsn;
7547 if (data_list[i]->whoTo == NULL) {
7548 data_list[i]->whoTo = net;
7549 atomic_add_int(&net->ref_count, 1);
7550 }
7551 /* on to the sent queue */
7552 tp1 = TAILQ_LAST(&asoc->sent_queue, sctpchunk_listhead);
7553 if ((tp1) && SCTP_TSN_GT(tp1->rec.data.tsn, data_list[i]->rec.data.tsn)) {
7554 struct sctp_tmit_chunk *tpp;
7555
7556 /* need to move back */
7557 back_up_more:
7558 tpp = TAILQ_PREV(tp1, sctpchunk_listhead, sctp_next);
7559 if (tpp == NULL) {
7560 TAILQ_INSERT_BEFORE(tp1, data_list[i], sctp_next);
7561 goto all_done;
7562 }
7563 tp1 = tpp;
7564 if (SCTP_TSN_GT(tp1->rec.data.tsn, data_list[i]->rec.data.tsn)) {
7565 goto back_up_more;
7566 }
7567 TAILQ_INSERT_AFTER(&asoc->sent_queue, tp1, data_list[i], sctp_next);
7568 } else {
7569 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&asoc->sent_queue,
7570 data_list[i],
7571 sctp_next);
7572 }
7573 all_done:
7574 /* This does not lower until the cum-ack passes it */
7575 asoc->sent_queue_cnt++;
7576 if ((asoc->peers_rwnd <= 0) &&
7577 (asoc->total_flight == 0) &&
7578 (bundle_at == 1)) {
7579 /* Mark the chunk as being a window probe */
7580 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_windowprobed);
7581 }
7582#ifdef SCTP_AUDITING_ENABLED
7583 sctp_audit_log(0xC2, 3);
7584#endif
7585 data_list[i]->sent = SCTP_DATAGRAM_SENT;
7586 data_list[i]->snd_count = 1;
7587 data_list[i]->rec.data.chunk_was_revoked = 0;
7588 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_FLIGHT_LOGGING_ENABLE) {
7589 sctp_misc_ints(SCTP_FLIGHT_LOG_UP,
7590 data_list[i]->whoTo->flight_size,
7591 data_list[i]->book_size,
7592 (uint32_t)(uintptr_t)data_list[i]->whoTo,
7593 data_list[i]->rec.data.tsn);
7594 }
7595 sctp_flight_size_increase(data_list[i]);
7596 sctp_total_flight_increase(stcb, data_list[i]);
7597 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_LOG_RWND_ENABLE) {
7598 sctp_log_rwnd(SCTP_DECREASE_PEER_RWND,
7599 asoc->peers_rwnd, data_list[i]->send_size, SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_peer_chunk_oh));
7600 }
7601 asoc->peers_rwnd = sctp_sbspace_sub(asoc->peers_rwnd,
7602 (uint32_t) (data_list[i]->send_size + SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_peer_chunk_oh)));
7603 if (asoc->peers_rwnd < stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_ep.sctp_sws_sender) {
7604 /* SWS sender side engages */
7605 asoc->peers_rwnd = 0;
7606 }
7607 }
7608 if (asoc->cc_functions.sctp_cwnd_update_packet_transmitted) {
7609 (*asoc->cc_functions.sctp_cwnd_update_packet_transmitted)(stcb, net);
7610 }
7611}
7612
7613static void
7614sctp_clean_up_ctl(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sctp_association *asoc, int so_locked)
7615{
7616 struct sctp_tmit_chunk *chk, *nchk;
7617
7618 TAILQ_FOREACH_SAFE(chk, &asoc->control_send_queue, sctp_next, nchk) {
7619 if ((chk->rec.chunk_id.id == SCTP_SELECTIVE_ACK) ||
7620 (chk->rec.chunk_id.id == SCTP_NR_SELECTIVE_ACK) || /* EY */
7621 (chk->rec.chunk_id.id == SCTP_HEARTBEAT_REQUEST) ||
7622 (chk->rec.chunk_id.id == SCTP_HEARTBEAT_ACK) ||
7623 (chk->rec.chunk_id.id == SCTP_FORWARD_CUM_TSN) ||
7624 (chk->rec.chunk_id.id == SCTP_SHUTDOWN) ||
7625 (chk->rec.chunk_id.id == SCTP_SHUTDOWN_ACK) ||
7626 (chk->rec.chunk_id.id == SCTP_OPERATION_ERROR) ||
7627 (chk->rec.chunk_id.id == SCTP_PACKET_DROPPED) ||
7628 (chk->rec.chunk_id.id == SCTP_COOKIE_ACK) ||
7629 (chk->rec.chunk_id.id == SCTP_ECN_CWR) ||
7630 (chk->rec.chunk_id.id == SCTP_ASCONF_ACK)) {
7631 /* Stray chunks must be cleaned up */
7632 clean_up_anyway:
7633 TAILQ_REMOVE(&asoc->control_send_queue, chk, sctp_next);
7634 asoc->ctrl_queue_cnt--;
7635 if (chk->data) {
7636 sctp_m_freem(chk->data);
7637 chk->data = NULL;
7638 }
7639 if (chk->rec.chunk_id.id == SCTP_FORWARD_CUM_TSN) {
7640 asoc->fwd_tsn_cnt--;
7641 }
7642 sctp_free_a_chunk(stcb, chk, so_locked);
7643 } else if (chk->rec.chunk_id.id == SCTP_STREAM_RESET) {
7644 /* special handling, we must look into the param */
7645 if (chk != asoc->str_reset) {
7646 goto clean_up_anyway;
7647 }
7648 }
7649 }
7650}
7651
7652static uint32_t
7653sctp_can_we_split_this(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, uint32_t length,
7654 uint32_t space_left, uint32_t frag_point, int eeor_on)
7655{
7656 /* Make a decision on if I should split a
7657 * msg into multiple parts. This is only asked of
7658 * incomplete messages.
7659 */
7660 if (eeor_on) {
7661 /* If we are doing EEOR we need to always send
7662 * it if its the entire thing, since it might
7663 * be all the guy is putting in the hopper.
7664 */
7665 if (space_left >= length) {
7666 /*-
7667 * If we have data outstanding,
7668 * we get another chance when the sack
7669 * arrives to transmit - wait for more data
7670 */
7671 if (stcb->asoc.total_flight == 0) {
7672 /* If nothing is in flight, we zero
7673 * the packet counter.
7674 */
7675 return (length);
7676 }
7677 return (0);
7678
7679 } else {
7680 /* You can fill the rest */
7681 return (space_left);
7682 }
7683 }
7684 /*-
7685 * For those strange folk that make the send buffer
7686 * smaller than our fragmentation point, we can't
7687 * get a full msg in so we have to allow splitting.
7688 */
7689 if (SCTP_SB_LIMIT_SND(stcb->sctp_socket) < frag_point) {
7690 return (length);
7691 }
7692 if ((length <= space_left) ||
7693 ((length - space_left) < SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_min_residual))) {
7694 /* Sub-optimial residual don't split in non-eeor mode. */
7695 return (0);
7696 }
7697 /* If we reach here length is larger
7698 * than the space_left. Do we wish to split
7699 * it for the sake of packet putting together?
7700 */
7701 if (space_left >= min(SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_min_split_point), frag_point)) {
7702 /* Its ok to split it */
7703 return (min(space_left, frag_point));
7704 }
7705 /* Nope, can't split */
7706 return (0);
7707}
7708
7709static uint32_t
7710sctp_move_to_outqueue(struct sctp_tcb *stcb,
7711 struct sctp_stream_out *strq,
7712 uint32_t space_left,
7713 uint32_t frag_point,
7714 int *giveup,
7715 int eeor_mode,
7716 int *bail,
7717 int so_locked)
7718{
7719 /* Move from the stream to the send_queue keeping track of the total */
7720 struct sctp_association *asoc;
7721 struct sctp_stream_queue_pending *sp;
7722 struct sctp_tmit_chunk *chk;
7723 struct sctp_data_chunk *dchkh=NULL;
7724 struct sctp_idata_chunk *ndchkh=NULL;
7725 uint32_t to_move, length;
7726 int leading;
7727 uint8_t rcv_flags = 0;
7728 uint8_t some_taken;
7729 uint8_t send_lock_up = 0;
7730
7731 SCTP_TCB_LOCK_ASSERT(stcb);
7732 asoc = &stcb->asoc;
7733one_more_time:
7734 /*sa_ignore FREED_MEMORY*/
7735 sp = TAILQ_FIRST(&strq->outqueue);
7736 if (sp == NULL) {
7737 if (send_lock_up == 0) {
7738 SCTP_TCB_SEND_LOCK(stcb);
7739 send_lock_up = 1;
7740 }
7741 sp = TAILQ_FIRST(&strq->outqueue);
7742 if (sp) {
7743 goto one_more_time;
7744 }
7745 if ((sctp_is_feature_on(stcb->sctp_ep, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_EXPLICIT_EOR) == 0) &&
7746 (stcb->asoc.idata_supported == 0) &&
7747 (strq->last_msg_incomplete)) {
7748 SCTP_PRINTF("Huh? Stream:%d lm_in_c=%d but queue is NULL\n",
7749 strq->sid,
7750 strq->last_msg_incomplete);
7751 strq->last_msg_incomplete = 0;
7752 }
7753 to_move = 0;
7754 if (send_lock_up) {
7755 SCTP_TCB_SEND_UNLOCK(stcb);
7756 send_lock_up = 0;
7757 }
7758 goto out_of;
7759 }
7760 if ((sp->msg_is_complete) && (sp->length == 0)) {
7761 if (sp->sender_all_done) {
7762 /* We are doing deferred cleanup. Last
7763 * time through when we took all the data
7764 * the sender_all_done was not set.
7765 */
7766 if ((sp->put_last_out == 0) && (sp->discard_rest == 0)) {
7767 SCTP_PRINTF("Gak, put out entire msg with NO end!-1\n");
7768 SCTP_PRINTF("sender_done:%d len:%d msg_comp:%d put_last_out:%d send_lock:%d\n",
7769 sp->sender_all_done,
7770 sp->length,
7771 sp->msg_is_complete,
7772 sp->put_last_out,
7773 send_lock_up);
7774 }
7775 if ((TAILQ_NEXT(sp, next) == NULL) && (send_lock_up == 0)) {
7776 SCTP_TCB_SEND_LOCK(stcb);
7777 send_lock_up = 1;
7778 }
7779 atomic_subtract_int(&asoc->stream_queue_cnt, 1);
7780 TAILQ_REMOVE(&strq->outqueue, sp, next);
7781 stcb->asoc.ss_functions.sctp_ss_remove_from_stream(stcb, asoc, strq, sp, send_lock_up);
7782 if ((strq->state == SCTP_STREAM_RESET_PENDING) &&
7783 (strq->chunks_on_queues == 0) &&
7784 TAILQ_EMPTY(&strq->outqueue)) {
7785 stcb->asoc.trigger_reset = 1;
7786 }
7787 if (sp->net) {
7788 sctp_free_remote_addr(sp->net);
7789 sp->net = NULL;
7790 }
7791 if (sp->data) {
7792 sctp_m_freem(sp->data);
7793 sp->data = NULL;
7794 }
7795 sctp_free_a_strmoq(stcb, sp, so_locked);
7796 /* we can't be locked to it */
7797 if (send_lock_up) {
7798 SCTP_TCB_SEND_UNLOCK(stcb);
7799 send_lock_up = 0;
7800 }
7801 /* back to get the next msg */
7802 goto one_more_time;
7803 } else {
7804 /* sender just finished this but
7805 * still holds a reference
7806 */
7807 *giveup = 1;
7808 to_move = 0;
7809 goto out_of;
7810 }
7811 } else {
7812 /* is there some to get */
7813 if (sp->length == 0) {
7814 /* no */
7815 *giveup = 1;
7816 to_move = 0;
7817 goto out_of;
7818 } else if (sp->discard_rest) {
7819 if (send_lock_up == 0) {
7820 SCTP_TCB_SEND_LOCK(stcb);
7821 send_lock_up = 1;
7822 }
7823 /* Whack down the size */
7824 atomic_subtract_int(&stcb->asoc.total_output_queue_size, sp->length);
7825 if ((stcb->sctp_socket != NULL) &&
7826 ((stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_TCPTYPE) ||
7827 (stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_IN_TCPPOOL))) {
7828 atomic_subtract_int(&stcb->sctp_socket->so_snd.sb_cc, sp->length);
7829 }
7830 if (sp->data) {
7831 sctp_m_freem(sp->data);
7832 sp->data = NULL;
7833 sp->tail_mbuf = NULL;
7834 }
7835 sp->length = 0;
7836 sp->some_taken = 1;
7837 *giveup = 1;
7838 to_move = 0;
7839 goto out_of;
7840 }
7841 }
7842 some_taken = sp->some_taken;
7843re_look:
7844 length = sp->length;
7845 if (sp->msg_is_complete) {
7846 /* The message is complete */
7847 to_move = min(length, frag_point);
7848 if (to_move == length) {
7849 /* All of it fits in the MTU */
7850 if (sp->some_taken) {
7851 rcv_flags |= SCTP_DATA_LAST_FRAG;
7852 } else {
7853 rcv_flags |= SCTP_DATA_NOT_FRAG;
7854 }
7855 sp->put_last_out = 1;
7856 if (sp->sinfo_flags & SCTP_SACK_IMMEDIATELY) {
7857 rcv_flags |= SCTP_DATA_SACK_IMMEDIATELY;
7858 }
7859 } else {
7860 /* Not all of it fits, we fragment */
7861 if (sp->some_taken == 0) {
7862 rcv_flags |= SCTP_DATA_FIRST_FRAG;
7863 }
7864 sp->some_taken = 1;
7865 }
7866 } else {
7867 to_move = sctp_can_we_split_this(stcb, length, space_left, frag_point, eeor_mode);
7868 if (to_move) {
7869 /*-
7870 * We use a snapshot of length in case it
7871 * is expanding during the compare.
7872 */
7873 uint32_t llen;
7874
7875 llen = length;
7876 if (to_move >= llen) {
7877 to_move = llen;
7878 if (send_lock_up == 0) {
7879 /*-
7880 * We are taking all of an incomplete msg
7881 * thus we need a send lock.
7882 */
7883 SCTP_TCB_SEND_LOCK(stcb);
7884 send_lock_up = 1;
7885 if (sp->msg_is_complete) {
7886 /* the sender finished the msg */
7887 goto re_look;
7888 }
7889 }
7890 }
7891 if (sp->some_taken == 0) {
7892 rcv_flags |= SCTP_DATA_FIRST_FRAG;
7893 sp->some_taken = 1;
7894 }
7895 } else {
7896 /* Nothing to take. */
7897 *giveup = 1;
7898 to_move = 0;
7899 goto out_of;
7900 }
7901 }
7902
7903 /* If we reach here, we can copy out a chunk */
7904 sctp_alloc_a_chunk(stcb, chk);
7905 if (chk == NULL) {
7906 /* No chunk memory */
7907 *giveup = 1;
7908 to_move = 0;
7909 goto out_of;
7910 }
7911 /* Setup for unordered if needed by looking
7912 * at the user sent info flags.
7913 */
7914 if (sp->sinfo_flags & SCTP_UNORDERED) {
7915 rcv_flags |= SCTP_DATA_UNORDERED;
7916 }
7917 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_enable_sack_immediately) &&
7918 (sp->sinfo_flags & SCTP_EOF) == SCTP_EOF) {
7919 rcv_flags |= SCTP_DATA_SACK_IMMEDIATELY;
7920 }
7921 /* clear out the chunk before setting up */
7922 memset(chk, 0, sizeof(*chk));
7923 chk->rec.data.rcv_flags = rcv_flags;
7924
7925 if (to_move >= length) {
7926 /* we think we can steal the whole thing */
7927 if ((sp->sender_all_done == 0) && (send_lock_up == 0)) {
7928 SCTP_TCB_SEND_LOCK(stcb);
7929 send_lock_up = 1;
7930 }
7931 if (to_move < sp->length) {
7932 /* bail, it changed */
7933 goto dont_do_it;
7934 }
7935 chk->data = sp->data;
7936 chk->last_mbuf = sp->tail_mbuf;
7937 /* register the stealing */
7938 sp->data = sp->tail_mbuf = NULL;
7939 } else {
7940 struct mbuf *m;
7941 dont_do_it:
7942 chk->data = SCTP_M_COPYM(sp->data, 0, to_move, M_NOWAIT);
7943 chk->last_mbuf = NULL;
7944 if (chk->data == NULL) {
7945 sp->some_taken = some_taken;
7946 sctp_free_a_chunk(stcb, chk, so_locked);
7947 *bail = 1;
7948 to_move = 0;
7949 goto out_of;
7950 }
7951#ifdef SCTP_MBUF_LOGGING
7952 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_MBUF_LOGGING_ENABLE) {
7953 sctp_log_mbc(chk->data, SCTP_MBUF_ICOPY);
7954 }
7955#endif
7956 /* Pull off the data */
7957 m_adj(sp->data, to_move);
7958 /* Now lets work our way down and compact it */
7959 m = sp->data;
7960 while (m && (SCTP_BUF_LEN(m) == 0)) {
7961 sp->data = SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m);
7962 SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m) = NULL;
7963 if (sp->tail_mbuf == m) {
7964 /*-
7965 * Freeing tail? TSNH since
7966 * we supposedly were taking less
7967 * than the sp->length.
7968 */
7969#ifdef INVARIANTS
7970 panic("Huh, freing tail? - TSNH");
7971#else
7972 SCTP_PRINTF("Huh, freeing tail? - TSNH\n");
7973 sp->tail_mbuf = sp->data = NULL;
7974 sp->length = 0;
7975#endif
7976 }
7977 sctp_m_free(m);
7978 m = sp->data;
7979 }
7980 }
7981 if (SCTP_BUF_IS_EXTENDED(chk->data)) {
7982 chk->copy_by_ref = 1;
7983 } else {
7984 chk->copy_by_ref = 0;
7985 }
7986 /* get last_mbuf and counts of mb usage
7987 * This is ugly but hopefully its only one mbuf.
7988 */
7989 if (chk->last_mbuf == NULL) {
7990 chk->last_mbuf = chk->data;
7991 while (SCTP_BUF_NEXT(chk->last_mbuf) != NULL) {
7992 chk->last_mbuf = SCTP_BUF_NEXT(chk->last_mbuf);
7993 }
7994 }
7995
7996 if (to_move > length) {
7997 /*- This should not happen either
7998 * since we always lower to_move to the size
7999 * of sp->length if its larger.
8000 */
8001#ifdef INVARIANTS
8002 panic("Huh, how can to_move be larger?");
8003#else
8004 SCTP_PRINTF("Huh, how can to_move be larger?\n");
8005 sp->length = 0;
8006#endif
8007 } else {
8008 atomic_subtract_int(&sp->length, to_move);
8009 }
8010 leading = SCTP_DATA_CHUNK_OVERHEAD(stcb);
8011 if (M_LEADINGSPACE(chk->data) < leading) {
8012 /* Not enough room for a chunk header, get some */
8013 struct mbuf *m;
8014
8015 m = sctp_get_mbuf_for_msg(1, 0, M_NOWAIT, 1, MT_DATA);
8016 if (m == NULL) {
8017 /*
8018 * we're in trouble here. _PREPEND below will free
8019 * all the data if there is no leading space, so we
8020 * must put the data back and restore.
8021 */
8022 if (send_lock_up == 0) {
8023 SCTP_TCB_SEND_LOCK(stcb);
8024 send_lock_up = 1;
8025 }
8026 if (sp->data == NULL) {
8027 /* unsteal the data */
8028 sp->data = chk->data;
8029 sp->tail_mbuf = chk->last_mbuf;
8030 } else {
8031 struct mbuf *m_tmp;
8032 /* reassemble the data */
8033 m_tmp = sp->data;
8034 sp->data = chk->data;
8035 SCTP_BUF_NEXT(chk->last_mbuf) = m_tmp;
8036 }
8037 sp->some_taken = some_taken;
8038 atomic_add_int(&sp->length, to_move);
8039 chk->data = NULL;
8040 *bail = 1;
8041 sctp_free_a_chunk(stcb, chk, so_locked);
8042 to_move = 0;
8043 goto out_of;
8044 } else {
8045 SCTP_BUF_LEN(m) = 0;
8046 SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m) = chk->data;
8047 chk->data = m;
8048 M_ALIGN(chk->data, 4);
8049 }
8050 }
8051 SCTP_BUF_PREPEND(chk->data, SCTP_DATA_CHUNK_OVERHEAD(stcb), M_NOWAIT);
8052 if (chk->data == NULL) {
8053 /* HELP, TSNH since we assured it would not above? */
8054#ifdef INVARIANTS
8055 panic("prepend failes HELP?");
8056#else
8057 SCTP_PRINTF("prepend fails HELP?\n");
8058 sctp_free_a_chunk(stcb, chk, so_locked);
8059#endif
8060 *bail = 1;
8061 to_move = 0;
8062 goto out_of;
8063 }
8064 sctp_snd_sb_alloc(stcb, SCTP_DATA_CHUNK_OVERHEAD(stcb));
8065 chk->book_size = chk->send_size = (uint16_t)(to_move + SCTP_DATA_CHUNK_OVERHEAD(stcb));
8066 chk->book_size_scale = 0;
8067 chk->sent = SCTP_DATAGRAM_UNSENT;
8068
8069 chk->flags = 0;
8070 chk->asoc = &stcb->asoc;
8071 chk->pad_inplace = 0;
8072 chk->no_fr_allowed = 0;
8073 if (stcb->asoc.idata_supported == 0) {
8074 if (rcv_flags & SCTP_DATA_UNORDERED) {
8075 /* Just use 0. The receiver ignores the values. */
8076 chk->rec.data.mid = 0;
8077 } else {
8078 chk->rec.data.mid = strq->next_mid_ordered;
8079 if (rcv_flags & SCTP_DATA_LAST_FRAG) {
8080 strq->next_mid_ordered++;
8081 }
8082 }
8083 } else {
8084 if (rcv_flags & SCTP_DATA_UNORDERED) {
8085 chk->rec.data.mid = strq->next_mid_unordered;
8086 if (rcv_flags & SCTP_DATA_LAST_FRAG) {
8087 strq->next_mid_unordered++;
8088 }
8089 } else {
8090 chk->rec.data.mid = strq->next_mid_ordered;
8091 if (rcv_flags & SCTP_DATA_LAST_FRAG) {
8092 strq->next_mid_ordered++;
8093 }
8094 }
8095 }
8096 chk->rec.data.sid = sp->sid;
8097 chk->rec.data.ppid = sp->ppid;
8098 chk->rec.data.context = sp->context;
8099 chk->rec.data.doing_fast_retransmit = 0;
8100
8101 chk->rec.data.timetodrop = sp->ts;
8102 chk->flags = sp->act_flags;
8103
8104 if (sp->net) {
8105 chk->whoTo = sp->net;
8106 atomic_add_int(&chk->whoTo->ref_count, 1);
8107 } else
8108 chk->whoTo = NULL;
8109
8110 if (sp->holds_key_ref) {
8111 chk->auth_keyid = sp->auth_keyid;
8112 sctp_auth_key_acquire(stcb, chk->auth_keyid);
8113 chk->holds_key_ref = 1;
8114 }
8115#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
8116 chk->rec.data.tsn = atomic_fetchadd_int(&asoc->sending_seq, 1);
8117#else
8118 chk->rec.data.tsn = asoc->sending_seq++;
8119#endif
8120 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_LOG_AT_SEND_2_OUTQ) {
8121 sctp_misc_ints(SCTP_STRMOUT_LOG_SEND,
8122 (uint32_t)(uintptr_t)stcb, sp->length,
8123 (uint32_t)((chk->rec.data.sid << 16) | (0x0000ffff & chk->rec.data.mid)),
8124 chk->rec.data.tsn);
8125 }
8126 if (stcb->asoc.idata_supported == 0) {
8127 dchkh = mtod(chk->data, struct sctp_data_chunk *);
8128 } else {
8129 ndchkh = mtod(chk->data, struct sctp_idata_chunk *);
8130 }
8131 /*
8132 * Put the rest of the things in place now. Size was done
8133 * earlier in previous loop prior to padding.
8134 */
8135
8136#ifdef SCTP_ASOCLOG_OF_TSNS
8137 SCTP_TCB_LOCK_ASSERT(stcb);
8138 if (asoc->tsn_out_at >= SCTP_TSN_LOG_SIZE) {
8139 asoc->tsn_out_at = 0;
8140 asoc->tsn_out_wrapped = 1;
8141 }
8142 asoc->out_tsnlog[asoc->tsn_out_at].tsn = chk->rec.data.tsn;
8143 asoc->out_tsnlog[asoc->tsn_out_at].strm = chk->rec.data.sid;
8144 asoc->out_tsnlog[asoc->tsn_out_at].seq = chk->rec.data.mid;
8145 asoc->out_tsnlog[asoc->tsn_out_at].sz = chk->send_size;
8146 asoc->out_tsnlog[asoc->tsn_out_at].flgs = chk->rec.data.rcv_flags;
8147 asoc->out_tsnlog[asoc->tsn_out_at].stcb = (void *)stcb;
8148 asoc->out_tsnlog[asoc->tsn_out_at].in_pos = asoc->tsn_out_at;
8149 asoc->out_tsnlog[asoc->tsn_out_at].in_out = 2;
8150 asoc->tsn_out_at++;
8151#endif
8152 if (stcb->asoc.idata_supported == 0) {
8153 dchkh->ch.chunk_type = SCTP_DATA;
8154 dchkh->ch.chunk_flags = chk->rec.data.rcv_flags;
8155 dchkh->dp.tsn = htonl(chk->rec.data.tsn);
8156 dchkh->dp.sid = htons(strq->sid);
8157 dchkh->dp.ssn = htons((uint16_t)chk->rec.data.mid);
8158 dchkh->dp.ppid = chk->rec.data.ppid;
8159 dchkh->ch.chunk_length = htons(chk->send_size);
8160 } else {
8161 ndchkh->ch.chunk_type = SCTP_IDATA;
8162 ndchkh->ch.chunk_flags = chk->rec.data.rcv_flags;
8163 ndchkh->dp.tsn = htonl(chk->rec.data.tsn);
8164 ndchkh->dp.sid = htons(strq->sid);
8165 ndchkh->dp.reserved = htons(0);
8166 ndchkh->dp.mid = htonl(chk->rec.data.mid);
8167 if (sp->fsn == 0)
8168 ndchkh->dp.ppid_fsn.ppid = chk->rec.data.ppid;
8169 else
8170 ndchkh->dp.ppid_fsn.fsn = htonl(sp->fsn);
8171 sp->fsn++;
8172 ndchkh->ch.chunk_length = htons(chk->send_size);
8173 }
8174 /* Now advance the chk->send_size by the actual pad needed. */
8175 if (chk->send_size < SCTP_SIZE32(chk->book_size)) {
8176 /* need a pad */
8177 struct mbuf *lm;
8178 int pads;
8179
8180 pads = SCTP_SIZE32(chk->book_size) - chk->send_size;
8181 lm = sctp_pad_lastmbuf(chk->data, pads, chk->last_mbuf);
8182 if (lm != NULL) {
8183 chk->last_mbuf = lm;
8184 chk->pad_inplace = 1;
8185 }
8186 chk->send_size += pads;
8187 }
8188 if (PR_SCTP_ENABLED(chk->flags)) {
8189 asoc->pr_sctp_cnt++;
8190 }
8191 if (sp->msg_is_complete && (sp->length == 0) && (sp->sender_all_done)) {
8192 /* All done pull and kill the message */
8193 if (sp->put_last_out == 0) {
8194 SCTP_PRINTF("Gak, put out entire msg with NO end!-2\n");
8195 SCTP_PRINTF("sender_done:%d len:%d msg_comp:%d put_last_out:%d send_lock:%d\n",
8196 sp->sender_all_done,
8197 sp->length,
8198 sp->msg_is_complete,
8199 sp->put_last_out,
8200 send_lock_up);
8201 }
8202 if ((send_lock_up == 0) && (TAILQ_NEXT(sp, next) == NULL)) {
8203 SCTP_TCB_SEND_LOCK(stcb);
8204 send_lock_up = 1;
8205 }
8206 atomic_subtract_int(&asoc->stream_queue_cnt, 1);
8207 TAILQ_REMOVE(&strq->outqueue, sp, next);
8208 stcb->asoc.ss_functions.sctp_ss_remove_from_stream(stcb, asoc, strq, sp, send_lock_up);
8209 if ((strq->state == SCTP_STREAM_RESET_PENDING) &&
8210 (strq->chunks_on_queues == 0) &&
8211 TAILQ_EMPTY(&strq->outqueue)) {
8212 stcb->asoc.trigger_reset = 1;
8213 }
8214 if (sp->net) {
8215 sctp_free_remote_addr(sp->net);
8216 sp->net = NULL;
8217 }
8218 if (sp->data) {
8219 sctp_m_freem(sp->data);
8220 sp->data = NULL;
8221 }
8222 sctp_free_a_strmoq(stcb, sp, so_locked);
8223 }
8224 asoc->chunks_on_out_queue++;
8225 strq->chunks_on_queues++;
8226 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&asoc->send_queue, chk, sctp_next);
8227 asoc->send_queue_cnt++;
8228out_of:
8229 if (send_lock_up) {
8230 SCTP_TCB_SEND_UNLOCK(stcb);
8231 }
8232 return (to_move);
8233}
8234
8235static void
8236sctp_fill_outqueue(struct sctp_tcb *stcb,
8237 struct sctp_nets *net, int frag_point, int eeor_mode, int *quit_now, int so_locked)
8238{
8239 struct sctp_association *asoc;
8240 struct sctp_stream_out *strq;
8241 uint32_t space_left, moved, total_moved;
8242 int bail, giveup;
8243
8244 SCTP_TCB_LOCK_ASSERT(stcb);
8245 asoc = &stcb->asoc;
8246 total_moved = 0;
8247 switch (net->ro._l_addr.sa.sa_family) {
8248#ifdef INET
8249 case AF_INET:
8250 space_left = net->mtu - SCTP_MIN_V4_OVERHEAD;
8251 break;
8252#endif
8253#ifdef INET6
8254 case AF_INET6:
8255 space_left = net->mtu - SCTP_MIN_OVERHEAD;
8256 break;
8257#endif
8258#if defined(__Userspace__)
8259 case AF_CONN:
8260 space_left = net->mtu - sizeof(struct sctphdr);
8261 break;
8262#endif
8263 default:
8264 /* TSNH */
8265 space_left = net->mtu;
8266 break;
8267 }
8268 /* Need an allowance for the data chunk header too */
8269 space_left -= SCTP_DATA_CHUNK_OVERHEAD(stcb);
8270
8271 /* must make even word boundary */
8272 space_left &= 0xfffffffc;
8273 strq = stcb->asoc.ss_functions.sctp_ss_select_stream(stcb, net, asoc);
8274 giveup = 0;
8275 bail = 0;
8276 while ((space_left > 0) && (strq != NULL)) {
8277 moved = sctp_move_to_outqueue(stcb, strq, space_left, frag_point,
8278 &giveup, eeor_mode, &bail, so_locked);
8279 stcb->asoc.ss_functions.sctp_ss_scheduled(stcb, net, asoc, strq, moved);
8280 if ((giveup != 0) || (bail != 0)) {
8281 break;
8282 }
8283 strq = stcb->asoc.ss_functions.sctp_ss_select_stream(stcb, net, asoc);
8284 total_moved += moved;
8285 if (space_left >= moved) {
8286 space_left -= moved;
8287 } else {
8288 space_left = 0;
8289 }
8290 if (space_left >= SCTP_DATA_CHUNK_OVERHEAD(stcb)) {
8291 space_left -= SCTP_DATA_CHUNK_OVERHEAD(stcb);
8292 } else {
8293 space_left = 0;
8294 }
8295 space_left &= 0xfffffffc;
8296 }
8297 if (bail != 0)
8298 *quit_now = 1;
8299
8300 stcb->asoc.ss_functions.sctp_ss_packet_done(stcb, net, asoc);
8301
8302 if (total_moved == 0) {
8303 if ((stcb->asoc.sctp_cmt_on_off == 0) &&
8304 (net == stcb->asoc.primary_destination)) {
8305 /* ran dry for primary network net */
8306 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_primary_randry);
8307 } else if (stcb->asoc.sctp_cmt_on_off > 0) {
8308 /* ran dry with CMT on */
8309 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_cmt_randry);
8310 }
8311 }
8312}
8313
8314void
8315sctp_fix_ecn_echo(struct sctp_association *asoc)
8316{
8317 struct sctp_tmit_chunk *chk;
8318
8319 TAILQ_FOREACH(chk, &asoc->control_send_queue, sctp_next) {
8320 if (chk->rec.chunk_id.id == SCTP_ECN_ECHO) {
8321 chk->sent = SCTP_DATAGRAM_UNSENT;
8322 }
8323 }
8324}
8325
8326void
8327sctp_move_chunks_from_net(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sctp_nets *net)
8328{
8329 struct sctp_association *asoc;
8330 struct sctp_tmit_chunk *chk;
8331 struct sctp_stream_queue_pending *sp;
8332 unsigned int i;
8333
8334 if (net == NULL) {
8335 return;
8336 }
8337 asoc = &stcb->asoc;
8338 for (i = 0; i < stcb->asoc.streamoutcnt; i++) {
8339 TAILQ_FOREACH(sp, &stcb->asoc.strmout[i].outqueue, next) {
8340 if (sp->net == net) {
8341 sctp_free_remote_addr(sp->net);
8342 sp->net = NULL;
8343 }
8344 }
8345 }
8346 TAILQ_FOREACH(chk, &asoc->send_queue, sctp_next) {
8347 if (chk->whoTo == net) {
8348 sctp_free_remote_addr(chk->whoTo);
8349 chk->whoTo = NULL;
8350 }
8351 }
8352}
8353
8354int
8355sctp_med_chunk_output(struct sctp_inpcb *inp,
8356 struct sctp_tcb *stcb,
8357 struct sctp_association *asoc,
8358 int *num_out,
8359 int *reason_code,
8360 int control_only, int from_where,
8361 struct timeval *now, int *now_filled, int frag_point, int so_locked)
8362{
8363 /**
8364 * Ok this is the generic chunk service queue. we must do the
8365 * following:
8366 * - Service the stream queue that is next, moving any
8367 * message (note I must get a complete message i.e. FIRST/MIDDLE and
8368 * LAST to the out queue in one pass) and assigning TSN's. This
8369 * only applys though if the peer does not support NDATA. For NDATA
8370 * chunks its ok to not send the entire message ;-)
8371 * - Check to see if the cwnd/rwnd allows any output, if so we go ahead and
8372 * fomulate and send the low level chunks. Making sure to combine
8373 * any control in the control chunk queue also.
8374 */
8375 struct sctp_nets *net, *start_at, *sack_goes_to = NULL, *old_start_at = NULL;
8376 struct mbuf *outchain, *endoutchain;
8377 struct sctp_tmit_chunk *chk, *nchk;
8378
8379 /* temp arrays for unlinking */
8380 struct sctp_tmit_chunk *data_list[SCTP_MAX_DATA_BUNDLING];
8381 int no_fragmentflg, error;
8382 unsigned int max_rwnd_per_dest, max_send_per_dest;
8383 int one_chunk, hbflag, skip_data_for_this_net;
8384 int asconf, cookie, no_out_cnt;
8385 int bundle_at, ctl_cnt, no_data_chunks, eeor_mode;
8386 unsigned int mtu, r_mtu, omtu, mx_mtu, to_out;
8387 int tsns_sent = 0;
8388 uint32_t auth_offset;
8389 struct sctp_auth_chunk *auth;
8390 uint16_t auth_keyid;
8391 int override_ok = 1;
8392 int skip_fill_up = 0;
8393 int data_auth_reqd = 0;
8394 /* JRS 5/14/07 - Add flag for whether a heartbeat is sent to
8395 the destination. */
8396 int quit_now = 0;
8397
8398#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
8399 if (so_locked) {
8400 sctp_lock_assert(SCTP_INP_SO(inp));
8401 } else {
8402 sctp_unlock_assert(SCTP_INP_SO(inp));
8403 }
8404#endif
8405 *num_out = 0;
8406 *reason_code = 0;
8407 auth_keyid = stcb->asoc.authinfo.active_keyid;
8408 if ((asoc->state & SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_PENDING) ||
8409 (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_RECEIVED) ||
8410 (sctp_is_feature_on(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_EXPLICIT_EOR))) {
8411 eeor_mode = 1;
8412 } else {
8413 eeor_mode = 0;
8414 }
8415 ctl_cnt = no_out_cnt = asconf = cookie = 0;
8416 /*
8417 * First lets prime the pump. For each destination, if there is room
8418 * in the flight size, attempt to pull an MTU's worth out of the
8419 * stream queues into the general send_queue
8420 */
8421#ifdef SCTP_AUDITING_ENABLED
8422 sctp_audit_log(0xC2, 2);
8423#endif
8424 SCTP_TCB_LOCK_ASSERT(stcb);
8425 hbflag = 0;
8426 if (control_only)
8427 no_data_chunks = 1;
8428 else
8429 no_data_chunks = 0;
8430
8431 /* Nothing to possible to send? */
8432 if ((TAILQ_EMPTY(&asoc->control_send_queue) ||
8433 (asoc->ctrl_queue_cnt == stcb->asoc.ecn_echo_cnt_onq)) &&
8434 TAILQ_EMPTY(&asoc->asconf_send_queue) &&
8435 TAILQ_EMPTY(&asoc->send_queue) &&
8436 sctp_is_there_unsent_data(stcb, so_locked) == 0) {
8437 nothing_to_send:
8438 *reason_code = 9;
8439 return (0);
8440 }
8441 if (asoc->peers_rwnd == 0) {
8442 /* No room in peers rwnd */
8443 *reason_code = 1;
8444 if (asoc->total_flight > 0) {
8445 /* we are allowed one chunk in flight */
8446 no_data_chunks = 1;
8447 }
8448 }
8449 if (stcb->asoc.ecn_echo_cnt_onq) {
8450 /* Record where a sack goes, if any */
8451 if (no_data_chunks &&
8452 (asoc->ctrl_queue_cnt == stcb->asoc.ecn_echo_cnt_onq)) {
8453 /* Nothing but ECNe to send - we don't do that */
8454 goto nothing_to_send;
8455 }
8456 TAILQ_FOREACH(chk, &asoc->control_send_queue, sctp_next) {
8457 if ((chk->rec.chunk_id.id == SCTP_SELECTIVE_ACK) ||
8458 (chk->rec.chunk_id.id == SCTP_NR_SELECTIVE_ACK)) {
8459 sack_goes_to = chk->whoTo;
8460 break;
8461 }
8462 }
8463 }
8464 max_rwnd_per_dest = ((asoc->peers_rwnd + asoc->total_flight) / asoc->numnets);
8465 if (stcb->sctp_socket)
8466 max_send_per_dest = SCTP_SB_LIMIT_SND(stcb->sctp_socket) / asoc->numnets;
8467 else
8468 max_send_per_dest = 0;
8469 if (no_data_chunks == 0) {
8470 /* How many non-directed chunks are there? */
8471 TAILQ_FOREACH(chk, &asoc->send_queue, sctp_next) {
8472 if (chk->whoTo == NULL) {
8473 /* We already have non-directed
8474 * chunks on the queue, no need
8475 * to do a fill-up.
8476 */
8477 skip_fill_up = 1;
8478 break;
8479 }
8480 }
8481 }
8482 if ((no_data_chunks == 0) &&
8483 (skip_fill_up == 0) &&
8484 (!stcb->asoc.ss_functions.sctp_ss_is_empty(stcb, asoc))) {
8485 TAILQ_FOREACH(net, &asoc->nets, sctp_next) {
8486 /*
8487 * This for loop we are in takes in
8488 * each net, if its's got space in cwnd and
8489 * has data sent to it (when CMT is off) then it
8490 * calls sctp_fill_outqueue for the net. This gets
8491 * data on the send queue for that network.
8492 *
8493 * In sctp_fill_outqueue TSN's are assigned and
8494 * data is copied out of the stream buffers. Note
8495 * mostly copy by reference (we hope).
8496 */
8497 net->window_probe = 0;
8498 if ((net != stcb->asoc.alternate) &&
8499 ((net->dest_state & SCTP_ADDR_PF) ||
8500 (!(net->dest_state & SCTP_ADDR_REACHABLE)) ||
8501 (net->dest_state & SCTP_ADDR_UNCONFIRMED))) {
8502 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_CWND_LOGGING_ENABLE) {
8503 sctp_log_cwnd(stcb, net, 1,
8504 SCTP_CWND_LOG_FILL_OUTQ_CALLED);
8505 }
8506 continue;
8507 }
8508 if ((stcb->asoc.cc_functions.sctp_cwnd_new_transmission_begins) &&
8509 (net->flight_size == 0)) {
8510 (*stcb->asoc.cc_functions.sctp_cwnd_new_transmission_begins)(stcb, net);
8511 }
8512 if (net->flight_size >= net->cwnd) {
8513 /* skip this network, no room - can't fill */
8514 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_CWND_LOGGING_ENABLE) {
8515 sctp_log_cwnd(stcb, net, 3,
8516 SCTP_CWND_LOG_FILL_OUTQ_CALLED);
8517 }
8518 continue;
8519 }
8520 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_CWND_LOGGING_ENABLE) {
8521 sctp_log_cwnd(stcb, net, 4, SCTP_CWND_LOG_FILL_OUTQ_CALLED);
8522 }
8523 sctp_fill_outqueue(stcb, net, frag_point, eeor_mode, &quit_now, so_locked);
8524 if (quit_now) {
8525 /* memory alloc failure */
8526 no_data_chunks = 1;
8527 break;
8528 }
8529 }
8530 }
8531 /* now service each destination and send out what we can for it */
8532 /* Nothing to send? */
8533 if (TAILQ_EMPTY(&asoc->control_send_queue) &&
8534 TAILQ_EMPTY(&asoc->asconf_send_queue) &&
8535 TAILQ_EMPTY(&asoc->send_queue)) {
8536 *reason_code = 8;
8537 return (0);
8538 }
8539
8540 if (asoc->sctp_cmt_on_off > 0) {
8541 /* get the last start point */
8542 start_at = asoc->last_net_cmt_send_started;
8543 if (start_at == NULL) {
8544 /* null so to beginning */
8545 start_at = TAILQ_FIRST(&asoc->nets);
8546 } else {
8547 start_at = TAILQ_NEXT(asoc->last_net_cmt_send_started, sctp_next);
8548 if (start_at == NULL) {
8549 start_at = TAILQ_FIRST(&asoc->nets);
8550 }
8551 }
8552 asoc->last_net_cmt_send_started = start_at;
8553 } else {
8554 start_at = TAILQ_FIRST(&asoc->nets);
8555 }
8556 TAILQ_FOREACH(chk, &asoc->control_send_queue, sctp_next) {
8557 if (chk->whoTo == NULL) {
8558 if (asoc->alternate) {
8559 chk->whoTo = asoc->alternate;
8560 } else {
8561 chk->whoTo = asoc->primary_destination;
8562 }
8563 atomic_add_int(&chk->whoTo->ref_count, 1);
8564 }
8565 }
8566 old_start_at = NULL;
8567again_one_more_time:
8568 for (net = start_at; net != NULL; net = TAILQ_NEXT(net, sctp_next)) {
8569 /* how much can we send? */
8570 /* SCTPDBG("Examine for sending net:%x\n", (uint32_t)net); */
8571 if (old_start_at && (old_start_at == net)) {
8572 /* through list ocmpletely. */
8573 break;
8574 }
8575 tsns_sent = 0xa;
8576 if (TAILQ_EMPTY(&asoc->control_send_queue) &&
8577 TAILQ_EMPTY(&asoc->asconf_send_queue) &&
8578 (net->flight_size >= net->cwnd)) {
8579 /* Nothing on control or asconf and flight is full, we can skip
8580 * even in the CMT case.
8581 */
8582 continue;
8583 }
8584 bundle_at = 0;
8585 endoutchain = outchain = NULL;
8586 auth = NULL;
8587 auth_offset = 0;
8588 no_fragmentflg = 1;
8589 one_chunk = 0;
8590 if (net->dest_state & SCTP_ADDR_UNCONFIRMED) {
8591 skip_data_for_this_net = 1;
8592 } else {
8593 skip_data_for_this_net = 0;
8594 }
8595 switch (((struct sockaddr *)&net->ro._l_addr)->sa_family) {
8596#ifdef INET
8597 case AF_INET:
8598 mtu = net->mtu - SCTP_MIN_V4_OVERHEAD;
8599 break;
8600#endif
8601#ifdef INET6
8602 case AF_INET6:
8603 mtu = net->mtu - SCTP_MIN_OVERHEAD;
8604 break;
8605#endif
8606#if defined(__Userspace__)
8607 case AF_CONN:
8608 mtu = net->mtu - sizeof(struct sctphdr);
8609 break;
8610#endif
8611 default:
8612 /* TSNH */
8613 mtu = net->mtu;
8614 break;
8615 }
8616 mx_mtu = mtu;
8617 to_out = 0;
8618 if (mtu > asoc->peers_rwnd) {
8619 if (asoc->total_flight > 0) {
8620 /* We have a packet in flight somewhere */
8621 r_mtu = asoc->peers_rwnd;
8622 } else {
8623 /* We are always allowed to send one MTU out */
8624 one_chunk = 1;
8625 r_mtu = mtu;
8626 }
8627 } else {
8628 r_mtu = mtu;
8629 }
8630 error = 0;
8631 /************************/
8632 /* ASCONF transmission */
8633 /************************/
8634 /* Now first lets go through the asconf queue */
8635 TAILQ_FOREACH_SAFE(chk, &asoc->asconf_send_queue, sctp_next, nchk) {
8636 if (chk->rec.chunk_id.id != SCTP_ASCONF) {
8637 continue;
8638 }
8639 if (chk->whoTo == NULL) {
8640 if (asoc->alternate == NULL) {
8641 if (asoc->primary_destination != net) {
8642 break;
8643 }
8644 } else {
8645 if (asoc->alternate != net) {
8646 break;
8647 }
8648 }
8649 } else {
8650 if (chk->whoTo != net) {
8651 break;
8652 }
8653 }
8654 if (chk->data == NULL) {
8655 break;
8656 }
8657 if (chk->sent != SCTP_DATAGRAM_UNSENT &&
8658 chk->sent != SCTP_DATAGRAM_RESEND) {
8659 break;
8660 }
8661 /*
8662 * if no AUTH is yet included and this chunk
8663 * requires it, make sure to account for it. We
8664 * don't apply the size until the AUTH chunk is
8665 * actually added below in case there is no room for
8666 * this chunk. NOTE: we overload the use of "omtu"
8667 * here
8668 */
8669 if ((auth == NULL) &&
8670 sctp_auth_is_required_chunk(chk->rec.chunk_id.id,
8671 stcb->asoc.peer_auth_chunks)) {
8672 omtu = sctp_get_auth_chunk_len(stcb->asoc.peer_hmac_id);
8673 } else
8674 omtu = 0;
8675 /* Here we do NOT factor the r_mtu */
8676 if ((chk->send_size < (int)(mtu - omtu)) ||
8677 (chk->flags & CHUNK_FLAGS_FRAGMENT_OK)) {
8678 /*
8679 * We probably should glom the mbuf chain
8680 * from the chk->data for control but the
8681 * problem is it becomes yet one more level
8682 * of tracking to do if for some reason
8683 * output fails. Then I have got to
8684 * reconstruct the merged control chain.. el
8685 * yucko.. for now we take the easy way and
8686 * do the copy
8687 */
8688 /*
8689 * Add an AUTH chunk, if chunk requires it
8690 * save the offset into the chain for AUTH
8691 */
8692 if ((auth == NULL) &&
8693 (sctp_auth_is_required_chunk(chk->rec.chunk_id.id,
8694 stcb->asoc.peer_auth_chunks))) {
8695 outchain = sctp_add_auth_chunk(outchain,
8696 &endoutchain,
8697 &auth,
8698 &auth_offset,
8699 stcb,
8700 chk->rec.chunk_id.id);
8701 SCTP_STAT_INCR_COUNTER64(sctps_outcontrolchunks);
8702 }
8703 outchain = sctp_copy_mbufchain(chk->data, outchain, &endoutchain,
8704 (int)chk->rec.chunk_id.can_take_data,
8705 chk->send_size, chk->copy_by_ref);
8706 if (outchain == NULL) {
8707 *reason_code = 8;
8708 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, stcb, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, ENOMEM);
8709 return (ENOMEM);
8710 }
8711 SCTP_STAT_INCR_COUNTER64(sctps_outcontrolchunks);
8712 /* update our MTU size */
8713 if (mtu > (chk->send_size + omtu))
8714 mtu -= (chk->send_size + omtu);
8715 else
8716 mtu = 0;
8717 to_out += (chk->send_size + omtu);
8718 /* Do clear IP_DF ? */
8719 if (chk->flags & CHUNK_FLAGS_FRAGMENT_OK) {
8720 no_fragmentflg = 0;
8721 }
8722 if (chk->rec.chunk_id.can_take_data)
8723 chk->data = NULL;
8724 /*
8725 * set hb flag since we can
8726 * use these for RTO
8727 */
8728 hbflag = 1;
8729 asconf = 1;
8730 /*
8731 * should sysctl this: don't
8732 * bundle data with ASCONF
8733 * since it requires AUTH
8734 */
8735 no_data_chunks = 1;
8736 chk->sent = SCTP_DATAGRAM_SENT;
8737 if (chk->whoTo == NULL) {
8738 chk->whoTo = net;
8739 atomic_add_int(&net->ref_count, 1);
8740 }
8741 chk->snd_count++;
8742 if (mtu == 0) {
8743 /*
8744 * Ok we are out of room but we can
8745 * output without effecting the
8746 * flight size since this little guy
8747 * is a control only packet.
8748 */
8749 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_ASCONF, inp, stcb, net);
8750 /*
8751 * do NOT clear the asconf
8752 * flag as it is used to do
8753 * appropriate source address
8754 * selection.
8755 */
8756 if (*now_filled == 0) {
8757 (void)SCTP_GETTIME_TIMEVAL(now);
8758 *now_filled = 1;
8759 }
8760 net->last_sent_time = *now;
8761 hbflag = 0;
8762 if ((error = sctp_lowlevel_chunk_output(inp, stcb, net,
8763 (struct sockaddr *)&net->ro._l_addr,
8764 outchain, auth_offset, auth,
8765 stcb->asoc.authinfo.active_keyid,
8766 no_fragmentflg, 0, asconf,
8767 inp->sctp_lport, stcb->rport,
8768 htonl(stcb->asoc.peer_vtag),
8769 net->port, NULL,
8770#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
8771 0, 0,
8772#endif
8773 so_locked))) {
8774 /* error, we could not output */
8775 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT3, "Gak send error %d\n", error);
8776 if (from_where == 0) {
8777 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_lowlevelerrusr);
8778 }
8779 if (error == ENOBUFS) {
8780 asoc->ifp_had_enobuf = 1;
8781 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_lowlevelerr);
8782 }
8783 /* error, could not output */
8784 if (error == EHOSTUNREACH) {
8785 /*
8786 * Destination went
8787 * unreachable
8788 * during this send
8789 */
8790 sctp_move_chunks_from_net(stcb, net);
8791 }
8792 *reason_code = 7;
8793 break;
8794 } else {
8795 asoc->ifp_had_enobuf = 0;
8796 }
8797 /*
8798 * increase the number we sent, if a
8799 * cookie is sent we don't tell them
8800 * any was sent out.
8801 */
8802 outchain = endoutchain = NULL;
8803 auth = NULL;
8804 auth_offset = 0;
8805 if (!no_out_cnt)
8806 *num_out += ctl_cnt;
8807 /* recalc a clean slate and setup */
8808 switch (net->ro._l_addr.sa.sa_family) {
8809#ifdef INET
8810 case AF_INET:
8811 mtu = net->mtu - SCTP_MIN_V4_OVERHEAD;
8812 break;
8813#endif
8814#ifdef INET6
8815 case AF_INET6:
8816 mtu = net->mtu - SCTP_MIN_OVERHEAD;
8817 break;
8818#endif
8819#if defined(__Userspace__)
8820 case AF_CONN:
8821 mtu = net->mtu - sizeof(struct sctphdr);
8822 break;
8823#endif
8824 default:
8825 /* TSNH */
8826 mtu = net->mtu;
8827 break;
8828 }
8829 to_out = 0;
8830 no_fragmentflg = 1;
8831 }
8832 }
8833 }
8834 if (error != 0) {
8835 /* try next net */
8836 continue;
8837 }
8838 /************************/
8839 /* Control transmission */
8840 /************************/
8841 /* Now first lets go through the control queue */
8842 TAILQ_FOREACH_SAFE(chk, &asoc->control_send_queue, sctp_next, nchk) {
8843 if ((sack_goes_to) &&
8844 (chk->rec.chunk_id.id == SCTP_ECN_ECHO) &&
8845 (chk->whoTo != sack_goes_to)) {
8846 /*
8847 * if we have a sack in queue, and we are looking at an
8848 * ecn echo that is NOT queued to where the sack is going..
8849 */
8850 if (chk->whoTo == net) {
8851 /* Don't transmit it to where its going (current net) */
8852 continue;
8853 } else if (sack_goes_to == net) {
8854 /* But do transmit it to this address */
8855 goto skip_net_check;
8856 }
8857 }
8858 if (chk->whoTo == NULL) {
8859 if (asoc->alternate == NULL) {
8860 if (asoc->primary_destination != net) {
8861 continue;
8862 }
8863 } else {
8864 if (asoc->alternate != net) {
8865 continue;
8866 }
8867 }
8868 } else {
8869 if (chk->whoTo != net) {
8870 continue;
8871 }
8872 }
8873 skip_net_check:
8874 if (chk->data == NULL) {
8875 continue;
8876 }
8877 if (chk->sent != SCTP_DATAGRAM_UNSENT) {
8878 /*
8879 * It must be unsent. Cookies and ASCONF's
8880 * hang around but there timers will force
8881 * when marked for resend.
8882 */
8883 continue;
8884 }
8885 /*
8886 * if no AUTH is yet included and this chunk
8887 * requires it, make sure to account for it. We
8888 * don't apply the size until the AUTH chunk is
8889 * actually added below in case there is no room for
8890 * this chunk. NOTE: we overload the use of "omtu"
8891 * here
8892 */
8893 if ((auth == NULL) &&
8894 sctp_auth_is_required_chunk(chk->rec.chunk_id.id,
8895 stcb->asoc.peer_auth_chunks)) {
8896 omtu = sctp_get_auth_chunk_len(stcb->asoc.peer_hmac_id);
8897 } else
8898 omtu = 0;
8899 /* Here we do NOT factor the r_mtu */
8900 if ((chk->send_size <= (int)(mtu - omtu)) ||
8901 (chk->flags & CHUNK_FLAGS_FRAGMENT_OK)) {
8902 /*
8903 * We probably should glom the mbuf chain
8904 * from the chk->data for control but the
8905 * problem is it becomes yet one more level
8906 * of tracking to do if for some reason
8907 * output fails. Then I have got to
8908 * reconstruct the merged control chain.. el
8909 * yucko.. for now we take the easy way and
8910 * do the copy
8911 */
8912 /*
8913 * Add an AUTH chunk, if chunk requires it
8914 * save the offset into the chain for AUTH
8915 */
8916 if ((auth == NULL) &&
8917 (sctp_auth_is_required_chunk(chk->rec.chunk_id.id,
8918 stcb->asoc.peer_auth_chunks))) {
8919 outchain = sctp_add_auth_chunk(outchain,
8920 &endoutchain,
8921 &auth,
8922 &auth_offset,
8923 stcb,
8924 chk->rec.chunk_id.id);
8925 SCTP_STAT_INCR_COUNTER64(sctps_outcontrolchunks);
8926 }
8927 outchain = sctp_copy_mbufchain(chk->data, outchain, &endoutchain,
8928 (int)chk->rec.chunk_id.can_take_data,
8929 chk->send_size, chk->copy_by_ref);
8930 if (outchain == NULL) {
8931 *reason_code = 8;
8932 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, stcb, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, ENOMEM);
8933 return (ENOMEM);
8934 }
8935 SCTP_STAT_INCR_COUNTER64(sctps_outcontrolchunks);
8936 /* update our MTU size */
8937 if (mtu > (chk->send_size + omtu))
8938 mtu -= (chk->send_size + omtu);
8939 else
8940 mtu = 0;
8941 to_out += (chk->send_size + omtu);
8942 /* Do clear IP_DF ? */
8943 if (chk->flags & CHUNK_FLAGS_FRAGMENT_OK) {
8944 no_fragmentflg = 0;
8945 }
8946 if (chk->rec.chunk_id.can_take_data)
8947 chk->data = NULL;
8948 /* Mark things to be removed, if needed */
8949 if ((chk->rec.chunk_id.id == SCTP_SELECTIVE_ACK) ||
8950 (chk->rec.chunk_id.id == SCTP_NR_SELECTIVE_ACK) || /* EY */
8951 (chk->rec.chunk_id.id == SCTP_HEARTBEAT_REQUEST) ||
8952 (chk->rec.chunk_id.id == SCTP_HEARTBEAT_ACK) ||
8953 (chk->rec.chunk_id.id == SCTP_SHUTDOWN) ||
8954 (chk->rec.chunk_id.id == SCTP_SHUTDOWN_ACK) ||
8955 (chk->rec.chunk_id.id == SCTP_OPERATION_ERROR) ||
8956 (chk->rec.chunk_id.id == SCTP_COOKIE_ACK) ||
8957 (chk->rec.chunk_id.id == SCTP_ECN_CWR) ||
8958 (chk->rec.chunk_id.id == SCTP_PACKET_DROPPED) ||
8959 (chk->rec.chunk_id.id == SCTP_ASCONF_ACK)) {
8960 if (chk->rec.chunk_id.id == SCTP_HEARTBEAT_REQUEST) {
8961 hbflag = 1;
8962 }
8963 /* remove these chunks at the end */
8964 if ((chk->rec.chunk_id.id == SCTP_SELECTIVE_ACK) ||
8965 (chk->rec.chunk_id.id == SCTP_NR_SELECTIVE_ACK)) {
8966 /* turn off the timer */
8967 if (SCTP_OS_TIMER_PENDING(&stcb->asoc.dack_timer.timer)) {
8968 sctp_timer_stop(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_RECV,
8969 inp, stcb, NULL,
8970 SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT + SCTP_LOC_1);
8971 }
8972 }
8973 ctl_cnt++;
8974 } else {
8975 /*
8976 * Other chunks, since they have
8977 * timers running (i.e. COOKIE)
8978 * we just "trust" that it
8979 * gets sent or retransmitted.
8980 */
8981 ctl_cnt++;
8982 if (chk->rec.chunk_id.id == SCTP_COOKIE_ECHO) {
8983 cookie = 1;
8984 no_out_cnt = 1;
8985 } else if (chk->rec.chunk_id.id == SCTP_ECN_ECHO) {
8986 /*
8987 * Increment ecne send count here
8988 * this means we may be over-zealous in
8989 * our counting if the send fails, but its
8990 * the best place to do it (we used to do
8991 * it in the queue of the chunk, but that did
8992 * not tell how many times it was sent.
8993 */
8994 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_sendecne);
8995 }
8996 chk->sent = SCTP_DATAGRAM_SENT;
8997 if (chk->whoTo == NULL) {
8998 chk->whoTo = net;
8999 atomic_add_int(&net->ref_count, 1);
9000 }
9001 chk->snd_count++;
9002 }
9003 if (mtu == 0) {
9004 /*
9005 * Ok we are out of room but we can
9006 * output without effecting the
9007 * flight size since this little guy
9008 * is a control only packet.
9009 */
9010 if (asconf) {
9011 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_ASCONF, inp, stcb, net);
9012 /*
9013 * do NOT clear the asconf
9014 * flag as it is used to do
9015 * appropriate source address
9016 * selection.
9017 */
9018 }
9019 if (cookie) {
9020 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_COOKIE, inp, stcb, net);
9021 cookie = 0;
9022 }
9023 /* Only HB or ASCONF advances time */
9024 if (hbflag) {
9025 if (*now_filled == 0) {
9026 (void)SCTP_GETTIME_TIMEVAL(now);
9027 *now_filled = 1;
9028 }
9029 net->last_sent_time = *now;
9030 hbflag = 0;
9031 }
9032 if ((error = sctp_lowlevel_chunk_output(inp, stcb, net,
9033 (struct sockaddr *)&net->ro._l_addr,
9034 outchain,
9035 auth_offset, auth,
9036 stcb->asoc.authinfo.active_keyid,
9037 no_fragmentflg, 0, asconf,
9038 inp->sctp_lport, stcb->rport,
9039 htonl(stcb->asoc.peer_vtag),
9040 net->port, NULL,
9041#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
9042 0, 0,
9043#endif
9044 so_locked))) {
9045 /* error, we could not output */
9046 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT3, "Gak send error %d\n", error);
9047 if (from_where == 0) {
9048 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_lowlevelerrusr);
9049 }
9050 if (error == ENOBUFS) {
9051 asoc->ifp_had_enobuf = 1;
9052 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_lowlevelerr);
9053 }
9054 if (error == EHOSTUNREACH) {
9055 /*
9056 * Destination went
9057 * unreachable
9058 * during this send
9059 */
9060 sctp_move_chunks_from_net(stcb, net);
9061 }
9062 *reason_code = 7;
9063 break;
9064 } else {
9065 asoc->ifp_had_enobuf = 0;
9066 }
9067 /*
9068 * increase the number we sent, if a
9069 * cookie is sent we don't tell them
9070 * any was sent out.
9071 */
9072 outchain = endoutchain = NULL;
9073 auth = NULL;
9074 auth_offset = 0;
9075 if (!no_out_cnt)
9076 *num_out += ctl_cnt;
9077 /* recalc a clean slate and setup */
9078 switch (net->ro._l_addr.sa.sa_family) {
9079#ifdef INET
9080 case AF_INET:
9081 mtu = net->mtu - SCTP_MIN_V4_OVERHEAD;
9082 break;
9083#endif
9084#ifdef INET6
9085 case AF_INET6:
9086 mtu = net->mtu - SCTP_MIN_OVERHEAD;
9087 break;
9088#endif
9089#if defined(__Userspace__)
9090 case AF_CONN:
9091 mtu = net->mtu - sizeof(struct sctphdr);
9092 break;
9093#endif
9094 default:
9095 /* TSNH */
9096 mtu = net->mtu;
9097 break;
9098 }
9099 to_out = 0;
9100 no_fragmentflg = 1;
9101 }
9102 }
9103 }
9104 if (error != 0) {
9105 /* try next net */
9106 continue;
9107 }
9108 /* JRI: if dest is in PF state, do not send data to it */
9109 if ((asoc->sctp_cmt_on_off > 0) &&
9110 (net != stcb->asoc.alternate) &&
9111 (net->dest_state & SCTP_ADDR_PF)) {
9112 goto no_data_fill;
9113 }
9114 if (net->flight_size >= net->cwnd) {
9115 goto no_data_fill;
9116 }
9117 if ((asoc->sctp_cmt_on_off > 0) &&
9118 (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_buffer_splitting) & SCTP_RECV_BUFFER_SPLITTING) &&
9119 (net->flight_size > max_rwnd_per_dest)) {
9120 goto no_data_fill;
9121 }
9122 /*
9123 * We need a specific accounting for the usage of the
9124 * send buffer. We also need to check the number of messages
9125 * per net. For now, this is better than nothing and it
9126 * disabled by default...
9127 */
9128 if ((asoc->sctp_cmt_on_off > 0) &&
9129 (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_buffer_splitting) & SCTP_SEND_BUFFER_SPLITTING) &&
9130 (max_send_per_dest > 0) &&
9131 (net->flight_size > max_send_per_dest)) {
9132 goto no_data_fill;
9133 }
9134 /*********************/
9135 /* Data transmission */
9136 /*********************/
9137 /*
9138 * if AUTH for DATA is required and no AUTH has been added
9139 * yet, account for this in the mtu now... if no data can be
9140 * bundled, this adjustment won't matter anyways since the
9141 * packet will be going out...
9142 */
9143 data_auth_reqd = sctp_auth_is_required_chunk(SCTP_DATA,
9144 stcb->asoc.peer_auth_chunks);
9145 if (data_auth_reqd && (auth == NULL)) {
9146 mtu -= sctp_get_auth_chunk_len(stcb->asoc.peer_hmac_id);
9147 }
9148 /* now lets add any data within the MTU constraints */
9149 switch (((struct sockaddr *)&net->ro._l_addr)->sa_family) {
9150#ifdef INET
9151 case AF_INET:
9152 if (net->mtu > SCTP_MIN_V4_OVERHEAD)
9153 omtu = net->mtu - SCTP_MIN_V4_OVERHEAD;
9154 else
9155 omtu = 0;
9156 break;
9157#endif
9158#ifdef INET6
9159 case AF_INET6:
9160 if (net->mtu > SCTP_MIN_OVERHEAD)
9161 omtu = net->mtu - SCTP_MIN_OVERHEAD;
9162 else
9163 omtu = 0;
9164 break;
9165#endif
9166#if defined(__Userspace__)
9167 case AF_CONN:
9168 if (net->mtu > sizeof(struct sctphdr)) {
9169 omtu = net->mtu - sizeof(struct sctphdr);
9170 } else {
9171 omtu = 0;
9172 }
9173 break;
9174#endif
9175 default:
9176 /* TSNH */
9177 omtu = 0;
9178 break;
9179 }
9180 if ((((SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_OPEN) ||
9181 (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_RECEIVED)) &&
9182 (skip_data_for_this_net == 0)) ||
9183 (cookie)) {
9184 TAILQ_FOREACH_SAFE(chk, &asoc->send_queue, sctp_next, nchk) {
9185 if (no_data_chunks) {
9186 /* let only control go out */
9187 *reason_code = 1;
9188 break;
9189 }
9190 if (net->flight_size >= net->cwnd) {
9191 /* skip this net, no room for data */
9192 *reason_code = 2;
9193 break;
9194 }
9195 if ((chk->whoTo != NULL) &&
9196 (chk->whoTo != net)) {
9197 /* Don't send the chunk on this net */
9198 continue;
9199 }
9200
9201 if (asoc->sctp_cmt_on_off == 0) {
9202 if ((asoc->alternate) &&
9203 (asoc->alternate != net) &&
9204 (chk->whoTo == NULL)) {
9205 continue;
9206 } else if ((net != asoc->primary_destination) &&
9207 (asoc->alternate == NULL) &&
9208 (chk->whoTo == NULL)) {
9209 continue;
9210 }
9211 }
9212 if ((chk->send_size > omtu) && ((chk->flags & CHUNK_FLAGS_FRAGMENT_OK) == 0)) {
9213 /*-
9214 * strange, we have a chunk that is
9215 * to big for its destination and
9216 * yet no fragment ok flag.
9217 * Something went wrong when the
9218 * PMTU changed...we did not mark
9219 * this chunk for some reason?? I
9220 * will fix it here by letting IP
9221 * fragment it for now and printing
9222 * a warning. This really should not
9223 * happen ...
9224 */
9225 SCTP_PRINTF("Warning chunk of %d bytes > mtu:%d and yet PMTU disc missed\n",
9226 chk->send_size, mtu);
9227 chk->flags |= CHUNK_FLAGS_FRAGMENT_OK;
9228 }
9229 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_enable_sack_immediately) &&
9230 (asoc->state & SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_PENDING)) {
9231 struct sctp_data_chunk *dchkh;
9232
9233 dchkh = mtod(chk->data, struct sctp_data_chunk *);
9234 dchkh->ch.chunk_flags |= SCTP_DATA_SACK_IMMEDIATELY;
9235 }
9236 if (((chk->send_size <= mtu) && (chk->send_size <= r_mtu)) ||
9237 ((chk->flags & CHUNK_FLAGS_FRAGMENT_OK) && (chk->send_size <= asoc->peers_rwnd))) {
9238 /* ok we will add this one */
9239
9240 /*
9241 * Add an AUTH chunk, if chunk
9242 * requires it, save the offset into
9243 * the chain for AUTH
9244 */
9245 if (data_auth_reqd) {
9246 if (auth == NULL) {
9247 outchain = sctp_add_auth_chunk(outchain,
9248 &endoutchain,
9249 &auth,
9250 &auth_offset,
9251 stcb,
9252 SCTP_DATA);
9253 auth_keyid = chk->auth_keyid;
9254 override_ok = 0;
9255 SCTP_STAT_INCR_COUNTER64(sctps_outcontrolchunks);
9256 } else if (override_ok) {
9257 /* use this data's keyid */
9258 auth_keyid = chk->auth_keyid;
9259 override_ok = 0;
9260 } else if (auth_keyid != chk->auth_keyid) {
9261 /* different keyid, so done bundling */
9262 break;
9263 }
9264 }
9265 outchain = sctp_copy_mbufchain(chk->data, outchain, &endoutchain, 0,
9266 chk->send_size, chk->copy_by_ref);
9267 if (outchain == NULL) {
9268 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT3, "No memory?\n");
9269 if (!SCTP_OS_TIMER_PENDING(&net->rxt_timer.timer)) {
9270 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_SEND, inp, stcb, net);
9271 }
9272 *reason_code = 3;
9273 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, stcb, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, ENOMEM);
9274 return (ENOMEM);
9275 }
9276 /* upate our MTU size */
9277 /* Do clear IP_DF ? */
9278 if (chk->flags & CHUNK_FLAGS_FRAGMENT_OK) {
9279 no_fragmentflg = 0;
9280 }
9281 /* unsigned subtraction of mtu */
9282 if (mtu > chk->send_size)
9283 mtu -= chk->send_size;
9284 else
9285 mtu = 0;
9286 /* unsigned subtraction of r_mtu */
9287 if (r_mtu > chk->send_size)
9288 r_mtu -= chk->send_size;
9289 else
9290 r_mtu = 0;
9291
9292 to_out += chk->send_size;
9293 if ((to_out > mx_mtu) && no_fragmentflg) {
9294#ifdef INVARIANTS
9295 panic("Exceeding mtu of %d out size is %d", mx_mtu, to_out);
9296#else
9297 SCTP_PRINTF("Exceeding mtu of %d out size is %d\n",
9298 mx_mtu, to_out);
9299#endif
9300 }
9301 chk->window_probe = 0;
9302 data_list[bundle_at++] = chk;
9303 if (bundle_at >= SCTP_MAX_DATA_BUNDLING) {
9304 break;
9305 }
9306 if (chk->sent == SCTP_DATAGRAM_UNSENT) {
9307 if ((chk->rec.data.rcv_flags & SCTP_DATA_UNORDERED) == 0) {
9308 SCTP_STAT_INCR_COUNTER64(sctps_outorderchunks);
9309 } else {
9310 SCTP_STAT_INCR_COUNTER64(sctps_outunorderchunks);
9311 }
9312 if (((chk->rec.data.rcv_flags & SCTP_DATA_LAST_FRAG) == SCTP_DATA_LAST_FRAG) &&
9313 ((chk->rec.data.rcv_flags & SCTP_DATA_FIRST_FRAG) == 0))
9314 /* Count number of user msg's that were fragmented
9315 * we do this by counting when we see a LAST fragment
9316 * only.
9317 */
9318 SCTP_STAT_INCR_COUNTER64(sctps_fragusrmsgs);
9319 }
9320 if ((mtu == 0) || (r_mtu == 0) || (one_chunk)) {
9321 if ((one_chunk) && (stcb->asoc.total_flight == 0)) {
9322 data_list[0]->window_probe = 1;
9323 net->window_probe = 1;
9324 }
9325 break;
9326 }
9327 } else {
9328 /*
9329 * Must be sent in order of the
9330 * TSN's (on a network)
9331 */
9332 break;
9333 }
9334 } /* for (chunk gather loop for this net) */
9335 } /* if asoc.state OPEN */
9336 no_data_fill:
9337 /* Is there something to send for this destination? */
9338 if (outchain) {
9339 /* We may need to start a control timer or two */
9340 if (asconf) {
9341 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_ASCONF, inp,
9342 stcb, net);
9343 /*
9344 * do NOT clear the asconf flag as it is used
9345 * to do appropriate source address selection.
9346 */
9347 }
9348 if (cookie) {
9349 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_COOKIE, inp, stcb, net);
9350 cookie = 0;
9351 }
9352 /* must start a send timer if data is being sent */
9353 if (bundle_at && (!SCTP_OS_TIMER_PENDING(&net->rxt_timer.timer))) {
9354 /*
9355 * no timer running on this destination
9356 * restart it.
9357 */
9358 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_SEND, inp, stcb, net);
9359 }
9360 if (bundle_at || hbflag) {
9361 /* For data/asconf and hb set time */
9362 if (*now_filled == 0) {
9363 (void)SCTP_GETTIME_TIMEVAL(now);
9364 *now_filled = 1;
9365 }
9366 net->last_sent_time = *now;
9367 }
9368 /* Now send it, if there is anything to send :> */
9369 if ((error = sctp_lowlevel_chunk_output(inp,
9370 stcb,
9371 net,
9372 (struct sockaddr *)&net->ro._l_addr,
9373 outchain,
9374 auth_offset,
9375 auth,
9376 auth_keyid,
9377 no_fragmentflg,
9378 bundle_at,
9379 asconf,
9380 inp->sctp_lport, stcb->rport,
9381 htonl(stcb->asoc.peer_vtag),
9382 net->port, NULL,
9383#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
9384 0, 0,
9385#endif
9386 so_locked))) {
9387 /* error, we could not output */
9388 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT3, "Gak send error %d\n", error);
9389 if (from_where == 0) {
9390 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_lowlevelerrusr);
9391 }
9392 if (error == ENOBUFS) {
9393 asoc->ifp_had_enobuf = 1;
9394 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_lowlevelerr);
9395 }
9396 if (error == EHOSTUNREACH) {
9397 /*
9398 * Destination went unreachable
9399 * during this send
9400 */
9401 sctp_move_chunks_from_net(stcb, net);
9402 }
9403 *reason_code = 6;
9404 /*-
9405 * I add this line to be paranoid. As far as
9406 * I can tell the continue, takes us back to
9407 * the top of the for, but just to make sure
9408 * I will reset these again here.
9409 */
9410 ctl_cnt = 0;
9411 continue; /* This takes us back to the for() for the nets. */
9412 } else {
9413 asoc->ifp_had_enobuf = 0;
9414 }
9415 endoutchain = NULL;
9416 auth = NULL;
9417 auth_offset = 0;
9418 if (!no_out_cnt) {
9419 *num_out += (ctl_cnt + bundle_at);
9420 }
9421 if (bundle_at) {
9422 /* setup for a RTO measurement */
9423 tsns_sent = data_list[0]->rec.data.tsn;
9424 /* fill time if not already filled */
9425 if (*now_filled == 0) {
9426 (void)SCTP_GETTIME_TIMEVAL(&asoc->time_last_sent);
9427 *now_filled = 1;
9428 *now = asoc->time_last_sent;
9429 } else {
9430 asoc->time_last_sent = *now;
9431 }
9432 if (net->rto_needed) {
9433 data_list[0]->do_rtt = 1;
9434 net->rto_needed = 0;
9435 }
9436 SCTP_STAT_INCR_BY(sctps_senddata, bundle_at);
9437 sctp_clean_up_datalist(stcb, asoc, data_list, bundle_at, net);
9438 }
9439 if (one_chunk) {
9440 break;
9441 }
9442 }
9443 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_CWND_LOGGING_ENABLE) {
9444 sctp_log_cwnd(stcb, net, tsns_sent, SCTP_CWND_LOG_FROM_SEND);
9445 }
9446 }
9447 if (old_start_at == NULL) {
9448 old_start_at = start_at;
9449 start_at = TAILQ_FIRST(&asoc->nets);
9450 if (old_start_at)
9451 goto again_one_more_time;
9452 }
9453
9454 /*
9455 * At the end there should be no NON timed chunks hanging on this
9456 * queue.
9457 */
9458 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_CWND_LOGGING_ENABLE) {
9459 sctp_log_cwnd(stcb, net, *num_out, SCTP_CWND_LOG_FROM_SEND);
9460 }
9461 if ((*num_out == 0) && (*reason_code == 0)) {
9462 *reason_code = 4;
9463 } else {
9464 *reason_code = 5;
9465 }
9466 sctp_clean_up_ctl(stcb, asoc, so_locked);
9467 return (0);
9468}
9469
9470void
9471sctp_queue_op_err(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct mbuf *op_err)
9472{
9473 /*-
9474 * Prepend a OPERATIONAL_ERROR chunk header and put on the end of
9475 * the control chunk queue.
9476 */
9477 struct sctp_chunkhdr *hdr;
9478 struct sctp_tmit_chunk *chk;
9479 struct mbuf *mat, *last_mbuf;
9480 uint32_t chunk_length;
9481 uint16_t padding_length;
9482
9483 SCTP_TCB_LOCK_ASSERT(stcb);
9484 SCTP_BUF_PREPEND(op_err, sizeof(struct sctp_chunkhdr), M_NOWAIT);
9485 if (op_err == NULL) {
9486 return;
9487 }
9488 last_mbuf = NULL;
9489 chunk_length = 0;
9490 for (mat = op_err; mat != NULL; mat = SCTP_BUF_NEXT(mat)) {
9491 chunk_length += SCTP_BUF_LEN(mat);
9492 if (SCTP_BUF_NEXT(mat) == NULL) {
9493 last_mbuf = mat;
9494 }
9495 }
9496 if (chunk_length > SCTP_MAX_CHUNK_LENGTH) {
9497 sctp_m_freem(op_err);
9498 return;
9499 }
9500 padding_length = chunk_length % 4;
9501 if (padding_length != 0) {
9502 padding_length = 4 - padding_length;
9503 }
9504 if (padding_length != 0) {
9505 if (sctp_add_pad_tombuf(last_mbuf, padding_length) == NULL) {
9506 sctp_m_freem(op_err);
9507 return;
9508 }
9509 }
9510 sctp_alloc_a_chunk(stcb, chk);
9511 if (chk == NULL) {
9512 /* no memory */
9513 sctp_m_freem(op_err);
9514 return;
9515 }
9516 chk->copy_by_ref = 0;
9517 chk->rec.chunk_id.id = SCTP_OPERATION_ERROR;
9518 chk->rec.chunk_id.can_take_data = 0;
9519 chk->flags = 0;
9520 chk->send_size = (uint16_t)chunk_length;
9521 chk->sent = SCTP_DATAGRAM_UNSENT;
9522 chk->snd_count = 0;
9523 chk->asoc = &stcb->asoc;
9524 chk->data = op_err;
9525 chk->whoTo = NULL;
9526 hdr = mtod(op_err, struct sctp_chunkhdr *);
9527 hdr->chunk_type = SCTP_OPERATION_ERROR;
9528 hdr->chunk_flags = 0;
9529 hdr->chunk_length = htons(chk->send_size);
9530 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&chk->asoc->control_send_queue, chk, sctp_next);
9531 chk->asoc->ctrl_queue_cnt++;
9532}
9533
9534int
9535sctp_send_cookie_echo(struct mbuf *m,
9536 int offset, int limit,
9537 struct sctp_tcb *stcb,
9538 struct sctp_nets *net)
9539{
9540 /*-
9541 * pull out the cookie and put it at the front of the control chunk
9542 * queue.
9543 */
9544 int at;
9545 struct mbuf *cookie;
9546 struct sctp_paramhdr param, *phdr;
9547 struct sctp_chunkhdr *hdr;
9548 struct sctp_tmit_chunk *chk;
9549 uint16_t ptype, plen;
9550
9551 SCTP_TCB_LOCK_ASSERT(stcb);
9552 /* First find the cookie in the param area */
9553 cookie = NULL;
