9554 at = offset + sizeof(struct sctp_init_chunk);
9555 for (;;) {
9556 phdr = sctp_get_next_param(m, at, &param, sizeof(param));
9557 if (phdr == NULL) {
9558 return (-3);
9559 }
9560 ptype = ntohs(phdr->param_type);
9561 plen = ntohs(phdr->param_length);
9562 if (plen < sizeof(struct sctp_paramhdr)) {
9563 return (-6);
9564 }
9565 if (ptype == SCTP_STATE_COOKIE) {
9566 int pad;
9567
9568 /* found the cookie */
9569 if (at + plen > limit) {
9570 return (-7);
9571 }
9572 cookie = SCTP_M_COPYM(m, at, plen, M_NOWAIT);
9573 if (cookie == NULL) {
9574 /* No memory */
9575 return (-2);
9576 }
9577 if ((pad = (plen % 4)) > 0) {
9578 pad = 4 - pad;
9579 }
9580 if (pad > 0) {
9581 if (sctp_pad_lastmbuf(cookie, pad, NULL) == NULL) {
9582 return (-8);
9583 }
9584 }
9585#ifdef SCTP_MBUF_LOGGING
9586 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_MBUF_LOGGING_ENABLE) {
9587 sctp_log_mbc(cookie, SCTP_MBUF_ICOPY);
9588 }
9589#endif
9590 break;
9591 }
9592 at += SCTP_SIZE32(plen);
9593 }
9594 /* ok, we got the cookie lets change it into a cookie echo chunk */
9595 /* first the change from param to cookie */
9596 hdr = mtod(cookie, struct sctp_chunkhdr *);
9597 hdr->chunk_type = SCTP_COOKIE_ECHO;
9598 hdr->chunk_flags = 0;
9599 /* get the chunk stuff now and place it in the FRONT of the queue */
9600 sctp_alloc_a_chunk(stcb, chk);
9601 if (chk == NULL) {
9602 /* no memory */
9603 sctp_m_freem(cookie);
9604 return (-5);
9605 }
9606 chk->copy_by_ref = 0;
9607 chk->rec.chunk_id.id = SCTP_COOKIE_ECHO;
9608 chk->rec.chunk_id.can_take_data = 0;
9609 chk->flags = CHUNK_FLAGS_FRAGMENT_OK;
9610 chk->send_size = SCTP_SIZE32(plen);
9611 chk->sent = SCTP_DATAGRAM_UNSENT;
9612 chk->snd_count = 0;
9613 chk->asoc = &stcb->asoc;
9614 chk->data = cookie;
9615 chk->whoTo = net;
9616 atomic_add_int(&chk->whoTo->ref_count, 1);
9617 TAILQ_INSERT_HEAD(&chk->asoc->control_send_queue, chk, sctp_next);
9618 chk->asoc->ctrl_queue_cnt++;
9619 return (0);
9620}
9621
9622void
9623sctp_send_heartbeat_ack(struct sctp_tcb *stcb,
9624 struct mbuf *m,
9625 int offset,
9626 int chk_length,
9627 struct sctp_nets *net)
9628{
9629 /*
9630 * take a HB request and make it into a HB ack and send it.
9631 */
9632 struct mbuf *outchain;
9633 struct sctp_chunkhdr *chdr;
9634 struct sctp_tmit_chunk *chk;
9635
9636 if (net == NULL)
9637 /* must have a net pointer */
9638 return;
9639
9640 outchain = SCTP_M_COPYM(m, offset, chk_length, M_NOWAIT);
9641 if (outchain == NULL) {
9642 /* gak out of memory */
9643 return;
9644 }
9645#ifdef SCTP_MBUF_LOGGING
9646 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_MBUF_LOGGING_ENABLE) {
9647 sctp_log_mbc(outchain, SCTP_MBUF_ICOPY);
9648 }
9649#endif
9650 chdr = mtod(outchain, struct sctp_chunkhdr *);
9651 chdr->chunk_type = SCTP_HEARTBEAT_ACK;
9652 chdr->chunk_flags = 0;
9653 if (chk_length % 4 != 0) {
9654 sctp_pad_lastmbuf(outchain, 4 - (chk_length % 4), NULL);
9655 }
9656 sctp_alloc_a_chunk(stcb, chk);
9657 if (chk == NULL) {
9658 /* no memory */
9659 sctp_m_freem(outchain);
9660 return;
9661 }
9662 chk->copy_by_ref = 0;
9663 chk->rec.chunk_id.id = SCTP_HEARTBEAT_ACK;
9664 chk->rec.chunk_id.can_take_data = 1;
9665 chk->flags = 0;
9666 chk->send_size = chk_length;
9667 chk->sent = SCTP_DATAGRAM_UNSENT;
9668 chk->snd_count = 0;
9669 chk->asoc = &stcb->asoc;
9670 chk->data = outchain;
9671 chk->whoTo = net;
9672 atomic_add_int(&chk->whoTo->ref_count, 1);
9673 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&chk->asoc->control_send_queue, chk, sctp_next);
9674 chk->asoc->ctrl_queue_cnt++;
9675}
9676
9677void
9678sctp_send_cookie_ack(struct sctp_tcb *stcb)
9679{
9680 /* formulate and queue a cookie-ack back to sender */
9681 struct mbuf *cookie_ack;
9682 struct sctp_chunkhdr *hdr;
9683 struct sctp_tmit_chunk *chk;
9684
9685 SCTP_TCB_LOCK_ASSERT(stcb);
9686
9687 cookie_ack = sctp_get_mbuf_for_msg(sizeof(struct sctp_chunkhdr), 0, M_NOWAIT, 1, MT_HEADER);
9688 if (cookie_ack == NULL) {
9689 /* no mbuf's */
9690 return;
9691 }
9692 SCTP_BUF_RESV_UF(cookie_ack, SCTP_MIN_OVERHEAD);
9693 sctp_alloc_a_chunk(stcb, chk);
9694 if (chk == NULL) {
9695 /* no memory */
9696 sctp_m_freem(cookie_ack);
9697 return;
9698 }
9699 chk->copy_by_ref = 0;
9700 chk->rec.chunk_id.id = SCTP_COOKIE_ACK;
9701 chk->rec.chunk_id.can_take_data = 1;
9702 chk->flags = 0;
9703 chk->send_size = sizeof(struct sctp_chunkhdr);
9704 chk->sent = SCTP_DATAGRAM_UNSENT;
9705 chk->snd_count = 0;
9706 chk->asoc = &stcb->asoc;
9707 chk->data = cookie_ack;
9708 if (chk->asoc->last_control_chunk_from != NULL) {
9709 chk->whoTo = chk->asoc->last_control_chunk_from;
9710 atomic_add_int(&chk->whoTo->ref_count, 1);
9711 } else {
9712 chk->whoTo = NULL;
9713 }
9714 hdr = mtod(cookie_ack, struct sctp_chunkhdr *);
9715 hdr->chunk_type = SCTP_COOKIE_ACK;
9716 hdr->chunk_flags = 0;
9717 hdr->chunk_length = htons(chk->send_size);
9718 SCTP_BUF_LEN(cookie_ack) = chk->send_size;
9719 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&chk->asoc->control_send_queue, chk, sctp_next);
9720 chk->asoc->ctrl_queue_cnt++;
9721 return;
9722}
9723
9724void
9725sctp_send_shutdown_ack(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sctp_nets *net)
9726{
9727 /* formulate and queue a SHUTDOWN-ACK back to the sender */
9728 struct mbuf *m_shutdown_ack;
9729 struct sctp_shutdown_ack_chunk *ack_cp;
9730 struct sctp_tmit_chunk *chk;
9731
9732 m_shutdown_ack = sctp_get_mbuf_for_msg(sizeof(struct sctp_shutdown_ack_chunk), 0, M_NOWAIT, 1, MT_HEADER);
9733 if (m_shutdown_ack == NULL) {
9734 /* no mbuf's */
9735 return;
9736 }
9737 SCTP_BUF_RESV_UF(m_shutdown_ack, SCTP_MIN_OVERHEAD);
9738 sctp_alloc_a_chunk(stcb, chk);
9739 if (chk == NULL) {
9740 /* no memory */
9741 sctp_m_freem(m_shutdown_ack);
9742 return;
9743 }
9744 chk->copy_by_ref = 0;
9745 chk->rec.chunk_id.id = SCTP_SHUTDOWN_ACK;
9746 chk->rec.chunk_id.can_take_data = 1;
9747 chk->flags = 0;
9748 chk->send_size = sizeof(struct sctp_chunkhdr);
9749 chk->sent = SCTP_DATAGRAM_UNSENT;
9750 chk->snd_count = 0;
9751 chk->asoc = &stcb->asoc;
9752 chk->data = m_shutdown_ack;
9753 chk->whoTo = net;
9754 if (chk->whoTo) {
9755 atomic_add_int(&chk->whoTo->ref_count, 1);
9756 }
9757 ack_cp = mtod(m_shutdown_ack, struct sctp_shutdown_ack_chunk *);
9758 ack_cp->ch.chunk_type = SCTP_SHUTDOWN_ACK;
9759 ack_cp->ch.chunk_flags = 0;
9760 ack_cp->ch.chunk_length = htons(chk->send_size);
9761 SCTP_BUF_LEN(m_shutdown_ack) = chk->send_size;
9762 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&chk->asoc->control_send_queue, chk, sctp_next);
9763 chk->asoc->ctrl_queue_cnt++;
9764 return;
9765}
9766
9767void
9768sctp_send_shutdown(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sctp_nets *net)
9769{
9770 /* formulate and queue a SHUTDOWN to the sender */
9771 struct mbuf *m_shutdown;
9772 struct sctp_shutdown_chunk *shutdown_cp;
9773 struct sctp_tmit_chunk *chk;
9774
9775 TAILQ_FOREACH(chk, &stcb->asoc.control_send_queue, sctp_next) {
9776 if (chk->rec.chunk_id.id == SCTP_SHUTDOWN) {
9777 /* We already have a SHUTDOWN queued. Reuse it. */
9778 if (chk->whoTo) {
9779 sctp_free_remote_addr(chk->whoTo);
9780 chk->whoTo = NULL;
9781 }
9782 break;
9783 }
9784 }
9785 if (chk == NULL) {
9786 m_shutdown = sctp_get_mbuf_for_msg(sizeof(struct sctp_shutdown_chunk), 0, M_NOWAIT, 1, MT_HEADER);
9787 if (m_shutdown == NULL) {
9788 /* no mbuf's */
9789 return;
9790 }
9791 SCTP_BUF_RESV_UF(m_shutdown, SCTP_MIN_OVERHEAD);
9792 sctp_alloc_a_chunk(stcb, chk);
9793 if (chk == NULL) {
9794 /* no memory */
9795 sctp_m_freem(m_shutdown);
9796 return;
9797 }
9798 chk->copy_by_ref = 0;
9799 chk->rec.chunk_id.id = SCTP_SHUTDOWN;
9800 chk->rec.chunk_id.can_take_data = 1;
9801 chk->flags = 0;
9802 chk->send_size = sizeof(struct sctp_shutdown_chunk);
9803 chk->sent = SCTP_DATAGRAM_UNSENT;
9804 chk->snd_count = 0;
9805 chk->asoc = &stcb->asoc;
9806 chk->data = m_shutdown;
9807 chk->whoTo = net;
9808 if (chk->whoTo) {
9809 atomic_add_int(&chk->whoTo->ref_count, 1);
9810 }
9811 shutdown_cp = mtod(m_shutdown, struct sctp_shutdown_chunk *);
9812 shutdown_cp->ch.chunk_type = SCTP_SHUTDOWN;
9813 shutdown_cp->ch.chunk_flags = 0;
9814 shutdown_cp->ch.chunk_length = htons(chk->send_size);
9815 shutdown_cp->cumulative_tsn_ack = htonl(stcb->asoc.cumulative_tsn);
9816 SCTP_BUF_LEN(m_shutdown) = chk->send_size;
9817 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&chk->asoc->control_send_queue, chk, sctp_next);
9818 chk->asoc->ctrl_queue_cnt++;
9819 } else {
9820 TAILQ_REMOVE(&stcb->asoc.control_send_queue, chk, sctp_next);
9821 chk->whoTo = net;
9822 if (chk->whoTo) {
9823 atomic_add_int(&chk->whoTo->ref_count, 1);
9824 }
9825 shutdown_cp = mtod(chk->data, struct sctp_shutdown_chunk *);
9826 shutdown_cp->cumulative_tsn_ack = htonl(stcb->asoc.cumulative_tsn);
9827 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&stcb->asoc.control_send_queue, chk, sctp_next);
9828 }
9829 return;
9830}
9831
9832void
9833sctp_send_asconf(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sctp_nets *net, int addr_locked)
9834{
9835 /*
9836 * formulate and queue an ASCONF to the peer.
9837 * ASCONF parameters should be queued on the assoc queue.
9838 */
9839 struct sctp_tmit_chunk *chk;
9840 struct mbuf *m_asconf;
9841 int len;
9842
9843 SCTP_TCB_LOCK_ASSERT(stcb);
9844
9845 if ((!TAILQ_EMPTY(&stcb->asoc.asconf_send_queue)) &&
9846 (!sctp_is_feature_on(stcb->sctp_ep, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_MULTIPLE_ASCONFS))) {
9847 /* can't send a new one if there is one in flight already */
9848 return;
9849 }
9850
9851 /* compose an ASCONF chunk, maximum length is PMTU */
9852 m_asconf = sctp_compose_asconf(stcb, &len, addr_locked);
9853 if (m_asconf == NULL) {
9854 return;
9855 }
9856
9857 sctp_alloc_a_chunk(stcb, chk);
9858 if (chk == NULL) {
9859 /* no memory */
9860 sctp_m_freem(m_asconf);
9861 return;
9862 }
9863
9864 chk->copy_by_ref = 0;
9865 chk->rec.chunk_id.id = SCTP_ASCONF;
9866 chk->rec.chunk_id.can_take_data = 0;
9867 chk->flags = CHUNK_FLAGS_FRAGMENT_OK;
9868 chk->data = m_asconf;
9869 chk->send_size = len;
9870 chk->sent = SCTP_DATAGRAM_UNSENT;
9871 chk->snd_count = 0;
9872 chk->asoc = &stcb->asoc;
9873 chk->whoTo = net;
9874 if (chk->whoTo) {
9875 atomic_add_int(&chk->whoTo->ref_count, 1);
9876 }
9877 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&chk->asoc->asconf_send_queue, chk, sctp_next);
9878 chk->asoc->ctrl_queue_cnt++;
9879 return;
9880}
9881
9882void
9883sctp_send_asconf_ack(struct sctp_tcb *stcb)
9884{
9885 /*
9886 * formulate and queue a asconf-ack back to sender.
9887 * the asconf-ack must be stored in the tcb.
9888 */
9889 struct sctp_tmit_chunk *chk;
9890 struct sctp_asconf_ack *ack, *latest_ack;
9891 struct mbuf *m_ack;
9892 struct sctp_nets *net = NULL;
9893
9894 SCTP_TCB_LOCK_ASSERT(stcb);
9895 /* Get the latest ASCONF-ACK */
9896 latest_ack = TAILQ_LAST(&stcb->asoc.asconf_ack_sent, sctp_asconf_ackhead);
9897 if (latest_ack == NULL) {
9898 return;
9899 }
9900 if (latest_ack->last_sent_to != NULL &&
9901 latest_ack->last_sent_to == stcb->asoc.last_control_chunk_from) {
9902 /* we're doing a retransmission */
9903 net = sctp_find_alternate_net(stcb, stcb->asoc.last_control_chunk_from, 0);
9904 if (net == NULL) {
9905 /* no alternate */
9906 if (stcb->asoc.last_control_chunk_from == NULL) {
9907 if (stcb->asoc.alternate) {
9908 net = stcb->asoc.alternate;
9909 } else {
9910 net = stcb->asoc.primary_destination;
9911 }
9912 } else {
9913 net = stcb->asoc.last_control_chunk_from;
9914 }
9915 }
9916 } else {
9917 /* normal case */
9918 if (stcb->asoc.last_control_chunk_from == NULL) {
9919 if (stcb->asoc.alternate) {
9920 net = stcb->asoc.alternate;
9921 } else {
9922 net = stcb->asoc.primary_destination;
9923 }
9924 } else {
9925 net = stcb->asoc.last_control_chunk_from;
9926 }
9927 }
9928 latest_ack->last_sent_to = net;
9929
9930 TAILQ_FOREACH(ack, &stcb->asoc.asconf_ack_sent, next) {
9931 if (ack->data == NULL) {
9932 continue;
9933 }
9934
9935 /* copy the asconf_ack */
9936 m_ack = SCTP_M_COPYM(ack->data, 0, M_COPYALL, M_NOWAIT);
9937 if (m_ack == NULL) {
9938 /* couldn't copy it */
9939 return;
9940 }
9941#ifdef SCTP_MBUF_LOGGING
9942 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_MBUF_LOGGING_ENABLE) {
9943 sctp_log_mbc(m_ack, SCTP_MBUF_ICOPY);
9944 }
9945#endif
9946
9947 sctp_alloc_a_chunk(stcb, chk);
9948 if (chk == NULL) {
9949 /* no memory */
9950 if (m_ack)
9951 sctp_m_freem(m_ack);
9952 return;
9953 }
9954 chk->copy_by_ref = 0;
9955 chk->rec.chunk_id.id = SCTP_ASCONF_ACK;
9956 chk->rec.chunk_id.can_take_data = 1;
9957 chk->flags = CHUNK_FLAGS_FRAGMENT_OK;
9958 chk->whoTo = net;
9959 if (chk->whoTo) {
9960 atomic_add_int(&chk->whoTo->ref_count, 1);
9961 }
9962 chk->data = m_ack;
9963 chk->send_size = ack->len;
9964 chk->sent = SCTP_DATAGRAM_UNSENT;
9965 chk->snd_count = 0;
9966 chk->asoc = &stcb->asoc;
9967
9968 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&chk->asoc->control_send_queue, chk, sctp_next);
9969 chk->asoc->ctrl_queue_cnt++;
9970 }
9971 return;
9972}
9973
9974static int
9975sctp_chunk_retransmission(struct sctp_inpcb *inp,
9976 struct sctp_tcb *stcb,
9977 struct sctp_association *asoc,
9978 int *cnt_out, struct timeval *now, int *now_filled, int *fr_done, int so_locked)
9979{
9980 /*-
9981 * send out one MTU of retransmission. If fast_retransmit is
9982 * happening we ignore the cwnd. Otherwise we obey the cwnd and
9983 * rwnd. For a Cookie or Asconf in the control chunk queue we
9984 * retransmit them by themselves.
9985 *
9986 * For data chunks we will pick out the lowest TSN's in the sent_queue
9987 * marked for resend and bundle them all together (up to a MTU of
9988 * destination). The address to send to should have been
9989 * selected/changed where the retransmission was marked (i.e. in FR
9990 * or t3-timeout routines).
9991 */
9992 struct sctp_tmit_chunk *data_list[SCTP_MAX_DATA_BUNDLING];
9993 struct sctp_tmit_chunk *chk, *fwd;
9994 struct mbuf *m, *endofchain;
9995 struct sctp_nets *net = NULL;
9996 uint32_t tsns_sent = 0;
9997 int no_fragmentflg, bundle_at, cnt_thru;
9998 unsigned int mtu;
9999 int error, i, one_chunk, fwd_tsn, ctl_cnt, tmr_started;
10000 struct sctp_auth_chunk *auth = NULL;
10001 uint32_t auth_offset = 0;
10002 uint16_t auth_keyid;
10003 int override_ok = 1;
10004 int data_auth_reqd = 0;
10005 uint32_t dmtu = 0;
10006
10007#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
10008 if (so_locked) {
10009 sctp_lock_assert(SCTP_INP_SO(inp));
10010 } else {
10011 sctp_unlock_assert(SCTP_INP_SO(inp));
10012 }
10013#endif
10014 SCTP_TCB_LOCK_ASSERT(stcb);
10015 tmr_started = ctl_cnt = 0;
10016 no_fragmentflg = 1;
10017 fwd_tsn = 0;
10018 *cnt_out = 0;
10019 fwd = NULL;
10020 endofchain = m = NULL;
10021 auth_keyid = stcb->asoc.authinfo.active_keyid;
10022#ifdef SCTP_AUDITING_ENABLED
10023 sctp_audit_log(0xC3, 1);
10024#endif
10025 if ((TAILQ_EMPTY(&asoc->sent_queue)) &&
10026 (TAILQ_EMPTY(&asoc->control_send_queue))) {
10027 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT1,"SCTP hits empty queue with cnt set to %d?\n",
10028 asoc->sent_queue_retran_cnt);
10029 asoc->sent_queue_cnt = 0;
10030 asoc->sent_queue_cnt_removeable = 0;
10031 /* send back 0/0 so we enter normal transmission */
10032 *cnt_out = 0;
10033 return (0);
10034 }
10035 TAILQ_FOREACH(chk, &asoc->control_send_queue, sctp_next) {
10036 if ((chk->rec.chunk_id.id == SCTP_COOKIE_ECHO) ||
10037 (chk->rec.chunk_id.id == SCTP_STREAM_RESET) ||
10038 (chk->rec.chunk_id.id == SCTP_FORWARD_CUM_TSN)) {
10039 if (chk->sent != SCTP_DATAGRAM_RESEND) {
10040 continue;
10041 }
10042 if (chk->rec.chunk_id.id == SCTP_STREAM_RESET) {
10043 if (chk != asoc->str_reset) {
10044 /*
10045 * not eligible for retran if its
10046 * not ours
10047 */
10048 continue;
10049 }
10050 }
10051 ctl_cnt++;
10052 if (chk->rec.chunk_id.id == SCTP_FORWARD_CUM_TSN) {
10053 fwd_tsn = 1;
10054 }
10055 /*
10056 * Add an AUTH chunk, if chunk requires it save the
10057 * offset into the chain for AUTH
10058 */
10059 if ((auth == NULL) &&
10060 (sctp_auth_is_required_chunk(chk->rec.chunk_id.id,
10061 stcb->asoc.peer_auth_chunks))) {
10062 m = sctp_add_auth_chunk(m, &endofchain,
10063 &auth, &auth_offset,
10064 stcb,
10065 chk->rec.chunk_id.id);
10066 SCTP_STAT_INCR_COUNTER64(sctps_outcontrolchunks);
10067 }
10068 m = sctp_copy_mbufchain(chk->data, m, &endofchain, 0, chk->send_size, chk->copy_by_ref);
10069 break;
10070 }
10071 }
10072 one_chunk = 0;
10073 cnt_thru = 0;
10074 /* do we have control chunks to retransmit? */
10075 if (m != NULL) {
10076 /* Start a timer no matter if we succeed or fail */
10077 if (chk->rec.chunk_id.id == SCTP_COOKIE_ECHO) {
10078 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_COOKIE, inp, stcb, chk->whoTo);
10079 } else if (chk->rec.chunk_id.id == SCTP_ASCONF)
10080 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_ASCONF, inp, stcb, chk->whoTo);
10081 chk->snd_count++; /* update our count */
10082 if ((error = sctp_lowlevel_chunk_output(inp, stcb, chk->whoTo,
10083 (struct sockaddr *)&chk->whoTo->ro._l_addr, m,
10084 auth_offset, auth, stcb->asoc.authinfo.active_keyid,
10085 no_fragmentflg, 0, 0,
10086 inp->sctp_lport, stcb->rport, htonl(stcb->asoc.peer_vtag),
10087 chk->whoTo->port, NULL,
10088#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
10089 0, 0,
10090#endif
10091 so_locked))) {
10092 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT3, "Gak send error %d\n", error);
10093 if (error == ENOBUFS) {
10094 asoc->ifp_had_enobuf = 1;
10095 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_lowlevelerr);
10096 }
10097 return (error);
10098 } else {
10099 asoc->ifp_had_enobuf = 0;
10100 }
10101 endofchain = NULL;
10102 auth = NULL;
10103 auth_offset = 0;
10104 /*
10105 * We don't want to mark the net->sent time here since this
10106 * we use this for HB and retrans cannot measure RTT
10107 */
10108 /* (void)SCTP_GETTIME_TIMEVAL(&chk->whoTo->last_sent_time); */
10109 *cnt_out += 1;
10110 chk->sent = SCTP_DATAGRAM_SENT;
10111 sctp_ucount_decr(stcb->asoc.sent_queue_retran_cnt);
10112 if (fwd_tsn == 0) {
10113 return (0);
10114 } else {
10115 /* Clean up the fwd-tsn list */
10116 sctp_clean_up_ctl(stcb, asoc, so_locked);
10117 return (0);
10118 }
10119 }
10120 /*
10121 * Ok, it is just data retransmission we need to do or that and a
10122 * fwd-tsn with it all.
10123 */
10124 if (TAILQ_EMPTY(&asoc->sent_queue)) {
10125 return (SCTP_RETRAN_DONE);
10126 }
10127 if ((SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_COOKIE_ECHOED) ||
10128 (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_COOKIE_WAIT)) {
10129 /* not yet open, resend the cookie and that is it */
10130 return (1);
10131 }
10132#ifdef SCTP_AUDITING_ENABLED
10133 sctp_auditing(20, inp, stcb, NULL);
10134#endif
10135 data_auth_reqd = sctp_auth_is_required_chunk(SCTP_DATA, stcb->asoc.peer_auth_chunks);
10136 TAILQ_FOREACH(chk, &asoc->sent_queue, sctp_next) {
10137 if (chk->sent != SCTP_DATAGRAM_RESEND) {
10138 /* No, not sent to this net or not ready for rtx */
10139 continue;
10140 }
10141 if (chk->data == NULL) {
10142 SCTP_PRINTF("TSN:%x chk->snd_count:%d chk->sent:%d can't retran - no data\n",
10143 chk->rec.data.tsn, chk->snd_count, chk->sent);
10144 continue;
10145 }
10146 if ((SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_max_retran_chunk)) &&
10147 (chk->snd_count >= SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_max_retran_chunk))) {
10148 struct mbuf *op_err;
10149 char msg[SCTP_DIAG_INFO_LEN];
10150
10151 SCTP_SNPRINTF(msg, sizeof(msg), "TSN %8.8x retransmitted %d times, giving up",
10152 chk->rec.data.tsn, chk->snd_count);
10153 op_err = sctp_generate_cause(SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_diag_info_code),
10154 msg);
10155 atomic_add_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
10156 sctp_abort_an_association(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, op_err,
10157 so_locked);
10158 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
10159 atomic_subtract_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
10160 return (SCTP_RETRAN_EXIT);
10161 }
10162 /* pick up the net */
10163 net = chk->whoTo;
10164 switch (net->ro._l_addr.sa.sa_family) {
10165#ifdef INET
10166 case AF_INET:
10167 mtu = net->mtu - SCTP_MIN_V4_OVERHEAD;
10168 break;
10169#endif
10170#ifdef INET6
10171 case AF_INET6:
10172 mtu = net->mtu - SCTP_MIN_OVERHEAD;
10173 break;
10174#endif
10175#if defined(__Userspace__)
10176 case AF_CONN:
10177 mtu = net->mtu - sizeof(struct sctphdr);
10178 break;
10179#endif
10180 default:
10181 /* TSNH */
10182 mtu = net->mtu;
10183 break;
10184 }
10185
10186 if ((asoc->peers_rwnd < mtu) && (asoc->total_flight > 0)) {
10187 /* No room in peers rwnd */
10188 uint32_t tsn;
10189
10190 tsn = asoc->last_acked_seq + 1;
10191 if (tsn == chk->rec.data.tsn) {
10192 /*
10193 * we make a special exception for this
10194 * case. The peer has no rwnd but is missing
10195 * the lowest chunk.. which is probably what
10196 * is holding up the rwnd.
10197 */
10198 goto one_chunk_around;
10199 }
10200 return (1);
10201 }
10202 one_chunk_around:
10203 if (asoc->peers_rwnd < mtu) {
10204 one_chunk = 1;
10205 if ((asoc->peers_rwnd == 0) &&
10206 (asoc->total_flight == 0)) {
10207 chk->window_probe = 1;
10208 chk->whoTo->window_probe = 1;
10209 }
10210 }
10211#ifdef SCTP_AUDITING_ENABLED
10212 sctp_audit_log(0xC3, 2);
10213#endif
10214 bundle_at = 0;
10215 m = NULL;
10216 net->fast_retran_ip = 0;
10217 if (chk->rec.data.doing_fast_retransmit == 0) {
10218 /*
10219 * if no FR in progress skip destination that have
10220 * flight_size > cwnd.
10221 */
10222 if (net->flight_size >= net->cwnd) {
10223 continue;
10224 }
10225 } else {
10226 /*
10227 * Mark the destination net to have FR recovery
10228 * limits put on it.
10229 */
10230 *fr_done = 1;
10231 net->fast_retran_ip = 1;
10232 }
10233
10234 /*
10235 * if no AUTH is yet included and this chunk requires it,
10236 * make sure to account for it. We don't apply the size
10237 * until the AUTH chunk is actually added below in case
10238 * there is no room for this chunk.
10239 */
10240 if (data_auth_reqd && (auth == NULL)) {
10241 dmtu = sctp_get_auth_chunk_len(stcb->asoc.peer_hmac_id);
10242 } else
10243 dmtu = 0;
10244
10245 if ((chk->send_size <= (mtu - dmtu)) ||
10246 (chk->flags & CHUNK_FLAGS_FRAGMENT_OK)) {
10247 /* ok we will add this one */
10248 if (data_auth_reqd) {
10249 if (auth == NULL) {
10250 m = sctp_add_auth_chunk(m,
10251 &endofchain,
10252 &auth,
10253 &auth_offset,
10254 stcb,
10255 SCTP_DATA);
10256 auth_keyid = chk->auth_keyid;
10257 override_ok = 0;
10258 SCTP_STAT_INCR_COUNTER64(sctps_outcontrolchunks);
10259 } else if (override_ok) {
10260 auth_keyid = chk->auth_keyid;
10261 override_ok = 0;
10262 } else if (chk->auth_keyid != auth_keyid) {
10263 /* different keyid, so done bundling */
10264 break;
10265 }
10266 }
10267 m = sctp_copy_mbufchain(chk->data, m, &endofchain, 0, chk->send_size, chk->copy_by_ref);
10268 if (m == NULL) {
10269 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, stcb, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, ENOMEM);
10270 return (ENOMEM);
10271 }
10272 /* Do clear IP_DF ? */
10273 if (chk->flags & CHUNK_FLAGS_FRAGMENT_OK) {
10274 no_fragmentflg = 0;
10275 }
10276 /* upate our MTU size */
10277 if (mtu > (chk->send_size + dmtu))
10278 mtu -= (chk->send_size + dmtu);
10279 else
10280 mtu = 0;
10281 data_list[bundle_at++] = chk;
10282 if (one_chunk && (asoc->total_flight <= 0)) {
10283 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_windowprobed);
10284 }
10285 }
10286 if (one_chunk == 0) {
10287 /*
10288 * now are there anymore forward from chk to pick
10289 * up?
10290 */
10291 for (fwd = TAILQ_NEXT(chk, sctp_next); fwd != NULL; fwd = TAILQ_NEXT(fwd, sctp_next)) {
10292 if (fwd->sent != SCTP_DATAGRAM_RESEND) {
10293 /* Nope, not for retran */
10294 continue;
10295 }
10296 if (fwd->whoTo != net) {
10297 /* Nope, not the net in question */
10298 continue;
10299 }
10300 if (data_auth_reqd && (auth == NULL)) {
10301 dmtu = sctp_get_auth_chunk_len(stcb->asoc.peer_hmac_id);
10302 } else
10303 dmtu = 0;
10304 if (fwd->send_size <= (mtu - dmtu)) {
10305 if (data_auth_reqd) {
10306 if (auth == NULL) {
10307 m = sctp_add_auth_chunk(m,
10308 &endofchain,
10309 &auth,
10310 &auth_offset,
10311 stcb,
10312 SCTP_DATA);
10313 auth_keyid = fwd->auth_keyid;
10314 override_ok = 0;
10315 SCTP_STAT_INCR_COUNTER64(sctps_outcontrolchunks);
10316 } else if (override_ok) {
10317 auth_keyid = fwd->auth_keyid;
10318 override_ok = 0;
10319 } else if (fwd->auth_keyid != auth_keyid) {
10320 /* different keyid, so done bundling */
10321 break;
10322 }
10323 }
10324 m = sctp_copy_mbufchain(fwd->data, m, &endofchain, 0, fwd->send_size, fwd->copy_by_ref);
10325 if (m == NULL) {
10326 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, stcb, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, ENOMEM);
10327 return (ENOMEM);
10328 }
10329 /* Do clear IP_DF ? */
10330 if (fwd->flags & CHUNK_FLAGS_FRAGMENT_OK) {
10331 no_fragmentflg = 0;
10332 }
10333 /* upate our MTU size */
10334 if (mtu > (fwd->send_size + dmtu))
10335 mtu -= (fwd->send_size + dmtu);
10336 else
10337 mtu = 0;
10338 data_list[bundle_at++] = fwd;
10339 if (bundle_at >= SCTP_MAX_DATA_BUNDLING) {
10340 break;
10341 }
10342 } else {
10343 /* can't fit so we are done */
10344 break;
10345 }
10346 }
10347 }
10348 /* Is there something to send for this destination? */
10349 if (m) {
10350 /*
10351 * No matter if we fail/or succeed we should start a
10352 * timer. A failure is like a lost IP packet :-)
10353 */
10354 if (!SCTP_OS_TIMER_PENDING(&net->rxt_timer.timer)) {
10355 /*
10356 * no timer running on this destination
10357 * restart it.
10358 */
10359 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_SEND, inp, stcb, net);
10360 tmr_started = 1;
10361 }
10362 /* Now lets send it, if there is anything to send :> */
10363 if ((error = sctp_lowlevel_chunk_output(inp, stcb, net,
10364 (struct sockaddr *)&net->ro._l_addr, m,
10365 auth_offset, auth, auth_keyid,
10366 no_fragmentflg, 0, 0,
10367 inp->sctp_lport, stcb->rport, htonl(stcb->asoc.peer_vtag),
10368 net->port, NULL,
10369#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
10370 0, 0,
10371#endif
10372 so_locked))) {
10373 /* error, we could not output */
10374 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT3, "Gak send error %d\n", error);
10375 if (error == ENOBUFS) {
10376 asoc->ifp_had_enobuf = 1;
10377 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_lowlevelerr);
10378 }
10379 return (error);
10380 } else {
10381 asoc->ifp_had_enobuf = 0;
10382 }
10383 endofchain = NULL;
10384 auth = NULL;
10385 auth_offset = 0;
10386 /* For HB's */
10387 /*
10388 * We don't want to mark the net->sent time here
10389 * since this we use this for HB and retrans cannot
10390 * measure RTT
10391 */
10392 /* (void)SCTP_GETTIME_TIMEVAL(&net->last_sent_time); */
10393
10394 /* For auto-close */
10395 cnt_thru++;
10396 if (*now_filled == 0) {
10397 (void)SCTP_GETTIME_TIMEVAL(&asoc->time_last_sent);
10398 *now = asoc->time_last_sent;
10399 *now_filled = 1;
10400 } else {
10401 asoc->time_last_sent = *now;
10402 }
10403 *cnt_out += bundle_at;
10404#ifdef SCTP_AUDITING_ENABLED
10405 sctp_audit_log(0xC4, bundle_at);
10406#endif
10407 if (bundle_at) {
10408 tsns_sent = data_list[0]->rec.data.tsn;
10409 }
10410 for (i = 0; i < bundle_at; i++) {
10411 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_sendretransdata);
10412 data_list[i]->sent = SCTP_DATAGRAM_SENT;
10413 /*
10414 * When we have a revoked data, and we
10415 * retransmit it, then we clear the revoked
10416 * flag since this flag dictates if we
10417 * subtracted from the fs
10418 */
10419 if (data_list[i]->rec.data.chunk_was_revoked) {
10420 /* Deflate the cwnd */
10421 data_list[i]->whoTo->cwnd -= data_list[i]->book_size;
10422 data_list[i]->rec.data.chunk_was_revoked = 0;
10423 }
10424 data_list[i]->snd_count++;
10425 sctp_ucount_decr(asoc->sent_queue_retran_cnt);
10426 /* record the time */
10427 data_list[i]->sent_rcv_time = asoc->time_last_sent;
10428 if (data_list[i]->book_size_scale) {
10429 /*
10430 * need to double the book size on
10431 * this one
10432 */
10433 data_list[i]->book_size_scale = 0;
10434 /* Since we double the booksize, we must
10435 * also double the output queue size, since this
10436 * get shrunk when we free by this amount.
10437 */
10438 atomic_add_int(&((asoc)->total_output_queue_size),data_list[i]->book_size);
10439 data_list[i]->book_size *= 2;
10440 } else {
10441 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_LOG_RWND_ENABLE) {
10442 sctp_log_rwnd(SCTP_DECREASE_PEER_RWND,
10443 asoc->peers_rwnd, data_list[i]->send_size, SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_peer_chunk_oh));
10444 }
10445 asoc->peers_rwnd = sctp_sbspace_sub(asoc->peers_rwnd,
10446 (uint32_t) (data_list[i]->send_size +
10447 SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_peer_chunk_oh)));
10448 }
10449 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_FLIGHT_LOGGING_ENABLE) {
10450 sctp_misc_ints(SCTP_FLIGHT_LOG_UP_RSND,
10451 data_list[i]->whoTo->flight_size,
10452 data_list[i]->book_size,
10453 (uint32_t)(uintptr_t)data_list[i]->whoTo,
10454 data_list[i]->rec.data.tsn);
10455 }
10456 sctp_flight_size_increase(data_list[i]);
10457 sctp_total_flight_increase(stcb, data_list[i]);
10458 if (asoc->peers_rwnd < stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_ep.sctp_sws_sender) {
10459 /* SWS sender side engages */
10460 asoc->peers_rwnd = 0;
10461 }
10462 if ((i == 0) &&
10463 (data_list[i]->rec.data.doing_fast_retransmit)) {
10464 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_sendfastretrans);
10465 if ((data_list[i] == TAILQ_FIRST(&asoc->sent_queue)) &&
10466 (tmr_started == 0)) {
10467 /*-
10468 * ok we just fast-retrans'd
10469 * the lowest TSN, i.e the
10470 * first on the list. In
10471 * this case we want to give
10472 * some more time to get a
10473 * SACK back without a
10474 * t3-expiring.
10475 */
10476 sctp_timer_stop(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_SEND, inp, stcb, net,
10477 SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT + SCTP_LOC_2);
10478 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_SEND, inp, stcb, net);
10479 }
10480 }
10481 }
10482 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_CWND_LOGGING_ENABLE) {
10483 sctp_log_cwnd(stcb, net, tsns_sent, SCTP_CWND_LOG_FROM_RESEND);
10484 }
10485#ifdef SCTP_AUDITING_ENABLED
10486 sctp_auditing(21, inp, stcb, NULL);
10487#endif
10488 } else {
10489 /* None will fit */
10490 return (1);
10491 }
10492 if (asoc->sent_queue_retran_cnt <= 0) {
10493 /* all done we have no more to retran */
10494 asoc->sent_queue_retran_cnt = 0;
10495 break;
10496 }
10497 if (one_chunk) {
10498 /* No more room in rwnd */
10499 return (1);
10500 }
10501 /* stop the for loop here. we sent out a packet */
10502 break;
10503 }
10504 return (0);
10505}
10506
10507static void
10508sctp_timer_validation(struct sctp_inpcb *inp,
10509 struct sctp_tcb *stcb,
10510 struct sctp_association *asoc)
10511{
10512 struct sctp_nets *net;
10513
10514 /* Validate that a timer is running somewhere */
10515 TAILQ_FOREACH(net, &asoc->nets, sctp_next) {
10516 if (SCTP_OS_TIMER_PENDING(&net->rxt_timer.timer)) {
10517 /* Here is a timer */
10518 return;
10519 }
10520 }
10521 SCTP_TCB_LOCK_ASSERT(stcb);
10522 /* Gak, we did not have a timer somewhere */
10523 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT3, "Deadlock avoided starting timer on a dest at retran\n");
10524 if (asoc->alternate) {
10525 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_SEND, inp, stcb, asoc->alternate);
10526 } else {
10527 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_SEND, inp, stcb, asoc->primary_destination);
10528 }
10529 return;
10530}
10531
10532void
10533sctp_chunk_output(struct sctp_inpcb *inp,
10534 struct sctp_tcb *stcb,
10535 int from_where,
10536 int so_locked)
10537{
10538 /*-
10539 * Ok this is the generic chunk service queue. we must do the
10540 * following:
10541 * - See if there are retransmits pending, if so we must
10542 * do these first.
10543 * - Service the stream queue that is next, moving any
10544 * message (note I must get a complete message i.e.
10545 * FIRST/MIDDLE and LAST to the out queue in one pass) and assigning
10546 * TSN's
10547 * - Check to see if the cwnd/rwnd allows any output, if so we
10548 * go ahead and fomulate and send the low level chunks. Making sure
10549 * to combine any control in the control chunk queue also.
10550 */
10551 struct sctp_association *asoc;
10552 struct sctp_nets *net;
10553 int error = 0, num_out, tot_out = 0, ret = 0, reason_code;
10554 unsigned int burst_cnt = 0;
10555 struct timeval now;
10556 int now_filled = 0;
10557 int nagle_on;
10558 int frag_point = sctp_get_frag_point(stcb, &stcb->asoc);
10559 int un_sent = 0;
10560 int fr_done;
10561 unsigned int tot_frs = 0;
10562
10563#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
10564 if (so_locked) {
10565 sctp_lock_assert(SCTP_INP_SO(inp));
10566 } else {
10567 sctp_unlock_assert(SCTP_INP_SO(inp));
10568 }
10569#endif
10570 asoc = &stcb->asoc;
10571do_it_again:
10572 /* The Nagle algorithm is only applied when handling a send call. */
10573 if (from_where == SCTP_OUTPUT_FROM_USR_SEND) {
10574 if (sctp_is_feature_on(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_NODELAY)) {
10575 nagle_on = 0;
10576 } else {
10577 nagle_on = 1;
10578 }
10579 } else {
10580 nagle_on = 0;
10581 }
10582 SCTP_TCB_LOCK_ASSERT(stcb);
10583
10584 un_sent = (stcb->asoc.total_output_queue_size - stcb->asoc.total_flight);
10585
10586 if ((un_sent <= 0) &&
10587 (TAILQ_EMPTY(&asoc->control_send_queue)) &&
10588 (TAILQ_EMPTY(&asoc->asconf_send_queue)) &&
10589 (asoc->sent_queue_retran_cnt == 0) &&
10590 (asoc->trigger_reset == 0)) {
10591 /* Nothing to do unless there is something to be sent left */
10592 return;
10593 }
10594 /* Do we have something to send, data or control AND
10595 * a sack timer running, if so piggy-back the sack.
10596 */
10597 if (SCTP_OS_TIMER_PENDING(&stcb->asoc.dack_timer.timer)) {
10598 sctp_send_sack(stcb, so_locked);
10599 sctp_timer_stop(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_RECV, stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, NULL,
10600 SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT + SCTP_LOC_3);
10601 }
10602 while (asoc->sent_queue_retran_cnt) {
10603 /*-
10604 * Ok, it is retransmission time only, we send out only ONE
10605 * packet with a single call off to the retran code.
10606 */
10607 if (from_where == SCTP_OUTPUT_FROM_COOKIE_ACK) {
10608 /*-
10609 * Special hook for handling cookiess discarded
10610 * by peer that carried data. Send cookie-ack only
10611 * and then the next call with get the retran's.
10612 */
10613 (void)sctp_med_chunk_output(inp, stcb, asoc, &num_out, &reason_code, 1,
10614 from_where,
10615 &now, &now_filled, frag_point, so_locked);
10616 return;
10617 } else if (from_where != SCTP_OUTPUT_FROM_HB_TMR) {
10618 /* if its not from a HB then do it */
10619 fr_done = 0;
10620 ret = sctp_chunk_retransmission(inp, stcb, asoc, &num_out, &now, &now_filled, &fr_done, so_locked);
10621 if (fr_done) {
10622 tot_frs++;
10623 }
10624 } else {
10625 /*
10626 * its from any other place, we don't allow retran
10627 * output (only control)
10628 */
10629 ret = 1;
10630 }
10631 if (ret > 0) {
10632 /* Can't send anymore */
10633 /*-
10634 * now lets push out control by calling med-level
10635 * output once. this assures that we WILL send HB's
10636 * if queued too.
10637 */
10638 (void)sctp_med_chunk_output(inp, stcb, asoc, &num_out, &reason_code, 1,
10639 from_where,
10640 &now, &now_filled, frag_point, so_locked);
10641#ifdef SCTP_AUDITING_ENABLED
10642 sctp_auditing(8, inp, stcb, NULL);
10643#endif
10644 sctp_timer_validation(inp, stcb, asoc);
10645 return;
10646 }
10647 if (ret < 0) {
10648 /*-
10649 * The count was off.. retran is not happening so do
10650 * the normal retransmission.
10651 */
10652#ifdef SCTP_AUDITING_ENABLED
10653 sctp_auditing(9, inp, stcb, NULL);
10654#endif
10655 if (ret == SCTP_RETRAN_EXIT) {
10656 return;
10657 }
10658 break;
10659 }
10660 if (from_where == SCTP_OUTPUT_FROM_T3) {
10661 /* Only one transmission allowed out of a timeout */
10662#ifdef SCTP_AUDITING_ENABLED
10663 sctp_auditing(10, inp, stcb, NULL);
10664#endif
10665 /* Push out any control */
10666 (void)sctp_med_chunk_output(inp, stcb, asoc, &num_out, &reason_code, 1, from_where,
10667 &now, &now_filled, frag_point, so_locked);
10668 return;
10669 }
10670 if ((asoc->fr_max_burst > 0) && (tot_frs >= asoc->fr_max_burst)) {
10671 /* Hit FR burst limit */
10672 return;
10673 }
10674 if ((num_out == 0) && (ret == 0)) {
10675 /* No more retrans to send */
10676 break;
10677 }
10678 }
10679#ifdef SCTP_AUDITING_ENABLED
10680 sctp_auditing(12, inp, stcb, NULL);
10681#endif
10682 /* Check for bad destinations, if they exist move chunks around. */
10683 TAILQ_FOREACH(net, &asoc->nets, sctp_next) {
10684 if (!(net->dest_state & SCTP_ADDR_REACHABLE)) {
10685 /*-
10686 * if possible move things off of this address we
10687 * still may send below due to the dormant state but
10688 * we try to find an alternate address to send to
10689 * and if we have one we move all queued data on the
10690 * out wheel to this alternate address.
10691 */
10692 if (net->ref_count > 1)
10693 sctp_move_chunks_from_net(stcb, net);
10694 } else {
10695 /*-
10696 * if ((asoc->sat_network) || (net->addr_is_local))
10697 * { burst_limit = asoc->max_burst *
10698 * SCTP_SAT_NETWORK_BURST_INCR; }
10699 */
10700 if (asoc->max_burst > 0) {
10701 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_use_cwnd_based_maxburst)) {
10702 if ((net->flight_size + (asoc->max_burst * net->mtu)) < net->cwnd) {
10703 /* JRS - Use the congestion control given in the congestion control module */
10704 asoc->cc_functions.sctp_cwnd_update_after_output(stcb, net, asoc->max_burst);
10705 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_LOG_MAXBURST_ENABLE) {
10706 sctp_log_maxburst(stcb, net, 0, asoc->max_burst, SCTP_MAX_BURST_APPLIED);
10707 }
10708 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_maxburstqueued);
10709 }
10710 net->fast_retran_ip = 0;
10711 } else {
10712 if (net->flight_size == 0) {
10713 /* Should be decaying the cwnd here */
10714 ;
10715 }
10716 }
10717 }
10718 }
10719 }
10720 burst_cnt = 0;
10721 do {
10722 error = sctp_med_chunk_output(inp, stcb, asoc, &num_out,
10723 &reason_code, 0, from_where,
10724 &now, &now_filled, frag_point, so_locked);
10725 if (error) {
10726 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT1, "Error %d was returned from med-c-op\n", error);
10727 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_LOG_MAXBURST_ENABLE) {
10728 sctp_log_maxburst(stcb, asoc->primary_destination, error, burst_cnt, SCTP_MAX_BURST_ERROR_STOP);
10729 }
10730 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_CWND_LOGGING_ENABLE) {
10731 sctp_log_cwnd(stcb, NULL, error, SCTP_SEND_NOW_COMPLETES);
10732 sctp_log_cwnd(stcb, NULL, 0xdeadbeef, SCTP_SEND_NOW_COMPLETES);
10733 }
10734 break;
10735 }
10736 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT3, "m-c-o put out %d\n", num_out);
10737
10738 tot_out += num_out;
10739 burst_cnt++;
10740 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_CWND_LOGGING_ENABLE) {
10741 sctp_log_cwnd(stcb, NULL, num_out, SCTP_SEND_NOW_COMPLETES);
10742 if (num_out == 0) {
10743 sctp_log_cwnd(stcb, NULL, reason_code, SCTP_SEND_NOW_COMPLETES);
10744 }
10745 }
10746 if (nagle_on) {
10747 /*
10748 * When the Nagle algorithm is used, look at how much
10749 * is unsent, then if its smaller than an MTU and we
10750 * have data in flight we stop, except if we are
10751 * handling a fragmented user message.
10752 */
10753 un_sent = stcb->asoc.total_output_queue_size - stcb->asoc.total_flight;
10754 if ((un_sent < (int)(stcb->asoc.smallest_mtu - SCTP_MIN_OVERHEAD)) &&
10755 (stcb->asoc.total_flight > 0)) {
10756/* && sctp_is_feature_on(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_EXPLICIT_EOR))) {*/
10757 break;
10758 }
10759 }
10760 if (TAILQ_EMPTY(&asoc->control_send_queue) &&
10761 TAILQ_EMPTY(&asoc->send_queue) &&
10762 sctp_is_there_unsent_data(stcb, so_locked) == 0) {
10763 /* Nothing left to send */
10764 break;
10765 }
10766 if ((stcb->asoc.total_output_queue_size - stcb->asoc.total_flight) <= 0) {
10767 /* Nothing left to send */
10768 break;
10769 }
10770 } while (num_out &&
10771 ((asoc->max_burst == 0) ||
10772 SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_use_cwnd_based_maxburst) ||
10773 (burst_cnt < asoc->max_burst)));
10774
10775 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_use_cwnd_based_maxburst) == 0) {
10776 if ((asoc->max_burst > 0) && (burst_cnt >= asoc->max_burst)) {
10777 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_maxburstqueued);
10778 asoc->burst_limit_applied = 1;
10779 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_LOG_MAXBURST_ENABLE) {
10780 sctp_log_maxburst(stcb, asoc->primary_destination, 0, burst_cnt, SCTP_MAX_BURST_APPLIED);
10781 }
10782 } else {
10783 asoc->burst_limit_applied = 0;
10784 }
10785 }
10786 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_CWND_LOGGING_ENABLE) {
10787 sctp_log_cwnd(stcb, NULL, tot_out, SCTP_SEND_NOW_COMPLETES);
10788 }
10789 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT1, "Ok, we have put out %d chunks\n",
10790 tot_out);
10791
10792 /*-
10793 * Now we need to clean up the control chunk chain if a ECNE is on
10794 * it. It must be marked as UNSENT again so next call will continue
10795 * to send it until such time that we get a CWR, to remove it.
10796 */
10797 if (stcb->asoc.ecn_echo_cnt_onq)
10798 sctp_fix_ecn_echo(asoc);
10799
10800 if (stcb->asoc.trigger_reset) {
10801 if (sctp_send_stream_reset_out_if_possible(stcb, so_locked) == 0) {
10802 goto do_it_again;
10803 }
10804 }
10805 return;
10806}
10807
10808int
10809sctp_output(
10810 struct sctp_inpcb *inp,
10811 struct mbuf *m,
10812 struct sockaddr *addr,
10813 struct mbuf *control,
10814#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
10815 struct thread *p,
10816#elif defined(_WIN32) && !defined(__Userspace__)
10817 PKTHREAD p,
10818#else
10819#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
10820 struct proc *p SCTP_UNUSED,
10821#else
10822 struct proc *p,
10823#endif
10824#endif
10825 int flags)
10826{
10827 if (inp == NULL) {
10828 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET_PKT(m, inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, EINVAL);
10829 return (EINVAL);
10830 }
10831
10832 if (inp->sctp_socket == NULL) {
10833 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET_PKT(m, inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, EINVAL);
10834 return (EINVAL);
10835 }
10836 return (sctp_sosend(inp->sctp_socket,
10837 addr,
10838 (struct uio *)NULL,
10839 m,
10840 control,
10841#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
10842 flags
10843#else
10844 flags, p
10845#endif
10846 ));
10847}
10848
10849void
10850send_forward_tsn(struct sctp_tcb *stcb,
10851 struct sctp_association *asoc)
10852{
10853 struct sctp_tmit_chunk *chk, *at, *tp1, *last;
10854 struct sctp_forward_tsn_chunk *fwdtsn;
10855 struct sctp_strseq *strseq;
10856 struct sctp_strseq_mid *strseq_m;
10857 uint32_t advance_peer_ack_point;
10858 unsigned int cnt_of_space, i, ovh;
10859 unsigned int space_needed;
10860 unsigned int cnt_of_skipped = 0;
10861
10862 SCTP_TCB_LOCK_ASSERT(stcb);
10863 TAILQ_FOREACH(chk, &asoc->control_send_queue, sctp_next) {
10864 if (chk->rec.chunk_id.id == SCTP_FORWARD_CUM_TSN) {
10865 /* mark it to unsent */
10866 chk->sent = SCTP_DATAGRAM_UNSENT;
10867 chk->snd_count = 0;
10868 /* Do we correct its output location? */
10869 if (chk->whoTo) {
10870 sctp_free_remote_addr(chk->whoTo);
10871 chk->whoTo = NULL;
10872 }
10873 goto sctp_fill_in_rest;
10874 }
10875 }
10876 /* Ok if we reach here we must build one */
10877 sctp_alloc_a_chunk(stcb, chk);
10878 if (chk == NULL) {
10879 return;
10880 }
10881 asoc->fwd_tsn_cnt++;
10882 chk->copy_by_ref = 0;
10883 /*
10884 * We don't do the old thing here since
10885 * this is used not for on-wire but to
10886 * tell if we are sending a fwd-tsn by
10887 * the stack during output. And if its
10888 * a IFORWARD or a FORWARD it is a fwd-tsn.
10889 */
10890 chk->rec.chunk_id.id = SCTP_FORWARD_CUM_TSN;
10891 chk->rec.chunk_id.can_take_data = 0;
10892 chk->flags = 0;
10893 chk->asoc = asoc;
10894 chk->whoTo = NULL;
10895 chk->data = sctp_get_mbuf_for_msg(MCLBYTES, 0, M_NOWAIT, 1, MT_DATA);
10896 if (chk->data == NULL) {
10897 sctp_free_a_chunk(stcb, chk, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
10898 return;
10899 }
10900 SCTP_BUF_RESV_UF(chk->data, SCTP_MIN_OVERHEAD);
10901 chk->sent = SCTP_DATAGRAM_UNSENT;
10902 chk->snd_count = 0;
10903 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&asoc->control_send_queue, chk, sctp_next);
10904 asoc->ctrl_queue_cnt++;
10905sctp_fill_in_rest:
10906 /*-
10907 * Here we go through and fill out the part that deals with
10908 * stream/seq of the ones we skip.
10909 */
10910 SCTP_BUF_LEN(chk->data) = 0;
10911 TAILQ_FOREACH(at, &asoc->sent_queue, sctp_next) {
10912 if ((at->sent != SCTP_FORWARD_TSN_SKIP) &&
10913 (at->sent != SCTP_DATAGRAM_NR_ACKED)) {
10914 /* no more to look at */
10915 break;
10916 }
10917 if (!asoc->idata_supported && (at->rec.data.rcv_flags & SCTP_DATA_UNORDERED)) {
10918 /* We don't report these */
10919 continue;
10920 }
10921 cnt_of_skipped++;
10922 }
10923 if (asoc->idata_supported) {
10924 space_needed = (sizeof(struct sctp_forward_tsn_chunk) +
10925 (cnt_of_skipped * sizeof(struct sctp_strseq_mid)));
10926 } else {
10927 space_needed = (sizeof(struct sctp_forward_tsn_chunk) +
10928 (cnt_of_skipped * sizeof(struct sctp_strseq)));
10929 }
10930 cnt_of_space = (unsigned int)M_TRAILINGSPACE(chk->data);
10931
10932 if (stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_BOUND_V6) {
10933 ovh = SCTP_MIN_OVERHEAD;
10934 } else {
10935 ovh = SCTP_MIN_V4_OVERHEAD;
10936 }
10937 if (cnt_of_space > (asoc->smallest_mtu - ovh)) {
10938 /* trim to a mtu size */
10939 cnt_of_space = asoc->smallest_mtu - ovh;
10940 }
10941 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_LOG_TRY_ADVANCE) {
10942 sctp_misc_ints(SCTP_FWD_TSN_CHECK,
10943 0xff, 0, cnt_of_skipped,
10944 asoc->advanced_peer_ack_point);
10945 }
10946 advance_peer_ack_point = asoc->advanced_peer_ack_point;
10947 if (cnt_of_space < space_needed) {
10948 /*-
10949 * ok we must trim down the chunk by lowering the
10950 * advance peer ack point.
10951 */
10952 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_LOG_TRY_ADVANCE) {
10953 sctp_misc_ints(SCTP_FWD_TSN_CHECK,
10954 0xff, 0xff, cnt_of_space,
10955 space_needed);
10956 }
10957 cnt_of_skipped = cnt_of_space - sizeof(struct sctp_forward_tsn_chunk);
10958 if (asoc->idata_supported) {
10959 cnt_of_skipped /= sizeof(struct sctp_strseq_mid);
10960 } else {
10961 cnt_of_skipped /= sizeof(struct sctp_strseq);
10962 }
10963 /*-
10964 * Go through and find the TSN that will be the one
10965 * we report.
10966 */
10967 at = TAILQ_FIRST(&asoc->sent_queue);
10968 if (at != NULL) {
10969 for (i = 0; i < cnt_of_skipped; i++) {
10970 tp1 = TAILQ_NEXT(at, sctp_next);
10971 if (tp1 == NULL) {
10972 break;
10973 }
10974 at = tp1;
10975 }
10976 }
10977 if (at && SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_LOG_TRY_ADVANCE) {
10978 sctp_misc_ints(SCTP_FWD_TSN_CHECK,
10979 0xff, cnt_of_skipped, at->rec.data.tsn,
10980 asoc->advanced_peer_ack_point);
10981 }
10982 last = at;
10983 /*-
10984 * last now points to last one I can report, update
10985 * peer ack point
10986 */
10987 if (last) {
10988 advance_peer_ack_point = last->rec.data.tsn;
10989 }
10990 if (asoc->idata_supported) {
10991 space_needed = sizeof(struct sctp_forward_tsn_chunk) +
10992 cnt_of_skipped * sizeof(struct sctp_strseq_mid);
10993 } else {
10994 space_needed = sizeof(struct sctp_forward_tsn_chunk) +
10995 cnt_of_skipped * sizeof(struct sctp_strseq);
10996 }
10997 }
10998 chk->send_size = space_needed;
10999 /* Setup the chunk */
11000 fwdtsn = mtod(chk->data, struct sctp_forward_tsn_chunk *);
11001 fwdtsn->ch.chunk_length = htons(chk->send_size);
11002 fwdtsn->ch.chunk_flags = 0;
11003 if (asoc->idata_supported) {
11004 fwdtsn->ch.chunk_type = SCTP_IFORWARD_CUM_TSN;
11005 } else {
11006 fwdtsn->ch.chunk_type = SCTP_FORWARD_CUM_TSN;
11007 }
11008 fwdtsn->new_cumulative_tsn = htonl(advance_peer_ack_point);
11009 SCTP_BUF_LEN(chk->data) = chk->send_size;
11010 fwdtsn++;
11011 /*-
11012 * Move pointer to after the fwdtsn and transfer to the
11013 * strseq pointer.
11014 */
11015 if (asoc->idata_supported) {
11016 strseq_m = (struct sctp_strseq_mid *)fwdtsn;
11017 strseq = NULL;
11018 } else {
11019 strseq = (struct sctp_strseq *)fwdtsn;
11020 strseq_m = NULL;
11021 }
11022 /*-
11023 * Now populate the strseq list. This is done blindly
11024 * without pulling out duplicate stream info. This is
11025 * inefficent but won't harm the process since the peer will
11026 * look at these in sequence and will thus release anything.
11027 * It could mean we exceed the PMTU and chop off some that
11028 * we could have included.. but this is unlikely (aka 1432/4
11029 * would mean 300+ stream seq's would have to be reported in
11030 * one FWD-TSN. With a bit of work we can later FIX this to
11031 * optimize and pull out duplicates.. but it does add more
11032 * overhead. So for now... not!
11033 */
11034 i = 0;
11035 TAILQ_FOREACH(at, &asoc->sent_queue, sctp_next) {
11036 if (i >= cnt_of_skipped) {
11037 break;
11038 }
11039 if (!asoc->idata_supported && (at->rec.data.rcv_flags & SCTP_DATA_UNORDERED)) {
11040 /* We don't report these */
11041 continue;
11042 }
11043 if (at->rec.data.tsn == advance_peer_ack_point) {
11044 at->rec.data.fwd_tsn_cnt = 0;
11045 }
11046 if (asoc->idata_supported) {
11047 strseq_m->sid = htons(at->rec.data.sid);
11048 if (at->rec.data.rcv_flags & SCTP_DATA_UNORDERED) {
11049 strseq_m->flags = htons(PR_SCTP_UNORDERED_FLAG);
11050 } else {
11051 strseq_m->flags = 0;
11052 }
11053 strseq_m->mid = htonl(at->rec.data.mid);
11054 strseq_m++;
11055 } else {
11056 strseq->sid = htons(at->rec.data.sid);
11057 strseq->ssn = htons((uint16_t)at->rec.data.mid);
11058 strseq++;
11059 }
11060 i++;
11061 }
11062 return;
11063}
11064
11065void
11066sctp_send_sack(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, int so_locked)
11067{
11068 /*-
11069 * Queue up a SACK or NR-SACK in the control queue.
11070 * We must first check to see if a SACK or NR-SACK is
11071 * somehow on the control queue.
11072 * If so, we will take and and remove the old one.
11073 */
11074 struct sctp_association *asoc;
11075 struct sctp_tmit_chunk *chk, *a_chk;
11076 struct sctp_sack_chunk *sack;
11077 struct sctp_nr_sack_chunk *nr_sack;
11078 struct sctp_gap_ack_block *gap_descriptor;
11079 const struct sack_track *selector;
11080 int mergeable = 0;
11081 int offset;
11082 caddr_t limit;
11083 uint32_t *dup;
11084 int limit_reached = 0;
11085 unsigned int i, siz, j;
11086 unsigned int num_gap_blocks = 0, num_nr_gap_blocks = 0, space;
11087 int num_dups = 0;
11088 int space_req;
11089 uint32_t highest_tsn;
11090 uint8_t flags;
11091 uint8_t type;
11092 uint8_t tsn_map;
11093
11094 if (stcb->asoc.nrsack_supported == 1) {
11095 type = SCTP_NR_SELECTIVE_ACK;
11096 } else {
11097 type = SCTP_SELECTIVE_ACK;
11098 }
11099 a_chk = NULL;
11100 asoc = &stcb->asoc;
11101 SCTP_TCB_LOCK_ASSERT(stcb);
11102 if (asoc->last_data_chunk_from == NULL) {
11103 /* Hmm we never received anything */
11104 return;
11105 }
11106 sctp_slide_mapping_arrays(stcb);
11107 sctp_set_rwnd(stcb, asoc);
11108 TAILQ_FOREACH(chk, &asoc->control_send_queue, sctp_next) {
11109 if (chk->rec.chunk_id.id == type) {
11110 /* Hmm, found a sack already on queue, remove it */
11111 TAILQ_REMOVE(&asoc->control_send_queue, chk, sctp_next);
11112 asoc->ctrl_queue_cnt--;
11113 a_chk = chk;
11114 if (a_chk->data) {
11115 sctp_m_freem(a_chk->data);
11116 a_chk->data = NULL;
11117 }
11118 if (a_chk->whoTo) {
11119 sctp_free_remote_addr(a_chk->whoTo);
11120 a_chk->whoTo = NULL;
11121 }
11122 break;
11123 }
11124 }
11125 if (a_chk == NULL) {
11126 sctp_alloc_a_chunk(stcb, a_chk);
11127 if (a_chk == NULL) {
11128 /* No memory so we drop the idea, and set a timer */
11129 if (stcb->asoc.delayed_ack) {
11130 sctp_timer_stop(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_RECV,
11131 stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, NULL,
11132 SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT + SCTP_LOC_4);
11133 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_RECV,
11134 stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, NULL);
11135 } else {
11136 stcb->asoc.send_sack = 1;
11137 }
11138 return;
11139 }
11140 a_chk->copy_by_ref = 0;
11141 a_chk->rec.chunk_id.id = type;
11142 a_chk->rec.chunk_id.can_take_data = 1;
11143 }
11144 /* Clear our pkt counts */
11145 asoc->data_pkts_seen = 0;
11146
11147 a_chk->flags = 0;
11148 a_chk->asoc = asoc;
11149 a_chk->snd_count = 0;
11150 a_chk->send_size = 0; /* fill in later */
11151 a_chk->sent = SCTP_DATAGRAM_UNSENT;
11152 a_chk->whoTo = NULL;
11153
11154 if (!(asoc->last_data_chunk_from->dest_state & SCTP_ADDR_REACHABLE)) {
11155 /*-
11156 * Ok, the destination for the SACK is unreachable, lets see if
11157 * we can select an alternate to asoc->last_data_chunk_from
11158 */
11159 a_chk->whoTo = sctp_find_alternate_net(stcb, asoc->last_data_chunk_from, 0);
11160 if (a_chk->whoTo == NULL) {
11161 /* Nope, no alternate */
11162 a_chk->whoTo = asoc->last_data_chunk_from;
11163 }
11164 } else {
11165 a_chk->whoTo = asoc->last_data_chunk_from;
11166 }
11167 if (a_chk->whoTo) {
11168 atomic_add_int(&a_chk->whoTo->ref_count, 1);
11169 }
11170 if (SCTP_TSN_GT(asoc->highest_tsn_inside_map, asoc->highest_tsn_inside_nr_map)) {
11171 highest_tsn = asoc->highest_tsn_inside_map;
11172 } else {
11173 highest_tsn = asoc->highest_tsn_inside_nr_map;
11174 }
11175 if (highest_tsn == asoc->cumulative_tsn) {
11176 /* no gaps */
11177 if (type == SCTP_SELECTIVE_ACK) {
11178 space_req = sizeof(struct sctp_sack_chunk);
11179 } else {
11180 space_req = sizeof(struct sctp_nr_sack_chunk);
11181 }
11182 } else {
11183 /* gaps get a cluster */
11184 space_req = MCLBYTES;
11185 }
11186 /* Ok now lets formulate a MBUF with our sack */
11187 a_chk->data = sctp_get_mbuf_for_msg(space_req, 0, M_NOWAIT, 1, MT_DATA);
11188 if ((a_chk->data == NULL) ||
11189 (a_chk->whoTo == NULL)) {
11190 /* rats, no mbuf memory */
11191 if (a_chk->data) {
11192 /* was a problem with the destination */
11193 sctp_m_freem(a_chk->data);
11194 a_chk->data = NULL;
11195 }
11196 sctp_free_a_chunk(stcb, a_chk, so_locked);
11197 /* sa_ignore NO_NULL_CHK */
11198 if (stcb->asoc.delayed_ack) {
11199 sctp_timer_stop(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_RECV,
11200 stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, NULL,
11201 SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT + SCTP_LOC_5);
11202 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_RECV,
11203 stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, NULL);
11204 } else {
11205 stcb->asoc.send_sack = 1;
11206 }
11207 return;
11208 }
11209 /* ok, lets go through and fill it in */
11210 SCTP_BUF_RESV_UF(a_chk->data, SCTP_MIN_OVERHEAD);
11211 space = (unsigned int)M_TRAILINGSPACE(a_chk->data);
11212 if (space > (a_chk->whoTo->mtu - SCTP_MIN_OVERHEAD)) {
11213 space = (a_chk->whoTo->mtu - SCTP_MIN_OVERHEAD);
11214 }
11215 limit = mtod(a_chk->data, caddr_t);
11216 limit += space;
11217
11218 flags = 0;
11219
11220 if ((asoc->sctp_cmt_on_off > 0) &&
11221 SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_cmt_use_dac)) {
11222 /*-
11223 * CMT DAC algorithm: If 2 (i.e., 0x10) packets have been
11224 * received, then set high bit to 1, else 0. Reset
11225 * pkts_rcvd.
11226 */
11227 flags |= (asoc->cmt_dac_pkts_rcvd << 6);
11228 asoc->cmt_dac_pkts_rcvd = 0;
11229 }
11230#ifdef SCTP_ASOCLOG_OF_TSNS
11231 stcb->asoc.cumack_logsnt[stcb->asoc.cumack_log_atsnt] = asoc->cumulative_tsn;
11232 stcb->asoc.cumack_log_atsnt++;
11233 if (stcb->asoc.cumack_log_atsnt >= SCTP_TSN_LOG_SIZE) {
11234 stcb->asoc.cumack_log_atsnt = 0;
11235 }
11236#endif
11237 /* reset the readers interpretation */
11238 stcb->freed_by_sorcv_sincelast = 0;
11239
11240 if (type == SCTP_SELECTIVE_ACK) {
11241 sack = mtod(a_chk->data, struct sctp_sack_chunk *);
11242 nr_sack = NULL;
11243 gap_descriptor = (struct sctp_gap_ack_block *)((caddr_t)sack + sizeof(struct sctp_sack_chunk));
11244 if (highest_tsn > asoc->mapping_array_base_tsn) {
11245 siz = (((highest_tsn - asoc->mapping_array_base_tsn) + 1) + 7) / 8;
11246 } else {
11247 siz = (((MAX_TSN - asoc->mapping_array_base_tsn) + 1) + highest_tsn + 7) / 8;
11248 }
11249 } else {
11250 sack = NULL;
11251 nr_sack = mtod(a_chk->data, struct sctp_nr_sack_chunk *);
11252 gap_descriptor = (struct sctp_gap_ack_block *)((caddr_t)nr_sack + sizeof(struct sctp_nr_sack_chunk));
11253 if (asoc->highest_tsn_inside_map > asoc->mapping_array_base_tsn) {
11254 siz = (((asoc->highest_tsn_inside_map - asoc->mapping_array_base_tsn) + 1) + 7) / 8;
11255 } else {
11256 siz = (((MAX_TSN - asoc->mapping_array_base_tsn) + 1) + asoc->highest_tsn_inside_map + 7) / 8;
11257 }
11258 }
11259
11260 if (SCTP_TSN_GT(asoc->mapping_array_base_tsn, asoc->cumulative_tsn)) {
11261 offset = 1;
11262 } else {
11263 offset = asoc->mapping_array_base_tsn - asoc->cumulative_tsn;
11264 }
11265 if (((type == SCTP_SELECTIVE_ACK) &&
11266 SCTP_TSN_GT(highest_tsn, asoc->cumulative_tsn)) ||
11267 ((type == SCTP_NR_SELECTIVE_ACK) &&
11268 SCTP_TSN_GT(asoc->highest_tsn_inside_map, asoc->cumulative_tsn))) {
11269 /* we have a gap .. maybe */
11270 for (i = 0; i < siz; i++) {
11271 tsn_map = asoc->mapping_array[i];
11272 if (type == SCTP_SELECTIVE_ACK) {
11273 tsn_map |= asoc->nr_mapping_array[i];
11274 }
11275 if (i == 0) {
11276 /*
11277 * Clear all bits corresponding to TSNs
11278 * smaller or equal to the cumulative TSN.
11279 */
11280 tsn_map &= (~0U << (1 - offset));
11281 }
11282 selector = &sack_array[tsn_map];
11283 if (mergeable && selector->right_edge) {
11284 /*
11285 * Backup, left and right edges were ok to
11286 * merge.
11287 */
11288 num_gap_blocks--;
11289 gap_descriptor--;
11290 }
11291 if (selector->num_entries == 0)
11292 mergeable = 0;
11293 else {
11294 for (j = 0; j < selector->num_entries; j++) {
11295 if (mergeable && selector->right_edge) {
11296 /*
11297 * do a merge by NOT setting
11298 * the left side
11299 */
11300 mergeable = 0;
11301 } else {
11302 /*
11303 * no merge, set the left
11304 * side
11305 */
11306 mergeable = 0;
11307 gap_descriptor->start = htons((selector->gaps[j].start + offset));
11308 }
11309 gap_descriptor->end = htons((selector->gaps[j].end + offset));
11310 num_gap_blocks++;
11311 gap_descriptor++;
11312 if (((caddr_t)gap_descriptor + sizeof(struct sctp_gap_ack_block)) > limit) {
11313 /* no more room */
11314 limit_reached = 1;
11315 break;
11316 }
11317 }
11318 if (selector->left_edge) {
11319 mergeable = 1;
11320 }
11321 }
11322 if (limit_reached) {
11323 /* Reached the limit stop */
11324 break;
11325 }
11326 offset += 8;
11327 }
11328 }
11329 if ((type == SCTP_NR_SELECTIVE_ACK) &&
11330 (limit_reached == 0)) {
11331 mergeable = 0;
11332
11333 if (asoc->highest_tsn_inside_nr_map > asoc->mapping_array_base_tsn) {
11334 siz = (((asoc->highest_tsn_inside_nr_map - asoc->mapping_array_base_tsn) + 1) + 7) / 8;
11335 } else {
11336 siz = (((MAX_TSN - asoc->mapping_array_base_tsn) + 1) + asoc->highest_tsn_inside_nr_map + 7) / 8;
11337 }
11338
11339 if (SCTP_TSN_GT(asoc->mapping_array_base_tsn, asoc->cumulative_tsn)) {
11340 offset = 1;
11341 } else {
11342 offset = asoc->mapping_array_base_tsn - asoc->cumulative_tsn;
11343 }
11344 if (SCTP_TSN_GT(asoc->highest_tsn_inside_nr_map, asoc->cumulative_tsn)) {
11345 /* we have a gap .. maybe */
11346 for (i = 0; i < siz; i++) {
11347 tsn_map = asoc->nr_mapping_array[i];
11348 if (i == 0) {
11349 /*
11350 * Clear all bits corresponding to TSNs
11351 * smaller or equal to the cumulative TSN.
11352 */
11353 tsn_map &= (~0U << (1 - offset));
11354 }
11355 selector = &sack_array[tsn_map];
11356 if (mergeable && selector->right_edge) {
11357 /*
11358 * Backup, left and right edges were ok to
11359 * merge.
11360 */
11361 num_nr_gap_blocks--;
11362 gap_descriptor--;
11363 }
11364 if (selector->num_entries == 0)
11365 mergeable = 0;
11366 else {
11367 for (j = 0; j < selector->num_entries; j++) {
11368 if (mergeable && selector->right_edge) {
11369 /*
11370 * do a merge by NOT setting
11371 * the left side
11372 */
11373 mergeable = 0;
11374 } else {
11375 /*
11376 * no merge, set the left
11377 * side
11378 */
11379 mergeable = 0;
11380 gap_descriptor->start = htons((selector->gaps[j].start + offset));
11381 }
11382 gap_descriptor->end = htons((selector->gaps[j].end + offset));
11383 num_nr_gap_blocks++;
11384 gap_descriptor++;
11385 if (((caddr_t)gap_descriptor + sizeof(struct sctp_gap_ack_block)) > limit) {
11386 /* no more room */
11387 limit_reached = 1;
11388 break;
11389 }
11390 }
11391 if (selector->left_edge) {
11392 mergeable = 1;
11393 }
11394 }
11395 if (limit_reached) {
11396 /* Reached the limit stop */
11397 break;
11398 }
11399 offset += 8;
11400 }
11401 }
11402 }
11403 /* now we must add any dups we are going to report. */
11404 if ((limit_reached == 0) && (asoc->numduptsns)) {
11405 dup = (uint32_t *) gap_descriptor;
11406 for (i = 0; i < asoc->numduptsns; i++) {
11407 *dup = htonl(asoc->dup_tsns[i]);
11408 dup++;
11409 num_dups++;
11410 if (((caddr_t)dup + sizeof(uint32_t)) > limit) {
11411 /* no more room */
11412 break;
11413 }
11414 }
11415 asoc->numduptsns = 0;
11416 }
11417 /*
11418 * now that the chunk is prepared queue it to the control chunk
11419 * queue.
11420 */
11421 if (type == SCTP_SELECTIVE_ACK) {
11422 a_chk->send_size = (uint16_t)(sizeof(struct sctp_sack_chunk) +
11423 (num_gap_blocks + num_nr_gap_blocks) * sizeof(struct sctp_gap_ack_block) +
11424 num_dups * sizeof(int32_t));
11425 SCTP_BUF_LEN(a_chk->data) = a_chk->send_size;
11426 sack->sack.cum_tsn_ack = htonl(asoc->cumulative_tsn);
11427 sack->sack.a_rwnd = htonl(asoc->my_rwnd);
11428 sack->sack.num_gap_ack_blks = htons(num_gap_blocks);
11429 sack->sack.num_dup_tsns = htons(num_dups);
11430 sack->ch.chunk_type = type;
11431 sack->ch.chunk_flags = flags;
11432 sack->ch.chunk_length = htons(a_chk->send_size);
11433 } else {
11434 a_chk->send_size = (uint16_t)(sizeof(struct sctp_nr_sack_chunk) +
11435 (num_gap_blocks + num_nr_gap_blocks) * sizeof(struct sctp_gap_ack_block) +
11436 num_dups * sizeof(int32_t));
11437 SCTP_BUF_LEN(a_chk->data) = a_chk->send_size;
11438 nr_sack->nr_sack.cum_tsn_ack = htonl(asoc->cumulative_tsn);
11439 nr_sack->nr_sack.a_rwnd = htonl(asoc->my_rwnd);
11440 nr_sack->nr_sack.num_gap_ack_blks = htons(num_gap_blocks);
11441 nr_sack->nr_sack.num_nr_gap_ack_blks = htons(num_nr_gap_blocks);
11442 nr_sack->nr_sack.num_dup_tsns = htons(num_dups);
11443 nr_sack->nr_sack.reserved = 0;
11444 nr_sack->ch.chunk_type = type;
11445 nr_sack->ch.chunk_flags = flags;
11446 nr_sack->ch.chunk_length = htons(a_chk->send_size);
11447 }
11448 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&asoc->control_send_queue, a_chk, sctp_next);
11449 asoc->my_last_reported_rwnd = asoc->my_rwnd;
11450 asoc->ctrl_queue_cnt++;
11451 asoc->send_sack = 0;
11452 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_sendsacks);
11453 return;
11454}
11455
11456void
11457sctp_send_abort_tcb(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct mbuf *operr, int so_locked)
11458{
11459 struct mbuf *m_abort, *m, *m_last;
11460 struct mbuf *m_out, *m_end = NULL;
11461 struct sctp_abort_chunk *abort;
11462 struct sctp_auth_chunk *auth = NULL;
11463 struct sctp_nets *net;
11464 uint32_t vtag;
11465 uint32_t auth_offset = 0;
11466 int error;
11467 uint16_t cause_len, chunk_len, padding_len;
11468
11469#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
11470 if (so_locked) {
11471 sctp_lock_assert(SCTP_INP_SO(stcb->sctp_ep));
11472 } else {
11473 sctp_unlock_assert(SCTP_INP_SO(stcb->sctp_ep));
11474 }
11475#endif
11476 SCTP_TCB_LOCK_ASSERT(stcb);
11477 /*-
11478 * Add an AUTH chunk, if chunk requires it and save the offset into
11479 * the chain for AUTH
11480 */
11481 if (sctp_auth_is_required_chunk(SCTP_ABORT_ASSOCIATION,
11482 stcb->asoc.peer_auth_chunks)) {
11483 m_out = sctp_add_auth_chunk(NULL, &m_end, &auth, &auth_offset,
11484 stcb, SCTP_ABORT_ASSOCIATION);
11485 SCTP_STAT_INCR_COUNTER64(sctps_outcontrolchunks);
11486 } else {
11487 m_out = NULL;
11488 }
11489 m_abort = sctp_get_mbuf_for_msg(sizeof(struct sctp_abort_chunk), 0, M_NOWAIT, 1, MT_HEADER);
11490 if (m_abort == NULL) {
11491 if (m_out) {
11492 sctp_m_freem(m_out);
11493 }
11494 if (operr) {
11495 sctp_m_freem(operr);
11496 }
11497 return;
11498 }
11499 /* link in any error */
11500 SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m_abort) = operr;
11501 cause_len = 0;
11502 m_last = NULL;
11503 for (m = operr; m; m = SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m)) {
11504 cause_len += (uint16_t)SCTP_BUF_LEN(m);
11505 if (SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m) == NULL) {
11506 m_last = m;
11507 }
11508 }
11509 SCTP_BUF_LEN(m_abort) = sizeof(struct sctp_abort_chunk);
11510 chunk_len = (uint16_t)sizeof(struct sctp_abort_chunk) + cause_len;
11511 padding_len = SCTP_SIZE32(chunk_len) - chunk_len;
11512 if (m_out == NULL) {
11513 /* NO Auth chunk prepended, so reserve space in front */
11514 SCTP_BUF_RESV_UF(m_abort, SCTP_MIN_OVERHEAD);
11515 m_out = m_abort;
11516 } else {
11517 /* Put AUTH chunk at the front of the chain */
11518 SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m_end) = m_abort;
11519 }
11520 if (stcb->asoc.alternate) {
11521 net = stcb->asoc.alternate;
11522 } else {
11523 net = stcb->asoc.primary_destination;
11524 }
11525 /* Fill in the ABORT chunk header. */
11526 abort = mtod(m_abort, struct sctp_abort_chunk *);
11527 abort->ch.chunk_type = SCTP_ABORT_ASSOCIATION;
11528 if (stcb->asoc.peer_vtag == 0) {
11529 /* This happens iff the assoc is in COOKIE-WAIT state. */
11530 vtag = stcb->asoc.my_vtag;
11531 abort->ch.chunk_flags = SCTP_HAD_NO_TCB;
11532 } else {
11533 vtag = stcb->asoc.peer_vtag;
11534 abort->ch.chunk_flags = 0;
11535 }
11536 abort->ch.chunk_length = htons(chunk_len);
11537 /* Add padding, if necessary. */
11538 if (padding_len > 0) {
11539 if ((m_last == NULL) ||
11540 (sctp_add_pad_tombuf(m_last, padding_len) == NULL)) {
11541 sctp_m_freem(m_out);
11542 return;
11543 }
11544 }
11545 if ((error = sctp_lowlevel_chunk_output(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, net,
11546 (struct sockaddr *)&net->ro._l_addr,
11547 m_out, auth_offset, auth, stcb->asoc.authinfo.active_keyid, 1, 0, 0,
11548 stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_lport, stcb->rport, htonl(vtag),
11549 stcb->asoc.primary_destination->port, NULL,
11550#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
11551 0, 0,
11552#endif
11553 so_locked))) {
11554 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT3, "Gak send error %d\n", error);
11555 if (error == ENOBUFS) {
11556 stcb->asoc.ifp_had_enobuf = 1;
11557 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_lowlevelerr);
11558 }
11559 } else {
11560 stcb->asoc.ifp_had_enobuf = 0;
11561 }
11562 SCTP_STAT_INCR_COUNTER64(sctps_outcontrolchunks);
11563}
11564
11565void
11566sctp_send_shutdown_complete(struct sctp_tcb *stcb,
11567 struct sctp_nets *net,
11568 int reflect_vtag)
11569{
11570 /* formulate and SEND a SHUTDOWN-COMPLETE */
11571 struct mbuf *m_shutdown_comp;
11572 struct sctp_shutdown_complete_chunk *shutdown_complete;
11573 uint32_t vtag;
11574 int error;
11575 uint8_t flags;
11576
11577 m_shutdown_comp = sctp_get_mbuf_for_msg(sizeof(struct sctp_chunkhdr), 0, M_NOWAIT, 1, MT_HEADER);
11578 if (m_shutdown_comp == NULL) {
11579 /* no mbuf's */
11580 return;
11581 }
11582 if (reflect_vtag) {
11583 flags = SCTP_HAD_NO_TCB;
11584 vtag = stcb->asoc.my_vtag;
11585 } else {
11586 flags = 0;
11587 vtag = stcb->asoc.peer_vtag;
11588 }
11589 shutdown_complete = mtod(m_shutdown_comp, struct sctp_shutdown_complete_chunk *);
11590 shutdown_complete->ch.chunk_type = SCTP_SHUTDOWN_COMPLETE;
11591 shutdown_complete->ch.chunk_flags = flags;
11592 shutdown_complete->ch.chunk_length = htons(sizeof(struct sctp_shutdown_complete_chunk));
11593 SCTP_BUF_LEN(m_shutdown_comp) = sizeof(struct sctp_shutdown_complete_chunk);
11594 if ((error = sctp_lowlevel_chunk_output(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, net,
11595 (struct sockaddr *)&net->ro._l_addr,
11596 m_shutdown_comp, 0, NULL, 0, 1, 0, 0,
11597 stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_lport, stcb->rport,
11598 htonl(vtag),
11599 net->port, NULL,
11600#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
11601 0, 0,
11602#endif
11603 SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED))) {
11604 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT3, "Gak send error %d\n", error);
11605 if (error == ENOBUFS) {
11606 stcb->asoc.ifp_had_enobuf = 1;
11607 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_lowlevelerr);
11608 }
11609 } else {
11610 stcb->asoc.ifp_had_enobuf = 0;
11611 }
11612 SCTP_STAT_INCR_COUNTER64(sctps_outcontrolchunks);
11613 return;
11614}
11615
11616#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
11617static void
11618sctp_send_resp_msg(struct sockaddr *src, struct sockaddr *dst,
11619 struct sctphdr *sh, uint32_t vtag,
11620 uint8_t type, struct mbuf *cause,
11621 uint8_t mflowtype, uint32_t mflowid, uint16_t fibnum,
11622 uint32_t vrf_id, uint16_t port)
11623#else
11624static void
11625sctp_send_resp_msg(struct sockaddr *src, struct sockaddr *dst,
11626 struct sctphdr *sh, uint32_t vtag,
11627 uint8_t type, struct mbuf *cause,
11628 uint32_t vrf_id SCTP_UNUSED, uint16_t port)
11629#endif
11630{
11631 struct mbuf *o_pak;
11632 struct mbuf *mout;
11633 struct sctphdr *shout;
11634 struct sctp_chunkhdr *ch;
11635#if defined(INET) || defined(INET6)
11636 struct udphdr *udp;
11637#endif
11638 int ret, len, cause_len, padding_len;
11639#ifdef INET
11640#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
11641 sctp_route_t ro;
11642#endif
11643 struct sockaddr_in *src_sin, *dst_sin;
11644 struct ip *ip;
11645#endif
11646#ifdef INET6
11647 struct sockaddr_in6 *src_sin6, *dst_sin6;
11648 struct ip6_hdr *ip6;
11649#endif
11650
11651 /* Compute the length of the cause and add final padding. */
11652 cause_len = 0;
11653 if (cause != NULL) {
11654 struct mbuf *m_at, *m_last = NULL;
11655
11656 for (m_at = cause; m_at; m_at = SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m_at)) {
11657 if (SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m_at) == NULL)
11658 m_last = m_at;
11659 cause_len += SCTP_BUF_LEN(m_at);
11660 }
11661 padding_len = cause_len % 4;
11662 if (padding_len != 0) {
11663 padding_len = 4 - padding_len;
11664 }
11665 if (padding_len != 0) {
11666 if (sctp_add_pad_tombuf(m_last, padding_len) == NULL) {
11667 sctp_m_freem(cause);
11668 return;
11669 }
11670 }
11671 } else {
11672 padding_len = 0;
11673 }
11674 /* Get an mbuf for the header. */
11675 len = sizeof(struct sctphdr) + sizeof(struct sctp_chunkhdr);
11676 switch (dst->sa_family) {
11677#ifdef INET
11678 case AF_INET:
11679 len += sizeof(struct ip);
11680 break;
11681#endif
11682#ifdef INET6
11683 case AF_INET6:
11684 len += sizeof(struct ip6_hdr);
11685 break;
11686#endif
11687 default:
11688 break;
11689 }
11690#if defined(INET) || defined(INET6)
11691 if (port) {
11692 len += sizeof(struct udphdr);
11693 }
11694#endif
11695#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
11696#if defined(APPLE_LEOPARD) || defined(APPLE_SNOWLEOPARD)
11697 mout = sctp_get_mbuf_for_msg(len + max_linkhdr, 1, M_NOWAIT, 1, MT_DATA);
11698#else
11699 mout = sctp_get_mbuf_for_msg(len + SCTP_MAX_LINKHDR, 1, M_NOWAIT, 1, MT_DATA);
11700#endif
11701#else
11702 mout = sctp_get_mbuf_for_msg(len + max_linkhdr, 1, M_NOWAIT, 1, MT_DATA);
11703#endif
11704 if (mout == NULL) {
11705 if (cause) {
11706 sctp_m_freem(cause);
11707 }
11708 return;
11709 }
11710#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
11711#if defined(APPLE_LEOPARD) || defined(APPLE_SNOWLEOPARD)
11712 SCTP_BUF_RESV_UF(mout, max_linkhdr);
11713#else
11714 SCTP_BUF_RESV_UF(mout, SCTP_MAX_LINKHDR);
11715#endif
11716#else
11717 SCTP_BUF_RESV_UF(mout, max_linkhdr);
11718#endif
11719 SCTP_BUF_LEN(mout) = len;
11720 SCTP_BUF_NEXT(mout) = cause;
11721#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
11722 M_SETFIB(mout, fibnum);
11723 mout->m_pkthdr.flowid = mflowid;
11724 M_HASHTYPE_SET(mout, mflowtype);
11725#endif
11726#ifdef INET
11727 ip = NULL;
11728#endif
11729#ifdef INET6
11730 ip6 = NULL;
11731#endif
11732 switch (dst->sa_family) {
11733#ifdef INET
11734 case AF_INET:
11735 src_sin = (struct sockaddr_in *)src;
11736 dst_sin = (struct sockaddr_in *)dst;
11737 ip = mtod(mout, struct ip *);
11738 ip->ip_v = IPVERSION;
11739 ip->ip_hl = (sizeof(struct ip) >> 2);
11740 ip->ip_tos = 0;
11741#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
11742 ip->ip_off = htons(IP_DF);
11743#elif defined(WITH_CONVERT_IP_OFF) || defined(__APPLE__)
11744 ip->ip_off = IP_DF;
11745#else
11746 ip->ip_off = htons(IP_DF);
11747#endif
11748#if defined(__Userspace__)
11749 ip->ip_id = htons(ip_id++);
11750#elif defined(__FreeBSD__)
11751 ip_fillid(ip);
11752#elif defined(__APPLE__)
11753#if RANDOM_IP_ID
11754 ip->ip_id = ip_randomid();
11755#else
11756 ip->ip_id = htons(ip_id++);
11757#endif
11758#else
11759 ip->ip_id = ip_id++;
11760#endif
11761 ip->ip_ttl = MODULE_GLOBAL(ip_defttl);
11762 if (port) {
11763 ip->ip_p = IPPROTO_UDP;
11764 } else {
11765 ip->ip_p = IPPROTO_SCTP;
11766 }
11767 ip->ip_src.s_addr = dst_sin->sin_addr.s_addr;
11768 ip->ip_dst.s_addr = src_sin->sin_addr.s_addr;
11769 ip->ip_sum = 0;
11770 len = sizeof(struct ip);
11771 shout = (struct sctphdr *)((caddr_t)ip + len);
11772 break;
11773#endif
11774#ifdef INET6
11775 case AF_INET6:
11776 src_sin6 = (struct sockaddr_in6 *)src;
11777 dst_sin6 = (struct sockaddr_in6 *)dst;
11778 ip6 = mtod(mout, struct ip6_hdr *);
11779 ip6->ip6_flow = htonl(0x60000000);
11780#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
11781 if (V_ip6_auto_flowlabel) {
11782 ip6->ip6_flow |= (htonl(ip6_randomflowlabel()) & IPV6_FLOWLABEL_MASK);
11783 }
11784#endif
11785#if defined(__Userspace__)
11786 ip6->ip6_hlim = IPv6_HOP_LIMIT;
11787#else
11788 ip6->ip6_hlim = MODULE_GLOBAL(ip6_defhlim);
11789#endif
11790 if (port) {
11791 ip6->ip6_nxt = IPPROTO_UDP;
11792 } else {
11793 ip6->ip6_nxt = IPPROTO_SCTP;
11794 }
11795 ip6->ip6_src = dst_sin6->sin6_addr;
11796 ip6->ip6_dst = src_sin6->sin6_addr;
11797 len = sizeof(struct ip6_hdr);
11798 shout = (struct sctphdr *)((caddr_t)ip6 + len);
11799 break;
11800#endif
11801 default:
11802 len = 0;
11803 shout = mtod(mout, struct sctphdr *);
11804 break;
11805 }
11806#if defined(INET) || defined(INET6)
11807 if (port) {
11808 if (htons(SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_udp_tunneling_port)) == 0) {
11809 sctp_m_freem(mout);
11810 return;
11811 }
11812 udp = (struct udphdr *)shout;
11813 udp->uh_sport = htons(SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_udp_tunneling_port));
11814 udp->uh_dport = port;
11815 udp->uh_sum = 0;
11816 udp->uh_ulen = htons((uint16_t)(sizeof(struct udphdr) +
11817 sizeof(struct sctphdr) +
11818 sizeof(struct sctp_chunkhdr) +
11819 cause_len + padding_len));
11820 len += sizeof(struct udphdr);
11821 shout = (struct sctphdr *)((caddr_t)shout + sizeof(struct udphdr));
11822 } else {
11823 udp = NULL;
11824 }
11825#endif
11826 shout->src_port = sh->dest_port;
11827 shout->dest_port = sh->src_port;
11828 shout->checksum = 0;
11829 if (vtag) {
11830 shout->v_tag = htonl(vtag);
11831 } else {
11832 shout->v_tag = sh->v_tag;
11833 }
11834 len += sizeof(struct sctphdr);
11835 ch = (struct sctp_chunkhdr *)((caddr_t)shout + sizeof(struct sctphdr));
11836 ch->chunk_type = type;
11837 if (vtag) {
11838 ch->chunk_flags = 0;
11839 } else {
11840 ch->chunk_flags = SCTP_HAD_NO_TCB;
11841 }
11842 ch->chunk_length = htons((uint16_t)(sizeof(struct sctp_chunkhdr) + cause_len));
11843 len += sizeof(struct sctp_chunkhdr);
11844 len += cause_len + padding_len;
11845
11846 if (SCTP_GET_HEADER_FOR_OUTPUT(o_pak)) {
11847 sctp_m_freem(mout);
11848 return;
11849 }
11850 SCTP_ATTACH_CHAIN(o_pak, mout, len);
11851 switch (dst->sa_family) {
11852#ifdef INET
11853 case AF_INET:
11854#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
11855 /* zap the stack pointer to the route */
11856 memset(&ro, 0, sizeof(sctp_route_t));
11857#endif
11858 if (port) {
11859#if !defined(_WIN32) && !defined(__Userspace__)
11860#if defined(__FreeBSD__)
11861 if (V_udp_cksum) {
11862 udp->uh_sum = in_pseudo(ip->ip_src.s_addr, ip->ip_dst.s_addr, udp->uh_ulen + htons(IPPROTO_UDP));
11863 } else {
11864 udp->uh_sum = 0;
11865 }
11866#else
11867 udp->uh_sum = in_pseudo(ip->ip_src.s_addr, ip->ip_dst.s_addr, udp->uh_ulen + htons(IPPROTO_UDP));
11868#endif
11869#else
11870 udp->uh_sum = 0;
11871#endif
11872 }
11873#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
11874 ip->ip_len = htons(len);
11875#elif defined(__APPLE__) || defined(__Userspace__)
11876 ip->ip_len = len;
11877#else
11878 ip->ip_len = htons(len);
11879#endif
11880 if (port) {
11881 shout->checksum = sctp_calculate_cksum(mout, sizeof(struct ip) + sizeof(struct udphdr));
11882 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_sendswcrc);
11883#if !defined(_WIN32) && !defined(__Userspace__)
11884#if defined(__FreeBSD__)
11885 if (V_udp_cksum) {
11886 SCTP_ENABLE_UDP_CSUM(o_pak);
11887 }
11888#else
11889 SCTP_ENABLE_UDP_CSUM(o_pak);
11890#endif
11891#endif
11892 } else {
11893#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
11894 mout->m_pkthdr.csum_flags = CSUM_SCTP;
11895 mout->m_pkthdr.csum_data = offsetof(struct sctphdr, checksum);
11896 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_sendhwcrc);
11897#else
11898 shout->checksum = sctp_calculate_cksum(mout, sizeof(struct ip));
11899 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_sendswcrc);
11900#endif
11901 }
11902#ifdef SCTP_PACKET_LOGGING
11903 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_LAST_PACKET_TRACING) {
11904 sctp_packet_log(o_pak);
11905 }
11906#endif
11907#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
11908 SCTP_IP_OUTPUT(ret, o_pak, &ro, NULL, vrf_id);
11909 /* Free the route if we got one back */
11910 if (ro.ro_rt) {
11911 RTFREE(ro.ro_rt);
11912 ro.ro_rt = NULL;
11913 }
11914#else
11915#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
11916 SCTP_PROBE5(send, NULL, NULL, ip, NULL, shout);
11917#endif
11918 SCTP_IP_OUTPUT(ret, o_pak, NULL, NULL, vrf_id);
11919#endif
11920 break;
11921#endif
11922#ifdef INET6
11923 case AF_INET6:
11924 ip6->ip6_plen = htons((uint16_t)(len - sizeof(struct ip6_hdr)));
11925 if (port) {
11926 shout->checksum = sctp_calculate_cksum(mout, sizeof(struct ip6_hdr) + sizeof(struct udphdr));
11927 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_sendswcrc);
11928#if !defined(__Userspace__)
11929#if defined(_WIN32)
11930 udp->uh_sum = 0;
11931#else
11932 if ((udp->uh_sum = in6_cksum(o_pak, IPPROTO_UDP, sizeof(struct ip6_hdr), len - sizeof(struct ip6_hdr))) == 0) {
11933 udp->uh_sum = 0xffff;
11934 }
11935#endif
11936#endif
11937 } else {
11938#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
11939 mout->m_pkthdr.csum_flags = CSUM_SCTP_IPV6;
11940 mout->m_pkthdr.csum_data = offsetof(struct sctphdr, checksum);
11941 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_sendhwcrc);
11942#else
11943 shout->checksum = sctp_calculate_cksum(mout, sizeof(struct ip6_hdr));
11944 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_sendswcrc);
11945#endif
11946 }
11947#ifdef SCTP_PACKET_LOGGING
11948 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_LAST_PACKET_TRACING) {
11949 sctp_packet_log(o_pak);
11950 }
11951#endif
11952#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
11953 SCTP_PROBE5(send, NULL, NULL, ip6, NULL, shout);
11954#endif
11955 SCTP_IP6_OUTPUT(ret, o_pak, NULL, NULL, NULL, vrf_id);
11956 break;
11957#endif
11958#if defined(__Userspace__)
11959 case AF_CONN:
11960 {
11961 char *buffer;
11962 struct sockaddr_conn *sconn;
11963
11964 sconn = (struct sockaddr_conn *)src;
11965 if (SCTP_BASE_VAR(crc32c_offloaded) == 0) {
11966 shout->checksum = sctp_calculate_cksum(mout, 0);
11967 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_sendswcrc);
11968 } else {
11969 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_sendhwcrc);
11970 }
11971#ifdef SCTP_PACKET_LOGGING
11972 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_LAST_PACKET_TRACING) {
11973 sctp_packet_log(mout);
11974 }
11975#endif
11976 /* Don't alloc/free for each packet */
11977 if ((buffer = malloc(len)) != NULL) {
11978 m_copydata(mout, 0, len, buffer);
11979 ret = SCTP_BASE_VAR(conn_output)(sconn->sconn_addr, buffer, len, 0, 0);
11980 free(buffer);
11981 } else {
11982 ret = ENOMEM;
11983 }
11984 sctp_m_freem(mout);
11985 break;
11986 }
11987#endif
11988 default:
11989 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT1, "Unknown protocol (TSNH) type %d\n",
11990 dst->sa_family);
11991 sctp_m_freem(mout);
11992 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET_PKT(mout, NULL, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, EFAULT);
11993 return;
11994 }
11995 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT3, "return from send is %d\n", ret);
11996#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
11997 if (port) {
11998 UDPSTAT_INC(udps_opackets);
11999 }
12000#endif
12001 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_sendpackets);
12002 SCTP_STAT_INCR_COUNTER64(sctps_outpackets);
12003 SCTP_STAT_INCR_COUNTER64(sctps_outcontrolchunks);
12004 if (ret) {
12005 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_senderrors);
12006 }
12007 return;
12008}
12009
12010void
12011sctp_send_shutdown_complete2(struct sockaddr *src, struct sockaddr *dst,
12012 struct sctphdr *sh,
12013#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
12014 uint8_t mflowtype, uint32_t mflowid, uint16_t fibnum,
12015#endif
12016 uint32_t vrf_id, uint16_t port)
12017{
12018 sctp_send_resp_msg(src, dst, sh, 0, SCTP_SHUTDOWN_COMPLETE, NULL,
12019#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
12020 mflowtype, mflowid, fibnum,
12021#endif
12022 vrf_id, port);
12023}
12024
12025void
12026sctp_send_hb(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sctp_nets *net,int so_locked)
12027{
12028 struct sctp_tmit_chunk *chk;
12029 struct sctp_heartbeat_chunk *hb;
12030 struct timeval now;
12031
12032 SCTP_TCB_LOCK_ASSERT(stcb);
12033 if (net == NULL) {
12034 return;
12035 }
12036 (void)SCTP_GETTIME_TIMEVAL(&now);
12037 switch (net->ro._l_addr.sa.sa_family) {
12038#ifdef INET
12039 case AF_INET:
12040 break;
12041#endif
12042#ifdef INET6
12043 case AF_INET6:
12044 break;
12045#endif
12046#if defined(__Userspace__)
12047 case AF_CONN:
12048 break;
12049#endif
12050 default:
12051 return;
12052 }
12053 sctp_alloc_a_chunk(stcb, chk);
12054 if (chk == NULL) {
12055 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT4, "Gak, can't get a chunk for hb\n");
12056 return;
12057 }
12058
12059 chk->copy_by_ref = 0;
12060 chk->rec.chunk_id.id = SCTP_HEARTBEAT_REQUEST;
