12061 chk->rec.chunk_id.can_take_data = 1;
12062 chk->flags = 0;
12063 chk->asoc = &stcb->asoc;
12064 chk->send_size = sizeof(struct sctp_heartbeat_chunk);
12065
12066 chk->data = sctp_get_mbuf_for_msg(chk->send_size, 0, M_NOWAIT, 1, MT_HEADER);
12067 if (chk->data == NULL) {
12068 sctp_free_a_chunk(stcb, chk, so_locked);
12069 return;
12070 }
12071 SCTP_BUF_RESV_UF(chk->data, SCTP_MIN_OVERHEAD);
12072 SCTP_BUF_LEN(chk->data) = chk->send_size;
12073 chk->sent = SCTP_DATAGRAM_UNSENT;
12074 chk->snd_count = 0;
12075 chk->whoTo = net;
12076 atomic_add_int(&chk->whoTo->ref_count, 1);
12077 /* Now we have a mbuf that we can fill in with the details */
12078 hb = mtod(chk->data, struct sctp_heartbeat_chunk *);
12079 memset(hb, 0, sizeof(struct sctp_heartbeat_chunk));
12080 /* fill out chunk header */
12081 hb->ch.chunk_type = SCTP_HEARTBEAT_REQUEST;
12082 hb->ch.chunk_flags = 0;
12083 hb->ch.chunk_length = htons(chk->send_size);
12084 /* Fill out hb parameter */
12085 hb->heartbeat.hb_info.ph.param_type = htons(SCTP_HEARTBEAT_INFO);
12086 hb->heartbeat.hb_info.ph.param_length = htons(sizeof(struct sctp_heartbeat_info_param));
12087 hb->heartbeat.hb_info.time_value_1 = now.tv_sec;
12088 hb->heartbeat.hb_info.time_value_2 = now.tv_usec;
12089 /* Did our user request this one, put it in */
12090 hb->heartbeat.hb_info.addr_family = (uint8_t)net->ro._l_addr.sa.sa_family;
12091#ifdef HAVE_SA_LEN
12092 hb->heartbeat.hb_info.addr_len = net->ro._l_addr.sa.sa_len;
12093#else
12094 switch (net->ro._l_addr.sa.sa_family) {
12095#ifdef INET
12096 case AF_INET:
12097 hb->heartbeat.hb_info.addr_len = sizeof(struct sockaddr_in);
12098 break;
12099#endif
12100#ifdef INET6
12101 case AF_INET6:
12102 hb->heartbeat.hb_info.addr_len = sizeof(struct sockaddr_in6);
12103 break;
12104#endif
12105#if defined(__Userspace__)
12106 case AF_CONN:
12107 hb->heartbeat.hb_info.addr_len = sizeof(struct sockaddr_conn);
12108 break;
12109#endif
12110 default:
12111 hb->heartbeat.hb_info.addr_len = 0;
12112 break;
12113 }
12114#endif
12115 if (net->dest_state & SCTP_ADDR_UNCONFIRMED) {
12116 /*
12117 * we only take from the entropy pool if the address is not
12118 * confirmed.
12119 */
12120 net->heartbeat_random1 = hb->heartbeat.hb_info.random_value1 = sctp_select_initial_TSN(&stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_ep);
12121 net->heartbeat_random2 = hb->heartbeat.hb_info.random_value2 = sctp_select_initial_TSN(&stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_ep);
12122 } else {
12123 net->heartbeat_random1 = hb->heartbeat.hb_info.random_value1 = 0;
12124 net->heartbeat_random2 = hb->heartbeat.hb_info.random_value2 = 0;
12125 }
12126 switch (net->ro._l_addr.sa.sa_family) {
12127#ifdef INET
12128 case AF_INET:
12129 memcpy(hb->heartbeat.hb_info.address,
12130 &net->ro._l_addr.sin.sin_addr,
12131 sizeof(net->ro._l_addr.sin.sin_addr));
12132 break;
12133#endif
12134#ifdef INET6
12135 case AF_INET6:
12136 memcpy(hb->heartbeat.hb_info.address,
12137 &net->ro._l_addr.sin6.sin6_addr,
12138 sizeof(net->ro._l_addr.sin6.sin6_addr));
12139 break;
12140#endif
12141#if defined(__Userspace__)
12142 case AF_CONN:
12143 memcpy(hb->heartbeat.hb_info.address,
12144 &net->ro._l_addr.sconn.sconn_addr,
12145 sizeof(net->ro._l_addr.sconn.sconn_addr));
12146 break;
12147#endif
12148 default:
12149 if (chk->data) {
12150 sctp_m_freem(chk->data);
12151 chk->data = NULL;
12152 }
12153 sctp_free_a_chunk(stcb, chk, so_locked);
12154 return;
12155 break;
12156 }
12157 net->hb_responded = 0;
12158 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&stcb->asoc.control_send_queue, chk, sctp_next);
12159 stcb->asoc.ctrl_queue_cnt++;
12160 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_sendheartbeat);
12161 return;
12162}
12163
12164void
12165sctp_send_ecn_echo(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sctp_nets *net,
12166 uint32_t high_tsn)
12167{
12168 struct sctp_association *asoc;
12169 struct sctp_ecne_chunk *ecne;
12170 struct sctp_tmit_chunk *chk;
12171
12172 if (net == NULL) {
12173 return;
12174 }
12175 asoc = &stcb->asoc;
12176 SCTP_TCB_LOCK_ASSERT(stcb);
12177 TAILQ_FOREACH(chk, &asoc->control_send_queue, sctp_next) {
12178 if ((chk->rec.chunk_id.id == SCTP_ECN_ECHO) && (net == chk->whoTo)) {
12179 /* found a previous ECN_ECHO update it if needed */
12180 uint32_t cnt, ctsn;
12181 ecne = mtod(chk->data, struct sctp_ecne_chunk *);
12182 ctsn = ntohl(ecne->tsn);
12183 if (SCTP_TSN_GT(high_tsn, ctsn)) {
12184 ecne->tsn = htonl(high_tsn);
12185 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_queue_upd_ecne);
12186 }
12187 cnt = ntohl(ecne->num_pkts_since_cwr);
12188 cnt++;
12189 ecne->num_pkts_since_cwr = htonl(cnt);
12190 return;
12191 }
12192 }
12193 /* nope could not find one to update so we must build one */
12194 sctp_alloc_a_chunk(stcb, chk);
12195 if (chk == NULL) {
12196 return;
12197 }
12198 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_queue_upd_ecne);
12199 chk->copy_by_ref = 0;
12200 chk->rec.chunk_id.id = SCTP_ECN_ECHO;
12201 chk->rec.chunk_id.can_take_data = 0;
12202 chk->flags = 0;
12203 chk->asoc = &stcb->asoc;
12204 chk->send_size = sizeof(struct sctp_ecne_chunk);
12205 chk->data = sctp_get_mbuf_for_msg(chk->send_size, 0, M_NOWAIT, 1, MT_HEADER);
12206 if (chk->data == NULL) {
12207 sctp_free_a_chunk(stcb, chk, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
12208 return;
12209 }
12210 SCTP_BUF_RESV_UF(chk->data, SCTP_MIN_OVERHEAD);
12211 SCTP_BUF_LEN(chk->data) = chk->send_size;
12212 chk->sent = SCTP_DATAGRAM_UNSENT;
12213 chk->snd_count = 0;
12214 chk->whoTo = net;
12215 atomic_add_int(&chk->whoTo->ref_count, 1);
12216
12217 stcb->asoc.ecn_echo_cnt_onq++;
12218 ecne = mtod(chk->data, struct sctp_ecne_chunk *);
12219 ecne->ch.chunk_type = SCTP_ECN_ECHO;
12220 ecne->ch.chunk_flags = 0;
12221 ecne->ch.chunk_length = htons(sizeof(struct sctp_ecne_chunk));
12222 ecne->tsn = htonl(high_tsn);
12223 ecne->num_pkts_since_cwr = htonl(1);
12224 TAILQ_INSERT_HEAD(&stcb->asoc.control_send_queue, chk, sctp_next);
12225 asoc->ctrl_queue_cnt++;
12226}
12227
12228void
12229sctp_send_packet_dropped(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sctp_nets *net,
12230 struct mbuf *m, int len, int iphlen, int bad_crc)
12231{
12232 struct sctp_association *asoc;
12233 struct sctp_pktdrop_chunk *drp;
12234 struct sctp_tmit_chunk *chk;
12235 uint8_t *datap;
12236 int was_trunc = 0;
12237 int fullsz = 0;
12238 long spc;
12239 int offset;
12240 struct sctp_chunkhdr *ch, chunk_buf;
12241 unsigned int chk_length;
12242
12243 if (!stcb) {
12244 return;
12245 }
12246 asoc = &stcb->asoc;
12247 SCTP_TCB_LOCK_ASSERT(stcb);
12248 if (asoc->pktdrop_supported == 0) {
12249 /*-
12250 * peer must declare support before I send one.
12251 */
12252 return;
12253 }
12254 if (stcb->sctp_socket == NULL) {
12255 return;
12256 }
12257 sctp_alloc_a_chunk(stcb, chk);
12258 if (chk == NULL) {
12259 return;
12260 }
12261 chk->copy_by_ref = 0;
12262 chk->rec.chunk_id.id = SCTP_PACKET_DROPPED;
12263 chk->rec.chunk_id.can_take_data = 1;
12264 chk->flags = 0;
12265 len -= iphlen;
12266 chk->send_size = len;
12267 /* Validate that we do not have an ABORT in here. */
12268 offset = iphlen + sizeof(struct sctphdr);
12269 ch = (struct sctp_chunkhdr *)sctp_m_getptr(m, offset,
12270 sizeof(*ch), (uint8_t *) & chunk_buf);
12271 while (ch != NULL) {
12272 chk_length = ntohs(ch->chunk_length);
12273 if (chk_length < sizeof(*ch)) {
12274 /* break to abort land */
12275 break;
12276 }
12277 switch (ch->chunk_type) {
12278 case SCTP_PACKET_DROPPED:
12279 case SCTP_ABORT_ASSOCIATION:
12280 case SCTP_INITIATION_ACK:
12281 /**
12282 * We don't respond with an PKT-DROP to an ABORT
12283 * or PKT-DROP. We also do not respond to an
12284 * INIT-ACK, because we can't know if the initiation
12285 * tag is correct or not.
12286 */
12287 sctp_free_a_chunk(stcb, chk, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
12288 return;
12289 default:
12290 break;
12291 }
12292 offset += SCTP_SIZE32(chk_length);
12293 ch = (struct sctp_chunkhdr *)sctp_m_getptr(m, offset,
12294 sizeof(*ch), (uint8_t *) & chunk_buf);
12295 }
12296
12297 if ((len + SCTP_MAX_OVERHEAD + sizeof(struct sctp_pktdrop_chunk)) >
12298 min(stcb->asoc.smallest_mtu, MCLBYTES)) {
12299 /* only send 1 mtu worth, trim off the
12300 * excess on the end.
12301 */
12302 fullsz = len;
12303 len = min(stcb->asoc.smallest_mtu, MCLBYTES) - SCTP_MAX_OVERHEAD;
12304 was_trunc = 1;
12305 }
12306 chk->asoc = &stcb->asoc;
12307 chk->data = sctp_get_mbuf_for_msg(MCLBYTES, 0, M_NOWAIT, 1, MT_DATA);
12308 if (chk->data == NULL) {
12309jump_out:
12310 sctp_free_a_chunk(stcb, chk, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
12311 return;
12312 }
12313 SCTP_BUF_RESV_UF(chk->data, SCTP_MIN_OVERHEAD);
12314 drp = mtod(chk->data, struct sctp_pktdrop_chunk *);
12315 if (drp == NULL) {
12316 sctp_m_freem(chk->data);
12317 chk->data = NULL;
12318 goto jump_out;
12319 }
12320 chk->book_size = SCTP_SIZE32((chk->send_size + sizeof(struct sctp_pktdrop_chunk) +
12321 sizeof(struct sctphdr) + SCTP_MED_OVERHEAD));
12322 chk->book_size_scale = 0;
12323 if (was_trunc) {
12324 drp->ch.chunk_flags = SCTP_PACKET_TRUNCATED;
12325 drp->trunc_len = htons(fullsz);
12326 /* Len is already adjusted to size minus overhead above
12327 * take out the pkt_drop chunk itself from it.
12328 */
12329 chk->send_size = (uint16_t)(len - sizeof(struct sctp_pktdrop_chunk));
12330 len = chk->send_size;
12331 } else {
12332 /* no truncation needed */
12333 drp->ch.chunk_flags = 0;
12334 drp->trunc_len = htons(0);
12335 }
12336 if (bad_crc) {
12337 drp->ch.chunk_flags |= SCTP_BADCRC;
12338 }
12339 chk->send_size += sizeof(struct sctp_pktdrop_chunk);
12340 SCTP_BUF_LEN(chk->data) = chk->send_size;
12341 chk->sent = SCTP_DATAGRAM_UNSENT;
12342 chk->snd_count = 0;
12343 if (net) {
12344 /* we should hit here */
12345 chk->whoTo = net;
12346 atomic_add_int(&chk->whoTo->ref_count, 1);
12347 } else {
12348 chk->whoTo = NULL;
12349 }
12350 drp->ch.chunk_type = SCTP_PACKET_DROPPED;
12351 drp->ch.chunk_length = htons(chk->send_size);
12352 spc = SCTP_SB_LIMIT_RCV(stcb->sctp_socket);
12353 if (spc < 0) {
12354 spc = 0;
12355 }
12356 drp->bottle_bw = htonl(spc);
12357 if (asoc->my_rwnd) {
12358 drp->current_onq = htonl(asoc->size_on_reasm_queue +
12359 asoc->size_on_all_streams +
12360 asoc->my_rwnd_control_len +
12361 stcb->sctp_socket->so_rcv.sb_cc);
12362 } else {
12363 /*-
12364 * If my rwnd is 0, possibly from mbuf depletion as well as
12365 * space used, tell the peer there is NO space aka onq == bw
12366 */
12367 drp->current_onq = htonl(spc);
12368 }
12369 drp->reserved = 0;
12370 datap = drp->data;
12371 m_copydata(m, iphlen, len, (caddr_t)datap);
12372 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&stcb->asoc.control_send_queue, chk, sctp_next);
12373 asoc->ctrl_queue_cnt++;
12374}
12375
12376void
12377sctp_send_cwr(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sctp_nets *net, uint32_t high_tsn, uint8_t override)
12378{
12379 struct sctp_association *asoc;
12380 struct sctp_cwr_chunk *cwr;
12381 struct sctp_tmit_chunk *chk;
12382
12383 SCTP_TCB_LOCK_ASSERT(stcb);
12384 if (net == NULL) {
12385 return;
12386 }
12387 asoc = &stcb->asoc;
12388 TAILQ_FOREACH(chk, &asoc->control_send_queue, sctp_next) {
12389 if ((chk->rec.chunk_id.id == SCTP_ECN_CWR) && (net == chk->whoTo)) {
12390 /* found a previous CWR queued to same destination update it if needed */
12391 uint32_t ctsn;
12392 cwr = mtod(chk->data, struct sctp_cwr_chunk *);
12393 ctsn = ntohl(cwr->tsn);
12394 if (SCTP_TSN_GT(high_tsn, ctsn)) {
12395 cwr->tsn = htonl(high_tsn);
12396 }
12397 if (override & SCTP_CWR_REDUCE_OVERRIDE) {
12398 /* Make sure override is carried */
12399 cwr->ch.chunk_flags |= SCTP_CWR_REDUCE_OVERRIDE;
12400 }
12401 return;
12402 }
12403 }
12404 sctp_alloc_a_chunk(stcb, chk);
12405 if (chk == NULL) {
12406 return;
12407 }
12408 chk->copy_by_ref = 0;
12409 chk->rec.chunk_id.id = SCTP_ECN_CWR;
12410 chk->rec.chunk_id.can_take_data = 1;
12411 chk->flags = 0;
12412 chk->asoc = &stcb->asoc;
12413 chk->send_size = sizeof(struct sctp_cwr_chunk);
12414 chk->data = sctp_get_mbuf_for_msg(chk->send_size, 0, M_NOWAIT, 1, MT_HEADER);
12415 if (chk->data == NULL) {
12416 sctp_free_a_chunk(stcb, chk, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
12417 return;
12418 }
12419 SCTP_BUF_RESV_UF(chk->data, SCTP_MIN_OVERHEAD);
12420 SCTP_BUF_LEN(chk->data) = chk->send_size;
12421 chk->sent = SCTP_DATAGRAM_UNSENT;
12422 chk->snd_count = 0;
12423 chk->whoTo = net;
12424 atomic_add_int(&chk->whoTo->ref_count, 1);
12425 cwr = mtod(chk->data, struct sctp_cwr_chunk *);
12426 cwr->ch.chunk_type = SCTP_ECN_CWR;
12427 cwr->ch.chunk_flags = override;
12428 cwr->ch.chunk_length = htons(sizeof(struct sctp_cwr_chunk));
12429 cwr->tsn = htonl(high_tsn);
12430 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&stcb->asoc.control_send_queue, chk, sctp_next);
12431 asoc->ctrl_queue_cnt++;
12432}
12433
12434static int
12435sctp_add_stream_reset_out(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sctp_tmit_chunk *chk,
12436 uint32_t seq, uint32_t resp_seq, uint32_t last_sent)
12437{
12438 uint16_t len, old_len, i;
12439 struct sctp_stream_reset_out_request *req_out;
12440 struct sctp_chunkhdr *ch;
12441 int at;
12442 int number_entries=0;
12443
12444 ch = mtod(chk->data, struct sctp_chunkhdr *);
12445 old_len = len = SCTP_SIZE32(ntohs(ch->chunk_length));
12446 /* get to new offset for the param. */
12447 req_out = (struct sctp_stream_reset_out_request *)((caddr_t)ch + len);
12448 /* now how long will this param be? */
12449 for (i = 0; i < stcb->asoc.streamoutcnt; i++) {
12450 if ((stcb->asoc.strmout[i].state == SCTP_STREAM_RESET_PENDING) &&
12451 (stcb->asoc.strmout[i].chunks_on_queues == 0) &&
12452 TAILQ_EMPTY(&stcb->asoc.strmout[i].outqueue)) {
12453 number_entries++;
12454 }
12455 }
12456 if (number_entries == 0) {
12457 return (0);
12458 }
12459 if (number_entries == stcb->asoc.streamoutcnt) {
12460 number_entries = 0;
12461 }
12462 if (number_entries > SCTP_MAX_STREAMS_AT_ONCE_RESET) {
12463 number_entries = SCTP_MAX_STREAMS_AT_ONCE_RESET;
12464 }
12465 len = (uint16_t)(sizeof(struct sctp_stream_reset_out_request) + (sizeof(uint16_t) * number_entries));
12466 req_out->ph.param_type = htons(SCTP_STR_RESET_OUT_REQUEST);
12467 req_out->ph.param_length = htons(len);
12468 req_out->request_seq = htonl(seq);
12469 req_out->response_seq = htonl(resp_seq);
12470 req_out->send_reset_at_tsn = htonl(last_sent);
12471 at = 0;
12472 if (number_entries) {
12473 for (i = 0; i < stcb->asoc.streamoutcnt; i++) {
12474 if ((stcb->asoc.strmout[i].state == SCTP_STREAM_RESET_PENDING) &&
12475 (stcb->asoc.strmout[i].chunks_on_queues == 0) &&
12476 TAILQ_EMPTY(&stcb->asoc.strmout[i].outqueue)) {
12477 req_out->list_of_streams[at] = htons(i);
12478 at++;
12479 stcb->asoc.strmout[i].state = SCTP_STREAM_RESET_IN_FLIGHT;
12480 if (at >= number_entries) {
12481 break;
12482 }
12483 }
12484 }
12485 } else {
12486 for (i = 0; i < stcb->asoc.streamoutcnt; i++) {
12487 stcb->asoc.strmout[i].state = SCTP_STREAM_RESET_IN_FLIGHT;
12488 }
12489 }
12490 if (SCTP_SIZE32(len) > len) {
12491 /*-
12492 * Need to worry about the pad we may end up adding to the
12493 * end. This is easy since the struct is either aligned to 4
12494 * bytes or 2 bytes off.
12495 */
12496 req_out->list_of_streams[number_entries] = 0;
12497 }
12498 /* now fix the chunk length */
12499 ch->chunk_length = htons(len + old_len);
12500 chk->book_size = len + old_len;
12501 chk->book_size_scale = 0;
12502 chk->send_size = SCTP_SIZE32(chk->book_size);
12503 SCTP_BUF_LEN(chk->data) = chk->send_size;
12504 return (1);
12505}
12506
12507static void
12508sctp_add_stream_reset_in(struct sctp_tmit_chunk *chk,
12509 int number_entries, uint16_t *list,
12510 uint32_t seq)
12511{
12512 uint16_t len, old_len, i;
12513 struct sctp_stream_reset_in_request *req_in;
12514 struct sctp_chunkhdr *ch;
12515
12516 ch = mtod(chk->data, struct sctp_chunkhdr *);
12517 old_len = len = SCTP_SIZE32(ntohs(ch->chunk_length));
12518
12519 /* get to new offset for the param. */
12520 req_in = (struct sctp_stream_reset_in_request *)((caddr_t)ch + len);
12521 /* now how long will this param be? */
12522 len = (uint16_t)(sizeof(struct sctp_stream_reset_in_request) + (sizeof(uint16_t) * number_entries));
12523 req_in->ph.param_type = htons(SCTP_STR_RESET_IN_REQUEST);
12524 req_in->ph.param_length = htons(len);
12525 req_in->request_seq = htonl(seq);
12526 if (number_entries) {
12527 for (i = 0; i < number_entries; i++) {
12528 req_in->list_of_streams[i] = htons(list[i]);
12529 }
12530 }
12531 if (SCTP_SIZE32(len) > len) {
12532 /*-
12533 * Need to worry about the pad we may end up adding to the
12534 * end. This is easy since the struct is either aligned to 4
12535 * bytes or 2 bytes off.
12536 */
12537 req_in->list_of_streams[number_entries] = 0;
12538 }
12539 /* now fix the chunk length */
12540 ch->chunk_length = htons(len + old_len);
12541 chk->book_size = len + old_len;
12542 chk->book_size_scale = 0;
12543 chk->send_size = SCTP_SIZE32(chk->book_size);
12544 SCTP_BUF_LEN(chk->data) = chk->send_size;
12545 return;
12546}
12547
12548static void
12549sctp_add_stream_reset_tsn(struct sctp_tmit_chunk *chk,
12550 uint32_t seq)
12551{
12552 uint16_t len, old_len;
12553 struct sctp_stream_reset_tsn_request *req_tsn;
12554 struct sctp_chunkhdr *ch;
12555
12556 ch = mtod(chk->data, struct sctp_chunkhdr *);
12557 old_len = len = SCTP_SIZE32(ntohs(ch->chunk_length));
12558
12559 /* get to new offset for the param. */
12560 req_tsn = (struct sctp_stream_reset_tsn_request *)((caddr_t)ch + len);
12561 /* now how long will this param be? */
12562 len = sizeof(struct sctp_stream_reset_tsn_request);
12563 req_tsn->ph.param_type = htons(SCTP_STR_RESET_TSN_REQUEST);
12564 req_tsn->ph.param_length = htons(len);
12565 req_tsn->request_seq = htonl(seq);
12566
12567 /* now fix the chunk length */
12568 ch->chunk_length = htons(len + old_len);
12569 chk->send_size = len + old_len;
12570 chk->book_size = SCTP_SIZE32(chk->send_size);
12571 chk->book_size_scale = 0;
12572 SCTP_BUF_LEN(chk->data) = SCTP_SIZE32(chk->send_size);
12573 return;
12574}
12575
12576void
12577sctp_add_stream_reset_result(struct sctp_tmit_chunk *chk,
12578 uint32_t resp_seq, uint32_t result)
12579{
12580 uint16_t len, old_len;
12581 struct sctp_stream_reset_response *resp;
12582 struct sctp_chunkhdr *ch;
12583
12584 ch = mtod(chk->data, struct sctp_chunkhdr *);
12585 old_len = len = SCTP_SIZE32(ntohs(ch->chunk_length));
12586
12587 /* get to new offset for the param. */
12588 resp = (struct sctp_stream_reset_response *)((caddr_t)ch + len);
12589 /* now how long will this param be? */
12590 len = sizeof(struct sctp_stream_reset_response);
12591 resp->ph.param_type = htons(SCTP_STR_RESET_RESPONSE);
12592 resp->ph.param_length = htons(len);
12593 resp->response_seq = htonl(resp_seq);
12594 resp->result = ntohl(result);
12595
12596 /* now fix the chunk length */
12597 ch->chunk_length = htons(len + old_len);
12598 chk->book_size = len + old_len;
12599 chk->book_size_scale = 0;
12600 chk->send_size = SCTP_SIZE32(chk->book_size);
12601 SCTP_BUF_LEN(chk->data) = chk->send_size;
12602 return;
12603}
12604
12605void
12606sctp_send_deferred_reset_response(struct sctp_tcb *stcb,
12607 struct sctp_stream_reset_list *ent,
12608 int response)
12609{
12610 struct sctp_association *asoc;
12611 struct sctp_tmit_chunk *chk;
12612 struct sctp_chunkhdr *ch;
12613
12614 asoc = &stcb->asoc;
12615
12616 /*
12617 * Reset our last reset action to the new one IP -> response
12618 * (PERFORMED probably). This assures that if we fail to send, a
12619 * retran from the peer will get the new response.
12620 */
12621 asoc->last_reset_action[0] = response;
12622 if (asoc->stream_reset_outstanding) {
12623 return;
12624 }
12625 sctp_alloc_a_chunk(stcb, chk);
12626 if (chk == NULL) {
12627 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(NULL, stcb, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, ENOMEM);
12628 return;
12629 }
12630 chk->copy_by_ref = 0;
12631 chk->rec.chunk_id.id = SCTP_STREAM_RESET;
12632 chk->rec.chunk_id.can_take_data = 0;
12633 chk->flags = 0;
12634 chk->asoc = &stcb->asoc;
12635 chk->book_size = sizeof(struct sctp_chunkhdr);
12636 chk->send_size = SCTP_SIZE32(chk->book_size);
12637 chk->book_size_scale = 0;
12638 chk->data = sctp_get_mbuf_for_msg(MCLBYTES, 0, M_NOWAIT, 1, MT_DATA);
12639 if (chk->data == NULL) {
12640 sctp_free_a_chunk(stcb, chk, SCTP_SO_LOCKED);
12641 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(NULL, stcb, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, ENOMEM);
12642 return;
12643 }
12644 SCTP_BUF_RESV_UF(chk->data, SCTP_MIN_OVERHEAD);
12645 /* setup chunk parameters */
12646 chk->sent = SCTP_DATAGRAM_UNSENT;
12647 chk->snd_count = 0;
12648 if (stcb->asoc.alternate) {
12649 chk->whoTo = stcb->asoc.alternate;
12650 } else {
12651 chk->whoTo = stcb->asoc.primary_destination;
12652 }
12653 ch = mtod(chk->data, struct sctp_chunkhdr *);
12654 ch->chunk_type = SCTP_STREAM_RESET;
12655 ch->chunk_flags = 0;
12656 ch->chunk_length = htons(chk->book_size);
12657 atomic_add_int(&chk->whoTo->ref_count, 1);
12658 SCTP_BUF_LEN(chk->data) = chk->send_size;
12659 sctp_add_stream_reset_result(chk, ent->seq, response);
12660 /* insert the chunk for sending */
12661 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&asoc->control_send_queue,
12662 chk,
12663 sctp_next);
12664 asoc->ctrl_queue_cnt++;
12665}
12666
12667void
12668sctp_add_stream_reset_result_tsn(struct sctp_tmit_chunk *chk,
12669 uint32_t resp_seq, uint32_t result,
12670 uint32_t send_una, uint32_t recv_next)
12671{
12672 uint16_t len, old_len;
12673 struct sctp_stream_reset_response_tsn *resp;
12674 struct sctp_chunkhdr *ch;
12675
12676 ch = mtod(chk->data, struct sctp_chunkhdr *);
12677 old_len = len = SCTP_SIZE32(ntohs(ch->chunk_length));
12678
12679 /* get to new offset for the param. */
12680 resp = (struct sctp_stream_reset_response_tsn *)((caddr_t)ch + len);
12681 /* now how long will this param be? */
12682 len = sizeof(struct sctp_stream_reset_response_tsn);
12683 resp->ph.param_type = htons(SCTP_STR_RESET_RESPONSE);
12684 resp->ph.param_length = htons(len);
12685 resp->response_seq = htonl(resp_seq);
12686 resp->result = htonl(result);
12687 resp->senders_next_tsn = htonl(send_una);
12688 resp->receivers_next_tsn = htonl(recv_next);
12689
12690 /* now fix the chunk length */
12691 ch->chunk_length = htons(len + old_len);
12692 chk->book_size = len + old_len;
12693 chk->send_size = SCTP_SIZE32(chk->book_size);
12694 chk->book_size_scale = 0;
12695 SCTP_BUF_LEN(chk->data) = chk->send_size;
12696 return;
12697}
12698
12699static void
12700sctp_add_an_out_stream(struct sctp_tmit_chunk *chk,
12701 uint32_t seq,
12702 uint16_t adding)
12703{
12704 uint16_t len, old_len;
12705 struct sctp_chunkhdr *ch;
12706 struct sctp_stream_reset_add_strm *addstr;
12707
12708 ch = mtod(chk->data, struct sctp_chunkhdr *);
12709 old_len = len = SCTP_SIZE32(ntohs(ch->chunk_length));
12710
12711 /* get to new offset for the param. */
12712 addstr = (struct sctp_stream_reset_add_strm *)((caddr_t)ch + len);
12713 /* now how long will this param be? */
12714 len = sizeof(struct sctp_stream_reset_add_strm);
12715
12716 /* Fill it out. */
12717 addstr->ph.param_type = htons(SCTP_STR_RESET_ADD_OUT_STREAMS);
12718 addstr->ph.param_length = htons(len);
12719 addstr->request_seq = htonl(seq);
12720 addstr->number_of_streams = htons(adding);
12721 addstr->reserved = 0;
12722
12723 /* now fix the chunk length */
12724 ch->chunk_length = htons(len + old_len);
12725 chk->send_size = len + old_len;
12726 chk->book_size = SCTP_SIZE32(chk->send_size);
12727 chk->book_size_scale = 0;
12728 SCTP_BUF_LEN(chk->data) = SCTP_SIZE32(chk->send_size);
12729 return;
12730}
12731

12743

12748 /* Fill it out. */

12752 addstr->number_of_streams = htons(adding);
12753 addstr->reserved = 0;
