12763
12764int
12765sctp_send_stream_reset_out_if_possible(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, int so_locked)
12766{
12767 struct sctp_association *asoc;
12768 struct sctp_tmit_chunk *chk;
12769 struct sctp_chunkhdr *ch;
12770 uint32_t seq;
12771
12772 asoc = &stcb->asoc;
12773 asoc->trigger_reset = 0;
12774 if (asoc->stream_reset_outstanding) {
12775 return (EALREADY);
12776 }
12777 sctp_alloc_a_chunk(stcb, chk);
12778 if (chk == NULL) {
12779 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(NULL, stcb, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, ENOMEM);
12780 return (ENOMEM);
12781 }
12782 chk->copy_by_ref = 0;
12783 chk->rec.chunk_id.id = SCTP_STREAM_RESET;
12784 chk->rec.chunk_id.can_take_data = 0;
12785 chk->flags = 0;
12786 chk->asoc = &stcb->asoc;
12787 chk->book_size = sizeof(struct sctp_chunkhdr);
12788 chk->send_size = SCTP_SIZE32(chk->book_size);
12789 chk->book_size_scale = 0;
12790 chk->data = sctp_get_mbuf_for_msg(MCLBYTES, 0, M_NOWAIT, 1, MT_DATA);
12791 if (chk->data == NULL) {
12792 sctp_free_a_chunk(stcb, chk, so_locked);
12793 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(NULL, stcb, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, ENOMEM);
12794 return (ENOMEM);
12795 }
12796 SCTP_BUF_RESV_UF(chk->data, SCTP_MIN_OVERHEAD);
12797
12798 /* setup chunk parameters */
12799 chk->sent = SCTP_DATAGRAM_UNSENT;
12800 chk->snd_count = 0;
12801 if (stcb->asoc.alternate) {
12802 chk->whoTo = stcb->asoc.alternate;
12803 } else {
12804 chk->whoTo = stcb->asoc.primary_destination;
12805 }
12806 ch = mtod(chk->data, struct sctp_chunkhdr *);
12807 ch->chunk_type = SCTP_STREAM_RESET;
12808 ch->chunk_flags = 0;
12809 ch->chunk_length = htons(chk->book_size);
12810 atomic_add_int(&chk->whoTo->ref_count, 1);
12811 SCTP_BUF_LEN(chk->data) = chk->send_size;
12812 seq = stcb->asoc.str_reset_seq_out;
12813 if (sctp_add_stream_reset_out(stcb, chk, seq, (stcb->asoc.str_reset_seq_in - 1), (stcb->asoc.sending_seq - 1))) {
12814 seq++;
12815 asoc->stream_reset_outstanding++;
12816 } else {
12817 m_freem(chk->data);
12818 chk->data = NULL;
12819 sctp_free_a_chunk(stcb, chk, so_locked);
12820 return (ENOENT);
12821 }
12822 asoc->str_reset = chk;
12823 /* insert the chunk for sending */
12824 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&asoc->control_send_queue,
12825 chk,
12826 sctp_next);
12827 asoc->ctrl_queue_cnt++;
12828
12829 if (stcb->asoc.send_sack) {
12830 sctp_send_sack(stcb, so_locked);
12831 }
12832 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_STRRESET, stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, chk->whoTo);
12833 return (0);
12834}
12835
12836int
12837sctp_send_str_reset_req(struct sctp_tcb *stcb,
12838 uint16_t number_entries, uint16_t *list,
12839 uint8_t send_in_req,
12840 uint8_t send_tsn_req,
12841 uint8_t add_stream,
12842 uint16_t adding_o,
12843 uint16_t adding_i, uint8_t peer_asked)
12844{
12845 struct sctp_association *asoc;
12846 struct sctp_tmit_chunk *chk;
12847 struct sctp_chunkhdr *ch;
12848 int can_send_out_req=0;
12849 uint32_t seq;
12850
12851 asoc = &stcb->asoc;
12852 if (asoc->stream_reset_outstanding) {
12853 /*-
12854 * Already one pending, must get ACK back to clear the flag.
12855 */
12856 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(NULL, stcb, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, EBUSY);
12857 return (EBUSY);
12858 }
12859 if ((send_in_req == 0) && (send_tsn_req == 0) &&
12860 (add_stream == 0)) {
12861 /* nothing to do */
12862 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(NULL, stcb, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, EINVAL);
12863 return (EINVAL);
12864 }
12865 if (send_tsn_req && send_in_req) {
12866 /* error, can't do that */
12867 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(NULL, stcb, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, EINVAL);
12868 return (EINVAL);
12869 } else if (send_in_req) {
12870 can_send_out_req = 1;
12871 }
12872 if (number_entries > (MCLBYTES -
12873 SCTP_MIN_OVERHEAD -
12874 sizeof(struct sctp_chunkhdr) -
12875 sizeof(struct sctp_stream_reset_out_request)) /
12876 sizeof(uint16_t)) {
12877 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(NULL, stcb, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, ENOMEM);
12878 return (ENOMEM);
12879 }
12880 sctp_alloc_a_chunk(stcb, chk);
12881 if (chk == NULL) {
12882 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(NULL, stcb, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, ENOMEM);
12883 return (ENOMEM);
12884 }
12885 chk->copy_by_ref = 0;
12886 chk->rec.chunk_id.id = SCTP_STREAM_RESET;
12887 chk->rec.chunk_id.can_take_data = 0;
12888 chk->flags = 0;
12889 chk->asoc = &stcb->asoc;
12890 chk->book_size = sizeof(struct sctp_chunkhdr);
12891 chk->send_size = SCTP_SIZE32(chk->book_size);
12892 chk->book_size_scale = 0;
12893 chk->data = sctp_get_mbuf_for_msg(MCLBYTES, 0, M_NOWAIT, 1, MT_DATA);
12894 if (chk->data == NULL) {
12895 sctp_free_a_chunk(stcb, chk, SCTP_SO_LOCKED);
12896 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(NULL, stcb, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, ENOMEM);
12897 return (ENOMEM);
12898 }
12899 SCTP_BUF_RESV_UF(chk->data, SCTP_MIN_OVERHEAD);
12900
12901 /* setup chunk parameters */
12902 chk->sent = SCTP_DATAGRAM_UNSENT;
12903 chk->snd_count = 0;
12904 if (stcb->asoc.alternate) {
12905 chk->whoTo = stcb->asoc.alternate;
12906 } else {
12907 chk->whoTo = stcb->asoc.primary_destination;
12908 }
12909 atomic_add_int(&chk->whoTo->ref_count, 1);
12910 ch = mtod(chk->data, struct sctp_chunkhdr *);
12911 ch->chunk_type = SCTP_STREAM_RESET;
12912 ch->chunk_flags = 0;
12913 ch->chunk_length = htons(chk->book_size);
12914 SCTP_BUF_LEN(chk->data) = chk->send_size;
12915
12916 seq = stcb->asoc.str_reset_seq_out;
12917 if (can_send_out_req) {
12918 int ret;
12919 ret = sctp_add_stream_reset_out(stcb, chk, seq, (stcb->asoc.str_reset_seq_in - 1), (stcb->asoc.sending_seq - 1));
12920 if (ret) {
12921 seq++;
12922 asoc->stream_reset_outstanding++;
12923 }
12924 }
12925 if ((add_stream & 1) &&
12926 ((stcb->asoc.strm_realoutsize - stcb->asoc.streamoutcnt) < adding_o)) {
12927 /* Need to allocate more */
12928 struct sctp_stream_out *oldstream;
12929 struct sctp_stream_queue_pending *sp, *nsp;
12930 int i;
12931#if defined(SCTP_DETAILED_STR_STATS)
12932 int j;
12933#endif
12934
12935 oldstream = stcb->asoc.strmout;
12936 /* get some more */
12937 SCTP_MALLOC(stcb->asoc.strmout, struct sctp_stream_out *,
12938 (stcb->asoc.streamoutcnt + adding_o) * sizeof(struct sctp_stream_out),
12939 SCTP_M_STRMO);
12940 if (stcb->asoc.strmout == NULL) {
12941 uint8_t x;
12942 stcb->asoc.strmout = oldstream;
12943 /* Turn off the bit */
12944 x = add_stream & 0xfe;
12945 add_stream = x;
12946 goto skip_stuff;
12947 }
12948 /* Ok now we proceed with copying the old out stuff and
12949 * initializing the new stuff.
12950 */
12951 SCTP_TCB_SEND_LOCK(stcb);
12952 stcb->asoc.ss_functions.sctp_ss_clear(stcb, &stcb->asoc, 0, 1);
12953 for (i = 0; i < stcb->asoc.streamoutcnt; i++) {
12954 TAILQ_INIT(&stcb->asoc.strmout[i].outqueue);
12955 /* FIX ME FIX ME */
12956 /* This should be a SS_COPY operation FIX ME STREAM SCHEDULER EXPERT */
12957 stcb->asoc.ss_functions.sctp_ss_init_stream(stcb, &stcb->asoc.strmout[i], &oldstream[i]);
12958 stcb->asoc.strmout[i].chunks_on_queues = oldstream[i].chunks_on_queues;
12959#if defined(SCTP_DETAILED_STR_STATS)
12960 for (j = 0; j < SCTP_PR_SCTP_MAX + 1; j++) {
12961 stcb->asoc.strmout[i].abandoned_sent[j] = oldstream[i].abandoned_sent[j];
12962 stcb->asoc.strmout[i].abandoned_unsent[j] = oldstream[i].abandoned_unsent[j];
12963 }
12964#else
12965 stcb->asoc.strmout[i].abandoned_sent[0] = oldstream[i].abandoned_sent[0];
12966 stcb->asoc.strmout[i].abandoned_unsent[0] = oldstream[i].abandoned_unsent[0];
12967#endif
12968 stcb->asoc.strmout[i].next_mid_ordered = oldstream[i].next_mid_ordered;
12969 stcb->asoc.strmout[i].next_mid_unordered = oldstream[i].next_mid_unordered;
12970 stcb->asoc.strmout[i].last_msg_incomplete = oldstream[i].last_msg_incomplete;
12971 stcb->asoc.strmout[i].sid = i;
12972 stcb->asoc.strmout[i].state = oldstream[i].state;
12973 /* now anything on those queues? */
12974 TAILQ_FOREACH_SAFE(sp, &oldstream[i].outqueue, next, nsp) {
12975 TAILQ_REMOVE(&oldstream[i].outqueue, sp, next);
12976 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&stcb->asoc.strmout[i].outqueue, sp, next);
12977 }
12978 }
12979 /* now the new streams */
12980 stcb->asoc.ss_functions.sctp_ss_init(stcb, &stcb->asoc, 1);
12981 for (i = stcb->asoc.streamoutcnt; i < (stcb->asoc.streamoutcnt + adding_o); i++) {
12982 TAILQ_INIT(&stcb->asoc.strmout[i].outqueue);
12983 stcb->asoc.strmout[i].chunks_on_queues = 0;
12984#if defined(SCTP_DETAILED_STR_STATS)
12985 for (j = 0; j < SCTP_PR_SCTP_MAX + 1; j++) {
12986 stcb->asoc.strmout[i].abandoned_sent[j] = 0;
12987 stcb->asoc.strmout[i].abandoned_unsent[j] = 0;
12988 }
12989#else
12990 stcb->asoc.strmout[i].abandoned_sent[0] = 0;
12991 stcb->asoc.strmout[i].abandoned_unsent[0] = 0;
12992#endif
12993 stcb->asoc.strmout[i].next_mid_ordered = 0;
12994 stcb->asoc.strmout[i].next_mid_unordered = 0;
12995 stcb->asoc.strmout[i].sid = i;
12996 stcb->asoc.strmout[i].last_msg_incomplete = 0;
12997 stcb->asoc.ss_functions.sctp_ss_init_stream(stcb, &stcb->asoc.strmout[i], NULL);
12998 stcb->asoc.strmout[i].state = SCTP_STREAM_CLOSED;
12999 }
13000 stcb->asoc.strm_realoutsize = stcb->asoc.streamoutcnt + adding_o;
13001 SCTP_FREE(oldstream, SCTP_M_STRMO);
13002 SCTP_TCB_SEND_UNLOCK(stcb);
13003 }
13004skip_stuff:
13005 if ((add_stream & 1) && (adding_o > 0)) {
13006 asoc->strm_pending_add_size = adding_o;
13007 asoc->peer_req_out = peer_asked;
13008 sctp_add_an_out_stream(chk, seq, adding_o);
13009 seq++;
13010 asoc->stream_reset_outstanding++;
13011 }
13012 if ((add_stream & 2) && (adding_i > 0)) {
13013 sctp_add_an_in_stream(chk, seq, adding_i);
13014 seq++;
13015 asoc->stream_reset_outstanding++;
13016 }
13017 if (send_in_req) {
13018 sctp_add_stream_reset_in(chk, number_entries, list, seq);
13019 seq++;
13020 asoc->stream_reset_outstanding++;
13021 }
13022 if (send_tsn_req) {
13023 sctp_add_stream_reset_tsn(chk, seq);
13024 asoc->stream_reset_outstanding++;
13025 }
13026 asoc->str_reset = chk;
13027 /* insert the chunk for sending */
13028 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&asoc->control_send_queue,
13029 chk,
13030 sctp_next);
13031 asoc->ctrl_queue_cnt++;
13032 if (stcb->asoc.send_sack) {
13033 sctp_send_sack(stcb, SCTP_SO_LOCKED);
13034 }
13035 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_STRRESET, stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, chk->whoTo);
13036 return (0);
13037}
13038
13039void
13040sctp_send_abort(struct mbuf *m, int iphlen, struct sockaddr *src, struct sockaddr *dst,
13041 struct sctphdr *sh, uint32_t vtag, struct mbuf *cause,
13042#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
13043 uint8_t mflowtype, uint32_t mflowid, uint16_t fibnum,
13044#endif
13045 uint32_t vrf_id, uint16_t port)
13046{
13047 /* Don't respond to an ABORT with an ABORT. */
13048 if (sctp_is_there_an_abort_here(m, iphlen, &vtag)) {
13049 if (cause)
13050 sctp_m_freem(cause);
13051 return;
13052 }
13053 sctp_send_resp_msg(src, dst, sh, vtag, SCTP_ABORT_ASSOCIATION, cause,
13054#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
13055 mflowtype, mflowid, fibnum,
13056#endif
13057 vrf_id, port);
13058 return;
13059}
13060
13061void
13062sctp_send_operr_to(struct sockaddr *src, struct sockaddr *dst,
13063 struct sctphdr *sh, uint32_t vtag, struct mbuf *cause,
13064#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
13065 uint8_t mflowtype, uint32_t mflowid, uint16_t fibnum,
13066#endif
13067 uint32_t vrf_id, uint16_t port)
13068{
13069 sctp_send_resp_msg(src, dst, sh, vtag, SCTP_OPERATION_ERROR, cause,
13070#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
13071 mflowtype, mflowid, fibnum,
13072#endif
13073 vrf_id, port);
13074 return;
13075}
13076
13077static struct mbuf *
13078sctp_copy_resume(struct uio *uio,
13079 int max_send_len,
13080#if defined(__FreeBSD__) || defined(__Userspace__)
13081 int user_marks_eor,
13082#endif
13083 int *error,
13084 uint32_t *sndout,
13085 struct mbuf **new_tail)
13086{
13087#if defined(__FreeBSD__) || defined(__Userspace__)
13088 struct mbuf *m;
13089
13090 m = m_uiotombuf(uio, M_WAITOK, max_send_len, 0,
13091 (M_PKTHDR | (user_marks_eor ? M_EOR : 0)));
13092 if (m == NULL) {
13093 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(NULL, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, ENOBUFS);
13094 *error = ENOBUFS;
13095 } else {
13096 *sndout = m_length(m, NULL);
13097 *new_tail = m_last(m);
13098 }
13099 return (m);
13100#else
13101 int left, cancpy, willcpy;
13102 struct mbuf *m, *head;
13103
13104#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
13105#if defined(APPLE_LEOPARD)
13106 left = (int)min(uio->uio_resid, max_send_len);
13107#else
13108 left = (int)min(uio_resid(uio), max_send_len);
13109#endif
13110#else
13111 left = (int)min(uio->uio_resid, max_send_len);
13112#endif
13113 /* Always get a header just in case */
13114 head = sctp_get_mbuf_for_msg(left, 0, M_WAITOK, 0, MT_DATA);
13115 if (head == NULL) {
13116 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(NULL, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, ENOBUFS);
13117 *error = ENOBUFS;
13118 return (NULL);
13119 }
13120 cancpy = (int)M_TRAILINGSPACE(head);
13121 willcpy = min(cancpy, left);
13122 *error = uiomove(mtod(head, caddr_t), willcpy, uio);
13123 if (*error) {
13124 sctp_m_freem(head);
13125 return (NULL);
13126 }
13127 *sndout += willcpy;
13128 left -= willcpy;
13129 SCTP_BUF_LEN(head) = willcpy;
13130 m = head;
13131 *new_tail = head;
13132 while (left > 0) {
13133 /* move in user data */
13134 SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m) = sctp_get_mbuf_for_msg(left, 0, M_WAITOK, 0, MT_DATA);
13135 if (SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m) == NULL) {
13136 sctp_m_freem(head);
13137 *new_tail = NULL;
13138 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(NULL, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, ENOBUFS);
13139 *error = ENOBUFS;
13140 return (NULL);
13141 }
13142 m = SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m);
13143 cancpy = (int)M_TRAILINGSPACE(m);
13144 willcpy = min(cancpy, left);
13145 *error = uiomove(mtod(m, caddr_t), willcpy, uio);
13146 if (*error) {
13147 sctp_m_freem(head);
13148 *new_tail = NULL;
13149 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(NULL, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, EFAULT);
13150 *error = EFAULT;
13151 return (NULL);
13152 }
13153 SCTP_BUF_LEN(m) = willcpy;
13154 left -= willcpy;
13155 *sndout += willcpy;
13156 *new_tail = m;
13157 if (left == 0) {
13158 SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m) = NULL;
13159 }
13160 }
13161 return (head);
13162#endif
13163}
13164
13165static int
13166sctp_copy_one(struct sctp_stream_queue_pending *sp,
13167 struct uio *uio,
13168 int resv_upfront)
13169{
13170#if defined(__FreeBSD__) || defined(__Userspace__)
13171 sp->data = m_uiotombuf(uio, M_WAITOK, sp->length,
13172 resv_upfront, 0);
13173 if (sp->data == NULL) {
13174 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(NULL, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, ENOBUFS);
13175 return (ENOBUFS);
13176 }
13177
13178 sp->tail_mbuf = m_last(sp->data);
13179 return (0);
13180#else
13181 int left;
13182 int cancpy, willcpy, error;
13183 struct mbuf *m, *head;
13184 int cpsz = 0;
13185
13186 /* First one gets a header */
13187 left = sp->length;
13188 head = m = sctp_get_mbuf_for_msg((left + resv_upfront), 0, M_WAITOK, 0, MT_DATA);
13189 if (m == NULL) {
13190 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(NULL, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, ENOBUFS);
13191 return (ENOBUFS);
13192 }
13193 /*-
13194 * Add this one for m in now, that way if the alloc fails we won't
13195 * have a bad cnt.
13196 */
13197 SCTP_BUF_RESV_UF(m, resv_upfront);
13198 cancpy = (int)M_TRAILINGSPACE(m);
13199 willcpy = min(cancpy, left);
13200 while (left > 0) {
13201 /* move in user data */
13202 error = uiomove(mtod(m, caddr_t), willcpy, uio);
13203 if (error) {
13204 sctp_m_freem(head);
13205 return (error);
13206 }
13207 SCTP_BUF_LEN(m) = willcpy;
13208 left -= willcpy;
13209 cpsz += willcpy;
13210 if (left > 0) {
13211 SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m) = sctp_get_mbuf_for_msg(left, 0, M_WAITOK, 0, MT_DATA);
13212 if (SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m) == NULL) {
13213 /*
13214 * the head goes back to caller, he can free
13215 * the rest
13216 */
13217 sctp_m_freem(head);
13218 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(NULL, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, ENOBUFS);
13219 return (ENOBUFS);
13220 }
13221 m = SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m);
13222 cancpy = (int)M_TRAILINGSPACE(m);
13223 willcpy = min(cancpy, left);
13224 } else {
13225 sp->tail_mbuf = m;
13226 SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m) = NULL;
13227 }
13228 }
13229 sp->data = head;
13230 sp->length = cpsz;
13231 return (0);
13232#endif
13233}
13234
13235static struct sctp_stream_queue_pending *
13236sctp_copy_it_in(struct sctp_tcb *stcb,
13237 struct sctp_association *asoc,
13238 struct sctp_sndrcvinfo *srcv,
13239 struct uio *uio,
13240 struct sctp_nets *net,
13241 ssize_t max_send_len,
13242 int user_marks_eor,
13243 int *error)
13244
13245{
13246 /*-
13247 * This routine must be very careful in its work. Protocol
13248 * processing is up and running so care must be taken to spl...()
13249 * when you need to do something that may effect the stcb/asoc. The
13250 * sb is locked however. When data is copied the protocol processing
13251 * should be enabled since this is a slower operation...
13252 */
13253 struct sctp_stream_queue_pending *sp = NULL;
13254 int resv_in_first;
13255
13256 *error = 0;
13257 /* Now can we send this? */
13258 if ((SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_SENT) ||
13259 (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_ACK_SENT) ||
13260 (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_RECEIVED) ||
13261 (asoc->state & SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_PENDING)) {
13262 /* got data while shutting down */
13263 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(NULL, stcb, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, ECONNRESET);
13264 *error = ECONNRESET;
13265 goto out_now;
13266 }
13267 sctp_alloc_a_strmoq(stcb, sp);
13268 if (sp == NULL) {
13269 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(NULL, stcb, net, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, ENOMEM);
13270 *error = ENOMEM;
13271 goto out_now;
13272 }
13273 sp->act_flags = 0;
13274 sp->sender_all_done = 0;
13275 sp->sinfo_flags = srcv->sinfo_flags;
13276 sp->timetolive = srcv->sinfo_timetolive;
13277 sp->ppid = srcv->sinfo_ppid;
13278 sp->context = srcv->sinfo_context;
13279 sp->fsn = 0;
13280 (void)SCTP_GETTIME_TIMEVAL(&sp->ts);
13281
13282 sp->sid = srcv->sinfo_stream;
13283#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
13284#if defined(APPLE_LEOPARD)
13285 sp->length = (uint32_t)min(uio->uio_resid, max_send_len);
13286#else
13287 sp->length = (uint32_t)min(uio_resid(uio), max_send_len);
13288#endif
13289#else
13290 sp->length = (uint32_t)min(uio->uio_resid, max_send_len);
13291#endif
13292#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
13293#if defined(APPLE_LEOPARD)
13294 if ((sp->length == (uint32_t)uio->uio_resid) &&
13295#else
13296 if ((sp->length == (uint32_t)uio_resid(uio)) &&
13297#endif
13298#else
13299 if ((sp->length == (uint32_t)uio->uio_resid) &&
13300#endif
13301 ((user_marks_eor == 0) ||
13302 (srcv->sinfo_flags & SCTP_EOF) ||
13303 (user_marks_eor && (srcv->sinfo_flags & SCTP_EOR)))) {
13304 sp->msg_is_complete = 1;
13305 } else {
13306 sp->msg_is_complete = 0;
13307 }
13308 sp->sender_all_done = 0;
13309 sp->some_taken = 0;
13310 sp->put_last_out = 0;
13311 resv_in_first = SCTP_DATA_CHUNK_OVERHEAD(stcb);
13312 sp->data = sp->tail_mbuf = NULL;
13313 if (sp->length == 0) {
13314 goto skip_copy;
13315 }
13316 if (srcv->sinfo_keynumber_valid) {
13317 sp->auth_keyid = srcv->sinfo_keynumber;
13318 } else {
13319 sp->auth_keyid = stcb->asoc.authinfo.active_keyid;
13320 }
13321 if (sctp_auth_is_required_chunk(SCTP_DATA, stcb->asoc.peer_auth_chunks)) {
13322 sctp_auth_key_acquire(stcb, sp->auth_keyid);
13323 sp->holds_key_ref = 1;
13324 }
13325#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
13326 SCTP_SOCKET_UNLOCK(SCTP_INP_SO(stcb->sctp_ep), 0);
13327#endif
13328 *error = sctp_copy_one(sp, uio, resv_in_first);
13329#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
13330 SCTP_SOCKET_LOCK(SCTP_INP_SO(stcb->sctp_ep), 0);
13331#endif
13332 skip_copy:
13333 if (*error) {
13334#if defined(__Userspace__)
13335 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
13336#endif
13337 sctp_free_a_strmoq(stcb, sp, SCTP_SO_LOCKED);
13338#if defined(__Userspace__)
13339 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
13340#endif
13341 sp = NULL;
13342 } else {
13343 if (sp->sinfo_flags & SCTP_ADDR_OVER) {
13344 sp->net = net;
13345 atomic_add_int(&sp->net->ref_count, 1);
13346 } else {
13347 sp->net = NULL;
13348 }
13349 sctp_set_prsctp_policy(sp);
13350 }
13351out_now:
13352 return (sp);
13353}
13354
13355int
13356sctp_sosend(struct socket *so,
13357 struct sockaddr *addr,
13358 struct uio *uio,
13359 struct mbuf *top,
13360 struct mbuf *control,
13361#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
13362 int flags
13363#else
13364 int flags,
13365#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
13366 struct thread *p
13367#elif defined(_WIN32) && !defined(__Userspace__)
13368 PKTHREAD p
13369#else
13370#if defined(__Userspace__)
13371 /*
13372 * proc is a dummy in __Userspace__ and will not be passed
13373 * to sctp_lower_sosend
13374 */
13375#endif
13376 struct proc *p
13377#endif
13378#endif
13379)
13380{
13381#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
13382 struct proc *p = current_proc();
13383#endif
13384 int error, use_sndinfo = 0;
13385 struct sctp_sndrcvinfo sndrcvninfo;
13386 struct sockaddr *addr_to_use;
13387#if defined(INET) && defined(INET6)
13388 struct sockaddr_in sin;
13389#endif
13390
13391#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
13392 SCTP_SOCKET_LOCK(so, 1);
13393#endif
13394 if (control) {
13395 /* process cmsg snd/rcv info (maybe a assoc-id) */
13396 if (sctp_find_cmsg(SCTP_SNDRCV, (void *)&sndrcvninfo, control,
13397 sizeof(sndrcvninfo))) {
13398 /* got one */
13399 use_sndinfo = 1;
13400 }
13401 }
13402 addr_to_use = addr;
13403#if defined(INET) && defined(INET6)
13404 if ((addr) && (addr->sa_family == AF_INET6)) {
13405 struct sockaddr_in6 *sin6;
13406
13407 sin6 = (struct sockaddr_in6 *)addr;
13408 if (IN6_IS_ADDR_V4MAPPED(&sin6->sin6_addr)) {
13409 in6_sin6_2_sin(&sin, sin6);
13410 addr_to_use = (struct sockaddr *)&sin;
13411 }
13412 }
13413#endif
13414 error = sctp_lower_sosend(so, addr_to_use, uio, top,
13415 control,
13416 flags,
13417 use_sndinfo ? &sndrcvninfo: NULL
13418#if !defined(__Userspace__)
13419 , p
13420#endif
13421 );
13422#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
13423 SCTP_SOCKET_UNLOCK(so, 1);
13424#endif
13425 return (error);
13426}
13427
13428int
13429sctp_lower_sosend(struct socket *so,
13430 struct sockaddr *addr,
13431 struct uio *uio,
13432 struct mbuf *i_pak,
13433 struct mbuf *control,
13434 int flags,
13435 struct sctp_sndrcvinfo *srcv
13436#if !defined(__Userspace__)
13437 ,
13438#if defined(__FreeBSD__)
13439 struct thread *p
13440#elif defined(_WIN32)
13441 PKTHREAD p
13442#else
13443 struct proc *p
13444#endif
13445#endif
13446 )
13447{
13448#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
13449 struct epoch_tracker et;
13450#endif
13451 ssize_t sndlen = 0, max_len, local_add_more;
13452 int error, len;
13453 struct mbuf *top = NULL;
13454 int queue_only = 0, queue_only_for_init = 0;
13455 int free_cnt_applied = 0;
13456 int un_sent;
13457 int now_filled = 0;
13458 unsigned int inqueue_bytes = 0;
13459 struct sctp_block_entry be;
13460 struct sctp_inpcb *inp;
13461 struct sctp_tcb *stcb = NULL;
13462 struct timeval now;
13463 struct sctp_nets *net;
13464 struct sctp_association *asoc;
13465 struct sctp_inpcb *t_inp;
13466 int user_marks_eor;
13467 int create_lock_applied = 0;
13468 int nagle_applies = 0;
13469 int some_on_control = 0;
13470 int got_all_of_the_send = 0;
13471 int hold_tcblock = 0;
13472 int non_blocking = 0;
13473 ssize_t local_soresv = 0;
13474 uint16_t port;
13475 uint16_t sinfo_flags;
13476 sctp_assoc_t sinfo_assoc_id;
13477
13478 error = 0;
13479 net = NULL;
13480 stcb = NULL;
13481 asoc = NULL;
13482
13483#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
13484 sctp_lock_assert(so);
13485#endif
13486 t_inp = inp = (struct sctp_inpcb *)so->so_pcb;
13487 if (inp == NULL) {
13488 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(NULL, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, EINVAL);
13489 error = EINVAL;
13490 if (i_pak) {
13491 SCTP_RELEASE_PKT(i_pak);
13492 }
13493 return (error);
13494 }
13495 if ((uio == NULL) && (i_pak == NULL)) {
13496 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, stcb, net, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, EINVAL);
13497 return (EINVAL);
13498 }
13499 user_marks_eor = sctp_is_feature_on(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_EXPLICIT_EOR);
13500 atomic_add_int(&inp->total_sends, 1);
13501 if (uio) {
13502#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
13503#if defined(APPLE_LEOPARD)
13504 if (uio->uio_resid < 0) {
13505#else
13506 if (uio_resid(uio) < 0) {
13507#endif
13508#else
13509 if (uio->uio_resid < 0) {
13510#endif
13511 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, stcb, net, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, EINVAL);
13512 return (EINVAL);
13513 }
13514#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
13515#if defined(APPLE_LEOPARD)
13516 sndlen = uio->uio_resid;
13517#else
13518 sndlen = uio_resid(uio);
13519#endif
13520#else
13521 sndlen = uio->uio_resid;
13522#endif
13523 } else {
13524 top = SCTP_HEADER_TO_CHAIN(i_pak);
13525 sndlen = SCTP_HEADER_LEN(i_pak);
13526 }
13527 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT1, "Send called addr:%p send length %zd\n",
13528 (void *)addr,
13529 sndlen);
13530 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_TCPTYPE) &&
13531 SCTP_IS_LISTENING(inp)) {
13532 /* The listener can NOT send */
13533 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(NULL, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, ENOTCONN);
13534 error = ENOTCONN;
13535 goto out_unlocked;
13536 }
13537 /**
13538 * Pre-screen address, if one is given the sin-len
13539 * must be set correctly!
13540 */
13541 if (addr) {
13542 union sctp_sockstore *raddr = (union sctp_sockstore *)addr;
13543 switch (raddr->sa.sa_family) {
13544#ifdef INET
13545 case AF_INET:
13546#ifdef HAVE_SIN_LEN
13547 if (raddr->sin.sin_len != sizeof(struct sockaddr_in)) {
13548 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, stcb, net, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, EINVAL);
13549 error = EINVAL;
13550 goto out_unlocked;
13551 }
13552#endif
13553 port = raddr->sin.sin_port;
13554 break;
13555#endif
13556#ifdef INET6
13557 case AF_INET6:
13558#ifdef HAVE_SIN6_LEN
13559 if (raddr->sin6.sin6_len != sizeof(struct sockaddr_in6)) {
13560 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, stcb, net, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, EINVAL);
13561 error = EINVAL;
13562 goto out_unlocked;
13563 }
13564#endif
13565 port = raddr->sin6.sin6_port;
13566 break;
13567#endif
13568#if defined(__Userspace__)
13569 case AF_CONN:
13570#ifdef HAVE_SCONN_LEN
13571 if (raddr->sconn.sconn_len != sizeof(struct sockaddr_conn)) {
13572 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, stcb, net, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, EINVAL);
13573 error = EINVAL;
13574 goto out_unlocked;
13575 }
13576#endif
13577 port = raddr->sconn.sconn_port;
13578 break;
13579#endif
13580 default:
13581 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, stcb, net, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, EAFNOSUPPORT);
13582 error = EAFNOSUPPORT;
13583 goto out_unlocked;
13584 }
13585 } else
13586 port = 0;
13587
13588 if (srcv) {
13589 sinfo_flags = srcv->sinfo_flags;
13590 sinfo_assoc_id = srcv->sinfo_assoc_id;
13591 if (INVALID_SINFO_FLAG(sinfo_flags) ||
13592 PR_SCTP_INVALID_POLICY(sinfo_flags)) {
13593 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, stcb, net, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, EINVAL);
13594 error = EINVAL;
13595 goto out_unlocked;
13596 }
13597 if (srcv->sinfo_flags)
13598 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_sends_with_flags);
13599 } else {
13600 sinfo_flags = inp->def_send.sinfo_flags;
13601 sinfo_assoc_id = inp->def_send.sinfo_assoc_id;
13602 }
13603#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
13604 if (flags & MSG_EOR) {
13605 sinfo_flags |= SCTP_EOR;
13606 }
13607 if (flags & MSG_EOF) {
13608 sinfo_flags |= SCTP_EOF;
13609 }
13610#endif
13611 if (sinfo_flags & SCTP_SENDALL) {
13612 /* its a sendall */
13613 error = sctp_sendall(inp, uio, top, srcv);
13614 top = NULL;
13615 goto out_unlocked;
13616 }
13617 if ((sinfo_flags & SCTP_ADDR_OVER) && (addr == NULL)) {
13618 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, stcb, net, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, EINVAL);
13619 error = EINVAL;
13620 goto out_unlocked;
13621 }
13622 /* now we must find the assoc */
13623 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_CONNECTED) ||
13624 (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_IN_TCPPOOL)) {
13625 SCTP_INP_RLOCK(inp);
13626 stcb = LIST_FIRST(&inp->sctp_asoc_list);
13627 if (stcb) {
13628 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
13629 hold_tcblock = 1;
13630 }
13631 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
13632 } else if (sinfo_assoc_id) {
13633 stcb = sctp_findassociation_ep_asocid(inp, sinfo_assoc_id, 1);
13634 if (stcb != NULL) {
13635 hold_tcblock = 1;
13636 }
13637 } else if (addr) {
13638 /*-
13639 * Since we did not use findep we must
13640 * increment it, and if we don't find a tcb
13641 * decrement it.
13642 */
13643 SCTP_INP_WLOCK(inp);
13644 SCTP_INP_INCR_REF(inp);
13645 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
13646 stcb = sctp_findassociation_ep_addr(&t_inp, addr, &net, NULL, NULL);
13647 if (stcb == NULL) {
13648 SCTP_INP_WLOCK(inp);
13649 SCTP_INP_DECR_REF(inp);
13650 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
13651 } else {
13652 hold_tcblock = 1;
13653 }
13654 }
13655 if ((stcb == NULL) && (addr)) {
13656 /* Possible implicit send? */
13657 SCTP_ASOC_CREATE_LOCK(inp);
13658 create_lock_applied = 1;
13659 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_GONE) ||
13660 (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_ALLGONE)) {
13661 /* Should I really unlock ? */
13662 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(NULL, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, EINVAL);
13663 error = EINVAL;
13664 goto out_unlocked;
13665 }
13666 if (((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_BOUND_V6) == 0) &&
13667 (addr->sa_family == AF_INET6)) {
13668 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, stcb, net, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, EINVAL);
13669 error = EINVAL;
13670 goto out_unlocked;
13671 }
13672 SCTP_INP_WLOCK(inp);
13673 SCTP_INP_INCR_REF(inp);
13674 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
13675 /* With the lock applied look again */
13676 stcb = sctp_findassociation_ep_addr(&t_inp, addr, &net, NULL, NULL);
13677#if defined(INET) || defined(INET6)
13678 if ((stcb == NULL) && (control != NULL) && (port > 0)) {
13679 stcb = sctp_findassociation_cmsgs(&t_inp, port, control, &net, &error);
13680 }
13681#endif
13682 if (stcb == NULL) {
13683 SCTP_INP_WLOCK(inp);
13684 SCTP_INP_DECR_REF(inp);
13685 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
13686 } else {
13687 hold_tcblock = 1;
13688 }
13689 if (error) {
13690 goto out_unlocked;
13691 }
13692 if (t_inp != inp) {
13693 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, stcb, net, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, ENOTCONN);
13694 error = ENOTCONN;
13695 goto out_unlocked;
13696 }
13697 }
13698 if (stcb == NULL) {
13699 if (addr == NULL) {
13700 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, stcb, net, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, ENOENT);
13701 error = ENOENT;
13702 goto out_unlocked;
13703 } else {
13704 /* We must go ahead and start the INIT process */
13705 uint32_t vrf_id;
13706
13707 if ((sinfo_flags & SCTP_ABORT) ||
13708 ((sinfo_flags & SCTP_EOF) && (sndlen == 0))) {
13709 /*-
13710 * User asks to abort a non-existant assoc,
13711 * or EOF a non-existant assoc with no data
13712 */
13713 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, stcb, net, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, ENOENT);
13714 error = ENOENT;
13715 goto out_unlocked;
13716 }
13717 /* get an asoc/stcb struct */
13718 vrf_id = inp->def_vrf_id;
13719#ifdef INVARIANTS
13720 if (create_lock_applied == 0) {
13721 panic("Error, should hold create lock and I don't?");
13722 }
13723#endif
13724 stcb = sctp_aloc_assoc(inp, addr, &error, 0, vrf_id,
13725 inp->sctp_ep.pre_open_stream_count,
13726 inp->sctp_ep.port,
13727#if !defined(__Userspace__)
13728 p,
13729#else
13730 (struct proc *)NULL,
13731#endif
13732 SCTP_INITIALIZE_AUTH_PARAMS);
13733 if (stcb == NULL) {
13734 /* Error is setup for us in the call */
13735 goto out_unlocked;
13736 }
13737 if (stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_TCPTYPE) {
13738 stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_flags |= SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_CONNECTED;
13739 /* Set the connected flag so we can queue data */
13740 soisconnecting(so);
13741 }
13742 hold_tcblock = 1;
13743 if (create_lock_applied) {
13744 SCTP_ASOC_CREATE_UNLOCK(inp);
13745 create_lock_applied = 0;
13746 } else {
13747 SCTP_PRINTF("Huh-3? create lock should have been on??\n");
13748 }
13749 /* Turn on queue only flag to prevent data from being sent */
13750 queue_only = 1;
13751 asoc = &stcb->asoc;
13752 SCTP_SET_STATE(stcb, SCTP_STATE_COOKIE_WAIT);
13753 (void)SCTP_GETTIME_TIMEVAL(&asoc->time_entered);
13754
13755 if (control) {
13756 if (sctp_process_cmsgs_for_init(stcb, control, &error)) {
13757 sctp_free_assoc(inp, stcb, SCTP_PCBFREE_FORCE,
13758 SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT + SCTP_LOC_6);
13759 hold_tcblock = 0;
13760 stcb = NULL;
13761 goto out_unlocked;
13762 }
13763 }
13764 /* out with the INIT */
13765 queue_only_for_init = 1;
13766 /*-
13767 * we may want to dig in after this call and adjust the MTU
13768 * value. It defaulted to 1500 (constant) but the ro
13769 * structure may now have an update and thus we may need to
13770 * change it BEFORE we append the message.
13771 */
13772 }
13773 } else
13774 asoc = &stcb->asoc;
13775 if (srcv == NULL) {
13776 srcv = (struct sctp_sndrcvinfo *)&asoc->def_send;
13777 sinfo_flags = srcv->sinfo_flags;
13778#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
13779 if (flags & MSG_EOR) {
13780 sinfo_flags |= SCTP_EOR;
13781 }
13782 if (flags & MSG_EOF) {
13783 sinfo_flags |= SCTP_EOF;
13784 }
13785#endif
13786 }
13787 if (sinfo_flags & SCTP_ADDR_OVER) {
13788 if (addr)
13789 net = sctp_findnet(stcb, addr);
13790 else
13791 net = NULL;
13792 if ((net == NULL) ||
13793 ((port != 0) && (port != stcb->rport))) {
13794 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, stcb, net, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, EINVAL);
13795 error = EINVAL;
13796 goto out_unlocked;
13797 }
13798 } else {
13799 if (stcb->asoc.alternate) {
13800 net = stcb->asoc.alternate;
13801 } else {
13802 net = stcb->asoc.primary_destination;
13803 }
13804 }
13805 atomic_add_int(&stcb->total_sends, 1);
13806 /* Keep the stcb from being freed under our feet */
13807 atomic_add_int(&asoc->refcnt, 1);
13808 free_cnt_applied = 1;
13809
13810 if (sctp_is_feature_on(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_NO_FRAGMENT)) {
13811 if (sndlen > (ssize_t)asoc->smallest_mtu) {
13812 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, stcb, net, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, EMSGSIZE);
13813 error = EMSGSIZE;
13814 goto out_unlocked;
13815 }
13816 }
13817#if defined(__Userspace__)
13818 if (inp->recv_callback) {
13819 non_blocking = 1;
13820 }
13821#endif
13822 if (SCTP_SO_IS_NBIO(so)
13823#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
13824 || (flags & (MSG_NBIO | MSG_DONTWAIT)) != 0
13825#endif
13826 ) {
13827 non_blocking = 1;
13828 }
13829 /* would we block? */
13830 if (non_blocking) {
13831 ssize_t amount;
13832
13833 if (hold_tcblock == 0) {
13834 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
13835 hold_tcblock = 1;
13836 }
13837 inqueue_bytes = stcb->asoc.total_output_queue_size - (stcb->asoc.chunks_on_out_queue * SCTP_DATA_CHUNK_OVERHEAD(stcb));
13838 if (user_marks_eor == 0) {
13839 amount = sndlen;
13840 } else {
13841 amount = 1;
13842 }
13843 if ((SCTP_SB_LIMIT_SND(so) < (amount + inqueue_bytes + stcb->asoc.sb_send_resv)) ||
13844 (stcb->asoc.chunks_on_out_queue >= SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_max_chunks_on_queue))) {
13845 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, stcb, net, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, EWOULDBLOCK);
13846 if (sndlen > (ssize_t)SCTP_SB_LIMIT_SND(so))
13847 error = EMSGSIZE;
13848 else
13849 error = EWOULDBLOCK;
13850 goto out_unlocked;
13851 }
13852 stcb->asoc.sb_send_resv += (uint32_t)sndlen;
13853 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
13854 hold_tcblock = 0;
13855 } else {
13856 atomic_add_int(&stcb->asoc.sb_send_resv, sndlen);
13857 }
13858 local_soresv = sndlen;
13859 if (stcb->asoc.state & SCTP_STATE_ABOUT_TO_BE_FREED) {
13860 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(NULL, stcb, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, ECONNRESET);
13861 error = ECONNRESET;
13862 goto out_unlocked;
13863 }
13864 if (create_lock_applied) {
13865 SCTP_ASOC_CREATE_UNLOCK(inp);
13866 create_lock_applied = 0;
13867 }
13868 /* Is the stream no. valid? */
13869 if (srcv->sinfo_stream >= asoc->streamoutcnt) {
13870 /* Invalid stream number */
13871 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, stcb, net, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, EINVAL);
13872 error = EINVAL;
13873 goto out_unlocked;
13874 }
13875 if ((asoc->strmout[srcv->sinfo_stream].state != SCTP_STREAM_OPEN) &&
13876 (asoc->strmout[srcv->sinfo_stream].state != SCTP_STREAM_OPENING)) {
13877 /*
13878 * Can't queue any data while stream reset is underway.
13879 */
13880 if (asoc->strmout[srcv->sinfo_stream].state > SCTP_STREAM_OPEN) {
13881 error = EAGAIN;
13882 } else {
13883 error = EINVAL;
13884 }
13885 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, stcb, net, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, error);
13886 goto out_unlocked;
13887 }
13888 if ((SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_COOKIE_WAIT) ||
13889 (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_COOKIE_ECHOED)) {
13890 queue_only = 1;
13891 }
13892 /* we are now done with all control */
13893 if (control) {
13894 sctp_m_freem(control);
13895 control = NULL;
13896 }
13897 if ((SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_SENT) ||
13898 (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_RECEIVED) ||
13899 (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_ACK_SENT) ||
13900 (asoc->state & SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_PENDING)) {
13901 if (sinfo_flags & SCTP_ABORT) {
13902 ;
13903 } else {
13904 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(NULL, stcb, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, ECONNRESET);
13905 error = ECONNRESET;
13906 goto out_unlocked;
13907 }
13908 }
13909 /* Ok, we will attempt a msgsnd :> */
13910#if !(defined(_WIN32) || defined(__Userspace__))
13911 if (p) {
13912#if defined(__FreeBSD__)
13913 p->td_ru.ru_msgsnd++;
13914#else
13915 p->p_stats->p_ru.ru_msgsnd++;
13916#endif
13917 }
13918#endif
13919 /* Are we aborting? */
13920 if (sinfo_flags & SCTP_ABORT) {
13921 struct mbuf *mm;
13922 ssize_t tot_demand, tot_out = 0, max_out;
13923
13924 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_sends_with_abort);
13925 if ((SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_COOKIE_WAIT) ||
13926 (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_COOKIE_ECHOED)) {
13927 /* It has to be up before we abort */
13928 /* how big is the user initiated abort? */
13929 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, stcb, net, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, EINVAL);
13930 error = EINVAL;
13931 goto out;
13932 }
13933 if (hold_tcblock) {
13934 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
13935 hold_tcblock = 0;
13936 }
13937 if (top) {
13938 struct mbuf *cntm = NULL;
13939
13940 mm = sctp_get_mbuf_for_msg(sizeof(struct sctp_paramhdr), 0, M_WAITOK, 1, MT_DATA);
13941 if (sndlen != 0) {
13942 for (cntm = top; cntm; cntm = SCTP_BUF_NEXT(cntm)) {
13943 tot_out += SCTP_BUF_LEN(cntm);
13944 }
13945 }
13946 } else {
13947 /* Must fit in a MTU */
13948 tot_out = sndlen;
13949 tot_demand = (tot_out + sizeof(struct sctp_paramhdr));
13950 if (tot_demand > SCTP_DEFAULT_ADD_MORE) {
13951 /* To big */
13952 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(NULL, stcb, net, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, EMSGSIZE);
13953 error = EMSGSIZE;
13954 goto out;
13955 }
13956 mm = sctp_get_mbuf_for_msg((unsigned int)tot_demand, 0, M_WAITOK, 1, MT_DATA);
13957 }
13958 if (mm == NULL) {
13959 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(NULL, stcb, net, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, ENOMEM);
13960 error = ENOMEM;
13961 goto out;
13962 }
13963 max_out = asoc->smallest_mtu - sizeof(struct sctp_paramhdr);
13964 max_out -= sizeof(struct sctp_abort_msg);
13965 if (tot_out > max_out) {
13966 tot_out = max_out;
13967 }
13968 if (mm) {
13969 struct sctp_paramhdr *ph;
13970
13971 /* now move forward the data pointer */
13972 ph = mtod(mm, struct sctp_paramhdr *);
13973 ph->param_type = htons(SCTP_CAUSE_USER_INITIATED_ABT);
13974 ph->param_length = htons((uint16_t)(sizeof(struct sctp_paramhdr) + tot_out));
13975 ph++;
13976 SCTP_BUF_LEN(mm) = (int)(tot_out + sizeof(struct sctp_paramhdr));
13977 if (top == NULL) {
13978#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
13979 SCTP_SOCKET_UNLOCK(so, 0);
13980#endif
13981 error = uiomove((caddr_t)ph, (int)tot_out, uio);
13982#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
13983 SCTP_SOCKET_LOCK(so, 0);
13984#endif
13985 if (error) {
13986 /*-
13987 * Here if we can't get his data we
13988 * still abort we just don't get to
13989 * send the users note :-0
13990 */
13991 sctp_m_freem(mm);
13992 mm = NULL;
13993 }
13994 } else {
13995 if (sndlen != 0) {
13996 SCTP_BUF_NEXT(mm) = top;
13997 }
13998 }
13999 }
14000 if (hold_tcblock == 0) {
14001 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
14002 }
14003 atomic_add_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, -1);
14004 free_cnt_applied = 0;
14005 /* release this lock, otherwise we hang on ourselves */
14006#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
14007 NET_EPOCH_ENTER(et);
14008#endif
14009 sctp_abort_an_association(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, mm, SCTP_SO_LOCKED);
14010#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
14011 NET_EPOCH_EXIT(et);
14012#endif
14013 /* now relock the stcb so everything is sane */
14014 hold_tcblock = 0;
14015 stcb = NULL;
14016 /* In this case top is already chained to mm
14017 * avoid double free, since we free it below if
14018 * top != NULL and driver would free it after sending
14019 * the packet out
14020 */
14021 if (sndlen != 0) {
14022 top = NULL;
14023 }
14024 goto out_unlocked;
14025 }
14026 /* Calculate the maximum we can send */
14027 inqueue_bytes = stcb->asoc.total_output_queue_size - (stcb->asoc.chunks_on_out_queue * SCTP_DATA_CHUNK_OVERHEAD(stcb));
14028 if (SCTP_SB_LIMIT_SND(so) > inqueue_bytes) {
14029 max_len = SCTP_SB_LIMIT_SND(so) - inqueue_bytes;
14030 } else {
14031 max_len = 0;
14032 }
14033 if (hold_tcblock) {
14034 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
14035 hold_tcblock = 0;
14036 }
14037 if (asoc->strmout == NULL) {
14038 /* huh? software error */
14039 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, stcb, net, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, EFAULT);
14040 error = EFAULT;
14041 goto out_unlocked;
14042 }
14043
14044 /* Unless E_EOR mode is on, we must make a send FIT in one call. */
14045 if ((user_marks_eor == 0) &&
14046 (sndlen > (ssize_t)SCTP_SB_LIMIT_SND(stcb->sctp_socket))) {
14047 /* It will NEVER fit */
14048 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(NULL, stcb, net, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, EMSGSIZE);
14049 error = EMSGSIZE;
14050 goto out_unlocked;
14051 }
14052 if ((uio == NULL) && user_marks_eor) {
14053 /*-
14054 * We do not support eeor mode for
14055 * sending with mbuf chains (like sendfile).
14056 */
14057 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(NULL, stcb, net, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, EINVAL);
14058 error = EINVAL;
14059 goto out_unlocked;
14060 }
14061
14062 if (user_marks_eor) {
14063 local_add_more = (ssize_t)min(SCTP_SB_LIMIT_SND(so), SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_add_more_threshold));
14064 } else {
14065 /*-
14066 * For non-eeor the whole message must fit in
14067 * the socket send buffer.
14068 */
14069 local_add_more = sndlen;
14070 }
14071 len = 0;
14072 if (non_blocking) {
14073 goto skip_preblock;
14074 }
14075 if (((max_len <= local_add_more) &&
14076 ((ssize_t)SCTP_SB_LIMIT_SND(so) >= local_add_more)) ||
14077 (max_len == 0) ||
14078 ((stcb->asoc.chunks_on_out_queue+stcb->asoc.stream_queue_cnt) >= SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_max_chunks_on_queue))) {
14079 /* No room right now ! */
14080 SOCKBUF_LOCK(&so->so_snd);
14081 inqueue_bytes = stcb->asoc.total_output_queue_size - (stcb->asoc.chunks_on_out_queue * SCTP_DATA_CHUNK_OVERHEAD(stcb));
14082 while ((SCTP_SB_LIMIT_SND(so) < (inqueue_bytes + local_add_more)) ||
14083 ((stcb->asoc.stream_queue_cnt + stcb->asoc.chunks_on_out_queue) >= SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_max_chunks_on_queue))) {
14084 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT1,"pre_block limit:%u <(inq:%d + %zd) || (%d+%d > %d)\n",
14085 (unsigned int)SCTP_SB_LIMIT_SND(so),
14086 inqueue_bytes,
14087 local_add_more,
14088 stcb->asoc.stream_queue_cnt,
14089 stcb->asoc.chunks_on_out_queue,
14090 SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_max_chunks_on_queue));
14091 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_BLK_LOGGING_ENABLE) {
14092 sctp_log_block(SCTP_BLOCK_LOG_INTO_BLKA, asoc, sndlen);
14093 }
14094 be.error = 0;
14095#if !(defined(_WIN32) && !defined(__Userspace__))
14096 stcb->block_entry = &be;
14097#endif
14098 error = sbwait(&so->so_snd);
14099 stcb->block_entry = NULL;
14100 if (error || so->so_error || be.error) {
14101 if (error == 0) {
14102 if (so->so_error)
14103 error = so->so_error;
14104 if (be.error) {
14105 error = be.error;
14106 }
14107 }
14108 SOCKBUF_UNLOCK(&so->so_snd);
14109 goto out_unlocked;
14110 }
14111 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_BLK_LOGGING_ENABLE) {
14112 sctp_log_block(SCTP_BLOCK_LOG_OUTOF_BLK,
14113 asoc, stcb->asoc.total_output_queue_size);
14114 }
14115 if (stcb->asoc.state & SCTP_STATE_ABOUT_TO_BE_FREED) {
14116 SOCKBUF_UNLOCK(&so->so_snd);
14117 goto out_unlocked;
14118 }
14119 inqueue_bytes = stcb->asoc.total_output_queue_size - (stcb->asoc.chunks_on_out_queue * SCTP_DATA_CHUNK_OVERHEAD(stcb));
14120 }
14121 if (SCTP_SB_LIMIT_SND(so) > inqueue_bytes) {
14122 max_len = SCTP_SB_LIMIT_SND(so) - inqueue_bytes;
14123 } else {
14124 max_len = 0;
14125 }
14126 SOCKBUF_UNLOCK(&so->so_snd);
14127 }
14128
14129skip_preblock:
14130 if (stcb->asoc.state & SCTP_STATE_ABOUT_TO_BE_FREED) {
14131 goto out_unlocked;
14132 }
14133#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
14134 error = sblock(&so->so_snd, SBLOCKWAIT(flags));
14135#endif
14136 /* sndlen covers for mbuf case
14137 * uio_resid covers for the non-mbuf case
14138 * NOTE: uio will be null when top/mbuf is passed
14139 */
14140 if (sndlen == 0) {
14141 if (sinfo_flags & SCTP_EOF) {
14142 got_all_of_the_send = 1;
14143 goto dataless_eof;
14144 } else {
14145 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, stcb, net, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, EINVAL);
14146 error = EINVAL;
14147 goto out;
14148 }
14149 }
14150 if (top == NULL) {
14151 struct sctp_stream_queue_pending *sp;
14152 struct sctp_stream_out *strm;
14153 uint32_t sndout;
14154
14155 SCTP_TCB_SEND_LOCK(stcb);
14156 if ((asoc->stream_locked) &&
14157 (asoc->stream_locked_on != srcv->sinfo_stream)) {
14158 SCTP_TCB_SEND_UNLOCK(stcb);
14159 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, stcb, net, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, EINVAL);
14160 error = EINVAL;
14161 goto out;
14162 }
14163 strm = &stcb->asoc.strmout[srcv->sinfo_stream];
14164 if (strm->last_msg_incomplete == 0) {
14165 do_a_copy_in:
14166 SCTP_TCB_SEND_UNLOCK(stcb);
14167 sp = sctp_copy_it_in(stcb, asoc, srcv, uio, net, max_len, user_marks_eor, &error);
14168 if (error) {
14169 goto out;
14170 }
14171 SCTP_TCB_SEND_LOCK(stcb);
14172 if (sp->msg_is_complete) {
14173 strm->last_msg_incomplete = 0;
14174 asoc->stream_locked = 0;
14175 } else {
14176 /* Just got locked to this guy in
14177 * case of an interrupt.
14178 */
14179 strm->last_msg_incomplete = 1;
14180 if (stcb->asoc.idata_supported == 0) {
14181 asoc->stream_locked = 1;
14182 asoc->stream_locked_on = srcv->sinfo_stream;
14183 }
14184 sp->sender_all_done = 0;
14185 }
14186 sctp_snd_sb_alloc(stcb, sp->length);
14187 atomic_add_int(&asoc->stream_queue_cnt, 1);
14188 if (sinfo_flags & SCTP_UNORDERED) {
14189 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_sends_with_unord);
14190 }
14191 sp->processing = 1;
14192 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&strm->outqueue, sp, next);
14193 stcb->asoc.ss_functions.sctp_ss_add_to_stream(stcb, asoc, strm, sp, 1);
14194 } else {
14195 sp = TAILQ_LAST(&strm->outqueue, sctp_streamhead);
14196 if (sp == NULL) {
14197 /* ???? Huh ??? last msg is gone */
14198#ifdef INVARIANTS
14199 panic("Warning: Last msg marked incomplete, yet nothing left?");
14200#else
14201 SCTP_PRINTF("Warning: Last msg marked incomplete, yet nothing left?\n");
14202 strm->last_msg_incomplete = 0;
14203#endif
14204 goto do_a_copy_in;
14205 }
14206 if (sp->processing) {
14207 SCTP_TCB_SEND_UNLOCK(stcb);
14208 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, stcb, net, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, EINVAL);
14209 error = EINVAL;
14210 goto out;
14211 } else {
14212 sp->processing = 1;
14213 }
14214 }
14215 SCTP_TCB_SEND_UNLOCK(stcb);
14216#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
14217#if defined(APPLE_LEOPARD)
14218 while (uio->uio_resid > 0) {
14219#else
14220 while (uio_resid(uio) > 0) {
14221#endif
14222#else
14223 while (uio->uio_resid > 0) {
14224#endif
14225 /* How much room do we have? */
14226 struct mbuf *new_tail, *mm;
14227
14228 inqueue_bytes = stcb->asoc.total_output_queue_size - (stcb->asoc.chunks_on_out_queue * SCTP_DATA_CHUNK_OVERHEAD(stcb));
14229 if (SCTP_SB_LIMIT_SND(so) > inqueue_bytes)
14230 max_len = SCTP_SB_LIMIT_SND(so) - inqueue_bytes;
14231 else
14232 max_len = 0;
14233
14234 if ((max_len > (ssize_t)SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_add_more_threshold)) ||
14235 (max_len && (SCTP_SB_LIMIT_SND(so) < SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_add_more_threshold))) ||
14236#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
14237#if defined(APPLE_LEOPARD)
14238 (uio->uio_resid && (uio->uio_resid <= max_len))) {
14239#else
14240 (uio_resid(uio) && (uio_resid(uio) <= max_len))) {
14241#endif
14242#else
14243 (uio->uio_resid && (uio->uio_resid <= max_len))) {
14244#endif
14245 sndout = 0;
14246 new_tail = NULL;
14247 if (hold_tcblock) {
14248 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
14249 hold_tcblock = 0;
14250 }
14251#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
14252 SCTP_SOCKET_UNLOCK(so, 0);
14253#endif
14254#if defined(__FreeBSD__) || defined(__Userspace__)
14255 mm = sctp_copy_resume(uio, (int)max_len, user_marks_eor, &error, &sndout, &new_tail);
14256#else
14257 mm = sctp_copy_resume(uio, (int)max_len, &error, &sndout, &new_tail);
14258#endif
14259#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
14260 SCTP_SOCKET_LOCK(so, 0);
14261#endif
14262 if ((mm == NULL) || error) {
14263 if (mm) {
14264 sctp_m_freem(mm);
14265 }
14266 SCTP_TCB_SEND_LOCK(stcb);
14267 if (((stcb->asoc.state & SCTP_STATE_ABOUT_TO_BE_FREED) == 0) &&
14268 ((stcb->asoc.state & SCTP_STATE_WAS_ABORTED) == 0) &&
14269 (sp != NULL)) {
14270 sp->processing = 0;
14271 }
14272 SCTP_TCB_SEND_UNLOCK(stcb);
14273 goto out;
14274 }
14275 /* Update the mbuf and count */
14276 SCTP_TCB_SEND_LOCK(stcb);
14277 if ((stcb->asoc.state & SCTP_STATE_ABOUT_TO_BE_FREED) ||
14278 (stcb->asoc.state & SCTP_STATE_WAS_ABORTED)) {
14279 /* we need to get out.
14280 * Peer probably aborted.
14281 */
14282 sctp_m_freem(mm);
14283 if (stcb->asoc.state & SCTP_STATE_WAS_ABORTED) {
14284 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(NULL, stcb, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_OUTPUT, ECONNRESET);
14285 error = ECONNRESET;
14286 }
14287 SCTP_TCB_SEND_UNLOCK(stcb);
14288 goto out;
14289 }
14290 if (sp->tail_mbuf) {
14291 /* tack it to the end */
14292 SCTP_BUF_NEXT(sp->tail_mbuf) = mm;
14293 sp->tail_mbuf = new_tail;
14294 } else {
14295 /* A stolen mbuf */
14296 sp->data = mm;
14297 sp->tail_mbuf = new_tail;
14298 }
14299 sctp_snd_sb_alloc(stcb, sndout);
14300 atomic_add_int(&sp->length, sndout);
14301 len += sndout;
14302 if (sinfo_flags & SCTP_SACK_IMMEDIATELY) {
14303 sp->sinfo_flags |= SCTP_SACK_IMMEDIATELY;
14304 }
14305
14306 /* Did we reach EOR? */
14307#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
14308#if defined(APPLE_LEOPARD)
14309 if ((uio->uio_resid == 0) &&
14310#else
14311 if ((uio_resid(uio) == 0) &&
14312#endif
14313#else
14314 if ((uio->uio_resid == 0) &&
14315#endif
14316 ((user_marks_eor == 0) ||
14317 (sinfo_flags & SCTP_EOF) ||
14318 (user_marks_eor && (sinfo_flags & SCTP_EOR)))) {
14319 sp->msg_is_complete = 1;
14320 } else {
14321 sp->msg_is_complete = 0;
14322 }
14323 SCTP_TCB_SEND_UNLOCK(stcb);
14324 }
14325#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
14326#if defined(APPLE_LEOPARD)
14327 if (uio->uio_resid == 0) {
14328#else
14329 if (uio_resid(uio) == 0) {
14330#endif
14331#else
14332 if (uio->uio_resid == 0) {
14333#endif
14334 /* got it all? */
14335 continue;
14336 }
14337 /* PR-SCTP? */
14338 if ((asoc->prsctp_supported) && (asoc->sent_queue_cnt_removeable > 0)) {
14339 /* This is ugly but we must assure locking order */
14340 if (hold_tcblock == 0) {
14341 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
14342 hold_tcblock = 1;
14343 }
14344 sctp_prune_prsctp(stcb, asoc, srcv, (int)sndlen);
14345 inqueue_bytes = stcb->asoc.total_output_queue_size - (stcb->asoc.chunks_on_out_queue * SCTP_DATA_CHUNK_OVERHEAD(stcb));
14346 if (SCTP_SB_LIMIT_SND(so) > inqueue_bytes)
14347 max_len = SCTP_SB_LIMIT_SND(so) - inqueue_bytes;
14348 else
14349 max_len = 0;
14350 if (max_len > 0) {
14351 continue;
14352 }
14353 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
14354 hold_tcblock = 0;
14355 }
14356 /* wait for space now */
14357 if (non_blocking) {
14358 /* Non-blocking io in place out */
14359 SCTP_TCB_SEND_LOCK(stcb);
14360 if (sp != NULL) {
14361 sp->processing = 0;
14362 }
14363 SCTP_TCB_SEND_UNLOCK(stcb);
14364 goto skip_out_eof;
14365 }
14366 /* What about the INIT, send it maybe */
14367 if (queue_only_for_init) {
14368 if (hold_tcblock == 0) {
14369 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
14370 hold_tcblock = 1;
14371 }
14372 if (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_OPEN) {
14373 /* a collision took us forward? */
14374 queue_only = 0;
14375 } else {
14376#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
14377 NET_EPOCH_ENTER(et);
14378#endif
14379 sctp_send_initiate(inp, stcb, SCTP_SO_LOCKED);
14380#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
14381 NET_EPOCH_EXIT(et);
14382#endif
14383 SCTP_SET_STATE(stcb, SCTP_STATE_COOKIE_WAIT);
14384 queue_only = 1;
14385 }
14386 }
14387 if ((net->flight_size > net->cwnd) &&
14388 (asoc->sctp_cmt_on_off == 0)) {
14389 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_send_cwnd_avoid);
14390 queue_only = 1;
14391 } else if (asoc->ifp_had_enobuf) {
14392 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_ifnomemqueued);
14393 if (net->flight_size > (2 * net->mtu)) {
14394 queue_only = 1;
14395 }
14396 asoc->ifp_had_enobuf = 0;
14397 }
14398 un_sent = stcb->asoc.total_output_queue_size - stcb->asoc.total_flight;
14399 if ((sctp_is_feature_off(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_NODELAY)) &&
14400 (stcb->asoc.total_flight > 0) &&
14401 (stcb->asoc.stream_queue_cnt < SCTP_MAX_DATA_BUNDLING) &&
14402 (un_sent < (int)(stcb->asoc.smallest_mtu - SCTP_MIN_OVERHEAD))) {
14403 /*-
14404 * Ok, Nagle is set on and we have data outstanding.
14405 * Don't send anything and let SACKs drive out the
14406 * data unless we have a "full" segment to send.
14407 */
14408 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_NAGLE_LOGGING_ENABLE) {
14409 sctp_log_nagle_event(stcb, SCTP_NAGLE_APPLIED);
14410 }
14411 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_naglequeued);
14412 nagle_applies = 1;
14413 } else {
14414 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_NAGLE_LOGGING_ENABLE) {
14415 if (sctp_is_feature_off(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_NODELAY))
14416 sctp_log_nagle_event(stcb, SCTP_NAGLE_SKIPPED);
14417 }
14418 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_naglesent);
14419 nagle_applies = 0;
14420 }
14421 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_BLK_LOGGING_ENABLE) {
14422 sctp_misc_ints(SCTP_CWNDLOG_PRESEND, queue_only_for_init, queue_only,
14423 nagle_applies, un_sent);
14424 sctp_misc_ints(SCTP_CWNDLOG_PRESEND, stcb->asoc.total_output_queue_size,
14425 stcb->asoc.total_flight,
14426 stcb->asoc.chunks_on_out_queue, stcb->asoc.total_flight_count);
14427 }
14428 if (queue_only_for_init)
14429 queue_only_for_init = 0;
14430 if ((queue_only == 0) && (nagle_applies == 0)) {
14431 /*-
14432 * need to start chunk output
14433 * before blocking.. note that if
14434 * a lock is already applied, then
14435 * the input via the net is happening
14436 * and I don't need to start output :-D
14437 */
14438#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
14439 NET_EPOCH_ENTER(et);
14440#endif
14441 if (hold_tcblock == 0) {
14442 if (SCTP_TCB_TRYLOCK(stcb)) {
14443 hold_tcblock = 1;
14444 sctp_chunk_output(inp,
14445 stcb,
14446 SCTP_OUTPUT_FROM_USR_SEND, SCTP_SO_LOCKED);
14447 }
14448 } else {
14449 sctp_chunk_output(inp,
14450 stcb,
14451 SCTP_OUTPUT_FROM_USR_SEND, SCTP_SO_LOCKED);
14452 }
14453#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
14454 NET_EPOCH_EXIT(et);
14455#endif
14456 }
14457 if (hold_tcblock == 1) {
14458 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
14459 hold_tcblock = 0;
14460 }
14461 SOCKBUF_LOCK(&so->so_snd);
14462 /*-
14463 * This is a bit strange, but I think it will
14464 * work. The total_output_queue_size is locked and
14465 * protected by the TCB_LOCK, which we just released.
14466 * There is a race that can occur between releasing it
14467 * above, and me getting the socket lock, where sacks
14468 * come in but we have not put the SB_WAIT on the
14469 * so_snd buffer to get the wakeup. After the LOCK
14470 * is applied the sack_processing will also need to
14471 * LOCK the so->so_snd to do the actual sowwakeup(). So
14472 * once we have the socket buffer lock if we recheck the
14473 * size we KNOW we will get to sleep safely with the
14474 * wakeup flag in place.
14475 */
14476 inqueue_bytes = stcb->asoc.total_output_queue_size - (stcb->asoc.chunks_on_out_queue * SCTP_DATA_CHUNK_OVERHEAD(stcb));
14477 if (SCTP_SB_LIMIT_SND(so) <= (inqueue_bytes +
14478 min(SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_add_more_threshold), SCTP_SB_LIMIT_SND(so)))) {
14479 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_BLK_LOGGING_ENABLE) {
14480#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
14481#if defined(APPLE_LEOPARD)
14482 sctp_log_block(SCTP_BLOCK_LOG_INTO_BLK,
14483 asoc, uio->uio_resid);
14484#else
14485 sctp_log_block(SCTP_BLOCK_LOG_INTO_BLK,
14486 asoc, uio_resid(uio));
14487#endif
14488#else
14489 sctp_log_block(SCTP_BLOCK_LOG_INTO_BLK,
14490 asoc, uio->uio_resid);
14491#endif
14492 }
14493 be.error = 0;
14494#if !(defined(_WIN32) && !defined(__Userspace__))
14495 stcb->block_entry = &be;
14496#endif
14497#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
14498 sbunlock(&so->so_snd, 1);
14499#endif
14500 error = sbwait(&so->so_snd);
14501 stcb->block_entry = NULL;
14502
14503 if (error || so->so_error || be.error) {
14504 if (error == 0) {
14505 if (so->so_error)
14506 error = so->so_error;
14507 if (be.error) {
14508 error = be.error;
14509 }
14510 }
14511 SOCKBUF_UNLOCK(&so->so_snd);
14512 SCTP_TCB_SEND_LOCK(stcb);
14513 if (((stcb->asoc.state & SCTP_STATE_ABOUT_TO_BE_FREED) == 0) &&
14514 ((stcb->asoc.state & SCTP_STATE_WAS_ABORTED) == 0) &&
14515 (sp != NULL)) {
14516 sp->processing = 0;
14517 }
14518 SCTP_TCB_SEND_UNLOCK(stcb);
14519 goto out_unlocked;
14520 }
14521
14522#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
14523 error = sblock(&so->so_snd, SBLOCKWAIT(flags));
14524#endif
14525 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_BLK_LOGGING_ENABLE) {
14526 sctp_log_block(SCTP_BLOCK_LOG_OUTOF_BLK,
14527 asoc, stcb->asoc.total_output_queue_size);
14528 }
14529 }
14530 SOCKBUF_UNLOCK(&so->so_snd);
14531 SCTP_TCB_SEND_LOCK(stcb);
14532 if ((stcb->asoc.state & SCTP_STATE_ABOUT_TO_BE_FREED) ||
14533 (stcb->asoc.state & SCTP_STATE_WAS_ABORTED)) {
14534 SCTP_TCB_SEND_UNLOCK(stcb);
14535 goto out_unlocked;
14536 }
14537 SCTP_TCB_SEND_UNLOCK(stcb);
14538 }
14539 SCTP_TCB_SEND_LOCK(stcb);
14540 if ((stcb->asoc.state & SCTP_STATE_ABOUT_TO_BE_FREED) ||
14541 (stcb->asoc.state & SCTP_STATE_WAS_ABORTED)) {
14542 SCTP_TCB_SEND_UNLOCK(stcb);
14543 goto out_unlocked;
14544 }
14545 if (sp) {
14546 if (sp->msg_is_complete == 0) {
14547 strm->last_msg_incomplete = 1;
14548 if (stcb->asoc.idata_supported == 0) {
14549 asoc->stream_locked = 1;
14550 asoc->stream_locked_on = srcv->sinfo_stream;
14551 }
14552 } else {
14553 sp->sender_all_done = 1;
14554 strm->last_msg_incomplete = 0;
14555 asoc->stream_locked = 0;
14556 }
14557 sp->processing = 0;
14558 } else {
14559 SCTP_PRINTF("Huh no sp TSNH?\n");
14560 strm->last_msg_incomplete = 0;
14561 asoc->stream_locked = 0;
14562 }
14563 SCTP_TCB_SEND_UNLOCK(stcb);
14564#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
14565#if defined(APPLE_LEOPARD)
14566 if (uio->uio_resid == 0) {
14567#else
14568 if (uio_resid(uio) == 0) {
14569#endif
14570#else
14571 if (uio->uio_resid == 0) {
14572#endif
14573 got_all_of_the_send = 1;
14574 }
14575 } else {
14576 /* We send in a 0, since we do NOT have any locks */
14577 error = sctp_msg_append(stcb, net, top, srcv, 0);
14578 top = NULL;
14579 if (sinfo_flags & SCTP_EOF) {
14580 got_all_of_the_send = 1;
14581 }
14582 }
14583 if (error) {
14584 goto out;
14585 }
14586dataless_eof:
14587 /* EOF thing ? */
14588 if ((sinfo_flags & SCTP_EOF) &&
14589 (got_all_of_the_send == 1)) {
14590 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_sends_with_eof);
14591 error = 0;
14592 if (hold_tcblock == 0) {
14593 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
14594 hold_tcblock = 1;
14595 }
14596 if (TAILQ_EMPTY(&asoc->send_queue) &&
14597 TAILQ_EMPTY(&asoc->sent_queue) &&
14598 sctp_is_there_unsent_data(stcb, SCTP_SO_LOCKED) == 0) {
14599 if ((*asoc->ss_functions.sctp_ss_is_user_msgs_incomplete)(stcb, asoc)) {
14600 goto abort_anyway;
14601 }
14602 /* there is nothing queued to send, so I'm done... */
14603 if ((SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) != SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_SENT) &&
14604 (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) != SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_RECEIVED) &&
14605 (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) != SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_ACK_SENT)) {
14606 struct sctp_nets *netp;
14607
14608 /* only send SHUTDOWN the first time through */
14609 if (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_OPEN) {
14610 SCTP_STAT_DECR_GAUGE32(sctps_currestab);
14611 }
14612 SCTP_SET_STATE(stcb, SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_SENT);
14613 sctp_stop_timers_for_shutdown(stcb);
14614 if (stcb->asoc.alternate) {
14615 netp = stcb->asoc.alternate;
14616 } else {
14617 netp = stcb->asoc.primary_destination;
14618 }
14619 sctp_send_shutdown(stcb, netp);
14620 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_SHUTDOWN, stcb->sctp_ep, stcb,
14621 netp);
14622 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_SHUTDOWNGUARD, stcb->sctp_ep, stcb,
14623 NULL);
14624 }
14625 } else {
14626 /*-
14627 * we still got (or just got) data to send, so set
14628 * SHUTDOWN_PENDING
14629 */
14630 /*-
14631 * XXX sockets draft says that SCTP_EOF should be
14632 * sent with no data. currently, we will allow user
14633 * data to be sent first and move to
14634 * SHUTDOWN-PENDING
14635 */
14636 if ((SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) != SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_SENT) &&
14637 (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) != SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_RECEIVED) &&
14638 (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) != SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_ACK_SENT)) {
14639 if (hold_tcblock == 0) {
14640 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
14641 hold_tcblock = 1;
14642 }
14643 if ((*asoc->ss_functions.sctp_ss_is_user_msgs_incomplete)(stcb, asoc)) {
14644 SCTP_ADD_SUBSTATE(stcb, SCTP_STATE_PARTIAL_MSG_LEFT);
14645 }
14646 SCTP_ADD_SUBSTATE(stcb, SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_PENDING);
14647 if (TAILQ_EMPTY(&asoc->send_queue) &&
14648 TAILQ_EMPTY(&asoc->sent_queue) &&
14649 (asoc->state & SCTP_STATE_PARTIAL_MSG_LEFT)) {
14650 struct mbuf *op_err;
14651 char msg[SCTP_DIAG_INFO_LEN];
14652
14653 abort_anyway:
14654 if (free_cnt_applied) {
14655 atomic_add_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, -1);
14656 free_cnt_applied = 0;
14657 }
14658 SCTP_SNPRINTF(msg, sizeof(msg),
14659 "%s:%d at %s", __FILE__, __LINE__, __func__);
14660 op_err = sctp_generate_cause(SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_diag_info_code),
14661 msg);
14662#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
14663 NET_EPOCH_ENTER(et);
14664#endif
14665 sctp_abort_an_association(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb,
14666 op_err, SCTP_SO_LOCKED);
14667#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
14668 NET_EPOCH_EXIT(et);
14669#endif
14670 /* now relock the stcb so everything is sane */
14671 hold_tcblock = 0;
14672 stcb = NULL;
14673 goto out;
14674 }
14675 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_SHUTDOWNGUARD, stcb->sctp_ep, stcb,
14676 NULL);
14677 sctp_feature_off(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_NODELAY);
14678 }
14679 }
14680 }
14681skip_out_eof:
14682 if (!TAILQ_EMPTY(&stcb->asoc.control_send_queue)) {
14683 some_on_control = 1;
14684 }
14685 if (queue_only_for_init) {
14686 if (hold_tcblock == 0) {
14687 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
14688 hold_tcblock = 1;
14689 }
14690 if (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_OPEN) {
14691 /* a collision took us forward? */
14692 queue_only = 0;
14693 } else {
14694#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
14695 NET_EPOCH_ENTER(et);
14696#endif
14697 sctp_send_initiate(inp, stcb, SCTP_SO_LOCKED);
14698#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
14699 NET_EPOCH_EXIT(et);
14700#endif
14701 SCTP_SET_STATE(stcb, SCTP_STATE_COOKIE_WAIT);
14702 queue_only = 1;
14703 }
14704 }
14705 if ((net->flight_size > net->cwnd) &&
14706 (stcb->asoc.sctp_cmt_on_off == 0)) {
14707 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_send_cwnd_avoid);
14708 queue_only = 1;
14709 } else if (asoc->ifp_had_enobuf) {
14710 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_ifnomemqueued);
14711 if (net->flight_size > (2 * net->mtu)) {
14712 queue_only = 1;
14713 }
14714 asoc->ifp_had_enobuf = 0;
14715 }
14716 un_sent = stcb->asoc.total_output_queue_size - stcb->asoc.total_flight;
14717 if ((sctp_is_feature_off(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_NODELAY)) &&
14718 (stcb->asoc.total_flight > 0) &&
14719 (stcb->asoc.stream_queue_cnt < SCTP_MAX_DATA_BUNDLING) &&
14720 (un_sent < (int)(stcb->asoc.smallest_mtu - SCTP_MIN_OVERHEAD))) {
14721 /*-
14722 * Ok, Nagle is set on and we have data outstanding.
14723 * Don't send anything and let SACKs drive out the
14724 * data unless wen have a "full" segment to send.
14725 */
14726 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_NAGLE_LOGGING_ENABLE) {
14727 sctp_log_nagle_event(stcb, SCTP_NAGLE_APPLIED);
14728 }
14729 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_naglequeued);
14730 nagle_applies = 1;
14731 } else {
14732 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_NAGLE_LOGGING_ENABLE) {
14733 if (sctp_is_feature_off(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_NODELAY))
14734 sctp_log_nagle_event(stcb, SCTP_NAGLE_SKIPPED);
14735 }
14736 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_naglesent);
14737 nagle_applies = 0;
14738 }
14739 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_BLK_LOGGING_ENABLE) {
14740 sctp_misc_ints(SCTP_CWNDLOG_PRESEND, queue_only_for_init, queue_only,
14741 nagle_applies, un_sent);
14742 sctp_misc_ints(SCTP_CWNDLOG_PRESEND, stcb->asoc.total_output_queue_size,
14743 stcb->asoc.total_flight,
14744 stcb->asoc.chunks_on_out_queue, stcb->asoc.total_flight_count);
14745 }
14746#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
14747 NET_EPOCH_ENTER(et);
14748#endif
14749 if ((queue_only == 0) && (nagle_applies == 0) && (stcb->asoc.peers_rwnd && un_sent)) {
14750 /* we can attempt to send too. */
14751 if (hold_tcblock == 0) {
14752 /* If there is activity recv'ing sacks no need to send */
14753 if (SCTP_TCB_TRYLOCK(stcb)) {
14754 sctp_chunk_output(inp, stcb, SCTP_OUTPUT_FROM_USR_SEND, SCTP_SO_LOCKED);
14755 hold_tcblock = 1;
14756 }
14757 } else {
14758 sctp_chunk_output(inp, stcb, SCTP_OUTPUT_FROM_USR_SEND, SCTP_SO_LOCKED);
14759 }
14760 } else if ((queue_only == 0) &&
14761 (stcb->asoc.peers_rwnd == 0) &&
14762 (stcb->asoc.total_flight == 0)) {
14763 /* We get to have a probe outstanding */
14764 if (hold_tcblock == 0) {
14765 hold_tcblock = 1;
14766 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
14767 }
14768 sctp_chunk_output(inp, stcb, SCTP_OUTPUT_FROM_USR_SEND, SCTP_SO_LOCKED);
14769 } else if (some_on_control) {
14770 int num_out, reason, frag_point;
14771
14772 /* Here we do control only */
14773 if (hold_tcblock == 0) {
14774 hold_tcblock = 1;
14775 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
14776 }
14777 frag_point = sctp_get_frag_point(stcb, &stcb->asoc);
14778 (void)sctp_med_chunk_output(inp, stcb, &stcb->asoc, &num_out,
14779 &reason, 1, 1, &now, &now_filled, frag_point, SCTP_SO_LOCKED);
14780 }
14781#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
14782 NET_EPOCH_EXIT(et);
14783#endif
14784 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT1, "USR Send complete qo:%d prw:%d unsent:%d tf:%d cooq:%d toqs:%d err:%d\n",
14785 queue_only, stcb->asoc.peers_rwnd, un_sent,
14786 stcb->asoc.total_flight, stcb->asoc.chunks_on_out_queue,
14787 stcb->asoc.total_output_queue_size, error);
14788
14789out:
14790#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
14791 sbunlock(&so->so_snd, 1);
14792#endif
14793out_unlocked:
14794
14795 if (local_soresv && stcb) {
14796 atomic_subtract_int(&stcb->asoc.sb_send_resv, sndlen);
14797 }
14798 if (create_lock_applied) {
14799 SCTP_ASOC_CREATE_UNLOCK(inp);
14800 }
14801 if ((stcb) && hold_tcblock) {
14802 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
14803 }
14804 if (stcb && free_cnt_applied) {
14805 atomic_add_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, -1);
14806 }
14807#ifdef INVARIANTS
14808#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
14809 if (stcb) {
14810 if (mtx_owned(&stcb->tcb_mtx)) {
14811 panic("Leaving with tcb mtx owned?");
14812 }
14813 if (mtx_owned(&stcb->tcb_send_mtx)) {
14814 panic("Leaving with tcb send mtx owned?");
14815 }
14816 }
14817#endif
14818#endif
14819 if (top) {
14820 sctp_m_freem(top);
14821 }
14822 if (control) {
14823 sctp_m_freem(control);
14824 }
14825 return (error);
14826}
14827
14828/*
14829 * generate an AUTHentication chunk, if required
14830 */
14831struct mbuf *
14832sctp_add_auth_chunk(struct mbuf *m, struct mbuf **m_end,
14833 struct sctp_auth_chunk **auth_ret, uint32_t * offset,
14834 struct sctp_tcb *stcb, uint8_t chunk)
14835{
14836 struct mbuf *m_auth;
14837 struct sctp_auth_chunk *auth;
14838 int chunk_len;
14839 struct mbuf *cn;
14840
14841 if ((m_end == NULL) || (auth_ret == NULL) || (offset == NULL) ||
14842 (stcb == NULL))
14843 return (m);
14844
14845 if (stcb->asoc.auth_supported == 0) {
14846 return (m);
14847 }
14848 /* does the requested chunk require auth? */
14849 if (!sctp_auth_is_required_chunk(chunk, stcb->asoc.peer_auth_chunks)) {
14850 return (m);
14851 }
14852 m_auth = sctp_get_mbuf_for_msg(sizeof(*auth), 0, M_NOWAIT, 1, MT_HEADER);
14853 if (m_auth == NULL) {
14854 /* no mbuf's */
14855 return (m);
14856 }
14857 /* reserve some space if this will be the first mbuf */
14858 if (m == NULL)
14859 SCTP_BUF_RESV_UF(m_auth, SCTP_MIN_OVERHEAD);
14860 /* fill in the AUTH chunk details */
14861 auth = mtod(m_auth, struct sctp_auth_chunk *);
14862 memset(auth, 0, sizeof(*auth));
14863 auth->ch.chunk_type = SCTP_AUTHENTICATION;
14864 auth->ch.chunk_flags = 0;
14865 chunk_len = sizeof(*auth) +
14866 sctp_get_hmac_digest_len(stcb->asoc.peer_hmac_id);
14867 auth->ch.chunk_length = htons(chunk_len);
14868 auth->hmac_id = htons(stcb->asoc.peer_hmac_id);
14869 /* key id and hmac digest will be computed and filled in upon send */
14870
14871 /* save the offset where the auth was inserted into the chain */
14872 *offset = 0;
14873 for (cn = m; cn; cn = SCTP_BUF_NEXT(cn)) {
14874 *offset += SCTP_BUF_LEN(cn);
14875 }
14876
14877 /* update length and return pointer to the auth chunk */
14878 SCTP_BUF_LEN(m_auth) = chunk_len;
14879 m = sctp_copy_mbufchain(m_auth, m, m_end, 1, chunk_len, 0);
14880 if (auth_ret != NULL)
14881 *auth_ret = auth;
14882
14883 return (m);
14884}

14886#if (defined(__FreeBSD__) || defined(__APPLE__)) && !defined(__Userspace__)
14887#ifdef INET6
14888int
14889sctp_v6src_match_nexthop(struct sockaddr_in6 *src6, sctp_route_t *ro)
14890{
14891 struct nd_prefix *pfx = NULL;
14892 struct nd_pfxrouter *pfxrtr = NULL;
14893 struct sockaddr_in6 gw6;
14894
14895#if defined(__FreeBSD__)
14896 if (ro == NULL || ro->ro_nh == NULL || src6->sin6_family != AF_INET6)
14897#else
14898 if (ro == NULL || ro->ro_rt == NULL || src6->sin6_family != AF_INET6)
14899#endif
14900 return (0);
14901
14902 /* get prefix entry of address */
14903#if defined(__FreeBSD__)
14904 ND6_RLOCK();
14905#endif
14906 LIST_FOREACH(pfx, &MODULE_GLOBAL(nd_prefix), ndpr_entry) {
14907 if (pfx->ndpr_stateflags & NDPRF_DETACHED)
14908 continue;
14909 if (IN6_ARE_MASKED_ADDR_EQUAL(&pfx->ndpr_prefix.sin6_addr,
14910 &src6->sin6_addr, &pfx->ndpr_mask))
14911 break;
14912 }
14913 /* no prefix entry in the prefix list */
14914 if (pfx == NULL) {
14915#if defined(__FreeBSD__)
14916 ND6_RUNLOCK();
14917#endif
14918 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT2, "No prefix entry for ");
14919 SCTPDBG_ADDR(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT2, (struct sockaddr *)src6);
14920 return (0);
14921 }
14922
14923 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT2, "v6src_match_nexthop(), Prefix entry is ");
14924 SCTPDBG_ADDR(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT2, (struct sockaddr *)src6);
14925
14926 /* search installed gateway from prefix entry */
14927 LIST_FOREACH(pfxrtr, &pfx->ndpr_advrtrs, pfr_entry) {
14928 memset(&gw6, 0, sizeof(struct sockaddr_in6));
14929 gw6.sin6_family = AF_INET6;
14930#ifdef HAVE_SIN6_LEN
14931 gw6.sin6_len = sizeof(struct sockaddr_in6);
14932#endif
14933 memcpy(&gw6.sin6_addr, &pfxrtr->router->rtaddr,
14934 sizeof(struct in6_addr));
14935 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT2, "prefix router is ");
14936 SCTPDBG_ADDR(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT2, (struct sockaddr *)&gw6);
14937 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT2, "installed router is ");
14938#if defined(__FreeBSD__)
14939 SCTPDBG_ADDR(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT2, &ro->ro_nh->gw_sa);
14940#else
14941 SCTPDBG_ADDR(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT2, ro->ro_rt->rt_gateway);
14942#endif
14943#if defined(__FreeBSD__)
14944 if (sctp_cmpaddr((struct sockaddr *)&gw6, &ro->ro_nh->gw_sa)) {
14945 ND6_RUNLOCK();
14946#else
14947 if (sctp_cmpaddr((struct sockaddr *)&gw6, ro->ro_rt->rt_gateway)) {
14948#endif
14949 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT2, "pfxrouter is installed\n");
14950 return (1);
14951 }
14952 }
14953#if defined(__FreeBSD__)
14954 ND6_RUNLOCK();
14955#endif
14956 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT2, "pfxrouter is not installed\n");
14957 return (0);
14958}
14959#endif
14960
14961int
14962sctp_v4src_match_nexthop(struct sctp_ifa *sifa, sctp_route_t *ro)
14963{
14964#ifdef INET
14965 struct sockaddr_in *sin, *mask;
14966 struct ifaddr *ifa;
14967 struct in_addr srcnetaddr, gwnetaddr;
14968
14969#if defined(__FreeBSD__)
14970 if (ro == NULL || ro->ro_nh == NULL ||
14971#else
14972 if (ro == NULL || ro->ro_rt == NULL ||
14973#endif
14974 sifa->address.sa.sa_family != AF_INET) {
14975 return (0);
14976 }
14977 ifa = (struct ifaddr *)sifa->ifa;
14978 mask = (struct sockaddr_in *)(ifa->ifa_netmask);
14979 sin = &sifa->address.sin;
14980 srcnetaddr.s_addr = (sin->sin_addr.s_addr & mask->sin_addr.s_addr);
14981 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT1, "match_nexthop4: src address is ");
14982 SCTPDBG_ADDR(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT2, &sifa->address.sa);
14983 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT1, "network address is %x\n", srcnetaddr.s_addr);
14984
14985#if defined(__FreeBSD__)
14986 sin = &ro->ro_nh->gw4_sa;
14987#else
14988 sin = (struct sockaddr_in *)ro->ro_rt->rt_gateway;
14989#endif
14990 gwnetaddr.s_addr = (sin->sin_addr.s_addr & mask->sin_addr.s_addr);
14991 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT1, "match_nexthop4: nexthop is ");
14992#if defined(__FreeBSD__)
14993 SCTPDBG_ADDR(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT2, &ro->ro_nh->gw_sa);
14994#else
14995 SCTPDBG_ADDR(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT2, ro->ro_rt->rt_gateway);
14996#endif
14997 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_OUTPUT1, "network address is %x\n", gwnetaddr.s_addr);
14998 if (srcnetaddr.s_addr == gwnetaddr.s_addr) {
14999 return (1);
15000 }
15001#endif
15002 return (0);
15003}
15004#elif defined(__Userspace__)
15005/* TODO __Userspace__ versions of sctp_vXsrc_match_nexthop(). */
15006int
15007sctp_v6src_match_nexthop(struct sockaddr_in6 *src6, sctp_route_t *ro)
15008{
15009 return (0);
15010}
15011int
15012sctp_v4src_match_nexthop(struct sctp_ifa *sifa, sctp_route_t *ro)
15013{
15014 return (0);
15015}
